 wasn''t until 40 years later, when Patrick Caulfield''s son(Q32) Seamus, who had become an archaeologist by then, began to explore further.',1,140343),(173,4,'他将铁探针插入沼泽，绘制出石头的分布图，这是当地人几千年来用来寻找埋在沼泽中燃料的传统方法。',163853,'He inserted iron probes into the bog to map the formation of the stones,a traditional method which local people had always used for finding fuel(Q33) buried in the bog for thousands of years.',1,150426),(174,4,'碳年代测定法后来证明，这个遗址已有5000多年的历史，是爱尔兰最大的新石器时代遗址。',174127,'Carbon dating later proved that the site was over 5,000 years old and was the largest Neolithic site in Ireland.',1,163853),(175,4,'由于该地区被沼泽覆盖，Céide Fields的定居点遗址保存得非常完好，已有5000多年的历史。',185640,'Thanks to the bog which covers the area, the remains of the settlement at Céide Fields, which is over 5,000 years old, are extremely well preserved.',1,174127),(176,4,'沼泽中90%是水，土壤非常饱和，因此表面的草和石南植物死亡后不会完全腐烂，而是分层堆积。',199626,'A bog is 90 percent water, its soil is so saturated that when the grasses and heathers that grow on its surface die, they don''t fully decay but accumulate in layers.',1,185640),(177,4,'由于泥炭的酸性和缺氧，物品在这种条件下保存得很好。',207387,'Objects remain so well preserved in these conditions because of the acidity of the peat and the deficiency of oxygen(Q34).',1,199626),(178,4,'每年至少需要175天的降雨才能形成这样的环境，而爱尔兰这一地区每年平均降雨天数为225天。',218757,'At least 175 days of rain a year are required for this to happen, this part of Ireland gets an average of 225 days.',1,207387),(179,4,'新石器时代的Céide农民可能享受了几个世纪的相对和平与稳定。',230330,'The Neolithic farmers at Céide would have enjoyed several centuries of relative peace and stability.',1,224137),(180,4,'新石器时代的农民通常比他们的前辈住在更大的社区里，在社区建筑周围建造了许多房子。',239198,'Neolithic farmers generally lived in larger communities than their predecessors, with a number of houses built around a community building.',1,230330),(181,4,'新石器时代的农民通常比他们的前辈住在更大的社区里，在社区建筑周围建造了许多房子。',245797,'As they lived in permanent settlements, Neolithic farmers were able to build bigger houses.',1,239198),(182,4,'这些房子不是人们通常认为的圆形，而是长方形的，屋