ss the country''s eight and a half minutes.',1,164267),(289,6,'我最近获得了\"舵手\"的资格，也就是说我对救生艇负有最终责任。',180342,'I''ve recently qualified as what''s called a ''helmsman'', which means I have the ultimate responsibility for the lifeboat.',1,172139),(290,6,'我必须检查我们使用的设备是否正常工作，船员们有特殊的救生衣，最多可以在水中容纳四个人。',189828,'I have to check that the equipment we use is in working order, the crew have special life jackets that can support up to four people in the water.',1,180342),(291,6,'最终还是由我来决定下水是否安全。',194638,'And it''s ultimately my decision whether it''s safe to launch the boat.(Q15)',1,189828),(292,6,'但即使在最恶劣的天气下，我们也很少不下水。',198598,'But it''s very rare not to launch it, even in the worst weather.',1,194638),(293,6,'除了乘救生艇外，我的工作还涉及其他事情。',204150,'As well as going out on the lifeboat, my work involves other things too.',1,198598),(294,6,'很多人低估了海上环境变化的速度，所以我会向当地的青年团体和帆船俱乐部讲解天气突然变坏时，水手和游泳者可能遇到的问题。',219114,'A lot of people underestimate how quickly conditions can change at sea, so i speak to youth groups and sailing clubs in the area about the sorts of problems that sailors and swimmers can have if the weather suddenly gets bad.(Q16)',1,204150),(295,6,'我们还有许多志愿者组织活动为我们筹集资金，没有他们我们无法运作。',227779,'We also have a lot of volunteers who organise activities to raise money for us, and we couldn''t manage without them.',1,219114),(296,6,'我们接受的培训是一个持续过程，侧重于技术能力和安全操作技巧，这让我在面对极端情况时能够从容应对。',278559,'The training we get is a continuous process, focusing on technical competence and safe handling techniques, and it''s given me the confidence to deal with extreme situations without panicking.(Q17)(Q18)',1,264804),(297,6,'我很庆幸在开始工作前上过急救课程，这对我们的伤员护理工作帮助很大。',286529,'I was glad I''d done a first aid course before I started, as that''s a big help with the casualty care activities we do.',1,278559),(298,6,'我们已经讲了很多关于如何使用绳子和打结，这是一项基本技能。',293426,'We''ve done a lot on how to deal with ropes and tie knots, that''s an essential skill.',1,286529),(299,6,'一年后，我参加了专家带领的为期一周的驻地课程。',299660,'After a year, I did a one week residential course, led by specialists.',1,293426),(300,6,'他们有一个波浪箱，可以模拟极端天气条件，例如，如果船在夜间暴风雨中翻船，我们可以在这里练习应对。',310217,'They had a wave tank where they could create extreme weather conditions, so we could get experience at what to do if the boat turned over in a storm at night, for example.(Q17)(Q18)',1,299660),(301,6,'自从我开始工作以来，我处理了各种紧急情况。',316446,'Since l started, I''ve had to deal with a range of emergency situations.',1,310217),(302,6,'但这项工作是非常有激励性。',319408,'But the work''s hugely motivating.',1,316446),(303,6,'这不仅仅是拯救生命，我还学到了很多相关技术。',325447,'It''s not just about saving lives. I''ve learned a lot about the technology involved.',1,319408),(304,6,'我的IT背景在这里派上了用场，我可以用我的专业知识帮助其他志愿者。',332481,'My background in IT''s been useful here, and I can use my expertise to help other volunteers.',1,325447),(305,6,'我们是一个很棒的团队，真的像家人一样，这在寒冷暴风雨的夜晚把自己从床上拖起来时尤其有帮助。',340600,'They''re a great group, we''re like a family really, which helps when you''re dragging yourself out of bed on a cold stormy night.(Q19)(Q20)',1,332481),(306,6,'但实际上，最寒冷的几个月往往是最有成就感的。',346097,'But actually, it''s the colder months that can be the most rewarding time.',1,340600),(307,6,'因为这时事件往往更严重，你会意识到自己能对结果产生巨大的影响。',353283,'That''s when the incidents tend to be more serious, and you realise that you can make a huge difference to the outcome.(Q19)(Q20)',1,346097),(308,6,'所以如果各位听众有兴趣的话。',357838,'So if any of you listeners are interested.',1,353283),(309,7,'嗨，唐，你收到我发给你的关于回收鞋子的文章了吗?',54112,'Hi Don, did you get the copy of the article on recycling footwear that I emailed you?',1,47476),(310,7,'是的，它在这里……',55511,'Yeah, it''s here ...',1,54112),(311,7,'我已经看过了。',57146,'I''ve had a look at it.',1,55511),(312,7,'你觉得这个话题适合做我们的演讲吗?',60886,'So do you think it''s a good topic for our presentation?',1,57146),(313,7,'在我开始读之前，我认为回收鞋子虽然很有趣，但可能没什么可说的，因为我们只是把鞋子放进回收箱，它们就被送到慈善商店，仅此而已。',77975,'Well, before I started reading it, I thought recycling footwear, well, although it''s quite interesting, perhaps there isn''t enough to say about it, bec