 legs, at the end of which are between four and eight sharp claws.',1,148695),(374,8,'我还要说，有些鱼是没有爪子的，它们有的只是圆盘，圆盘是靠吸力起作用的。',166087,'I should also say that some species don''t have any claws; what they have are discs(Q33), and these work by means of suction.',1,156050),(375,8,'它们使缓步动物能够附着在物体表面或抓住猎物。',171818,'They enable the tardigrade to cling on to surfaces or to grip its prey.',1,166087),(376,8,'在它们体内，没有肺，也没有任何呼吸器官。',176883,'Within the body, there are no lungs, or any organs for breathing at all.',1,171818),(377,8,'相反，氧气和血液在充满体腔的液体中运输。',184780,'Instead, oxygen(Q34) and also blood are transported in a fluid that fills the cavity of the body.',1,176883),(378,8,'至于水熊虫的头，我能描述的最好的方式就是它看起来相当奇怪，甚至有点被压扁了，尽管我看过的许多网站都说它的外表很可爱，但这并不十分科学。',202514,'As far as the tardigrade''s head is concerned, the best way I can descrlbe this is that it looks rather strange a bit squashed even though many of the websites l looked at described its appearance as cute, which isn''t exactly very scientific.',1,184780),(379,8,'缓步动物的嘴是一种管子，可以向外张开，露出被称为“小猾牙”的牙齿状结构。',211326,'The tardigrade''s mouth is a kind of tube(Q35) that can open outwards to reveal teeth like structures known as ''slylets''.',1,202514),(380,8,'它们足够锋利，可以刺穿植物或动物细胞。',215443,'These are sharp enough to pierce plant or animal cells.',1,211326),(381,8,'那么，在哪里可以找到缓步动物呢?',219374,'So, where are tardigrades found?',1,215443),(382,8,'嗯，它们生活在世界上的每一个角落，以各种各样的习性:最常见的是，在湖底上，或在多种植物上，或在非常潮湿的环境中。',232329,'Well, they live in every part of the word, in a variety of habitals: most commonly, on the bed of a lake,or on many kinds of plants or in very wet environments.',1,219374),(383,8,'有一些有趣的研究发现，缓步动物能够在辐射和高压下生存，它们也能承受零下200摄氏度的低温，或者超过148摄氏度的高温，这是非常热的。',255228,'There''s been some interesting research which has found that tardigrades are capable of surviving radiation and very high pressure, and they''re also able to withstand temperatures(Q36) as cold as 200 degrees centigrade, or highs of more than 148 degrees centigrade, which is incredibly hot.',1,232329),(384,8,'有人说，在人类灭绝后，即使小行星撞击地球，蜥蜴也能存活很长时间。',269583,'It has been said that tardigrades could survive long after human beings have been wiped out, even in the event of an asteroid hitting the earth.',1,259663),(385,8,'如果环境变得过于极端，水熊虫有干涸的危险，它们就会进入一种被称为隐生的状态。',278727,'If conditions become too extreme and tardigrades are at risk of drying out, they enter a state called cryptobiosis.',1,269583),(386,8,'通过放松头部和腿部，它们蜷缩成一个球，这就是t - u - n，它们的新陈代谢下降到正常水平的1%以下。',291271,'They curl into a ball, called a tun-thats T-U-N-by retracting their head and legs, and their metabolism drops to less than one percent of normal levels.',1,278727),(387,8,'它们可以保持这种状态，直到重新接触到水，然后它们会在几个小时内恢复活力。',298982,'They can remain like this until they are re-introduced to water, when they will come back to life in a matter of a few hours.',1,291271),(388,8,'在隐生状态下，水熊虫会产生一种蛋白质来保护它们的DNA。',306867,'While in a state of cryptobiosis, tardigrades produce a protein(Q37) that protects their DNA.',1,298982),(389,8,'2016年，科学家们复活了两只已经死亡30多年的缓步动物。',314576,'In 2016, scientists revived two tardigrades that had been tuns for more than 30 years.',1,306867),(390,8,'有报道说，在1948年，一个120岁的老人复活了，但这个实验从未重复过。',325262,'There was a report that, in 1948, a 120-year-old tun was revived, but this experiment has never been repeated.',1,314576),(391,8,'目前有几项测试正在太空中进行，以确定缓步动物能够在那里生存多久。',334163,'There are currently several tests taking place in space(Q38), to determine how long tardigrades might be able to survive there.',1,325262),(392,8,'我记得目前的记录是10天。',337521,'I believe the record so far is 10 days.',1,334163),(393,8,'所以,嗯,继续。',340452,'So, erm, moving on.',1,337521),(394,8,'就它们的饮食而言，退化动物消耗液体以生存。',347106,'In terms of their diet, tardigrades consume liquids in order to survive.',1,340452),(395,8,'虽然它们有牙齿，但它们并不用牙齿咀嚼。',351058,'All though they have teeth, they don''t use these for chewing.',1,347106),(396,8,'它们从苔藓中吸取汁液，或从海藻中提取液体，但有些物种捕食其他缓步动物，从其他物种或自己的内部。',363166,'They suck the juices from moss, or extract fluid from seaweed(Q39), but some specie