men.',1,116563),(1235,24,'18世纪的时尚与现在大不相同，口袋的样式也天差地别。如果我们先聊男性时尚，会发现那是西装流行的时期。',139440,'In the 18th century, fashions were quite different from the way they are now, and pockets were too. If we think about male fashion first … that was the time when suits became popular(Q32).',1,123961),(1236,24,'裤子只有膝盖长，被称为“马裤”，马甲很短，夹克很长，但这三件衣服都用布料做衬里，口袋是由顾客指定的裁缝缝制的。',158710,'Trousers were knee-length only and referred to as ‘breeches’, the waistcoats were short and the jackets were long, but all three garments were lined with material and pockets were sewn into this cloth by whichever tailor the customer used(Q33).',1,139443),(1237,24,'然后，穿西装的人可以随身携带铅笔或硬币等小物件，通过衬里的缝隙就能够到它们。',168830,'The wearer could then carry small objects such as pencils or coins on their person and reach them through a gap in the lining.',1,158711),(1238,24,'对于想要看起来时尚的男士来说，外套的外侧口袋变得越来越具有装饰性。但如果穿衣服的人从事的是需要携带医疗器械的职业，例如医生或医师，他们的口袋通常会更大但更朴素。',188420,'Coat pockets became increasingly decorative on the outside for men who wanted to look stylish, but they were often larger but plainer if the wearer was someone with a profession who needed to carry medical instruments(Q34) – a doctor or physician, for example.',1,168833),(1239,24,'女性口袋的发展有些不同。',197590,'The development of women’s pockets was a little different.',1,188426),(1240,24,'一方面，女装口袋不像男装口袋那样显眼，也不容易够到。',203270,'For one thing, they weren’t nearly as visible(Q35) or as easy to reach as men’s.',1,197593),(1241,24,'在18世纪和19世纪，女性随身携带大量财产，其中一些可能值很多钱。',213990,'In the 18th and 19th centuries, women carried numerous possessions on their person and some of these could be worth a lot of money.',1,203271),(1242,24,'女性更容易被偷窃，尤其是富有的女性，经常担心扒手。',222830,'Women were more vulnerable to theft and wealthy women, in particular, worried constantly about pickpockets.',1,213998),(1243,24,'所以她们用的是用绳子系在一起的口袋。',229950,'So – what they did was to have a pair of pockets made that were tied together with string(Q36).',1,222835),(1244,24,'口袋是用布料做的，如果穿着者没钱，可能是回收布，或者是更昂贵的东西，比如亚麻，有时还有非常精致的刺绣。',243820,'The pockets were made of fabric, which might be recycled cloth if the wearer had little money or something more expensive, such as linen, sometimes featuring very delicate embroidery.',1,229956),(1245,24,'女人们把口袋系在腰上，以便挂在衣服下面。',250070,'Women tied the pockets around their waist(Q37) so that they hung beneath their clothes.',1,243827),(1246,24,'记住，当时的裙子很长，在人们常穿的几层衬裙之间有足够的空间来隐藏各种各样的小物件。',260880,'Remember, skirts were long then and there was plenty of room to hide a whole range of small possessions between the layers of petticoats that were commonly worn.',1,250071),(1247,24,'她们的裙子褶皱处会有一个开口，她们可以从那里拿到她们需要的东西，比如香水。',269290,'They would have an opening in the folds of their skirts through which they could reach whatever they needed, like their perfume(Q38).',1,260887),(1248,24,'当然，职业女性也需要随身携带她们可能用于办公或者做买卖所需的任何物品，但她们的口袋仍然留在衣服内侧，只是变大或变长，有时会到膝盖处！',289670,'Working women, of course, also needed to carry around items that they might use for whatever job or trade they were involved in, but their pairs of pockets still remained on the inside of their clothing, they just got bigger or longer – sometimes reaching down to their knees!',1,269291),(1249,24,'因此，领带口袋一直延续到19世纪，直到19世纪末时尚发生变化时才有所改变。',300960,'So the tie-on pockets went well into the 19th century and only changed when fashion altered towards the end of that period.',1,289678),(1250,24,'那时裙子变得更紧身，不再笨重。一对袋子变得非常引人注目，太过突出，有损女性形象。',313250,'That’s when dresses became tighter and less bulky, and the pairs of pockets became very noticeable – they stood out too much and detracted from the woman’s image(Q39).',1,300961),(1251,24,'习惯于随身携带各种个人物品的女性不愿意改变，所以需要找个地方装下随身携带的这些物品。',324130,'Women who had been used to carrying around a range of personal possessions – and still wanted to – needed somewhere to carry these items about their person.',1,313254),(1252,24,'那时小包也就是众所周知的手袋开始流行，当然，当时尚风潮彻底抛弃口袋的时候，手袋不可避免地演变成了更具现代感的手提包。',342219,'That was when small bags, or pouches as they were known, came into fashion and, of course, they inevitably led on to