 tree, and they''ll grow without fertilizer in areas where there''s plenty of moisture in the soil.',1,129949),(2369,48,'然而，他们只有在满足另一个重要标准的情况下才会这样做，那就是他们必须在白天充分或部分暴露在阳光下，而在非常凉爽的夜晚——我马上会详细讨论这个问题。',157540,'However, they''ll only do this if another important criterion is fulfilled, which is that they must have full or partial sun exposure during the day and very cool nights – and I''ll talk more about that in a minute.',1,140787),(2370,48,'世界上只有某些地区提供了所有这些条件:一个是加拿大，我指的是加拿大的所有地区，另一个是北美的东北部各州。',172740,'There are only certain parts of the world that provide all these conditions: one is Canada, and by that, I mean all parts of Canada, and the other is the north-eastern states of North America.',1,157545),(2371,48,'这些地区的气候非常适合树木生长。',178320,'In these areas, the climate suits the trees perfectly.(Q33)',1,172749),(2372,48,'事实上，加拿大生产了世界上超过三分之二的枫糖浆，这就是为什么五角形的枫叶是加拿大的象征，自1964年以来一直出现在国旗上。',192310,'In fact, Canada produces over two-thirds of the world''s maple syrup, which is why the five-pointed maple leaf is a Canadian symbol and has featured on the flag since 1964.',1,178320),(2373,48,'那么枫糖浆是如何开始生产的呢?',196780,'So how did maple syrup production begin?',1,192313),(2374,48,'早在欧洲人在这些地方定居之前，土著社区就已经开始生产枫糖了。',206760,'Well, long before Europeans settled in these parts of the world, the indigenous communities had started producing maple sugar.',1,196783),(2375,48,'他们在枫树的树干上钻洞，用树皮做的容器收集倒出来的液体汁液。',216510,'They bored holes in the trunks of maple trees and used containers made of tree bark to collect the liquid sap as it poured out.',1,206767),(2376,48,'由于他们无法将液体保存很长时间——当时他们没有储存设施——他们把被太阳晒得很热的岩石块放入树液中煮沸液体。',232890,'As they were unable to keep the liquid for any length of time – they didn''t have storage facilities in those days – they boiled the liquid by placing pieces of rock that had become scorching hot from the sun into the sap.(Q34)',1,216517),(2377,48,'他们这样做，直到它变成糖，然后他们可以用它来增加他们的食物和饮料的甜味。',241290,'They did this until it turned into sugar, and they were then able to use this to sweeten 