名的斯多葛学派从来没有写过任何东西供出版。',125730,'Amazingly, we still have access to these ideas, despite the fact that the most famous Stoics never wrote anything down for publication. (Q32)',1,116271),(2567,52,'卡托绝对没有。',128000,'Cato definitely didn''t.',1,125731),(2568,52,'马可·奥勒留从来没有想过让他的《沉思录》不是针对个人的。',133620,'Marcus Aurelius never intended his Meditations to be anything but personal.',1,128001),(2569,52,'塞内加的书信和爱比克泰德的思想都是通过一个做笔记的学生而来的。',143730,'Seneca''s letters were, well, letters and Epictetus'' thoughts come to us by way of a note-taking student.',1,133621),(2570,52,'斯多葛学派的原则是建立在这样一种观念上的，即其追随者可以在这一生中获得不可动摇的幸福，而实现这一幸福的关键是美德。',155430,'Stoic principles were based on the idea that its followers could have an unshakable happiness in this life and the key to achieving this was virtue.',1,143731),(2571,52,'反过来说，通往美德之路在于理解像愤怒和嫉妒这样的破坏性情绪是在我们有意识的控制之下的——它们不需要控制我们，因为我们可以学会控制它们。',172980,'The road to virtue, in turn, lay in understanding that destructive emotions, like anger and jealousy, are under our conscious control-they don''t have to control us, because we can learn to control them.',1,155431),(2572,52,'用爱比克泰德的话来说\"我无法控制外部事件，但我可以控制与之相关的选择\"(Q33)',183520,'In the words of Epictetus:\"external events I cannot control, but the choices I make with regard to them,I do control\". (Q33)',1,172981),(2573,52,'现代哲学家兼作家纳西姆·尼古拉斯·塔勒布(Nassim Nicholas Taleb)将斯多葛主义者定义为对我们大多数人认为完全消极的经历持不同观点的人;斯多葛主义者“将恐惧转化为谨慎，将痛苦转化为转变，将错误转化为启蒙，将欲望转化为承担”。',211420,'The modern day philosopher and writer Nassim Nicholas Taleb defines a Stoic as someone who has a different perspective on experiences which most of us would see as wholly negative;a Stoic \"transforms fear into caution, pain into transformation, mistakes into initiation and desire into undertaking\". (Q34)',1,183525),(2574,52,'用这个定义作为模型，我们可以看到，在最近的历史中，国王、总统、艺术家、作家和企业家在几个世纪里一直奉行斯多葛主义。',231630,'Using this definition as a model, we can see that throughout the centuries Stoicism has been practised in more recent history by kings, presidents, artists, writers and entr