id you actually start the scheme, Alice?',1,98861),(3592,74,'嗯，我第一次想到这个主意是在我的大儿子还刚学会走路的时候，所以那是大约六年前的事了，但是我们至少花了两年的时间才真正做到这一点。',114860,'Well,I first had the idea when my oldest child was still a toddler,so that''s about six years ago now - but it took at least two years of campaigning before we were actually able to make it happen.',1,102061),(3593,74,'因此，该计划已经启动并运行了三年。(Q11) ',118060,'So the scheme''s been up and running for (Q11) three years now.',1,114861),(3594,74,'我们希望能够封锁我们的街道更长的时间-整个周末，例如从星期六上午到星期天晚上。',125610,'We''d love to be able to close our road for longer - for the whole weekend, from Saturday morning until Sunday evening,for example.',1,118061),(3595,74,'目前只是一周一次(Q12)',128210,'At the moment it''s just once a week. (Q12)',1,125611),(3596,74,'但我们开始的时候只是每月进行一次，我们正在努力争取。',132510,'But when we started it was only once a month.But we''re working on it.',1,128211),(3597,74,'那么当比奇伍德路封锁的时候发生了什么？',135910,'So what actually happens when Beechwood Road is closed?',1,132511),(3598,74,'我们有义务看守的人，大部分是家长，但也有一些年长的住户，他们把我们的街道两头都堵住了。(Q13)',144910,'We have volunteer wardens,mostly parents but some elderly residents too,who block off our road at either end.(Q13)',1,135911),(3599,74,'理事会已经提供了特殊的标志，但总会有一个志愿者在那里向驾车者解释。',153210,'The council have provided special signs but there''s always a volunteer there to explain what''s happening to any motorists.',1,144911),(3600,74,'一般来说，他们对此没什么意见——我们只需要让警察介入一两次就行了。',159510,'Generally,they''re fine about it - we''ve only had to get the police involved once or twice.',1,153211),(3601,74,'现在我应该解释一下，这条路并没有完全禁止汽车通行，只有居民的汽车是可以通行的。',167710,'Now I should explain that the road isn''t completely closed to cars. But only residents'' cars are allowed.',1,159511),(3602,74,'如果人们真的需要进出比奇伍德路，这不是一个问题——只要他们以低于每小时20公里的速度行驶。(Q14)',177510,'If people really need to get in or out of Beechwood Road,it''s not a problem - as long as they drive at under 20 kilometres per hour. (Q14)',1,167711),(3603,74,'但是大多数人会决定在这段时间不开车，或者把车停在另一条街上。',184210,'But most people just deci