upervised by their parents -but for me the biggest advantage is that kids develop confidence in themselves to be outside without their parents.(Q17/Q18)',1,293621),(3616,74,'另一件非常棒的事情是，孩子们开始了解街上的大人们——这就像一个大家庭。(Q17/Q18)',316920,'The other really fantastic thing is that children get to know the adults in the street - it''s like having a big extended family.(Q17/Q18)',1,308721),(3617,74,'的确有很多好处。',319720,'It certainly does have a lot of benefits.',1,316921),(3618,74,'现在我想继续向你们询问一个有关国王街的项目。',324520,'I want to move on now and ask you about a related project in King Street.',1,319721),(3619,74,'对。这是我参与的一个实验，当地居民决定劝说人们一天不要开车，以此来减少国王街的交通，国王街是我们地区最繁忙的主要道路。',341120,'Right.Well this was an experiment I was involved in where local residents decided to try and reduce the traffic along King Street, which is the busiest main road in our area,by persuading people not to use their cars for one day.',1,324521),(3620,74,'我们考虑过让人们支付更高的停车费，但我们认为这样做会非常不受欢迎，所以我们只是禁止人们在国王街停车，而让其他停车场保持开放。',354120,'We thought about making people pay more for parking - but we decided that would be really unpopular - so instead we just stopped people from parking on King Street but left the other car parks open.',1,341121),(3621,74,'令人惊讶的是，这产生了很大的影响。',358320,'It was surprising how much of a difference all this made.',1,354121),(3622,74,'正如我们预测的那样，空气质量明显要好得多，但我没有想到的是那里会变得如此安静(Q19/Q20)——即使公交车还在运行。',369420,'As we''d predicted,air quality was significantly better but what I hadn''t expected was how much quieter it would be(Q19/Q20) - even with the buses still running.',1,358321),(3623,74,'当然每个人都说他们感到更安全，但是我们实际上很惊讶，因为那天商店的销售量大幅上升(Q19/Q20)——我们认为外出购物的人会更少——而不是更多。',380320,'Of course everyone said they felt safer but we were actually amazed that sales in the shops went up considerably that day(Q19/Q20) - we thought there''d be fewer people out shopping - not more.',1,369421),(3624,74,'这真的很有趣，那么事实上... ..。',386720,'That''s really interesting so the fact that...',1,380321),(3625,75,'汤姆，我能请你给我提些建议吗？',57000,'Tom, could I ask you for some advice, please?',1,53501),(3626,75,'当然可以，如果你认为我可以帮忙的话。是关于什么的？',61810,' Yes of course, if you think I can help.What''s it about?',1,57001),(3627,75,'这是我的第一个媒体学习作业，我不知道该怎么做。你去年一定做过的。',69710,'It''s my first media studies assignment,and I''m not sure how to go about it.You must have done it last year.',1,61811),(3628,75,'是对比一系列报纸对某个特定故事的报道的那个作业吗？',75310,' Is that the one comparing the coverage of a particular story in a range of newspapers?',1,69711),(3629,75,'没错。',76210,'That''s right.',1,75311),(3630,75,'哦，是的，我真的很喜欢做这个作业。',79310,' Oh yes, I really enjoyed writing it.',1,76211),(3631,75,'那么我需要对比哪些东西呢？',82710,'So what sort of things do I need to compare?',1,79311),(3632,75,'有几件事是需要的。',85610,' Well, there are several things.',1,82711),(3633,75,'例如，有一个问题，即该条目出现在报纸的哪一页(Q21)上。',90600,'For example,there''s the question of which page(Q21) of the newspaper the item appears on.',1,85611),(3634,75,'你的意思是，比如说，把它放在头版和第十页的底部有很大的不同？',98210,'You mean,because there''s a big difference between having it on the front page and the bottom of page ten, for instance?',1,90601),(3635,75,'没错，这说明主编认为这个故事的重要程度。',104810,' Exactly.And that shows how important the editor thinks the story is.',1,98211),(3636,75,'然后是尺寸(Q22)——故事给出了多少栏目英寸，分布了多少栏目。',113010,'Then there''s the size(Q22) - how many column inches the story is given, how many columns it spreads over.',1,104811),(3637,75,'我想这也包括标题。',116010,' And I suppose that includes the headline.',1,113011),(3638,75,'的确如此。这都是吸引读者注意力的部分。',120670,'It certainly does.It''s all part of attracting the reader''s attention.',1,116011),(3639,75,'那么图片呢(Q23)-除了文字之外是否还有其他可视的东西？',125970,' What about graphics(Q23) - whether there''s anything visual in addition to the text?',1,120671),(3640,75,'是的，你也需要考虑这些因素，因为它们会对读者对故事的理解产生很大的影响——有时甚至比文本本身产生更大的影响。',137370,'Yes, you need to consider those, too,because they can have a big effect on the reader''s understanding of the story - sometimes a bigger effect than the text itself.',1,125971),(3641,75,'接着,你需要看看整个故事是怎么编排的:它给出了什么结构(Q24) ？',143470,'Then you''ll need to look at how the item is put together：what structure(Q24) is it given?',1,137371),(3642,75,'记住，很少有人阅读超过第一段的内容，那么记者在开头写了什么呢？',152270,'Bear in mind that not many people read beyond the first paragraph, so what has the journalist put at the beginning?',1,143471),(3643,75,'如果，比方说，对于某件事有相互矛盾的意见，是否会在最后部分出现，因为这部分人们可能不会读到？',160870,'And if, say, there are conflicting opinions about something,does one appear near the end,where people probably won''t read it?',1,152271),(3644,75,'报纸有时会给出错误或误导性的信息，不是吗？',166870,' And newspapers sometimes give wrong or misleading information, don''t they?',1,160871),(3645,75,'无论是故意的还是偶然的。',169480,'Either deliberately or by accident.',1,166871),(3646,75,'我是不是也应该看看这个？',171570,'Should I be looking at that, too?',1,169481),(3647,75,'是的，如果你可以的话。比较不同版本的内容，尽可能地找出哪些是真实的，哪些不是。',181800,'Yes, if you can.Compare what’s in different versions, and as far as possible,try and work out what''s true and what isn''t.',1,171571),(3648,75,'作者的目的是什么，(Q25) ，或者如果有几个目的的话，最重要的目的是什么。',192500,'And that relates to a very important point：what''s the writer''s purpose,(Q25) or at least the most important one,if they have several.',1,181801),(3649,75,'这似乎是告知公众，但通常是他们想制造恐惧，或争议，或使某人看起来可笑。',203300,'It may seem to be to inform the public,but often it''s that they want to create fear, or controversy,or to make somebody look ridiculous.',1,192501),(3650,75,'天啊，我明白你的意思了。我想作者可能会对读者做出一些假设。(Q26)',210400,'Gosh, I see what you mean.And I suppose the writer may make assumptions(Q26) about the reader.',1,203301),(3651,75,'没错——关于他们对主题的了解，他们的态度，以及他们的教育水平，这就意味着写作要让读者理解而不感到屈尊俯就。',222300,'That''s right - about their knowledge of the subject,their attitudes, and their level of education,which means writing so that the readers understand without feeling patronised.',1,210401),(3652,75,'所有这些都会改变故事的呈现方式。',229200,'All of that will make a difference to how the story is presented.',1,222301),(3653,75,'我写的是什么类型的故事重要吗？',267110,'Does it matter what type of 