hing about funding for the arts - I''ll think about that.',1,350471),(3664,75,'是的，那可能会很有趣。',361870,' Yes, that might be interesting.',1,359471),(3665,75,'好的，非常感谢你的帮助，汤姆，这真的很有用。',365970,'OK, well thanks a lot for your help, Tom.It''s been really useful.',1,361871),(3666,75,'不客气。祝你的作业好运，黑兹尔。',371970,' You''re welcome.Good luck with the assignment, Hazel.',1,365971),(3667,75,'第三部分结束了，你现在有30秒的时间来核对第三部分的答案。',379850,'That is the end of part 3.You now have 30 seconds to check your answers to part3.',1,371971),(3668,76,'如今，我们使用不同的产品用于个人清洁，洗衣，洗碗和家庭清洁，但这在很大程度上是20世纪的发展。',83360,'Nowadays, we use different products for personal cleanliness,laundry, dishwashing and household cleaning,but this is very much a 20th-century development.',1,70860),(3669,76,'清洁的起源可以追溯到史前时代。',88260,'The origins of cleanliness date back to prehistoric times.',1,83361),(3670,76,'由于水对生命是必不可少的，早期人类生活在水域附近，知道水的净化功能——至少它能把他们手上的泥洗掉。(Q31)',101260,'Since water is essential for life,the earliest people lived near water and knew something about its cleansing properties - at least that it rinsed mud off(Q31) their hands.',1,88261),(3671,76,'在古巴比伦的挖掘过程中，有证据表明，人们早在公元前2800年就知道制造肥皂了。',112160,'During the excavation of ancient Babylon,evidence was found that soapmaking was known as early as 2800 BC.',1,101261),(3672,76,'考古学家发现了粘土制成的圆柱，(Q32)上面有文字说把脂肪和灰烬一起煮。',121060,'Archaeologists discovered cylinders made of clay,(Q32) with inscriptions on them saying that fats were boiled with ashes.',1,112161),(3673,76,'这是一种制作肥皂的方法，尽管没有提到这种材料的用途。',127610,'This is a method of making soap,though there''s no reference to the purpose of this material.',1,121061),(3674,76,'早期希腊人洗澡是出于美学原因，而且显然不用肥皂。',133310,'The early Greeks bathed for aesthetic reasons and apparently didn''t use soap.',1,127611),(3675,76,'取而代之的是，他们用大块的沙子、浮石和灰烬清洗身体，然后用油涂抹身体，用一种被称为刮身板的金属工具刮去油和灰尘。(Q33)',148610,'Instead, they cleaned their bodies with blocks of sand,pumice and ashes, then anointed themselves with oil,and scraped off the oil and dirt with a metal instrument known