n side. (Q19/Q20)',1,289581),(3796,78,'超过8万英镑被用于更换玻璃墙和金属支架，以及被毁坏的植物，但不幸的是，到目前为止，收集热带棕榈树的费用过于昂贵，无法更换。',318980,'Over £80,000 was spent on replacing the glass walls and the metal supports, as well as the plants that had been destroyed,although unfortunately the collection of tropical palm trees has proved too expensive to replace up to now.',1,300181),(3797,78,'目前，玻璃房星期一至星期四上午10时至下午3时开放，希望能尽快延长到周末。(Q19/Q20)',330880,'At present the glass houses are open from 10am to 3pm Mondays to Thursdays,and it''s hoped to extend this to the weekend soon. (Q19/Q20)',1,318981),(3798,78,'我们感谢所有那些为这项成就付出了时间和金钱的人们。',338480,'We''re grateful to all those who helped us by contributing their time and money to this achievement.',1,330881),(3799,78,'花园里还有...',343480,'The gardens have ...',1,338481),(3800,79,'好的，杰克。在我们计划关于制冷的演讲之前，让我们先讨论一下到目前为止我们发现了什么。',61910,'OK, Jack.Before we plan our presentation about refrigeration,let''s discuss what we''ve discovered so far.',1,54401),(3801,79,'很好，安妮。不过我得承认我还没有做太多的研究。',65510,'Fine, Annie.Though I have to admit I haven''t done much research yet.',1,61911),(3802,79,'我也是，不过我发现了一篇关于冰窖的有趣的文章。',70410,'Nor me.But I found an interesting article about icehouses.',1,65511),(3803,79,'我在英国见过一些18世纪和19世纪的建筑，所以我知道它们通常建在阴凉的地方或者地下，靠近冬天可能结冰的湖泊。',82510,'I''d seen some 18th-and 19th-century ones here in the UK,so I knew they were often built in a shady area or underground, close to lakes that might freeze in the winter.',1,70411),(3804,79,'然后，冰块可以被切割并储存在冰窖里。',86710,'Then blocks of ice could be cut and stored in the icehouse.',1,82511),(3805,79,'但我没有意识到，用稻草或锯屑隔热可以让它们在几个月内不会融化(Q21)',94210,'But I didn''t realise that insulating the blocks with straw or sawdust meant they didn''t melt for months.(Q21)',1,86711),(3806,79,'古罗马人也有制冷设备。',96810,'The ancient Romans had refrigeration, too.',1,94211),(3807,79,'我不知道。',97910,'I didn''t know that.',1,96811),(3808,79,'是的，地上挖了很多坑，雪也是从山上运来的——尽管距离很远。',106410,'Yes, pits were dug in the ground,and snow was imported from the mountains - even though they were at quite a distance.',1,97911),(3809,79,'雪藏在坑里，坑底结了冰。',111210,'The snow was stored in the pits.Ice formed at the bottom of it.',1,106411),(3810,79,'然后冰和雪都可以卖掉(Q22)',114110,'Both the ice and the snow were then sold. (Q22)',1,111211),(3811,79,'冰比雪还贵，我猜只有富裕的人家才买得起。',121070,'The ice cost more than the snow and my guess is that only the wealthy members of society could afford it.',1,114111),(3812,79,'我并不感到惊讶。我还看到一篇关于现代家用冰箱的文章。',127050,'I wouldn''t be surprised.I also came across an article about modern domestic fridges.',1,121071),(3813,79,'我们使用了几种不同的技术，但它们太复杂了，我无法理解。',131650,'Several different technologies are used,but they were too complex for me to understand.',1,127051),(3814,79,'你不得不好奇当人们把旧的东西处理掉时会发生什么。',135350,'You have to wonder what happens when people get rid of old ones.',1,131651),(3815,79,'你的意思是因为它们中的气体对环境有害？',138350,'You mean because the gases in them are harmful for the environment?',1,135351),(3816,79,'没错。至少现在有很多组织可以安全地回收大部分零部件，但还有些人把旧冰箱扔在乡下。(Q23)',149450,'Exactly.At least there are now plenty of organisations that will recycle most of the components safely,but of course some people just dump old fridges in the countryside.(Q23)',1,138351),(3817,79,'很难想象怎样才能阻止他们。',152950,'It''s hard to see how they can be stopped unfortunately.',1,149451),(3818,79,'在英国，我们每年总共要处理掉三百万旧冰箱！',156550,'In the UK we get rid of three million a year altogether!',1,152951),(3819,79,'听起来很多，特别是因为冰箱几乎不会坏。',160950,'That sounds a lot,especially because fridges hardly ever break down.',1,156551),(3820,79,'是的。在这个国家，我们家里的冰箱平均使用11年，很多可以使用20年或更长时间。(Q24)',168350,'That''s right.In this country we keep domestic fridges for 11 years on average, and a lot last for 20 or more.(Q24)',1,160951),(3821,79,'因此，如果你用冰箱的使用年限除以成本，与一些家用电器相比，它们并不贵。',174950,'So if you divide the cost by the number of years you can use a fridge, they''re not expensive,compared with some household appliances.',1,168351),(3822,79,'是啊，我想制造商想让人们多花钱，才把它们做成不同的颜色和图案。',182450,'True.I suppose manufacturers encourage people to spend more by making them different colours and designs.',1,174951),(3823,79,'我敢肯定，我父母买他们的第一个冰箱的时候，他们几乎没有任何选择！',186750,'I''m sure when my parents bought their first fridge they had hardly any choice!',1,182451),(3824,79,'是的，变化很大。',191950,'Yes, there''s been quite a change.',1,186751),(3825,79,'好的，让我们列一个演讲的主题清单，然后决定针对这些主题谁来做更多的研究。',242010,'Right,let''s make a list of topics to cover in our presentation,and decide who''s going to do more research on them.',1,236311),(3826,79,'然后，我们可以聚在一起计划下一步。',244910,'Then later, we can get together and plan the next step.',1,242011),(3827,79,'好的，那就从冷藏的实用程度，以及现在冷藏货物的种类(Q25)说起吧？',253710,'OK.How about starting with how useful refrigeration is,and the range of goods that are refrigerated(Q25) nowadays?',1,244911),(3828,79,'因为当然不仅仅是冷藏食物和饮料。',256710,'Because of course it''s not just food and drinks.',1,253711),(3829,79,'是的，我想花和药品也是需要冷藏的吧。',260610,'No, I suppose flowers and medicines are refrigerated,too.',1,256711),(3830,79,'还有电脑，我可以做这个主题，除非你特别想做。',265510,'And computers.I could do that, unless you particularly want to.',1,260611),(3831,79,'不，我没意见。那么冷藏对人体健康的影响呢? (Q26)',270810,'No, that''s fine by me.What about the effects of refrigeration on people''s health?(Q26)',1,265511),(3832,79,'毕竟，在19世纪使用的一些化学物质是相当有害的，但也有很多好处，比如总是可以获得新鲜的食物。',280110,'After all,some of the chemicals used in the 19th century were pretty harmful, but there have been lots of benefits too,like always having access to fresh food.',1,270811),(3833,79,'你喜欢研究这个吗？',281710,'Do you fancy dealing with that?',1,280111),(3834,79,'说实话，我不是很喜欢。',284510,'I''m not terribly keen, to be honest.',1,281711),(3835,79,'我也是。当我读到任何关于化学品的东西时，我的大脑就一片空白。',289110,'Nor me.My mind just goes blank when I read anything about chemicals.',1,284511),(3836,79,'那好吧，我帮你一个忙。但是你欠我的，杰克。',294470,'Oh, all right then. I''ll do you a favour. But you owe me, Jack.',1,289111),(3837,79,'那么，这对粮食生产者的影响又如何呢? 比如贫穷国家的农民能够将他们的产品出口到发达国家？',304570,'OK.What about the effects on food producers(Q27),like farmers in poorer countries being able to export their produce to developed countries?',1,294471),(3838,79,'这个主题给你可以吗？',306370,'Something for you, maybe?',1,304571),(3839,79,'我不介意，应该会很有趣的。',309170,'I don''t mind. It should be quite interesting.',1,306371),(3840,79,'我认为我们也应该看看冷藏是如何帮助整个城市的（Q28），比如拉斯维加斯，没有冷藏是不可能的，因为它位于沙漠中间。',319470,'I think we should also look at how refrigeration has helped whole cities(Q28) - like Las Vegas,which couldn''t exist without refrigeration because it''s in the middle of a desert.',1,309171),(3841,79,'是的，我在图书馆看了一本经济学书，里面有一章是关于这类事情的。',325470,'Right.I had a quick look at an economics book in the library that''s got a chapter about this sort of thing.',1,319471),(3842,79,'如果你想做这个部分，我可以给你书名。',327970,'I could give you the title, if you want to do this section.',1,325471),(3843,79,'说实话，不是特别喜欢。我觉得读经济类书籍通常都很费劲。',333670,'Not particularly, to be honest.I find economics books pretty heavy going, as a rule.',1,327971),(3844,79,'好吧，那就交给我吧。',335270,'OK, leave it to me, then.',1,333671),(3845,79,'谢谢。还有运输，以及冷藏车所带来的不同。',342470,'Thanks.Then there''s transport,and the difference that refrigerated trucks have made.',1,335271),(3846,79,'我不介意尝试一下(Q29)',344370,'I wouldn''t mind having a go at that.(Q29)',1,342471),(3847,79,'别忘了火车。',346380,'Don''t forget trains, too.',1,344371),(3848,79,'我读到过一些关于牛奶和黄油在19世纪40年代被冷藏火车运送到美国的故事。',353780,'I read something about milk and butter being transported in refrigerated railroad cars in the USA,right back in the 1840s.',1,346381),(3849,79,'我还没想到火车，谢谢。',356680,'I hadn''t thought of trains. Thanks.',1,353781),(3850,79,'我们要不要在家用冰箱上另设一节(Q30)',359180,'Shall we have a separate section on domestic fridges?(Q30)',1,356681),(3851,79,'毕竟，它们是每个人都熟悉的东西。',361580,'After all, they''re something everyone''s familiar with.',1,359181),(3852,79,'把它一分为二怎么样？',364180,'What about splitting it into two?',1,361581),(3853,79,'你可以研究一下19世纪和20世纪的冰箱，而我将集中研究现在有哪些产品，以及制造商如何区分他们的产品和竞争对手的产品。',376180,'You could investigate 19th- and 20th- century fridges,and I''ll concentrate on what''s