urse this is only one small village, one window into a lost world.',1,199323),(4796,96,'为了了解更全面的情况，研究人员需要更多的下沉定居点，但困难的部分是找到它们。',216920,'For a fuller picture, researchers need more sunken settlements, but the hard part is finding them.',1,207061),(4797,96,'水下研究过去需要潜水员去寻找沉船或人工制品，但在20世纪下半叶，各种类型的水下航行器被开发出来，有些是由水面上的船只控制的，有些是自动的，这意味着它们不需要由人操作。',240150,'Underwater research used to require divers to find shipwrecks or artefacts, but in the second half of the twentieth century, various types of underwater vehicles were developed, some controlled from a ship on the surface, and some of them autonomous, which means they don''t need to be operated by a person.',1,216921),(4798,96,'例如，自动水下航行器(auv)被用于石油工业，在安装钻井平台和管道之前绘制海底地图。',254840,'Autonomous underwater vehicles, or AUVs, are used in the oil industry, for instance, to create maps of the seabed before rigs and pipelines are installed.(Q33)',1,240156),(4799,96,'为了导航，它们使用罗盘和声纳等传感器。',261330,'To navigate they use sensors, such as compasses and sonar.',1,254842),(4800,96,'直到最近，它们都非常昂贵，而且很重，以至于它们必须用绞车从一艘大船上发射。',275530,'Until relatively recently they were very expensive, and so heavy that they had to be launched from a large vessel with a winch.(Q34) ',1,261337),(4801,96,'但最新的自动水下机器人操作起来要容易得多——它们可以从岸边或小船上发射。',284960,'But the latest AUVs are much easier to manoeuvre - they can be launched from the shore or a small ship.',1,275539),(4802,96,'而且它们更便宜，这使得研究团队更容易获得它们。',291060,'And they''re much cheaper, which makes them more accessible to research teams.',1,284968),(4803,96,'它们也非常复杂。',294780,'They''re also very sophisticated.',1,291067),(4804,96,'他们可以相互交流，例如，制定出最有效的方法来调查一个地点，或在海底找到特定的物体。',307460,'They can communicate with each other and, for example, work out the most efficient way to survey a site, or to find particular objects on the seabed.',1,294789),(4805,96,'现场试验表明，该方法是可行的。',310830,'Field tests show the approach can work.',1,307464),(4806,96,'例如，在2015年的一次试验中，三架auv在西西里岛海岸附近的Marzamemi搜索沉船。',320640,'For example, in a trial in 2015, three