dic memory',1,123561),(5181,104,'情景记忆不同于另一种称为语义记忆的记忆。',143540,'Episodic memory is distinct from another type of memory called semantic memory.',1,135441),(5182,104,'这是一种我们和其他人都有的事实记忆，即你对世界的普遍认识。',155210,'This is the type of factual memory that we have in common with everyone else-that is your general knowledge of the world. (Q32)',1,143541),(5183,104,'以前面的例子为基础，记住你把车停在哪里是一个情景记忆，但是你对什么是汽车和发动机如何工作的理解就是语义记忆的例子',175510,'To build upon a previous example,remembering where you parked your car is an example of episodic memory,but your understanding of what a car is and how an engine works are examples of semantic memory.',1,155211),(5184,104,'与情景记忆不同，语义记忆并不依赖于回忆个人经历',186330,'Unlike episodic memory, semantic memory isn''t dependent on recalling personal experiences. (Q33)',1,175511),(5185,104,'情景记忆可以被认为是一个过程，包括几个不同的记忆处理步骤：编码、巩固和检索',202000,'Episodic memory can be thought of as a process with several different steps of memory processing:encoding, consolidation and retrieval.',1,186331),(5186,104,'初始步骤称为编码',206350,'The initial step is called encoding.',1,202001),(5187,104,'这包括收集和登记信息的过程，这对于创造你所经历的信息或事件的记忆是必要的',219830,'This involves the process of receiving and registering information,which is necessary for creating memories of information or events that you experience.',1,206351),(5188,104,'你能成功地编码信息的程度取决于你在事件实际发生时对它的关注程度',232830,'The degree to which you can successfully encode information depends on the level of attention you give to an event while it''s actually happening. (Q34)',1,219831),(5189,104,'分心会使有效编码变得非常困难',239300,'Being distracted can make effective encoding very difficult.',1,232831),(5190,104,'情节记忆的编码也受到你处理事件的方式的影响',247790,'Encoding of episodic memories is also influenced by how you process the event.',1,239301),(5191,104,'例如，如果有人给你介绍一个叫查理的人，你可能会把你同样叫查理的叔叔联系起来',259290,'For example, if you were introduced to someone called Charlie,you might make the connection that your uncle has the same name. (Q35)',1,247791),(5192,104,'如果你有一个策略来帮助你对查理的名字进行编码，那么将来对他的回忆就会容易得多',269