uld meet to drink coffee and chat about issues of the day.',1,154771),(5624,112,'但是当时，这种分享思想和观点的机会被认为是潜在的危险。1623年，君士坦丁堡统治者要求摧毁这座城市的所有咖啡馆，但他死后开设了许多新的咖啡店，咖啡消费仍在继续。',185820,'But at the time, this chance to share ideas and opinions was seen as something that was potentially dangerous, and in 1623 the ruler of Constantinople demanded the destruction of all the coffee houses in the city, (Q31) although after his death many new ones opened, and coffee consumption continued.',1,162001),(5625,112,'在17世纪，喝咖啡的风潮席卷了欧洲，这里的咖啡店也变成了普通人（几乎总是男人）聚在一起交流思想的地方。',199360,'In the seventeenth century, coffee drinking spread to Europe, and here too coffee shops became places where ordinary people, nearly always men, could meet to exchange ideas. (Q32)',1,185821),(5626,112,'因此，有人说这些地方的功能与大学类似。',206800,'Because of this, some people said that these places performed a similar function to universities. (Q32)',1,199361),(5627,112,'他们为人们提供了在自己的家外聚会，讨论当今话题的机会，对社会生活产生了巨大影响，许多社会运动和政治发展都起源于咖啡馆的讨论。',229530,'The opportunity they provided for people to meet together outside their own homes and to discuss the topics of the day had an enormous impact on social life, and many social movements and political developments had their origins in coffee house discussions. (Q33)',1,206801),(5628,112,'在1600年代后期，也门在咖啡生产方面的垄断地位被打破，在欧洲殖民统治的帮助下，咖啡生产开始在世界范围内蔓延。',241410,'In the late 1600s, the Yemeni monopoly on coffee production broke down and coffee production started to spread around the world, helped by European colonisation.',1,229531),(5629,112,'欧洲人在印度尼西亚和加勒比海建立了咖啡种植园，殖民地的咖啡产量猛增。',251570,'Europeans set up coffee plantations in Indonesia and the Caribbean and production of coffee in the colonies skyrocketed.',1,241411),(5630,112,'在不同地区生产不同类型的咖啡，而且有趣的是，赋予这些不同类型的名称（如摩卡咖啡或爪哇咖啡）通常取自将其运往欧洲的港口。',266420,'Different types of coffee were produced in different areas, and it''s interesting that the names given to these different types, like Mocha or Java coffee, were often taken from the port they were shipped to Europe from. (Q34