,1,59881),(5741,115,'几个世纪以来图书馆的变化，例如，或者不同国家/地区是如何组织他们的。',68950,'How libraries have changed over the centuries,for instance,or how different countries organise them.',1,62731),(5742,115,'你觉得呢，特鲁迪？',70450,'What do you think, Trudie?',1,68951),(5743,115,'也许我们应该关注这个国家，试着把图书馆的改变与外部发展联系起来，比如现在比一个世纪前有更多的人能够阅读，当地人口可能会说很多不同的语言。',84620,'Maybe we should concentrate on this country, and try and relate the changes in libraries to external developments, like the fact that far more people can read than a century ago,and that the local population may speak lots of different languages. (Q21)',1,70451),(5744,115,'我们也可以提供一些有关资金来源变化的信息。',88660,'We could include something about changes in the source of funding, too.',1,84621),(5745,115,'是的，但是请记住，我们只需要写一篇简短的论文，所以最好是不涉及任何细节。',95540,'Yes, but remember we''re only supposed to write a short paper, so it''s probably best if we don''t go into funding in any detail.',1,88661),(5746,115,'好吧，我们先集思广益一下，好吗？',101000,'Right. Well, shall we just brainstorm a few ideas, to get started?',1,95541),(5747,115,'好的。我们显然需要研究新技术的影响，尤其是互联网的影响。',106860,'OK. We obviously need to look at the impact of new technology, particularly the internet.',1,101001),(5748,115,'现在，许多书籍已被数字化，人们可以在家中通过自己的电脑进行阅读。',112000,'Now that lots of books have been digitalised, people can access them from their own computers at home.',1,106861),(5749,115,'如果每个人都这样做，图书馆将被淘汰。',114650,'And if everyone did that, libraries would be obsolete.',1,112001),(5750,115,'是的。',115540,'Yes.',1,114651),(5751,115,'但是可以免费在线获取的数字化书籍大部分都没有版权，不是吗？',122320,'But the digitalised books that are available online for free are mostly out of copyright, aren''t they? (Q22)',1,115541),(5752,115,'作者死后，该国的版权持续70年。',127510,'And copyright in this country lasts for 70 years after the author dies. (Q22)',1,122321),(5753,115,'因此，你将找不到最新的畅销书或最新信息。',131610,'So you won''t find the latest best-seller or up-to-date information. (Q22)',1,127515),(5754,115,'这是重要的一点。',133800,'That''s an important point. (Q22)',1,131611),(5755,115,'无论如何，当我在屏幕上阅读较长的文字时，我很难集中精力。',137730,'Anyway, I find it hard to concentrate when I''m reading a long text on a screen.',1,133801),(5756,115,'我宁愿读一本纸质书。',140320,'I''d much rather read a physical book.',1,137731),(5757,115,'而且在屏幕上阅读需要更长的时间。',142700,'And it takes longer to read on a screen.',1,140321),(5758,115,'哦，我喜欢。',144800,'Oh, I prefer it.',1,142701),(5759,115,'我想这只是个人喜好。',147250,'I suppose it''s just a personal preference.',1,144801),(5760,115,'嗯嗯。我希望图书馆在未来几年内会不断发展。',151520,'Mm. I expect that libraries will go on evolving in the next few years.',1,147251),(5761,115,'有些已经成为进行社区活动的中心，例如当地的俱乐部在那儿聚会。',157320,'Some have already become centres where community activities take place, like local clubs meeting there.',1,151521),(5762,115,'我认为这将变得更加普遍。',159350,'I think that'' ll become even more common.',1,157321),(5763,115,'我想这样想，他们仍然会继续履行其传统职能，但我不确定。',165730,'I''d like to think so, and that they''ll still be serving their traditional function, but I''m not so sure.',1,159351),(5764,115,'毕竟，这涉及到财务问题。',168520,'There are financial implications, after all.',1,165731),(5765,115,'我担心会发生的事情是，书籍和杂志都将消失，而只有一排又一排的计算机。',175230,'What I''m afraid will happen is that books and magazines will all disappear and there''ll just be rows and rows of computers. (Q23)',1,168521),(5766,115,'它们看起来不会像我们惯用的图书馆那样。',177750,'They won''t look anything like the libraries we''re used to.',1,175231),(5767,115,'是的，我们将会看到。',231720,'Well.we''ll see.',1,177751),(5768,115,'我刚有了个主意。',233610,'I''ve just had an idea.',1,231721),(5769,115,'我们为什么不深入研究本地公共图书馆作为我们论文的背景呢？',238560,'Why don''t we make an in-depth study of our local public library as background to our paper?',1,233611),(5770,115,'是的，那会很有趣，可以提出各种各样的问题。',242690,'Yes, that''d be interesting, and raise all sorts of issues.',1,238561),(5771,115,'让我们列出可能要问的问题，然后制定某种结构。',248240,'Let''s make a list of possible things we could ask about, then work out some sort of structure.',1,242691),(5772,115,'例如，呃，我们可以采访一些员工，并找出图书馆是否有自己的预算，或者是否由地方议会控制。',256680,'For instance,um, we could interview some of the staff,and find out whether the library has its own budget, or if that''s controlled by the local council. (Q24)',1,248241),(5773,115,'以及他们的政策是什么。',258260,'And what their policies are.',1,256681),(5774,115,'我知道他们不允许吃东西，但我很想知道他们禁止使用哪种类型的噪音--那里似乎总是在谈论很多话题，但从来没有音乐。',266580,'I know they don''t allow food,but I''d love to find out what types of noise they ban-there always seems to be a lot of talking, but never music.',1,258261),(5775,115,'我不知道这是一项政策，还是就这么发生了。',269000,'I don''t know if that''s a policy or it just happens.',1,266581),(5776,115,'啊，我经常想知道。',271000,'Ah, I''ve often wondered.',1,269001),(5777,115,'然后是诸如图书馆如何受到雇佣法的影响之类的事情。',276640,'Then there are things like how the library is affected by employment laws. (Q25)',1,271001),(5778,115,'我想应该有关于工作时间和设施等方面的规定。',281000,'I suppose there are rules about working hours,facilities for staff, and so on. (Q25)',1,276641),(5779,115,'是的，然后还有其他与建筑物设计以及客户使用方式有关的问题。',286800,'Right.Then there are other issues relating to the design of the building and how customers use it. （Q26)',1,281001),(5780,115,'比如图书馆采取什么措施来确保其安全？',290340,'Like what measures does the library take to ensure their safety? (Q26)',1,286801),(5781,115,'他们需要不滑的地板，比如紧急出口。',295490,'They''d need floor coverings that aren''t slippery, and emergency exits, for instance.',1,290341),(5782,115,'哦，还有一件事--问题是图书馆需要提供什么样的保险，以防万一有人受伤。',301710,'Oh, and another thing-there''s the question of the kind of insurance the library needs to have, in case anyone gets injured. (Q27)',1,295491),(5783,115,'是的，这是另一件需要发现的事。',304000,'Yes, that''s something else to find out.',1,301711),(5784,115,'你知道我经常想知道的事情吗？',306000,'You know something I''ve often wondered?',1,304001),(5785,115,'那是什么？',307000,'What''s that?',1,306001),(5786,115,'好吧，你知道他们有几年前当地报纸的档案吗？',311000,'Well, you know they''ve got an archive of local newspapers going back years?',1,307001),(5787,115,'嗯，在它旁边是19世纪晚期一位著名政治家的日记。',317000,'Well, next to it they''ve got the diary of a well-known politician from the late 19th century. (Q28)',1,311001),(5788,115,'我想知道为什么它在那里。',319000,'I wonder why it''s there.',1,317001),(5789,115,'你知道他和这个地区有什么关系吗？',321830,'Do you know what his connection was with this area?',1,319001),(5790,115,'不知道。让我们将其添加到要查找的事物列表中。',326000,'No idea. Let''s add it to our list of things to find out.',1,321831),(5791,115,'哦，我只是在想——你知道人们可能会在图书馆问关于当地或像体育俱乐部这样的组织吗?',333000,'Oh, I''ve Just thought - you know people might ask in the library about local organisations like sports clubs? (Q29)',1,326001),(5792,115,'嗯，想知道他们是否保留数据库，或者他们是否只是在线上看。',337170,'Well,I wonder if they keep a database,or whether they just look online. (Q29)',1,333001),(5793,115,'对的。我很想知道向公众开放的图书馆与作为博物馆一部分的图书馆之间的区别是什么--它们一定非常不同。',347000,'Right. I quite fancy finding out what the differences are between a library that''s open to the public and one that''s part of a museum,for example-they must be very different. (Q30)',1,337171),(5794,115,'嗯。然后我想知道的是……',349670,'Mmm. Then something else I''d like to know is…',1,347001),(5795,116,'在公开讨论业务时，我们认为某些价值观是理所当然的。',79250,'In public discussion of business, we take certain values for granted.',1,74001),(5796,116,'今天，我将谈论其中的四个：协作，努力，创造力和卓越。',88310,'Today I''m going to talk about four of them: collaboration, hard work，creativity and excellence.',1,79251),(5797,116,'大多数人会说他们都是“好东西”。',92000,'Most people would say they''re all ''good things''.',1,88311),(5798,116,'我认为这是一种过于简单的观点。',96000,'I''m going to suggest that''s an over-simple view.',1,92001),(5799,116,'这些价值观的问题在于，它们只是理论概念，与日常业务的现实脱节。',104000,'The trouble with these values is that they''re theoretical concepts,removed from the reality of day-to-day business.',1,96001),(5800,116,'一定要追求价值，但要为可能发生的结果做好准备。',110000,'Pursue values by all means，but be prepared for what may happen as a result. (Q31)',1,104001),(5801,116,'它们实际上可能造成损坏，这完全不是我们的本意。',115480,'They can actually cause damage, which is not at all the intention. (Q31)',1,110001),(5802,116,'商业领袖通常努力做正确的事情。',119000,'Business leaders generally try to do the right thing.',1,115481),(5803,116,'但是，如果这些领导者在没有理解和管理由此产生的副作用的情况下采用价值观，那么正确的做法往往会适得其反。',128790,'But all too often the right thing backfires,if those leaders adopt values without understanding and managing the side effects that arise. (Q32)',1,119001),(5804,116,'这些值很容易妨碍实际的意图。',133760,'The values can easily get in the way of what''s actually intended.',1,128791),(5805,116,'好的。因此，我要讨论的第一个价值是协作。',139740,'OK. So the first value I''m going to discuss is collaboration.',1,133761),(5806,116,'嗯，让我举个例子。',142390,'Er, let me give you an example.',1,139741),(5807,116,'我曾经参加过一个管理培训课程中，我们被分成小组，必须用我们得到的积木建造一座横跨溪流的桥。',153470,'On a management training course I once attended,we were put into groups and had to construct a bridge across a stream,using building blocks that we were given. (Q33)',1,142391),(5808,116,'规则是，团队中的每个人都必须在建造过程中至少移动一个积木。',160670,'The rule was that everyone in the team had to move at least one building block during the construction.',1,153471),(5809,116,'这是为了鼓励团队合作。',164230,'This was intended to encourage teamwork.',1,160671),(5810,116,'但这确实是一个人做的最好的工作。',168000,'But it was really a Job best done by one person.',1,164231),(5811,116,'其他团队尝试合作构建结构，并陷入混乱，每个人都互相妨碍。',177000,'The other teams tried to collaborate on building the structure, and descended into confusion,with everyone getting in each other''s way. (Q34)',1,168001),(5812,116,'我们的团队负责人出色地解决了挑战。',180180,'Our team leader solved the challenge brilliantly.',1,177001),(5813,116,'她只是简单地要求团队中的每个人都移动几厘米，以遵守规则，然后让团队中有天赋的人独自解决这种难题。',192370,'She simply asked everyone in the team to move a piece a few centimetres, to comply with the rule,and then let the person in the team with an aptitude for puzzles like this build it alone.',1,180181),(5814,116,'我们比其他任何团队都要先完成。',195710,'We finished before any other team.',1,192371),(5815,116,'我的观点是，这项任务并不真正适合团队合作，那么为什么要这样做呢？',203660,'My point is that the task wasn''t really suited to teamworking, so why make it one?',1,195711),(5816,116,'团队合作还可能导致不一致--这是销售不佳的常见原因。',210000,'Teamwork can also lead to inconsistency-a common cause of poor sales.',1,203661),(5817,116,'在某家公司推出智能手机的案例中，一名董事希望瞄准商业市场，另一名董事则要求瞄准消费者。',222000,'In the case of a smartphone that a certain company launched,one director wanted to target the business market,and another demanded it was aimed at consumers. (Q35)',1,210001),(5818,116,'该公司希望两位董事都参与其中,因此给产品起了便于消费者使用的名称，但却把它推销给了公司。',232000,'The company wanted both directors to be involved,so gave the product a consumer-friendly name,but marketed it to companies. (Q35)',1,222001),(5819,116,'结果是，这两个群体的需求都没有得到满足。',236000,'The result was that it met the needs of neither group. (Q35)',1,232001),(5820,116,'最好让一位董事或另一位董事按自己的方式行事，而不是两者兼而有之。',246610,'It would have been better to let one director or the other have his way, not both. (Q35)',1,236001),(5821,116,'现在是勤劳，或辛苦的工作。',252000,'Now industriousness, or hard work.',1,246611),(5822,116,'嘲笑那些说他们努力工作的人很容易：毕竟，一只仓鼠在轮子上跑来跑去，努力工作，却一事无成。',262000,'It''s easy to mock people who say they work hard:after all, a hamster running around in a wheel is working hard-and getting nowhere.',1,252001),(5823,116,'当然，努力工作是很有价值的，但前提是要有针对性的。',267000,'Of course hard work is valuable, but only when properly targeted. (Q36)',1,262001),(5824,116,'否则会浪费公司最宝贵的时间和精力。',272590,'Otherwise it wastes the resources that companies value most-time and energy. (Q36)',1,267001),(5825,116,'这对组织不利。',276000,'And that''s bad for the organisation. (Q36)',1,272591),(5826,116,'有一种管理模式根据四个标准对人们进行分组:聪明、勤奋、愚蠢和懒惰。',286180,'There''s a management model that groups people according to four criteria:clever, hard- working, stupid and lazy.',1,276001),(5827,116,'这里的“懒惰”指的是有一个理性的决心不去执行不必要的任务。',293000,'Here ''lazy'' means having a rational determination not to carry out unnecessary tasks. (Q37)',1,286181),(5828,116,'这并不意味着要完全避免工作。',296320,'It doesn''t mean trying to avoid work altogether.',1,293001),(5829,116,'大多数人表现出以下两个特征，而最有价值的人是那些既聪明又懒惰的人：他们具有理智的头脑，而且不急于做出决定。',311640,'Most people display two of these characteristics, and the most valuable people are those who are both clever and lazy:they possess intellectual clarity,and they don''t rush into making decisions.',1,296321),(5830,116,'他们提出了解决方案，以节省愚蠢而努力的团队所花费的时间和精力。',318450,'They come up with solutions to save the time and energy spent by the stupid and hard-working group.',1,311641),(5831,116,'与其花更多的工时解决问题，聪明而懒惰的团队正在寻找更有效的解决方案。',326590,'Instead of throwing more man-hours at a problem,the clever and lazy group looks for a more effective solution.',1,318451),(5832,116,'接下来，我们来谈谈创造力。',330380,'Next we come to creativity.',1,326591),(5833,116,'这通常很有效——例如，创造一个吸引眼球的电视广告，可能会增加销售额。',339230,'This often works well-creating an attention-grabbing TV commercial, for example, might lead to increased sales.',1,330381),(5834,116,'但这并不总是一件好事。',342630,'But it isn''t always a good thing.',1,339231),(5835,116,'一些广告活动因其创意而被人们记住，但对销售额却没有任何影响。',349660,'Some advertising campaigns are remembered for their creativity,without having any effect on sales.',1,342631),(5836,116,'这发生在几年前一款巧克力棒推出时:随后的研究表明，许多消费者记得广告，但不知道广告是什么。',361590,'This happened a few years ago with the launch of a chocolate bar:subsequent research showed that plenty of consumers remembered the adverts,but had no idea what was being advertised. (Q38)',1,349661),(5837,116,'问题在于创作者从提出创意中获得乐趣，并错误地认为活动的用户也会分享这种感觉。',372610,'The trouble is that the creator derives pleasure from coming up with the idea,and wrongly assumes the audience for the campaign will share that feeling.',1,361591);
INSERT INTO `cambridge_listening_item` VALUES (5838,116,'一个生产数千种新产品的公司可能看起来比一个只有几种新产品的公司更有创意，但它可能太有创意了，利润更少。',385460,'A company that brings out thousands of new products may seem more creative than a company that only has a few,but it may be too creative, and make smaller profits.',1,372611),(5839,116,'创造力需要有针对性，以解决公司已确定的问题。',391760,'Creativity needs to be targeted,to solve a problem that the company has identified. (Q39)',1,385461),(5840,116,'仅仅提出越来越多的新颖产品不一定是一件好事。',398270,'Just coming up with more and more novel products isn¡¯t necessarily a good thing.',1,391761),(5841,116,'最后，卓越。我们都知道公司声称自己“追求卓越”，但是要实现卓越需要很长时间。',409770,'And finally,excellence. We all know companies that claim they ''strive for excellence'',but it takes a long time to achieve excellence.',1,398271),(5842,116,'在业务上，首先拥有一种产品比拥有最好的产品更有利可图。',416820,'In business, being first with a product is more profitable than having the best product.',1,409771),(5843,116,'一项关于公司绩效的主要研究比较了先驱者(即推出某一特定产品的第一个版本的公司)和追随者(即复制并改进该产品的公司)。',432320,'A major study of company performance compared pioneers-that is, companies bringing out the first version of a particular product-with followers,the companies that copied and improved on that product.',1,416821),(5844,116,'研究发现，先驱者的平均市场份额为29%，而追随者的市场份额不到前者的一半，只有13%——尽管他们的产品可能更好。',448430,'The study found that the pioneers commanded an average market share of 29 percent,while the followers achieved less than half that,only 13 percent-even though their product might have been better. (Q40)',1,432321),(5845,116,'在我们所做的每一件事中坚持追求卓越是很费时的，浪费能量，导致失去机会。',458220,'Insisting on excellence in everything we do is time-consuming,wastes energy and leads to losing out on opportunities.',1,448431),(5846,116,'有时，二流的工作比卓越的工作更值得。',463480,'Sometimes, second-rate work is more worthwhile than Excellence.',1,458221),(5847,116,'“确保其优秀”听起来像是一个很好的商业方法，但是“首先开始”方法可能更成功。',472980,'Make sure it''s excellent'' sounds like a good approach to business,but the ''just- get-started''approach is likely to be more successful.',1,463481),(5848,117,'早上好，肯顿音乐节票房。我可以帮你一些忙吗？',104760,'Good morning, Kenton Festival box office. How can I help you?',1,100789),(5849,117,'哦，早上好。',106550,'Oh, good morning.',1,104761),(5850,117,'我下个月要去肯顿度假几天，一个朋友告诉我有个节日。',113580,'I''m coming to Kenton for a few days'' holiday next month,and a friend told me there''s a festival.',1,106551),(5851,117,'她给了我这个号码以查找有关的信息。',116020,'She gave me this number to find out about it.',1,113588),(5852,117,'没错，音乐节从5月16日开始，一直持续到19日。',123390,'That''s right, the festival begins on the 16th of May and goes on till the 19th.',1,116021),(5853,117,'哦，太好了。',125100,'Oh, that''s great.',1,123390),(5854,117,'我将从15号到19号在那里。',129080,'I''ll be there from the 15th till the 19th.',1,125109),(5855,117,'所以请问你能告诉我这个程序吗？',132160,'So could you tell me the programme. please?',1,129081),(5856,117,'当然，第一天在市中心有开幕式。',137600,'Well, on the first day, there''s the opening ceremony, in the town centre.',1,132168),(5857,117,'为了找一个好地方观看，人们在2点左右开始聚集，活动将在2.45开始，大约5.30结束。',150780,'People start gathering around 2 o''clock, to get a good place to see from,and the events will start at 2.45, and finish about 5.30. (Q1)',1,137605),(5858,117,'好，谢谢。',152040,'OK, thanks.',1,150781),(5859,117,'我会确保早点到达那里，这是一个好地方。',155780,'I''ll make sure I get there early to get a good spot.',1,152048),(5860,117,'该节日将由市长正式开幕。',159660,'The festival will be officially opened by the mayor.',1,155781),(5861,117,'他将发言几分钟，欢迎大家参加音乐节。',165200,'He''ll just speak for a few minutes, welcoming everyone to the festival.',1,159664),(5862,117,'所有的镇议员都将在那里，当然还有很多其他人。',170650,'All the town councillors will be there, and of course lots of other people.',1,165204),(5863,117,'是的。',171700,'Right.',1,170654),(5864,117,'然后将有乐队表演。',175570,'Then there''ll be a performance by a band. (Q2)',1,171708),(5865,117,'多数年来，我们有一个儿童合唱团，但是今年当地的陆军学员愿意提供表演，他们非常出色。',184090,'Most years we have a children''s choir, but this year the local army cadets offered to perform,and they''re very good.',1,175572),(5866,117,'嗯哈。',184960,'Uhuh.',1,184091),(5867,117,'之后，镇上的一个社区团体将表演他们自己写的戏剧，只是一小段。关于海伦·通盖特（Helen Tungate）。',195590,'After that,a community group from the town will perform a play they''ve written themselves,just a short one.It''s about Helen Tungate.  (Q3)',1,184969),(5868,117,'我不知道你是否听说过她？',197930,'I don''t know if you''ve heard of her?',1,195595),(5869,117,'我当然有。',200030,'I certainly have.',1,197930),(5870,117,'她几年前是一名科学家。',202530,'She was a scientist years ago. (Q4)',1,200038),(5871,117,'是的。',203770,'That''s right.',1,202536),(5872,117,'她正好100年前出生在肯顿，所以我们正在庆祝她的百年诞辰。',210780,'She was born in Kenton exactly 100 years ago,so we''re celebrating her centenary.',1,203771),(5873,117,'我是生物学家，所以我一直对她感兴趣。',214770,'I''m a biologist, so I''ve always been interested in her.',1,210787),(5874,117,'我不知道她来自肯顿。',217210,'I didn''t realise she came from Kenton.',1,214773),(5875,117,'是的。好吧，所有的事情都在下午进行，再晚些时候，当太阳落山时，将会有烟火表演。',227010,'Yes. Well, all that will take place in the afternoon,and later, as the sun sets, there''ll be a firework display. (Q5)',1,217215),(5876,117,'你应该去公园观看，因为从那里你可以看到最好的风景，而展览在河的对面进行。',236610,'You should go to the park to watch，as you''ll get the best view from there,and the display takes place on the opposite side of the river. (Q5)',1,227011),(5877,117,'它始终是音乐节中最受欢迎的活动之一。',240180,'It''s always one of the most popular events in the festival.',1,236610),(5878,117,'听起来不错。',283490,'Sounds great.',1,240182),(5879,117,'那其他几天呢?',286330,'And what''s happening on the other days?',1,283495),(5880,117,'有几个事件一直在进行。',290020,'There are several events that go on the whole time.',1,286334),(5881,117,'例如，艺术学院的学生制作了许多视频，都与孩子和祖父母之间的关系有关。',301200,'For example, the students of the art college have produced a number of videos, all connected with relationships between children and their grandparents. (Q6)',1,290029),(5882,117,'听起来很有趣。',303280,'That sounds interesting.',1,301206),(5883,117,'这跟孩子和父母不一样，不是吗?',306910,'It makes a change from children and parents, doesn''t it!',1,303282),(5884,117,'完全正确。因为艺术学院是用来上课的，所以在整个艺术节期间，这些视频都在Handsworth House播放。',317850,'Exactly. Because the art college is in use for classes, throughout the festival, the videos are being shown in Handsworth House. (Q7)',1,306916),(5885,117,'这个名字怎么拼?',319800,'How do you spell the name?',1,317852),(5886,117,'H-A-N-D-S-W-O-R-T-H, Handsworth房子。',329420,'H-A-N-D-S-W-O-R-T-H, Handsworth House.',1,319806),(5887,117,'离市政厅很近。',331710,'It''s close to the Town Hall.',1,329425),(5888,117,'是的。',332960,'Right.',1,331716),(5889,117,'让我想想，我还能告诉你什么?',337180,'Now let me see, what else can I tell you about?',1,332968),(5890,117,'有芭蕾舞表演吗?',340440,'Are there any displays of ballet dancing?',1,337182),(5891,117,'我对此特别感兴趣，因为这是我的业余爱好。',344380,'I''m particularly interested in that as I do it as a hobby.',1,340449),(5892,117,'恐怕没有芭蕾舞表演了，但是将有来自全国各地的传统舞蹈表演。',352410,'There isn''t any ballet, I''m afraid, but there''ll be a demonstration of traditional dances from all round the country. (Q8)',1,344388),(5893,117,'哦，那太好了。',354150,'Oh, that''d be nice.',1,352417),(5894,117,'在哪里举行?',355710,'Where''s that being held?',1,354158),(5895,117,'是在市中心的市场，户外的那个，不是有盖的市场。',362250,'It''s in the market in the town centre - the outdoor one, not the covered market. (Q9)',1,355715),(5896,117,'除了第一天，艺术节每天下午2点和5点开始。',369730,'And it''s on at 2 and 5 every afternoon of the festival, apart from the first day.',1,362250),(5897,117,'好极了。我对各种舞蹈都很感兴趣，所以我相信我会喜欢的!',375530,'Lovely. I''m interested in all kinds of dancing, so I''m sure I''ll enjoy that!',1,369731),(5898,117,'嗯。我相信你会的。',377210,'Mmm. I''m sure you will.',1,375533),(5899,117,'如果有音乐会的话，我真的很想去。',381670,'And I''d really like to go to some concerts, if there are any.',1,377213),(5900,117,'是的，有几个。',383650,'Yes, there are several.',1,381671),(5901,117,'三场由专业人士表演，一场由当地儿童表演。',388780,'Three performed by professionals, and one by local children.',1,383656),(5902,117,'在哪里举行?',390830,'And where is it being held?',1,388786),(5903,117,'在公园街的图书馆，18号，晚上6点半。',398830,'It''s in the library, which is in Park Street, on the 18th, at 6.30 in the evening.',1,390832),(5904,117,'我想我需要门票。',401520,'I presume I''ll need tickets for that.',1,398835),(5905,117,'是的，你可以在网上预订，也可以在到达肯顿后在节日售票处购买，或者在橱窗里展示我们标志的商店购买。',415340,'Yes, you can book online, or you can buy them when you arrive in Kenton, either at the festival box office, or from any shops displaying our logo in the windows.  (Q10)',1,401522),(5906,117,'嗯，我想我在Kenton的整个时间都会很忙。',420820,'Well, I think that''ll keep me busy for the whole of my stay in Kenton.',1,415343),(5907,117,'非常感谢你的帮助。',423350,'Thank you so much for all your help.',1,420821),(5908,117,'不用客气，希望你在这里过得愉快。',426650,'You''re welcome, I hope you enjoy your stay.',1,423356),(5909,117,'谢谢你！再见。',428059,'Thank you. Goodbye.',1,426654),(5910,118,'是的。我现在几乎已经成功地确定了我们的旅行计划，所以我会把我所知道的最新情况告诉你们',73700,'Right. I’ve now almost succeeded in finalising plans for our tour, so I’ll bring you up to date with what I know.',1,63581),(5911,118,'如你所知，我们将在4号星期一先飞往慕尼黑。',80000,'As you know, we''re flying first to Munich, on Monday the 4th.',1,73701),(5912,118,'飞机11点半起飞，所以现在去机场吃午饭太早了。',86790,'The flight is at 11.30, so it''s too early to have lunch at the airport.',1,80001),(5913,118,'我建议我们10点在那里见面喝杯咖啡，这样我们在离开家之前有足够的时间吃早餐。',97380,'I suggest we meet there for coffee at 10, which should give us plenty of time for breakfast before we leave home. (Q11)',1,86791),(5914,118,'当我们到达慕尼黑时，克劳斯·鲍尔会在机场迎接我们。',104000,'When we arrive in Munich, we''ll be met at the airport by Claus Bauer. (Q12)',1,97381),(5915,118,'克劳斯为一家旅行社工作，我们在德国期间他会照顾我们。',111620,'Claus works for a tour operator, and he''ll look after us for the time we''ll be in Germany. (Q12)',1,104001),(5916,118,'他已经和我们要去的剧院的经理联系过了，他还安排了一位慕尼黑国家剧院的官员在我们逗留期间的一个下午带我们参观剧院。',127620,'He''s already liaised with the managers of the theatres we''re going to visit, and he''s also arranged for an officer of the National Theatre in Munich to show us round the theatre one afternoon during our stay.',1,111621),(5917,118,'上次我们讨论这次旅行的时候，我没有酒店房间的确切费用，但是现在我有了。',136810,'Now last time we discussed this trip, I didn''t have the precise cost for hotel rooms, but now I have.',1,127621),(5918,118,'我们住的旅馆的正常价格是双人房每晚150欧元。',144790,'The normal rate at the hotel where we''re staying is 150 euros a night for a double room. (Q13)',1,136811),(5919,118,'我本来希望能降到120欧元，但事实上我已经谈到了110欧元。',155000,'I''d hoped to get that down to 120 euros, but in fact I''ve been able to negotiate a rate of 110. (Q13)',1,144791),(5920,118,'这将反映在你本周末需要支付的最后一笔款项中。',162000,'That''ll be reflected in the final payment which you''ll need to make by the end of this week.',1,155001),(5921,118,'周二，也就是我们抵达后的第二天，我本希望我们能在一家剧院旁听彩排，但不幸的是，这被证明是很难安排的，所以我们只好坐长途汽车去慕尼黑南部山区的一个令人惊奇的城堡。',185000,'On Tuesday, the day after our arrival, I had hoped we could sit in on a rehearsal at one of the theatres, but unfortunately that''s proved very difficult to arrange, so instead we''ll have a coach trip to one of the amazing castles in the mountains south of Munich.',1,162001),(5922,118,'星期二晚上，我们将在酒店附近的餐厅一起吃晚饭。',191520,'On Tuesday evening, we''ll all have dinner together in a restaurant near our hotel.',1,185001),(5923,118,'通过和你们谈论自己的偏好，很明显，对你们中的一些人来说，一家典型的当地餐馆太以肉类为主了。',203210,'From talking to you all about your preferences, it was clear that a typical local restaurant would be too meat-oriented for some of you.',1,191521),(5924,118,'你们中有些人建议去意大利餐厅，但我必须承认，我决定订一家黎巴嫩餐厅，因为我们在家有很多机会去意大利餐厅。',217000,'Some of you suggested an Italian restaurant, but I must confess that I decided to book a Lebanese one, as we have plenty of opportunities to go to an Italian restaurant at home. (Q14)',1,203211),(5925,118,'星期三下午，我们晚上要看的那出戏的导演将在剧院和我们谈话。',225400,'On Wednesday afternoon, the director of the play we''re going to see that evening will talk to us at the theatre. (Q15)',1,217001),(5926,118,'她将描述制作一出戏的整个过程，包括她如何选择演员，以及，因为我们将要看到的是一部现代剧，她是如何与剧作家合作的。',280690,'She''ll describe the whole process of producing a play, including how she chose the actors, and, as the play we''re going to see is a modern one, how she worked with the playwright.',1,225401),(5927,118,'现在我想就我们将要看的戏剧发表几点看法，部分原因是它可能会影响你对随身衣服的选择!',293700,'Right. Now I''d just like to make a few points about the plays we''re going to see, partly because it might influence your choice of clothes to take with you!',1,280691),(5928,118,'我们星期三晚上看的是一出现代话剧，我们要去看首映式，所以那将是一个很讲究的场合，当然你不必穿得很正式。',307000,'The play we''re seeing on Wednesday evening is a modern one, and we''re going to the premiere, so it''ll be quite a dressy occasion, though of course you don''t have to dress formally. (Q16)',1,293701),(5929,118,'我猜这是一部多媒体作品，有着惊人的灯光效果和电子音乐，但不幸的是，剧作家生病了，不太可能出席。',323210,'I gather it''s rather a multimedia production, with amazing lighting effects and a soundtrack of electronic music, though unfortunately the playwright is ill and is unlikely to be able to attend.',1,307001),(5930,118,'周四我们将观看去年首次上演的戏剧，当时是为了纪念一位著名科学家在这个小镇诞生100周年。',335450,'On Thursday we''re seeing a play that was first performed last year, when it was commissioned to mark a hundred years since the birth in the town of a well-known scientist. (Q17)',1,323211),(5931,118,'我们将看到那部作品的复兴，它引起了很多人的兴趣。',342000,'We''re going to see a revival of that production, which aroused a lot of interest.',1,335451),(5932,118,'周五的演出真的会让你绞尽脑汁地考虑该带些什么衣服，因为它将在一座宫殿的花园里上演。',350540,'Friday''s play will really make you think hard about what clothes to pack, as it''ll be in the garden of a palace. (Q18)',1,342001),(5933,118,'那里的环境很美，但我最好提醒你，那里没有什么挡风的防护设施。',358260,'It''s a beautiful setting, but I''d better warn you, there won''t be much protection from the wind.',1,350541),(5934,118,'星期六，我们要乘长途汽车去离慕尼黑不远的另一个城镇的一家剧院。',365610,'On Saturday, we''re going by coach to a theatre in another town, not far from Munich. (Q19)',1,358261),(5935,118,'这将是一个戏剧节的开幕式，市长和镇上所有的达官贵人都将出席。',374750,'This will be the opening of a drama festival, and the mayor and all the other dignitaries of the town will be attending. (Q19)',1,365611),(5936,118,'演出结束后，市长将为所有观众举行招待会，届时将有乐队演奏当地传统音乐。',384770,'After the performance, the mayor is hosting a reception for all the audience, and there''ll be a band playing traditional music of the region.',1,374751),(5937,118,'周日休息一天后，我们的最后一场演出是在周一，演出地点是古老的市政厅，可以追溯到14世纪。',398480,'And after having a day off on Sunday, our final play is on Monday, and it''s in the stunning setting of the old Town Hall, which dates back to the 14th century. (Q20)',1,384771),(5938,118,'这出戏标志着男主角登台五十周年，也是多年前他第一次登台演出的那出戏。',411470,'The performance marks the fifty years that the lead actor has been on stage, and the play is the one where he made his first professional appearance, all those years ago.',1,398481),(5939,118,'第二天，我们就可以飞回家了。',416490,'And the day after that, we''ll be flying back home.',1,411471),(5940,118,'在此之前，你还有什么问题吗...',421020,'Now have you got any questions before I…',1,416491),(5941,119,'噢,早上好。你一定是詹姆斯。',65000,'Oh good morning. You must be James.',1,62461),(5942,119,'我是贝丝·卡特莱特，请叫我贝丝。',68000,'I''m Beth Cartwright - please call me Beth.',1,65001),(5943,119,'谢谢。',69190,'Thank you.',1,68001),(5944,119,'这是你上斯堪的纳维亚研究课程后的第一次辅导课，我想了解一下你的情况。',78000,'Now as this is your first tutorial since you started on the Scandinavian Studies course, I''d like to find out something about you.',1,69191),(5945,119,'你为什么决定选这门课?',80400,'Why did you decide to take this course?',1,78001),(5946,119,'嗯，我母亲是丹麦人，虽然我们一直住在英国，但她经常谈论她的家，这让我想去丹麦看看。',90810,'Well, my mother is Danish, and although we always lived in England, she used to talk about her home a lot, and that made me want to visit Denmark. (Q21)',1,80401),(5947,119,'但我们很少去，因为我妈妈通常一个人去。',95370,'We hardly ever did, though - my mother usually went on her own. (Q21)',1,90811),(5948,119,'但只要她的亲戚或朋友在英国，他们总是来看我们。',100640,'But whenever her relations or friends were in England they always came to see us.  (Q21)',1,95371),(5949,119,'我明白了。我猜你已经会说丹麦语了，这是你将要学习的语言之一。',108810,'I see. So I assume you already speak Danish, one of the languages you''ll be studying.',1,100641),(5950,119,'我和别人说话的时候还过得去，虽然我不是很准确。',112380,'I can get by when I talk to people, though I''m not ter