义的和适当的流动。',379680,'Make sure that this skeleton makes sense and flows properly, before writing up the paper in full.',1,373601),(5999,119,'好的。谢谢，这很有帮助。',383000,'OK. Thanks, that''s very helpful.',1,379681),(6000,120,'这些年来，人们对工人的态度发生了很大的变化。',80460,'Over the years, attitudes towards workers have changed considerably.',1,74321),(6001,120,'毕竟，有过一段时间工人根本就没什么权利，而且是在很可怕的条件下劳动。',89180,'After all, there was a time when workers had no rights at all, and laboured in&nbsp;appalling&nbsp;conditions.',1,80461),(6002,120,'条件改善了很多，但工作场所的冲突仍然很常见。',96680,'Conditions have improved a lot, but conflict in the workplace is still common.',1,89181),(6003,120,'现在的人力资源经理需要有能力在必要的时候处理它。',104460,'And human resources managers nowadays need to be able to deal with it when necessary.',1,96681),(6004,120,'什么是职场冲突?',108260,'What is conflict in the workplace? (Q31)',1,104461),(6005,120,'定义各不相同，但我认为它指的是受害者认为不可接受的一系列行为，从轻微的、无害的争论到相反的极端——身体暴力。',126470,'Definitions vary, but I''m taking it to refer to a whole range of behaviours that the victim finds unacceptable, from minor, harmless arguments to - at the opposite extreme - physical violence. (Q31)',1,108261),(6006,120,'这在很大程度上包含在欺凌一词中，我指的是一个或多个人对处于弱势地位的另一个人进行虐待或攻击性的行为。',142260,'Much of this is covered by the term bullying, by which I mean one or more people behaving abusively or aggressively against another who is in a weaker position. (Q31)',1,126471),(6007,120,'尽管所有这样的行为都是冲突的一种形式，但并不是所有的冲突都可以用这些术语来描述。',152000,'Although all behaviour like this is a form of conflict, not all conflict can be described in these terms.',1,142261),(6008,120,'就像所有的人类行为一样，这有许多原因。',157790,'As with all human behaviour, there are numerous reasons for it.',1,152001),(6009,120,'但这通常是由某人感到需要显示他们对其他人的优越性，以感到他们不是在一个等级或一群人的最低水平。',174250,'But often it''s caused by someone who feels the need to show their superiority over someone else, in order to feel that they aren''t at the lowest level in a hierarchy or a group of people. (Q32)',1,157791),(6010,120,'在某些情况下，一个人就是不喜欢另一个人，因为一个人的性格在某种程度上与另一个人的性格不相容。',189000,'In some cases one person simply dislikes the other, on the basis that the personality of one is in some way incompatible with that of the other person. (Q33)',1,174251),(6011,120,'一个人的乐观习惯可能会让他们无法容忍一个经常悲观的同事——当然，这并不是恶劣对待他们的理由。',204440,'A general habit of optimism in one person could make them intolerant of a colleague who''s constantly pessimistic - not that that justifies treating them badly, of course.',1,189001),(6012,120,'当人们更关心提升自己和团队而不是公司整体时，就会出现一些冲突。',215480,'Some conflicts arise when people are more interested in promoting themselves and their team than in the company as a whole. (Q34)',1,204441),(6013,120,'这些冲突被称为“结构性”冲突，例如，当一个销售团队认为他们是业务中唯一做有用工作的人，而看不起幕后的管理人员时，就可能发生这种冲突。',234850,'These conflicts are called ''structural'', and could come about, for example, when a sales team believe they are the only people in the business who do any useful work, and look down on behind-the-scenes administrators. (Q34)',1,215481),(6014,120,'冲突显然影响到有关的个人--这种情况很可能使受害者感到非常紧张，导致他们旷工，可能长达数月。',250870,'Conflict obviously affects the individuals concerned - the situation is likely to be very stressful for victims, resulting in their absence from work, possibly for months. (Q35)',1,234851),(6015,120,'对于公司来说，如果不努力去处理冲突，冲突就会逐渐失控，甚至导致业务崩溃。',267270,'For the company, if no effort is made to deal with conflict, it can spiral out of control, and even lead to the breakdown of the business.',1,250871),(6016,120,'一些关于首席执行官的有趣研究揭示了他们可能对同事不好的一些原因。',279020,'Some interesting work with chief executives - CEOs - has uncovered some of the reasons why they may treat colleagues badly.',1,267271),(6017,120,'许多ceo结合了两种相反的特征:自信——即相信自己有能力取得巨大成就——和高度的焦虑，害怕无法实现自己或公司董事设定的目标。',303200,'Many CEOs combine two opposing characteristics: confidence - that is, the belief that they''re capable of great achievements - with a high level of anxiety, a fear of missing targets, whether set by themselves or by the directors of the company. (Q36)',1,279021),(6018,120,'这种组合会让他们对任何质疑他们决定的人做出糟糕的反应。',311580,'This combination can make them respond badly to anyone who questions their decisions.',1,303201),(6019,120,'在高压力的工作环境中，这样的特点就会成为问题。',318360,'In a high pressure work environment, such characteristics become problematic.',1,311581),(6020,120,'当同事、经理和董事会成员都试图实现自己的愿景时，处理这种情况尤其困难。',332000,'And it''s particularly difficult to tackle the situation where colleagues, managers and board members are all trying to achieve their own visions. (Q37)',1,318361),(6021,120,'当他们不能就战略问题和业务发展方向达成一致时，就存在真正的问题。',341300,'When they can''t agree on strategic issues and on where they see the business going, there are real problems. (Q37)',1,332001),(6022,120,'对于组织内较低级别的管理者来说，独裁的管理形式——首席执行官下达命令，其他人都必须服从——似乎会比其他形式发生更多冲突。',359450,'For managers at lower levels within the organisation, it might seem that an autocratic form of management - where the chief executive gives orders and everyone else has to obey - would see more conflict than others.',1,341301),(6023,120,'然而，有趣的是，当不确定向谁汇报时，一个拥有更民主商业模式的公司可能会遭受更多的损失。',376740,'Interestingly, though, a company with a more democratic business model, can suffer more, when uncertainty about who to report to leads to conflicting demands. (Q38)',1,359451),(6024,120,'现在我要讲一下如何处理这种有有害影响的冲突。',384890,'Now I''ll say a little about dealing with the type of conflict that has harmful effects.',1,376741),(6025,120,'当然，最理想的是首先防止它的出现。',390690,'Of course the ideal is to prevent it arising in the first place.',1,384891),(6026,120,'一个好的管理者，无论级别如何，都会努力赢得同事的尊重，尤其是那些向他们汇报的人。',402960,'A good manager, at any level, will make efforts to earn the respect of the people they work with, particularly those who report to them. (Q39)',1,390691),(6027,120,'这将包括在所有的沟通中都要礼貌，并平等地对待那些碰巧在组织中扮演不同角色的人。',414760,'That will involve politeness in all communications, and treating them as equals who happen to have a different role within the organisation.',1,402961),(6028,120,'当然，有时冲突确实会发生，而且可能会失控。',421640,'Sometimes, of course, conflict does occur, and can get out of hand.',1,414761),(6029,120,'在这种情况下，人力资源部门往往会介入。',427630,'In such cases the human resources department often gets involved.',1,421641),(6030,120,'然而，如果冲突的一方认为人力资源只是首席执行官的喉舌，那么外部调解人或许能提供帮助。',442940,'However, if one of the parties in a conflict sees human resources as simply a mouthpiece for the chief executive, then an external mediator might be able to help. (Q40)',1,427631),(6031,120,'通过与双方对话，并试图找到正在发生的事情的真相，他们可以建立一个清楚的情况，并给出双方都会接受的反馈，正是因为他们是独立的。',462510,'By talking to both sides, and trying to find the truth of what''s been happening, they can build a clear picture of the situation, and give feedback that both sides will accept, precisely because they''re independent. ',1,442941),(6032,121,'你好？',120090,'Hello?',1,119412),(6033,121,'嗨，苏茜，我是保罗。你好吗？',124040,'Hi, Susie, it''s Paul here. How are you?',1,120098),(6034,121,'喜欢你的新工作吗？',125860,'Enjoying your new job?',1,124046),(6035,121,'你在图书馆工作，是吗？',128370,'You''re working at the library, aren''t you?',1,125863),(6036,121,'是的。我是在一个月前重新开放图书馆时开始的。',128370,'Yes. I started when the library re-opened a month ago.',1,128370),(6037,121,'这很棒。',134130,'It''s great.',1,128370),(6038,121,'实际上，卡罗尔和我早就想加入了。',137720,'Actually Carol and I have been meaning to join for a while.',1,134131),(6039,121,'哦，你应该的。',139320,'Oh, you should.',1,137722),(6040,121,'它不需要花费任何钱，而且新图书馆有各种各样的设施。',144840,'It doesn''t cost anything,and the new library has all sorts of facilities.',1,139327),(6041,121,'这不仅是你借书的地方。',148190,'It''s not just a place where you borrow books.',1,144846),(6042,121,'例如，有一个座位舒适的区域，你可以坐在那里阅读那里的杂志。',154950,'For instance, there''s an area with comfortable seats where you can sit and read the magazines they have there.',1,148195),(6043,121,'有些人在这里度过了整个上午。',158070,'Some people spend the whole morning there.',1,154953),(6044,121,'真希望我有那么多时间可以花!',160900,'Mmm.Wish I had that amount of time to spend!',1,158077),(6045,121,'是的，你现在一定很忙，孩子们和其他东西？',165810,'Yes, you must be pretty busy at present,with the children and everything?',1,160901),(6046,121,'是的，我们是的。',167370,'We are