ountain in a town square,for example. (Q34)',1,232901),(6393,128,'不一定是我们想要控制或减少的东西。',251270,'That''s not necessarily something that we''d want to control or reduce.',1,246331),(6394,128,'因此，也许研究人员应该在城市设计中考虑这类声音。',256780,'So maybe researchers should consider these sorts of sounds in urban design.',1,251271),(6395,128,'这将很棘手，因为仅测量分贝水平不会对我们有帮助。',263160,'This is going to be tricky because just measuring decibel levels isn''t going to help us here.',1,256781),(6396,128,'相反，许多研究人员使用社会科学技术，通过问卷调查等方式研究人们对声音的情绪反应。',277710,'Instead, many researchers are using social science techniques, studying people''s emotional response to sound by using questionnaires and so on. (Q35)',1,263161),(6397,128,'那么人们想要在城市环境中听到什么呢？',282450,'So what exactly do people want to hear in an urban environment?',1,277711),(6398,128,'最近的一些跨学科研究得出的结果乍一看似乎是矛盾的--一个城市需要有一种活动感，所以它需要生动活泼，听起来像人行道上高跟鞋的拍手声或咖啡的嘶嘶声机器，但是这些一定不能太麻烦，因为同时我们需要能够放松。',307770,'Some recent interdisciplinary research has come out with results that at first sight seem contradictory - a city needs to have a sense of activity,so it needs to be lively,with sounds like the clack of high heels on a pavement or the hiss of a coffee machine,but these mustn'' be too intrusive,because at the same time we need to be able to relax. (Q36)',1,282451),(6399,128,'实现这一目标的主要问题之一将是促使建筑师和城市规划者使用这项研究。',314540,'One of the major problems in achieving this will be getting architects and town planners to use the research. (Q37)',1,307771),(6400,128,'除了研究声学基础知识,这些人在这方面接受的培训很少。',321400,'Apart from studying the basics of acoustics, these people receive very little training in this area. (Q37)',1,314541),(6401,128,'但是实际上，他们应该将声音视为增加城市生活体验的机会，而目前，他们倾向于将声音视为尽可能避免或减少的事情，或者仅仅是像工程师这样的工作。街道排水系统，或者像街道排水系统那样对工程师来说只是工作而已。',339430,'But in fact they should be regarding sound as an opportunity to add to the experience of urban living,whereas at present they tend to see it as something to be avoided or reduced as far as possible,or something that''s just a job for engineers like the 