 and use the stage door there.(Q7)',1,359231),(6445,129,'你可以从里面打开它，但不要忘记在最后锁上它.',374000,'You can open that from inside but don''t forget to lock it at the end.',1,369142),(6446,129,'好的。',375000,'OK.',1,374001),(6447,129,'说到乐队，我确定我不需要告诉你这个，但你必须确保没有人摆弄防火门旁边的黑匣子——',385690,'And talking of bands, I''m sure I don''t need to tell you this, but you must make sure that no one fiddles about with the black box by the fire door -',1,375001),(6448,129,'这是一个系统，当音量达到一定的水平时，它就会加入。这是一个法律要求。',392670,'that''s a system that cuts in when the volume reaches a certain level.It''s a legal requirement.',1,385691),(6449,129,'当然。无论如何，我们希望人们能够相互交谈，所以我们不希望任何声音太大。哦，这提醒我，我们将进行演讲 - 是否有可用的麦克风？',407000,'Sure.Anyway, we want people to be able to talk to one another so we don''t want anything too loud.Oh, that reminds me, we''ll be having speeches - are there any microphones available?',1,392671),(6450,129,'是的。让管理员知道，他会帮你拿的。对了，现在活动结束后，我们确实要求场地保持良好状态。',418460,'Yeah.Just let the caretaker know, he''ll get those for you.Right, now when the event is over we do ask that the premises are left in good condition.',1,407001),(6451,129,'所以有一个上锁的橱柜，你会被告知密码你需要打开它。里面有所有的清洁设备，刷子和清洁剂等等。(Q8)',430740,'So there''s a locked cupboard and you''ll be informed of the code you need to open that.It''s got all the cleaning equipment, brushes and detergent and so on.(Q8)',1,418461),(6452,129,'是的。那么大家都走了之后我们需要做什么？我想是扫地吧？(Q9)',438000,'Right.So what do we need to do after everyone''s gone?Sweep the floors I suppose?(Q9)',1,430741),(6453,129,'嗯，其实他们是要洗的，不光是扫。然后你会得到黑色的塑料袋，所以所有的垃圾都必须收集起来放在门外。',451000,'Well, actually they have to be washed, not just swept.Then you''ll be provided with black plastic bags, so all the rubbish must be collected up and left outside the door.',1,438001),(6454,129,'当然。我们会确保一切都保持整洁。哦，我忘了问，我想我们可以在房间里装饰一下吗？(Q10)',461000,'Of course.We''ll make sure everything''s left tidy.Oh, and I forgot to ask, I presume we can have decorations in the room?(Q10)',1,451001),(6455,129,'是的，但您必须在之后将它们取下。',464530,'Yes, but you must take them down afterwards.',1,461001),(6456,129,'当然。',465410,'Sure.',1,464531),(6457,129,'并且椅子和桌子应该整齐地堆放在房间的后面。',471000,'And the chairs and tables should be stacked up neatly at the back of the room.',1,465411),(6458,129,'我会确保我有几个人来帮助我。',474000,'I''ll make sure I''ve got a few people to help me.',1,471001),(6459,130,'欢迎来到 Fiddy Working Heritage Farm。',49330,'Welcome to the Fiddy Working Heritage Farm.',1,45001),(6460,130,'这个露天博物馆让您体验十九世纪末英国乡村的农业和乡村生活。',58970,'This open-air museum gives you the experience of agriculture and rural life in the English countryside at the end of the nineteenth century.',1,49331),(6461,130,'所以你会看到一个典型的那个时期的农场，和我一样，所有的工作人员都穿着那个时代的衣服。',67220,'So you''ll see a typical farm of that period, and like me, all the staff are dressed in clothes of that time.',1,58971),(6462,130,'在我们继续之前，我必须给你一些建议和安全提示。',72520,'I must give you some advice and safety tips before we go any further.',1,67221),(6463,130,'由于这是一个工作农场，请不要惊吓或伤害动物。(Q11)',77860,'As it''s a working farm, please don''t frighten or injure the animals.(Q11)',1,72521),(6464,130,'我们这里有很多，其中许多是现在非常罕见的品种。',83410,'We have a lot here, and many of them are breeds that are now quite rare.',1,77861),(6465,130,'并与工具保持安全距离(Q12)：其中一些工具有锋利的尖端，可能非常危险，所以请不要触摸它们。',93490,'And do stay at a safe distance from the tools(Q12): some of them have sharp points which can be pretty dangerous, so please don''t touch them.',1,83411),(6466,130,'我们不希望发生任何事故，对吗？',96420,'We don''t want any accidents, do we?',1,93491),(6467,130,'地面非常不平整，如果你穿凉鞋可能会滑倒，所以我很高兴看到你们都穿着鞋子(Q13)——我们总是建议人们这样做。',108760,'The ground is very uneven, and you might slip if you''re wearing sandals soI''m glad to see you''re all wearing shoes(Q13) - we always advise people to do that.',1,96421),(6468,130,'现在，这里非常欢迎所有年龄段的孩子，通常即使是很小的孩子也喜欢鸭子和羊羔，所以下次来时一定要带上它们。',121140,'Now, children of all ages are very welcome here, and usually even very young children love the ducks and lambs, so do bring them along next time you come.',1,108761),(6469,130,'我想你们当中没有人带过狗，但以防万一。(Q14)',126680,'I don''t think any of you have brought dogs with you, but in case you have.(Q14)',1,121141),(6470,130,'恐怕他们得待在停车场，除非他们是导盲犬。',131840,'I''m afraid they''ll have to stay in the car park, unless they''re guide dogs.',1,126681),(6471,130,'我相信你会明白它们可能会给农场带来很多问题。',185000,'I''m sure you''ll understand that they could cause a lot of problems on a farm.',1,131841),(6472,130,'现在让我给你们介绍一下农场的布局。',190480,'Now let me give you some idea of the layout of the farm.',1,185001),(6473,130,'您购买门票的大楼是新谷仓，就在您的右边，我们现在正处于通往农田的主干道的起点 - 当然停车场就在您的左边。',204000,'The building where you bought your tickets is the New Barn, immediately to your right, and we''re now at the beginning of the main path to the farmland - and of course the car park is on your left.',1,190481),(6474,130,'您可以在拐角处的停车场看到稻草人，在主干道旁边，(Q15)它是使鸟类远离庄稼的传统人物，但我们的稻草人是永久性雕塑。',218000,'The scarecrow you can see in the car park in the corner, beside the main path,(Q15) is a traditional figure for keeping the birds away from crops, but our scarecrow is a permanent sculpture.',1,204001),(6475,130,'它比人还高，所以你可以从很远的地方看到它。',224430,'It''s taller than a human being, so you can see it from quite a distance.',1,218001),(6476,130,'如果你向前看，你会看到一个迷宫。',228000,'If you look ahead of you, you''ll see a maze.',1,224431),(6477,130,'它位于新谷仓面，旁边是一条向右分支的小路。(Q16)',235510,'It''s opposite the New Barn, beside the side path that branches off to the right just over there.(Q16)',1,228001),(6478,130,'迷宫是用树篱做成的，树篱太高了，小孩子看不到它们，但它很小，所以你不会在里面迷路！',246440,'The maze is made out of hedges which are too tall for young children to see over them, but it''s quite small, so you can''t get lost in it!',1,235511),(6479,130,'现在。',247350,'Now.',1,246441),(6480,130,'你能看到在主路更远的地方穿过鱼池的桥吗？',252290,'can you see the bridge crossing the fish pool further up the main path?',1,247351),(6481,130,'如果您想去咖啡馆，请朝桥走，然后在桥前右转。',259200,'If you want to go to the café, go towards the bridge and turn right just before it.',1,252291),(6482,130,'沿着小路走，咖啡馆就在您来到的第一个弯道上。(Q17)',265470,'Walk along the side path and the café''s on the first bend you come to.(Q17)',1,259201),(6483,130,'这座建筑原本是校舍，已经有一百多年的历史了。',272380,'The building was originally the schoolhouse, and it''s well over a hundred years old.',1,265471),(6484,130,'您可能知道，我们在这里举办技能工作坊，您可以在那里学习木工和篮子制作等传统工艺。',282000,'As you may know, we run skills workshops here, where you can learn traditional crafts like woodwork and basket-making.',1,272381),(6485,130,'您可以在黑谷仓中查看样品，并与其他人讨论这些课程。',289460,'You can see examples of the work, and talk to someone about the courses, in the Black Barn.',1,282001),(6486,130,'如果你从右边的小路走，就在新谷仓旁边，你会来到黑谷仓，就在小路第一次弯曲的地方。(Q18)',299660,'If you take the side path to the right, here, just by the New Barn, you''ll come to the Black Barn just where the Path first bends.(Q18)',1,289461),(6487,130,'现在我一定不能忘记告诉你关于野餐的事，因为我看到你们中的一些人带了午餐。',307520,'Now I mustn''t forget to tell you about picnicking, as I can see some of you have brought your lunch with you.',1,299661),(6488,130,'当然，您可以在野外野餐，当然事后需要清理干净。',313000,'You can picnic in the field, though do clear up behind you, of course.',1,307521),(6489,130,'或者，如果您更喜欢有顶棚的野餐区，农家院附近就有一个：刚过桥后，右侧就有一个有顶棚的野餐区。(Q19)',324200,'Or if you''d prefer a covered picnic area, there''s one near the farmyard: just after you cross the bridge, there''s a covered picnic spot on the right.(Q19)',1,313001),(6490,130,'最后要提到的是费迪房间这件事。',328710,'And the last thing to mention is Fiddy House itself.',1,324201),(6491,130,'从这里您可以过桥，然后沿着人行道穿过田野，到达农家院的左侧。那就是房子，它会给你一个美丽的景色。(Q20)',341390,'From here you can cross the bridge then walk along the footpath through the field to the left of the farmyard.That goes to the house, and it''ll give you a lovely view of it.(Q20)',1,328711),(6492,130,'拍几张照片当然值得，但既然是私人住宅，恐怕进不去。',349230,'It''s certainly worth a few photographs, but as it''s a private home, I''m afraid you can''t go inside.',1,341391),(6493,130,'好了。',350260,'Right.',1,349231),(6494,130,'如果你们都准备好了，我们就开始参观农场。',355430,'Well, if you''re all ready, we''ll set off on our tour of the farm.',1,350261),(6495,131,'好的，格雷格，所以我终于读到了你提到的那篇关于物理学中性别研究的文章。',73000,'OK, Greg, so I finally managed to read the article you mentioned - the one about the study on gender in physics.',1,63101),(6496,131,'关于三宅彰和他的团队对大学生所做的研究？',78180,'About the study of college students done by Akira Miyake and his team?',1,73001),(6497,131,'是的。我很感兴趣的是，研究人员实际上是心理学家和物理学家的混合体。',85270,'Yeah. I was interested that the researchers were actually a mix of psychologists and physicists.',1,78181),(6498,131,'这是一个不寻常的组合。',87260,'That''s an unusual combination.',1,85271),(6499,131,'是的。起初我对这项研究是基于哪些学生感到有些困惑。',94270,'Yeah. I got a little confused at first about which students the study was based on.',1,87261),(6500,131,'他们实际上并不是主修物理学——他们主修的是所谓的 STEM 学科。那是科学、技术、工程和...(Q21)',104890,'They weren''t actually majoring in physics - they were majoring in what''s known as the STEM disciplines.That''s science, technology, engineering and ...(Q21)',1,94271),(6501,131,'……和数学。',106140,'… and math.',1,104891),(6502,131,'是的，但他们都在上物理课作为他们学习的一部分。',111080,'Yes, but they were all doing physics courses as part of their studies.',1,106141),(6503,131,'没错。',112300,'That''s correct.',1,111081),(6504,131,'因此，据我所知，三宅一生的出发点是大学物理入门课程中女性人数不足，而且平均而言，参加这些课程的女性比男性表现更差。',131760,'So as I understood it, Miyake and co started from the fact that women are underrepresented in introductory physics courses at college, and also that on average, the women who do enrol on these courses perform more poorly than the men.',1,112301),(6505,131,'没有人真正知道为什么会这样。',134500,'No one really knows why this is the case.',1,131761),(6506,131,'是的。但研究人员想要了解的基本上是他们可以对相对较低水平的女性结果做些什么。(Q22)',143380,'Yeah. But what the researchers wanted to find out was basically what they could do about the relatively low level of the women''s results.(Q22)',1,134501),(6507,131,'但是为了找到解决方案，他们需要更多地了解问题的性质。',149320,'But in order to find a solution they needed to find out more about the nature of the problem.',1,143381),(6508,131,'对 - 现在让我们看看我是否还记得......',152850,'Right - now let''s see if I can remember ...',1,149321),(6509,131,'就是在物理课上，女同学以为男同学都认为女生物理不好……',162850,'it was that in the physics class, the female students thought the male students all assumed that women weren''t any good at physics ...',1,152851),(6510,131,'是这样吗？',164000,'was that it?',1,162851),(6511,131,'她们认为这些男生期望她们在测试中取得糟糕的成绩。',169560,'And they thought that the men expected them to get poor results in their tests.',1,164001),(6512,131,'女人就是这么想的，这让她们很紧张，所以她们的成绩确实很差。',175330,'That''s what the women thought, and that made them nervous, so they did get poor results.',1,169561),(6513,131,'但实际上他们错了......没有人对女学生做任何假设。(Q23)',182220,'But actually they were wrong ...No one was making any assumptions about the female students at all.(Q23)',1,175331),(6514,131,'不管怎样，三宅的团队所做的很简单——让学生们在上物理课之前先写点东西。',191250,'Anyway, what Miyake''s team did was quite simple - getting the students to do some writing before they went into the physics class.',1,182221),(6515,131,'他们叫它什么？',192710,'What did they call it?',1,191251),(6516,131,'价值观——肯定——他们必须写一篇文章，专注于对他们有意义的事情(Q24)，不只是特别地与他们正在学习的主题，而是更一般的事情，如音乐，或对他们重要的人。',207940,'Values-affirmation- they had to write an essay focusing on things that were significant to them(Q24), not particularly to do with the subject they were studying, but more general things like music, or people who mattered to them.',1,192711),(6517,131,'是的。因此，写作的想法是让学生以积极的方式思考。',215260,'Right. So the idea of doing the writing is that this gets the students thinking in a positive way.',1,207941),(6518,131,'而把这些想法变成文字，可以让他们放松下来(Q25)，帮助他们克服导致表现不佳的心理因素。',223400,'And putting these thoughts into words can relax them(Q25) and help them overcome the psychological factors that lead to poor performance.',1,215261),(6519,131,'是的。但研究中的研究人员没想到的是，这一活动将女子物理成绩从 C 级提高到 B 级。(Q26)',233790,'Yeah. But what the researchers in the study hadn''t expected was that this one activity raised the women''s physics grades from the C to the B range.(Q26)',1,223401),(6520,131,'一个巨大的变化。',235880,'A huge change.',1,233791),(6521,131,'可惜不是A，但仍然