 very high concentrations of food.(Q32)',1,161571),(6569,132,'但令他惊讶的是，这仅适用于四个热点——其余热点在这方面的情况非常糟糕。',176680,'But to his surprise that was only true for four of the hotspots - the remaining hotspot was quite badly off in that regard.',1,167741),(6570,132,'但他确实发现，在所有情况下，海洋表面(Q33)的水都具有相对较高的温度，即使在更深的地方很冷，所以这似乎是支持这些大型捕食者种类繁多的一个因素。',194470,'But what he did find was that in all cases, the water at the surface(Q33) of the ocean had relatively high temperatures, even when it was cool at greater depths, so this seemed to be a factor in supporting a diverse range of these large predators.',1,176681),(6571,132,'然而，这本身还不够，因为他还发现水中需要有足够的氧气(Q34)——所以这两个因素似乎是支持这些大鱼的高代谢率所必需的。',209690,'However, this wasn''t enough on its own, because he also found that the water needed to have enough oxygen (Q34)in it - so these two factors seemed necessary to support the high metabolic rate of these large fish.',1,194471),(6572,132,'几年后，也就是 2007 年，在加利福尼亚工作的研究人员丽莎·巴伦斯也开始寻找海洋热点，而不是鱼类——她感兴趣的是海洋哺乳动物，比如海豹。(Q35)',227670,'A couple of years later, in 2007, a researcher called Lisa Ballance, who was working in California, also started looking for ocean hotspots, but not for fish - what she was interested in was marine mammals, things like seals.(Q35)',1,209691),(6573,132,'她在海洋中发现了三个热点，这些热点的共同点是，这些热点都位于洋流之间的边界，这似乎是一个有很多浮游生物的地方，其中一些物种以浮游生物为食。',246000,'And she found three places in the oceans which were hotspots, and what these had in common was that these hotspots were all located at boundaries between ocean currents, and this seems to be the sort of place that has lots of the plankton that some of these species feed on.',1,227671),(6574,132,'所以现在想要保护濒危物种的人们需要获得尽可能多的信息。',253300,'So now people who want to protect the species that are endangered need to get as much information as possible.',1,246001),(6575,132,'例如，有一个名为“海洋生物普查”的国际项目。',258560,'For example, there''s an international project called the Census of Marine Life.',1,253301),(6576,132,'他们一直在调查世界各地的海洋，包括北极。',263360,'They''ve been surveying oceans all over the world, including the Arctic.',1,258561),(6577,132,'他们在那里发现的让其他研究人员震惊的一件事是，有大量的物种生活在冰层之下(Q36)——有时在高达 20 米厚的层之下。',276000,'One thing they found there which stunned other researchers was that there were large numbers of species which live below the ice(Q36) - sometimes under a layer up to 20 metres thick.',1,263361),(6578,132,'其中一些物种以前从未见过。',280260,'Some of these species had never been seen before.',1,276001),(6579,132,'他们甚至发现了生活在这种条件下的章鱼种类。',284960,'They''ve even found species of octopus living in these conditions.',1,280261),(6580,132,'从事同一个项目的其他科学家，但研究海底非常不同的栖息地，发现大量物种聚集在火山周围，被那里的温暖和营养物质吸引。',306000,'And other scientists working on the same project, but researching very different habitats on the ocean floor, have found large numbers of species congregating around volcanoes, attracted to them by the warmth and nutrients there.',1,284961),(6581,132,'然而，生物学家仍然不知道每个物种对它们生存的威胁有多严重。',314960,'However, biologists still don''t know how serious the threat to their survival is for each individual species.',1,306001),(6582,132,'因此，一个被称为全球海洋物种评估的机构现在在陆地上创造了濒危物种的列表，所以他们考虑了一个物种的大小——一个物种在一个特定的地方有多少个成员——然后从地理上看它们的分布。虽然当你观察鱼类时，这是相当困难的，因为它们的流动性很强，然后第三，他们计算出物种数量下降的速度（Q37）。',348000,'So a body called the Global Marine Species Assessment is now creating a list of endangered species on land, so they consider things like the size of the population - how many members of one species there are in a particular place - and then they look at their distribution in geographical terms, although this is quite difficult when you''re looking at fish, because they''re so mobile, and then thirdly they calculate the rate at which the decline(Q37) of the species is happening.',1,314961),(6583,132,'到目前为止，只评估了 1,500 个物种，但他们希望将这个数字增加到 20,000 个。',356800,'So far only 1,500 species have been assessed, but they want to increase this figure to 20,000.',1,348001),(6584,132,'对于他们评估的每一个，他们使用他们收集的关于该物种的数据来制作一张显示其分布的地图。(Q38)',365490,'For each one they assess, they use the data they collect on that species to produce a 