23).',1,138341),(6739,135,'好的。我再看一遍。',153310,'OK.I''ll look at that again.',1,150001),(6740,135,'然后我们必须详细描述我们的调查方法。',158330,'Then we have to describe our method of investigation in detail.',1,153311),(6741,135,'让我们从如何测量波速开始。',161740,'So let''s begin with how we measured wave speed.',1,158331),(6742,135,'我很惊讶这是多么的简单。',164480,'I was surprised how straightforward that was(Q24).',1,161741),(6743,135,'我原以为我们应该有某种高科技设备，而不是站在那里，数每分钟有多少波。',172000,'I''d expected us to have some sort of high-tech device, not just stand there and count the number of waves per minute. ',1,164481),(6744,135,'不是很精确，但我想已经足够了。',175690,'Not very precise, but I suppose it was good enough. ',1,172001),(6745,135,'但是我们测量盐含量的方法很有趣。',179000,'But the way we measured the amount of salt was interesting.',1,175691),(6746,135,'在岩石池里的水里吗?',180770,'In the water from the rock pools?',1,179001),(6747,135,'是的，哦，我想检查一下我们在实验室分析那些样品时使用的化学物质，是铬酸钾和硝酸银吗?',190000,'Yeah, oh,I wanted to check the chemicals we used in the lab when we analysed those samples-was it potassium chromate and silver nitrate?',1,180771),(6748,135,'是的。',190820,'That''s right.',1,190001),(6749,135,'好的。我们还需要海岸地图。',194480,'OK. And we need the map of the seashore. ',1,190821),(6750,135,'你把这事留给了我。',196670,'You just left that to me. ',1,194481),(6751,135,'我必须在退潮的时候做这件事，这没什么，但我从海滩上开始，然后我意识到我应该爬得更高，以获得更好的能见度，所以我不得不重新开始。',210780,'And I had to do it while the tide was low, well that was OK, but the place I started it from was down on the beach, then I realised I should have gone up higher to get better visibility (Q25), so I had to start all over again. ',1,196671),(6752,135,'但至少我有一张方形的纸，否则我就很难按比例画出来了。',216190,'But at least I''d got the squared paper or I''d have had problems drawing it all to scale.',1,210781),(6753,135,'是的。看起来不错。',218450,'Yes. It looks good. ',1,216191),(6754,135,'我们可以从网上找一张这个地区的地图看看是否需要做些改变。',223000,'We could get a map of the region off the internet and see if we need to make any changes.',1,218451),(6755,135,'我看了看，但什么也没找到。',226690,'I had a