,140,'让我们来看一些人种学研究如何在商业中发挥作用的例子。',150000,'Let''s look at some examples of how ethnographic research works in business. ',1,144001),(6994,140,'一组研究人员为一家制造厨房设备的公司做了一个项目。',155490,'One team of researchers did a project for a company manufacturing kitchen equipment. ',1,150001),(6995,140,'他们观察了厨师如何使用量杯来测量糖和面粉等东西。',162000,'They watched how cooks used measuring cups to measure out things like sugar and flour. ',1,155491),(6996,140,'他们发现厨师必须反复检查量杯的内容，因为虽然量杯里面有数字，但厨师不容易看到这些数字。',172000,'They saw that the cooks had to check and recheck the contents, because although the measuring cups had numbers (Q32) inside them, the cooks couldn''t see these easily. ',1,162001),(6997,140,'因此，一种新的杯子设计被开发出来，以克服这个问题，它是最畅销的。',179650,'So a new design of cup was developed to overcome this problem, and it was a top seller.',1,172001),(6998,140,'另一组人种学研究人员观察了非洲乌干达的手机使用情况。',187020,'Another team of ethnographic researchers looked at how cell phones were used in Uganda, in Africa. ',1,179651),(6999,140,'他们发现，没有自己手机的人可以付费使用当地企业家的手机。',194000,'They found that people who didn''t have their own phones could pay to use the phones of local entrepreneurs. ',1,187021),(7000,140,'因为这些客户提前支付了电话费，他们很想知道到目前为止他们在电话上花费了多少时间。',202000,'Because these customers paid in advance for their calls, they were eager to know how much time (Q33) they'' d spent on the call so far. ',1,194001),(7001,140,'因此，这家电话公司设计了带有这一附加功能的全球手机。',208780,'So the phone company designed phones for use globally with this added feature.',1,202001),(7002,140,'计算机公司也进行了人种学研究。',214000,'Ethnographic research has also been carried out in computer companies. ',1,208781),(7003,140,'在一家公司，IT系统管理员被观察了几周。',219710,'In one company, IT systems administrators were observed for several weeks. ',1,214001),(7004,140,'我们发现，他们的大量工作涉及到与同事沟通以解决问题，但他们没有从电子表格等交换信息的标准方式。',232780,'It was found that a large amount of their work involved communicating with colleagues in order to solve problems, but that they didn'' t have a standard way of exchanging information from spreadsheets and so on.',1,219711),(7005,140,'因此，这个团队想出了一个软件的想法，可以帮助他们做到这一点。',238730,'So the team came up with an idea for software (Q34) that would help them to do this.',1,232781),(7006,140,'在另一项研究中，一个团队观察并与在医院工作的护士交谈。',245370,'In another piece of research,a team observed and talked to nurses working in hospitals. ',1,238731),(7007,140,'这使人们认识到，护士需要访问病人的计算机记录，无论他们在哪里。',254000,'This led to the recognition that the nurses needed to access the computer records of their patients (Q35), no matter where they were. ',1,245371),(7008,140,'这导致了一种便携式平板电脑的发展，使护士可以在整个医院的各个位置检查记录。',263520,'This led to the development of a portable computer tablet that allowed the nurses to check records in locations throughout the hospital.',1,254001),(7009,140,'有时候，研究甚至可以在研究人员不在的环境中进行。',270000,'Occasionally, research can be done even in environments where the researchers can'' t be present. ',1,263521),(7010,140,'例如，在为一家航空公司做的一个项目中，受访者在航空旅行中使用他们的智能手机记录信息，目的是跟踪乘客在飞行期间的情绪。',288900,'For example, in one project done for an airline, respondents used their smartphones to record information during airline trips, in a study aiming at tracking the emotions (Q36) of passengers during a flight.',1,270001),(7011,140,'那么，是什么让这些研究不同于普通研究呢?',293720,'So what makes studies like these different from ordinary research? ',1,288901),(7012,140,'让我们来看看商业人种学研究背后的一些一般原则。',299410,'Let''s look at some of the general principles behind ethnographic research in business. ',1,293721),(7013,140,'首先，研究者必须是完全开放的，他或她没有想到要检验的假设，就像其他类型的研究一样。',311320,'First of all, the researcher has to be completely open-minded-he or she hasn''t thought up a hypothesis to be tested, as is the case in other types of research. ',1,299411),(7014,140,'相反，他们会等待研究参与者的通知。',316720,'Instead they wait for the participants in the research to inform them. ',1,311321),(7015,140,'就选择参与者本身而言，这与普通研究并没有太大的不同——参与者被选择的标准可能是一些简单的事情，如他们所处的年龄等级，或者研究人员可能根据他们的收入来选择他们，例如，他们可能会试图找到一组都使用某种特定产品的人。',340000,'As far as choosing the participants themselves is concerned, that''s not really all that different from ordinary research-the criteria according to which the participants are chosen may be something as simple as the age bracket they fall into, or the researchers may select them according to their income (Q37), or they might try to find a set of people who all use a particular product, for example. ',1,316721),(7016,140,'但招募合适的人作为参与者绝对是至关重要的。',346000,'But it''s absolutely crucial to recruit the right people as participants. ',1,340001),(7017,140,'正如我提到的标准，他们必须舒适地谈论自己，并在他们进行活动时被观察。',355570,'As well as the criteria l'' ve mentioned, they have to be comfortable (Q38) talking about themselves and being watched as they go about their activities. ',1,346001),(7018,140,'事实上，大多数研究人员说，人们很容易敞开心扉，也许是因为他们经常在自己的家里或工作场所。',364690,'Actually, most researchers say that people open up pretty easily, maybe because they'' re often in their own home or workplace.',1,355571),(7019,140,'所以，这种类型的研究的特别之处在于，它不仅仅是发送一份问卷给参与者，相反，研究通常是基于第一手的观察他们在当时正在做什么。',378450,'So what makes this type of research special is that it''s not just a matter of sending a questionnaire to the participants, instead the research is usually based on first-hand observation (Q39) of what they are doing at the time. ',1,364691),(7020,140,'\n\n但这并不意味着研究人员从不与参与者交谈。',382820,'But that doesn''t mean that the researcher never talks to the participants. ',1,378451),(7021,140,'然而，与传统研究不同的是，在这种情况下，决定访谈走向的是参与者，而不是研究人员。',395050,'However, unlike in traditional research, in this case it''s the participant rather than the researchers who decides what direction the interview will follow. ',1,382821),(7022,140,'\n\n这意味着研究者将自己的想法强加给参与者的可能性更小。',403430,'This means that there''s less likelihood of the researcher imposing his or her own ideas on the participant.',1,395051),(7023,140,'\n\n但当他们与参与者道别回到办公室后，研究人员的工作还没有完成。',411640,'But after they''ve said goodbye to their participants and got back to their office, the researchers'' work isn'' t finished.',1,403431),(7024,140,'大多数研究人员估计，他们70%到80%的时间不是花在数据收集上，而是花在数据分析上——看照片，听录音，抄录，等等。',425410,'Most researchers estimate that 70 to 80 per cent of their time is spent not on the collecting of data but on its analysis (Q40)-looking at photos, listening to recordings and transcribing them, and so on. ',1,411641),(7025,140,'\n\n研究人员最终可能会得到数百页的笔记。',429600,'The researchers may end up with hundreds of pages of notes. ',1,425411),(7026,140,'为了确定什么是重要的，他们不关注耸人听闻的事情或不寻常的事情，相反，他们试图在所有这些数据中找出某种模式，并辨别其背后的意义。',444000,'And to determine what''s significant, they don''t focus on the sensational things or the unusual things, instead they try to identify a pattern of some sort in all this data, and to discern the meaning behind it. ',1,429601),(7027,140,'这可能会产生一些引人注目的见解，进而反馈给整个设计过程。',452840,'This can result in some compelling insights that can in turn feed back to the whole design process.',1,444001),(7028,141,'早上好。',102790,'Good morning. ',1,101791),(7029,141,'斯特雷顿电影节售票处。',104650,'Stretton Festival box office. ',1,102791),(7030,141,'我能帮你什么忙吗?',106000,'How can I help you?',1,104651),(7031,141,'哦,你好。',107000,'Oh, hello. ',1,106001),(7032,141,'我和我的家人正在这个地区度假，这周我们已经看到了一些关于这个节日的海报。',114000,'My family and I are on holiday in the area, and we''ve seen some posters about the festival this week. ',1,107001),(7033,141,'你能告诉我一些有关的活动吗?',117000,'Could you tell me about some of the events, please?',1,114001),(7034,141,'当然可以。',118190,'Of course.',1,117001),(7035,141,'首先，周六的爵士乐队还有票吗?',123730,'First of all, are there still tickets available for the jazz band on Saturday?',1,118191),(7036,141,'有,但只有￡15(例子)。',127720,'There are, but only(Example)￡15. ',1,123731),(7037,141,'￡12座位都卖出去了。',130480,'The ￡12 seats have all been sold.',1,127721),(7038,141,'好的。地点是学校，对吧?',134310,'OK. And the venue is the school, isn''t  it?',1,130481),(7039,141,'是的，没错，是中学。',137300,'Yes, that''s right, the secondary (Q1) school. ',1,134311),(7040,141,'确保你不要误去小学！',141000,'Make sure you don''t go to the primary school by mistake! ',1,137301),(7041,141,'还有一位海报上没有提到的演员，卡洛琳·哈特将和乐队一起演奏。',148550,'And there''s an