fore we go, let me just give you a taste of what we have here.',1,68321),(7097,142,'嗯，首先，我们有一些20世纪和21世纪的画作，其中很多是非常著名的艺术家的作品。',79740,'Well, for one thing, we have a fine collection of twentieth and twenty-first century paintings, many by very well-known artists.',1,72821),(7098,142,'我相信你会认出其中几幅画的。',82260,'I''m sure you''ll recognise several of the paintings. ',1,79741),(7099,142,'这是吸引最多游客的画廊，所以最好在一天的早些时候，在人群到来之前进入。',89600,'This is the gallery that attracts the largest number of visitors (Q11), so it''s best to go in early in the day, before the crowds arrive.',1,82261),(7100,142,'还有十九世纪的画作。',92650,'Then there are the nineteenth-century paintings. ',1,89601),(7101,142,'博物馆在那个世纪中叶开馆，几位艺术家每人捐赠了一件作品——以启动博物馆，就像它一样。',100870,'The museum was opened in the middle of that century, and several of the artists each donated one work (Q12)-to get the museum started, as it were. ',1,92651),(7102,142,'所以我们对它们特别感兴趣，我们觉得它们比其他作品更接近我们。',106000,'So they''re of special interest to us-we feel closer to them than to other works.',1,100871),(7103,142,'雕塑展览馆有一些很好的展品，但是现在恐怕要关门整修了。',112300,'The sculpture gallery has a number of fine exhibits, but I''m afraid it s currently closed for refurbishment. ',1,106001),(7104,142,'你需要明年再来看它，但一些雕塑已经被转移到博物馆的其他部分。',119320,'You''ll need to come back next year to see it properly, but a number of the sculptures have been moved to other parts of the museum (Q13).',1,112301),(7105,142,'“世界各地”是一个临时展览——你可能已经在电视或报纸上看到过有关它的一些东西。',126790,'''Around the world'' is a temporary exhibition-you''ve probably seen something about it on TV or in the newspapers (Q14). ',1,119321),(7106,142,'它引起了人们极大的兴趣，因为它展示了来自各个大陆和许多国家的物品，并提供了有关它们的社会背景的信息——它们为什么被制造，为谁制造，等等。',140000,'It''s created a great deal of interest, because it presents objects from every continent and many countries, and provides information about their social context-why they were made, who for, and so on.',1,126791),(7107,142,'然后是硬币收集。',142740,'Then there''s the collection of coins. ',1,140001),(7108,142,'这就是你可以称之为集中的、专业的收藏，因为所有的硬币都来自这个国家，并且是在两千年到一千年前生产的。',152960,'This is what you might call a focused, specialist collection, because all the coins come from this country, and were produced between two thousand and a thousand years ago. ',1,142741),(7109,142,'其中许多是由普通民众在花园里挖掘时发现的，并捐赠给了博物馆!',160000,'And many of them were discovered by ordinary people digging their gardens, and donated to the museum (Q15)!',1,152961),(7110,142,'我们所有的瓷器和玻璃都是其创始人在1878年去世时留给博物馆的。',165690,'All our porcelain and glass was left to the museum by its founder (Q16), when he died in 1878. ',1,160001),(7111,142,'在他的遗嘱中，我们不允许在这批藏品中再添加任何东西:他认为它本身就是完美的，我们没有任何理由不同意!',213270,'And in the terms of his will, we''re not allowed to add anything to that collection: he believed it was perfect in itself, and we don''t see any reason to disagree!',1,165691),(7112,142,'好的，这是关于收藏的一些东西，现在有一些更实用的信息，以防你需要它。',220580,'OK, that was something about the collections, and now here''s some more practical information, in case you need it.',1,213271),(7113,142,'博物馆的大部分设施都在楼下，在地下室，所以你从这里下楼。',227320,'Most of the museum facilities are downstairs, in the basement, so you go down the stairs here. ',1,220581),(7114,142,'当你走到楼梯底部时，你会发现自己在一个休息区，有舒适的椅子和沙发，在那里你可以休息一下，然后继续你的博物馆探索。',238510,'When you reach the bottom of the stairs, you''ll find yourself in a sitting area, with comfortable chairs and sofas where you can have a rest before continuing your exploration of the museum.',1,227321),(7115,142,'我们有一家很好的餐厅，全天供应很好的食物，气氛很轻松。',244490,'We have a very good restaurant, which serves excellent food all day, in a relaxing atmosphere. ',1,238511),(7116,142,'要到达那里，当你走到楼梯底部时，直走到休息区的另一边，然后右转进入走廊。',254490,'To reach it, when you get to the bottom of the stairs, go straight ahead to the far side of the sitting area, then turn right into the corridor.',1,244491),(7117,142,'你会看到餐厅的门正对着你。',258180,'You''ll see the door of the restaurant facing you (Q17).',1,254491),(7118,142,'如果你只是想吃点零食，或者想去有儿童设施的地方吃饭，我们还有咖啡厅。',264840,'If you just want a snack, or if you''d like to eat somewhere with facilities for children, we also have a cafe. ',1,258181),(7119,142,'当你到达楼梯底部时，你需要直走，右转进入走廊，咖啡馆就在右边。',275380,'When you reach the bottom of the stairs, you''ll need to go straight ahead, turn right into the corridor, and the cafe is immediately on the right (Q18).',1,264841),(7120,142,'说到孩子，楼下有换婴儿的设施:穿过休息区，沿着左边的走廊一直往前走，你和你的宝宝就会在左边找到换婴儿的设施。',290900,'And talking about children, there are baby-changing facilities downstairs: cross the sitting area, continue straight ahead along the corridor on the left, and you and your baby will find the facilities on the left-hand side (Q19).',1,275381),(7121,142,'衣帽间在休息区的左手边，你应该把大衣、雨伞和大包放在那里。',299190,'The cloakroom, where you should leave coats, umbrellas and any large bags, is on the left hand side of the sitting area. ',1,290901),(7122,142,'穿过走廊前的最后一扇门。',303460,'It''s through the last door before you come to the corridor (Q20).',1,299191),(7123,142,'每层楼都有厕所，但在地下室，当你下到那里时，洗手间在左边的第一个房间。',310740,'There are toilets on every floor, but in the basement they''re the first rooms on the left when you get down there.',1,303461),(7124,142,'好了，如果你有什么东西要留在衣帽间，请现在就去，然后我们就开始参观了。',317510,'OK, now if you''ve got anything to leave in the cloakroom, please do that now, and then we''ll start our tour.',1,310741),(7125,143,'嗨，乔安娜，很高兴认识你。',63000,'Hi, Joanna, good to meet you. ',1,61001),(7126,143,'现在，在我们讨论你的新研究项目之前，我想听一听你去年为你的硕士学位所做的心理学研究。',72950,'Now, before we discuss your new research project,I''d like to hear something about the psychology study you did last year for your Master''s degree. ',1,63001),(7127,143,'你是怎么选择拍摄对象的?',76900,'So how did you choose your subjects for that?',1,72951),(7128,143,'我有六个实验对象，都是职业音乐家，而且都是女性。',83350,'Well,I had six subjects, all professional musicians, and all female. ',1,76901),(7129,143,'有三个小提琴手，还有一个大提琴演奏家，一个钢琴家和一个长笛演奏家。',90980,'Three were violinists and there was also a cello player and a pianist and a flute player. ',1,83351),(7130,143,'他们在音乐界都享有很高的声誉，他们在不同的大洲进行了广泛的巡演，其中不少还赢得了奖项和比赛。',100930,'They were all very highly regarded in the music world and they''d done quite extensive tours in different continents (Q21), and quite a few had won prizes and competitions as well.',1,90981),(7131,143,'他们还很年轻，不是吗?',102900,'And they were quite young, weren''t they?',1,100931),(7132,143,'是的，在25岁到29岁之间，平均是27.8。',110200,'Yes, between 25 and 29-the mean was 27.8.',1,102901),(7133,143,'我并没有特别寻找那些制作过唱片的艺术家，但这些天来，这是理所当然的事情，他们都有',119210,'I wasn''t specifically looking for artists who''d produced recordings, but this is something that''s just taken for granted these days, and they all had (Q22).',1,110201),(7134,143,'好的。你是通过电话采访收集数据的，对吗?',124420,'Right. Now you collected your data through telephone interviews, didn''t you?',1,119211),(7135,143,'是的。我意识到，如果我要采访顶尖音乐人，只能通过电话，因为他们太忙了。',133370,'Yes.I realised if I was going to interview leading musicians it''d only be possible over the phone because they''re so busy (Q23).',1,124421),(7136,143,'我用电话录音转接器录下了它们。',137400,'I recorded them using a telephone recording adaptor.',1,133371),(7137,143,'我一直担心质量问题，但结果还不错。',142000,'I''d been worried about the quality, but it worked out all right.',1,137401),(7138,143,'我设法与每个受试者进行了至少30分钟的采访，有时时间更长。',148330,'I managed at least a 30-minute interview with each subject, sometimes longer.',1,142001),(7139,143,'在电话里说会让你更有压力吗?',152000,'Did doing it on the phone make it more stressful?',1,148331),(7140,143,'我原以为会的。不过，这一切都是非正式的，事实上，他们似乎非常渴望交谈。',159490,'I''d thought it might...it was all quite informal though and in fact they seemed very keen to talk. ',1,152001),(7141,143,'我不认为使用电话意味着我得到较少的丰富的数据，而事实上恰恰相反。',166000,'And I don''t think using the phone meant I got less rich data, rather the opposite in fact (Q24).',1,159491),(7142,143,'有趣。',167130,'Interesting. ',1,166001),(7143,143,'你在看演奏家在音乐会表演时是如何着装的?',171810,'And you were looking at how performers dress for concert performances?',1,167131),(7144,143,'这是正确的。',173130,'That''s right. ',1,171811),(7145,143,'我的研究调查了演奏家如何看待自己作为音乐家的角色，以及这与他们决定穿的衣服类型之间的关系。',182870,'My research investigated the way players see their role as a musician and how this is linked to the type of clothing they decide to wear. ',1,173131),(7146,143,'但这种关注并没有立即显现出来。',186000,'But that focus didn''t emerge immediately. ',1,182871),(7147,143,'当我开始研究时，我更感兴趣的是研究穿什么衣服对听众的影响，以及像小提琴家这样的人是否会采用与吹长笛或小号的人不同的服装风格。',202400,'When I started I was more interested in trying to investigate the impact of what was worn on those listening (Q25), and also whether someone like a violinist might adopt a different style of clothing from, say, someone playing the flute or the trumpet(Q26).',1,186001),(7148,143,'服装的选择取决于个人，这很有趣，不是吗?',206450,'It''s interesting that the choice of dress is up to the individual, isn''t it?',1,202401),(7149,143,'是的，你会认为在管弦乐队中这是有规则的，但这是非常罕见的。',250990,'Yes, you''d expect there to be rules about it in orchestras, but that''s quite rare.',1,206451),(7150,143,'你的研究中只有女性参与者。',254620,'You only had women performers in your study. ',1,250991),(7151,143,'这是因为男性音乐家不那么担心时尚吗?',258650,'Was that because male musicians are less worried about fashion?',1,254621),(7152,143,'我认为很多男性受时尚的影响很大，但从社会角度来说，他们的选择更有限',266570,'I think a lot of the men are very much influenced by fashion, but in social terms the choices they have are more limited',1,258651),(7153,143,'如果他们偏离了非常狭窄的界限，他们真的会让观众失望。',271280,'…they''d really upset audiences if they strayed away from quite narrow boundaries (Q27).',1,266571),(7154,143,'嗯。现在，流行音乐有相当不同的期望。',276000,'Hmm. Now, popular music has quite different expectations. ',1,271281),(7155,143,'你读过迈克·弗罗斯特关于流行音乐中女性表演者的服装的文章吗?',281460,'Did you read Mike Frost''s article about the dress of women performers in popular music?',1,276001),(7156,143,'不。',282000,'No.',1,281461),(7157,143,'他指出，很多流行音乐中的女性歌手和音乐家在表演中倾向于穿着休闲，穿较少女性化的衣服，比如牛仔裤而不是裙子，他认为这是因为，否则她们就会被认为是微不足道的。',298320,'He points out that a lot of female singers and musicians in popular music tend to dress down in performances, and wear less feminine clothes, like jeans instead of skirts, and he suggests this is be