s, but musicians don''t really consider it. ',1,371741),(7171,143,'他们会避免穿着明显限制他们行动的衣服，但他们也仅此而已。',381370,'They avoid clothing that obviously restricts their movements, but that''s as far as they go.',1,375691),(7172,143,'不管怎样，回到你自己的研究上来，你知道你接下来要做什么吗?',386850,'Anyway, coming back to your own research, do you have any idea where you''re going from here?',1,381371),(7173,143,'我在考虑做一项研究利用观众，包括.....',391610,'I was thinking of doing a study using an audience, including...',1,386851),(7174,144,'正如我们在上节课所看到的，气候变化的一个主要原因是上个世纪大气中二氧化碳含量的快速上升。',104000,'As we saw in the last lecture,a major cause of climate change is the rapid rise in the level of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere over the last century. ',1,93251),(7175,144,'如果我们能减少二氧化碳的含量，也许气候变化的速度也能减缓下来。',111220,'If we could reduce the amount of CO2, perhaps the rate of climate change could also be slowed down. ',1,104001),(7176,144,'一种可能的方法是加强植物生长的土壤在吸收二氧化碳方面的作用。',120000,'One potential method involves enhancing the role of the soil that plants grow in, with regard to absorbing CO2. ',1,111221),(7177,144,'美国俄亥俄州立大学的土壤科学家拉坦·拉尔声称，世界上的农业土壤有可能吸收大气中13%的二氧化碳，这相当于过去30年释放的二氧化碳量。',138540,'Rattan Lal,a soil scientist from Ohio State University, in the USA, claims that the world''s agricultural soils could potentially absorb 13 per cent of the carbon dioxide in the atmosphere-the equivalent of the amount released in the last 30 years. ',1,120001),(7178,144,'关于如何实现这一目标的研究正在进行中。',142780,'And research is going on into how this might be achieved.',1,138541),(7179,144,'拉尔首先想到，土壤之所以有价值，不是因为对气候变化感兴趣，而是出于对土地本身和依赖土地的人的关心。',156000,'Lal first came to the idea that soil might be valuable in this way not through an interest in climate change, but rather outof concern for the land itself and the people dependent on it. ',1,142781),(7180,144,'富含碳的土壤颜色暗，易碎且肥沃，还能保留一些水分。',162430,'Carbon-rich soil is dark, crumbly and fertile, and retains some water. ',1,156001),(7181,144,'但是如果土壤干燥，就会发生侵蚀，如果土壤中碳含量不足，就有可能造成侵蚀。',171220,'But erosion can occur if soil is dry (Q31), which is a likely effect if it contains inadequate amounts of carbon. ',1,162431),(7182,144,'侵蚀当然不利于人们在那片土地上种植庄稼或饲养动物。',178000,'Erosion is of course bad for people trying to grow crops or breed animals on that terrain. ',1,171221),(7183,144,'在20世纪70年代和80年代，拉尔在非洲研究土壤，由于缺乏有机物质，土壤变得极其坚硬，就像水泥一样。',190000,'In the 1970s and 80s, Lal was studying soils in Africa so devoid of organic matter that the ground had become extremely hard (Q32), like cement. ',1,178001),(7184,144,'在那里，他遇到了一位研究全球变暖的先驱，这位先驱认为土壤中的碳已经进入了大气。',199080,'There he met a pioneer in the study of global warming, who suggested that carbon from the soil had moved into the atmosphere. ',1,190001),(7185,144,'现在看来，这种可能性越来越大。',202410,'This is now looking increasingly likely.',1,199081),(7186,144,'让我解释一下。',204000,'Let me explain. ',1,202411),(7187,144,'数百万年来，大气中的二氧化碳水平在一定程度上是由植物和微生物(土壤中的微小生物体)之间的天然伙伴关系控制的。',217560,'For millions of years, carbon dioxide levels in the atmosphere have been regulated, in part, by a natural partnership between plants and microbes-tiny organisms in the soil. ',1,204001),(7188,144,'植物从空气中吸收二氧化碳并将其转化为糖和其他碳基物质。',226000,'Plants absorb CO2 from the air and transform it into sugars (Q33) and other carbon-based substances. ',1,217561),(7189,144,'虽然这些碳产品的一部分仍然存在于植物中，但一些从根部转移到真菌和土壤微生物，将碳储存在土壤中。',237460,'While a proportion of these carbon products remain in the plant, some transfer from the roots (Q34) to fungi and soil microbes, which store the carbon in the soil.',1,226001),(7190,144,'大约1万年前，农业的发明破坏了这些古老的土壤形成过程，导致土壤中的碳流失。',249410,'The invention of agriculture some 10,000 years ago disrupted these ancient soil-building processes and led to the loss of carbon from the soil. ',1,237461),(7191,144,'当人类开始排干天然表层土壤的水，将其翻耕种植时，他们将埋藏的碳暴露在氧气中。',258940,'When humans started draining the natural topsoil, and ploughing it up for planting, they exposed the buried carbon to oxygen. ',1,249411),(7192,144,'这就产生了二氧化碳并将其释放到空气中。',264000,'This created carbon dioxide and released it into the air. ',1,258941),(7193,144