rk.',1,250941),(7471,149,'是的。嗯，我想过，在我工作的地方没有安全的地方停放自行车。',264550,'Yep. Well,I have thought about it and where I work there are no safe (Q8) places to leave your bikes.',1,258001),(7472,149,'好的。',265500,'OK.',1,264551),(7473,149,'还有。',266220,'And also.',1,265501),(7474,149,'我必须骑自行车上坡，在炎热的一天，我到达工作地点时满身是汗，所以我想我需要在工作的某个地方洗个澡。',273310,'I''d have to cycle uphill and on a hot day,I''d arrive at work pretty sweaty so I think I''d need a shower (Q9) somewhere at work.',1,266221),(7475,149,'好的。',274000,'Right.',1,273311),(7476,149,'我想最后一件事是，在如此繁忙的道路上骑自行车，我不会那么自信。',280660,'And I suppose the last thing is that I wouldn''t be all that confident about cycling on such busy roads.',1,274001),(7477,149,'我想我希望看到你为此提供培训（Q10），你知道，如果是这样的话，我会对开始感觉好多了。',287290,'I think I''d like to see you offering training (Q10) for that, you know,I''d feel a lot better about starting if that was the case.',1,280661),(7478,149,'这很有帮助。',289130,'Well that''s very helpful. ',1,287291),(7479,149,'非常感谢您的时间。',290910,'Thank you very much for your time.',1,289131),(7480,149,'没有问题。',291790,'No problem. ',1,290911),(7481,149,'再见。',292500,'Bye.',1,291791),(7482,150,'早上好。',45000,'Good morning.',1,44001),(7483,150,'我很高兴能有机会谈谈这个城市的两个令人兴奋的新发展:布拉肯赛德露天游泳池和中央公园的儿童冒险游乐场。',56370,'I''m very pleased to have this opportunity to say a little about two exciting new developments in the city: the Brackenside Open-Air Swimming Pool and the children''s Adventure Playground in Central Park.',1,45001),(7484,150,'正如你们中的许多人所知道的，这些倡议的想法来自于你们，即公众，在去年市议会进行的广泛的咨询活动中。',67000,'As many of you may know, the idea for these initiatives came from you, the public (Q11), in the extensive consultation exercise which the City Council conducted last year.',1,56371),(7485,150,'它们是通过西南地区发展委员会的资金实现的。',73820,'And they have been realised using money from the SWRDC-the South West Regional Development Commission.',1,67001),(7486,150,'首先是布拉肯赛德泳池',77000,'First of all, Brackenside Pool.',1,73821),(7487,150,'许多年长的观众可能还记得，30年前，海边曾经有一个很棒的露天游泳池，但由于被认为不安全，不得不关闭。',88000,'As many of the older members of the audience will remember, there used to be a wonderful open-air pool on the sea front 30 years ago but it had to close when it was judged to be unsafe.',1,77001),(7488,150,'对于这个新的加热泳池的设计，我们非常高兴地邀请到了国际著名建筑师艾伦·温登，她成功地结合了一个迷人的20世纪30年代的设计，它与该地区的许多其他建筑非常契合，具有最新的功能，如循环系统——这类系统中唯一的一个——可以将海水用于水池。',112500,'For the design of this new heated pool, we were very happy to secure the talents of internationally renowned architect Ellen Wendon, who has managed to combine a charming 1930s design, which fits in so well with many of the other buildings in the area, with up-to-the-minute features such as a recycling system -the only one of its kind in the world-which enables seawater to be used in the pool (Q12).',1,88001),(7489,150,'现在，有相当多的讨论在当地媒体是否有足够的空间，我们希望吸引游客的数量，但设计是欺骗性的，有严格的检查容量。',125460,'Now, there has been quite a bit of discussion in the local press about whether there would be enough room for the number of visitors we''re hoping to attract (Q13), but the design is deceptive and there have been rigorous checks about capacity.',1,112501),(7490,150,'另外，如果你想知道，我们计划在6月15日开业，而且在预算范围内:这是当地承包商希克曼公司出色工作的证明。',137490,'Also, just in case you were wondering, we''re on schedule for a June 15th opening date and well within budget:a testimony to the excellent work of local contractors Hickman''s.',1,125461),(7491,150,'我们希望6月15日有尽可能多的人在那里。',142000,'We hope that as many people as possible will be there on June 15th.',1,137491),(7492,150,'我们聘请了获奖女演员科洛·怀特宣布泳池开放，泳池边会有饮料和零食供应。',150510,'We have engaged award-winning actress Coral White to declare the pool open and there''ll be drinks and snacks available at the pool side.',1,142001),(7493,150,'还有一个比赛，让公众决定我们计划在入口处有一个雕塑:你将决定我们应该有哪个著名的历史人物。',208000,'There''ll also be a competition for the public to decide on the sculpture we plan to have at the entrance (Q14): you will decide which famous historical figure from the city we should have.',1,150511),(7494,150,'现在，我们来看看中央公园游乐场，我们很高兴地宣布它刚刚获得了道格拉斯安全奖，这个消息是上周才得到的。',218340,'And now, moving on to the Central Park Playground, which we''re pleased to announce has just won the Douglas Award for safety: the news came through only last week.',1,208001),(7495,150,'这个独特的设计是基于地球村的概念，操场被划分为六个区域，展示了世界的不同部分，每个区域都有一个代表性的特征。',230000,'The unique design is based on the concept of the Global Village, with the playground being divided into six areas showing different parts of the world-each with a representative feature.',1,218341),(7496,150,'例如，有一个关于亚洲的部分，这是由蛇、猩猩、老虎等形状的游乐设施和设备代表的——这些都是该地区森林里的动物。',242000,'For example, there is a section on Asia, and this is represented by rides and equipment in the shape of snakes, orangutans, tigers and so on (Q15)-fauna native to the forests of the region.',1,230001),(7497,150,'往南走到南极——我们不能跑到溜冰场，我担心，而是选择了攀登山的形状的石块——我认为他们可以有冰川的滑梯，但设计师确实想避免太字面化!',257000,'Moving south to the Antarctic-we couldn''t run to an ice rink I''m afraid but opted instead for climbing blocks in the shape of mountains (Q16)-I thought they could have had slides for the glaciers but the designers did want to avoid being too literal! ',1,242001),(7498,150,'然后是南美-这里的主题是黄金国-游戏复制了寻找充满宝石的矿山。',266350,'Then on to South America-and here the theme is El Dorado-games replicating the search for mines full of precious Stone (Q17).',1,257001),(7499,150,'然后再来看看北美，这里有一个相当大的争论——我知道电影和爵士乐的贡献被考虑过，但设计师最终选择了火箭和国际空间站。',280640,'And then moving up to North America, here there was a considerable debate-I know the contribution of cinema and jazz was considered but the designers finally opted for rockets and the International Space Station(Q18).',1,266351),(7500,150,'然后向东到欧洲，也许是所有地区中最传统的选择:中世纪城堡和其他防御工事。',289000,'Eastwards to Europe then, and perhaps the most traditional choice of all the areas: medieval castles and other fortifications(Q19).',1,280641),(7501,150,'最后，但并非最不重要的是，向南移动到非洲，一套精妙的马赛克和小径，以代表这个迷人和多样的大陆的伟大的河流(Q20)。',300530,'Then last, but not least, moving south to Africa anda whole set of wonderful mosaics and trails to represent the great rivers(Q20) of this fascinating and varied continent.',1,289001),(7502,150,'现在，我们的全球游乐场的开放日期是7月10日。',306000,'Now, the opening date for our Global Playground is 10th July.',1,300531),(7503,150,'我们也很想在那里见到你，所以约个时间来看看这个位于市中心的宏伟的、原始的新设施。',315000,'And again we''d love to see you there-so make a date and come and see this magnificent, original new amenity right in the heart of the city.',1,306001),(7504,151,'好的，那么我们的演讲我能从索尔·海尔达尔的早期生活开始吗?',53360,'Right, well for our presentation shall I start with the early life of Thor Heyerdahl?',1,47511),(7505,151,'当然。为什么你不从描述他是哪种类型的男孩开始，尤其是他对收集东西的热情。',60000,'Sure.Why don''t you begin with describing the type of boy he was, especially -his passion for collecting things(Q21).',1,53361),(7506,151,'没错，他有自己的小博物馆。',63320,'That''s right, he had his own little museum.',1,60001),(7507,151,'我认为孩子们发展自己的价值观而不加入父母的爱好是不寻常的;例如，我在想海尔达尔怎么会不跟他爸爸去打猎。',74430,'And I think it''s unusual for children to develop their own values and not join in their parents''hobbies;I''m thinking of how Heyerdahl wouldn''t go hunting with his dad, for example.',1,63321),(7508,151,'是的，他更喜欢听妈妈念书给他听来了解大自然。',79000,'Yeah, he preferred to learn about nature by listening to his mother read to him.',1,74431),(7509,151,'他很早就知道自己长大后要成为一名探险家。',84490,'And quite early on he knew he wanted to become an explorer when he grew up.',1,79001),(7510,151,'我想这是他在挪威露营时的想法……',89000,'That came from his camping trips he went on in Norway I think...',1,84491),(7511,151,'不，是攀岩，他年轻时把时间花在了攀岩上。',93000,'No,it was climbing that he spent his time on as a young man (Q22).',1,89001),(7512,151,'哦，对的...大学毕业后，他和同学结了婚，他们决定一起生活在一个小岛上，以了解恶劣的天气条件如何影响人们的生活方式。',106000,'Oh, right...After university he married a classmate and together,they decided to experience living on a small island,to find out how harsh weather conditions shaped people''s lifestyles (Q23).',1,93001),(7513,151,'作为离家前准备工作的一部分，他们学习了基本的生存技能，比如建造一个庇护所。',113640,'As part of their preparation before they left home, they learnt basic survival skills like building a shelter.',1,106001),(7514,151,'我猜他们需要这种知识，以便在一个人烟稀少、被大海切断的偏远地区野外生活，这就是他们的目标。',123760,'I guess they needed that knowledge in order to live wild in a remote location with few inhabitants, cut off by the sea (Q24), which is what they were aiming to do.',1,113641),(7515,151,'你演讲的一个重要部分应该是海尔达尔通过检查他在岛上偶然发现的神秘古代雕刻而形成的激进理论。',133340,'An important part of your talk should be the radical theory Heyerdahl formed from examining mysterious ancient carvings that he happened to find on the island.',1,123761),(7516,151,'我觉得你应该把它写完。',135320,'I think you should finish with that.',1,133341),(7517,151,'好的。',199000,'OK.',1,135321),(7518,151,'好的，维克多，在你的部分结束后，我会从他关于波利尼西亚移民的理论，继续讲海尔达尔的成年生活。',209000,'All right, Victor, so after your part I''ll talk about Thor Heyerdahl''s adult life, continuing from the theory he had about Polynesian migration.',1,199001),(7519,151,'当然，直到那时，学者们才相信人类最初是从西方的亚洲迁移到波利尼西亚群岛的。',217640,'Up until that time of course, academics had believed that humans first migrated to the islands in Polynesia from Asia, in the west.',1,209001),(7520,151,'是的，他们认为从东方来是不可能的，因为在岛屿和最近的有人居住的土地之间有一片巨大的、空旷的海洋。',227780,'Yes, they thought that travel from the east was impossible, because of the huge, empty stretch of ocean that lies between the islands and the nearest inhabited land (Q25).',1,217641),(7521,151,'是的，但是海尔达尔花了很长时间研究云的运动，洋流和风的模式来确定这是否真的可能。',236000,'Yes, but Heyerdahl spent ages studying the cloud movements, ocean currents and wind patterns to find if it was actually possible.',1,227781),(7522,151,'另一个争论是，在波利尼西亚东部的社区没有大型造船的传统。',243000,'And another argument was that there was no tradition of large ship-building in the communities lying to the east of Polynesia.',1,236001),(7523,151,'但是海尔达尔知道他们用当地制造的独木舟进行了多次沿海航行。',248180,'But Heyerdahl knew they made lots of coastal voyages in locally built canoes.',1,243001),(7524,151,'是的，或者乘木筏航行，海尔达尔接下来的长途航行就证明了这一点。',254450,'Yes, or sailing on rafts, as was shown by the long voyage that Heyerdahl did next.',1,248181),(7525,151,'这是一段非常冒险的旅程，有时我怀疑他是否有私人原因?',261800,'It was an incredibly risky journey to undertake-sometimes I wonder if he did that trip for private reasons, you know? ',1,254451),(7526,151,'向别人展示他可以有精彩的冒险经历。',265530,'To show others that he could have spectacular adventures.',1,261801),(7527,151,'你觉得呢，奥利维亚?',267000,'What do you think, Olivia?',1,265531),(7528,151,'嗯，我认为这更多的是一个简单的尝试他的想法，看看从东部迁移是否可能。',274360,'Well,I think it was more a matter of simply trying out his idea, to see if migration from the east was possible (Q26).',1,267001),(7529,151,'是的，可能就是这样。',276560,'Yes, that''s probably it.',1,274361),(7530,151,'这个可怜的家伙在那个时候遭受了一些痛苦，因为战争迫使他停止了几年的工作……',282440,'And the poor guy suffered a bit at that time because the war forced him to stop his work for some years...',1,276561),(7531,151,'是的。当他重新开始并计划他的史诗般的旅程时，你认为他在其他人之前完成它对他很重要吗?',291380,'Yes.When he got started again and planned his epic voyage, do you think it was important to him that he achieve it before anyone else did?',1,282441),(7532,151,'我还没在哪儿读到过这是他的动机。',296000,'Um,I haven''t read anywhere that that was his motivation.',1,291381),(7533,151,'最重要的因素似乎是他只使用古代技术和当地材料建造他的木筏。',303210,'The most important factor seems to have been that he use only ancient techniques and local materials to build his raft (Q27).',1,296001),(7534,151,'是的。我想知道它跑得有多快。',306500,'Yes.I wonder how fast it went.',1,303211),(7535,151,'他们花了97天从南美到太平洋岛屿。',312250,'Well, it took them 97 days from South America to the Pacific lslands.',1,306501),(7536,151,'在那之后，海尔达尔去了复活节岛，对吧?',317000,'Mm.And after that, Heyerdahl went to Easter Island, didn''t he? ',1,312251),(7537,151,'我们应该提到那次旅行的目的。',319340,'We should mention the purpose of that trip.',1,317001),(7538,151,'我想他是坐芦苇做的船去的。',323290,'I think he sailed there in a boat made out of reeds.',1,319341),(7539,151,'不，那是后来在埃及，奥利维亚。',326000,'No, that was later on in Egypt, Olivia.',1,323291),(7540,151,'哦，是的，没错。',327520,'Oh, yes, that''s right.',1,326001),(7541,151,'但他想做的是与当地人谈论他们的古老石雕，然后自己做一个，以了解更多的过程。',335810,'But what he wanted to do was talk to the local people about their old stone carvings and then make one himself to learn more about the process (Q28).',1,327521),(7542,151,'我明白了。',337000,'I see.',1,335811),(7543,151,'多么美好的生活啊。',339000,'Well, what a great life.',1,337001),(7544,151,'虽然他的很多理论都被证明是错误的，但他确实给很多学科留下了深刻的印象，不是吗?',346270,'Even though many of his theories have been disproven, he certainly left a lasting impression on many disciplines, didn''t he? ',1,339001),(7545,151,'在我看来，他是第一个建立现代学者所说的实用考古学的人。',353290,'To my mind, he was the first person to establish what modern academics call practical archaeology (Q29).',1,346271),(7546,151,'我是说，他们今天试图重现过去的东西，就像他的筏子之旅一样。',360180,'I mean, that they try to recreate something from the past today, like he did with his raft trip.',1,353291),(7547,151,'不幸的是，他关于波利尼西亚人起源的观点被完全否定了。',366790,'It''s unfortunate that his ideas about where Polynesians originated from have been completely discredited.',1,360181),(7548,151,'是的。好的，我会在最后准备一份ppt来承认我们的资料来源。',373660,'Yes.Right, well,I''ll prepare a PowerPoint slide at the end that acknowledges our sources.',1,366791),(7549,151,'我主要用的是威廉·奥利弗的《托尔·海尔达尔的生活和工作》。',378270,'I mainly used The Life and Work of Thor Heyerdahl by William Oliver.',1,373661),(7550,151,'我认为他使用的研究方法是非常健全的，尽管必须说，我发现整体基调有点过时。',386430,'I thought the research methods he used were very sound, althoughl must say I found the overall tone somewhat old-fashioned (Q30).',1,378271),(7551,151,'我觉得他们需要做一个新的修订版。',389270,'I think they need to do a new, revised edition.',1,386431),(7552,151,'是的。我同意。',391000,'Yeah.I agree.',1,389271),(7553,151,'主题呢?我发现它真的很有挑战性!',395000,'What about the subject matter-I found it realty challenging!',1,391001),(7554,151,'这是一个复杂的问题…',397270,'Well, it''s a complex issue...',1,395001),(7555,151,'我认为这本书有很多优点。',400210,'I thought the book had lots of good points.',1,397271),(7556,151,'你认为怎么样......',402000,'What did you think of...',1,400211),(7557,152,'我一直在和一些企业的经理交谈，阅读关于管理未来的调查。',79210,'Well,I''ve been talking to managers in a number of businesses, and reading surveys about the future of management.',1,72001),(7558,152,'我要在这个研讨会上介绍的是一些关于这个活动在未来十年可能发生的变化的想法。',88000,'And what I''m going to present in this seminar is a few ideas about how the activity is likely to change in the next ten years.',1,79211),(7559,152,'这不是科学的统计分析，只是一些供我们讨论的想法。',94680,'It isn''t a scientific, statistical analysis-just some ideas for us to discuss.',1,88001),(7560,152,'我想提到的一个领域是商业市场，我确信一个真正重要的发展将是竞争的主要增加(Q31)，来自世界各地的公司试图销售类似的产品。',108870,'One area I want to mention is business markets, and I''m sure a really significant development will be a major increase in competition (Q31), with companies from all round the world trying to sell similar products.',1,94681),(7561,152,'消费者将有更多的选择——例如，在澳大利亚销售的食品可能是在美国、中国、芬兰和其他几十个国家生产的。',122000,'Consumers will have much more choice-for instance, food products sold in Australia might be manufactured in the USA, China, Finland and dozens of other countries.',1,108871),(7562,152,'与此同时，合并和收购意味着，政府的权力实际上正在输给大型跨国公司。',130340,'At the same time, mergers and takeovers mean that governments are actually losing power to major global (Q32)\ncorporations.',1,122001),(7563,152,'我们可能都能想到那些施加巨大影响的公司，这可能对消费者有利。',138430,'We can probably all think of companies that exert a great deal of influence, which may be good for consumers.',1,130341),(7564,152,'关于市场，我想说的第三点是，在快速扩张的经济体中，如印度、中国、巴西和俄罗斯，需求增长非常快。',150930,'A third point I want to make about markets is that in the rapidly expanding economies, such as India, China, Brazil and Russia, demand (Q33) is growing very fast.',1,138431),(7565,152,'这给世界各地的资源带来了压力。',155460,'This is putting pressure on resources all over the world.',1,150931),(7566,152,'我认为企业对外部影响越来越开放。',160610,'I think businesses are becoming more open to external influences.',1,155461),(7567,152,'特别是，企业在做出商业决策之前，越来越多地咨询客户。',167300,'In particular, companies are consulting customers\n(Q34) more and more before making their business decisions.',1,160611),(7568,152,'公司正在寻找他们想要的东西并提供给他们，而不是制造产品然后试图销售，这是多年前的模式。',176640,'Companies are finding out what they want and providing it, instead of making products and then trying to sell them, which is the model of years ago.',1,167301),(7569,152,'另一个影响是，对环境的担忧将迫使制造商延长产品的生命周期，以减少污染和浪费。',187230,'Another influence is that concerns about the environment will force manufacturers to extend product lifecycles, to reduce the amount of pollution and waste.',1,176641),(7570,152,'在某些情况下，监管需要加强。',193000,'And in some cases, regulation (Q35) will need to be strengthened.',1,187231),(7571,152,'许多社会的流动性和民主性要高得多，公司结构也在发生变化以反映这一点。',200800,'Many societies are much more fluid and democratic, and the structure of companies is changing to reflect that.',1,193001),(7572,152,'我认为我们将会看到公司内部更加重视基于特定项目创建团队。',208600,'I think we''re going to see a greater emphasis within companies on teams created with a specific project (Q36) in mind.',1,200801),(7573,152,'当它们完成后，这些团队将被解散，并成立新的团队。',214000,'And when they''re completed, the teams will be disbanded and new ones formed.',1,208601),(7574,152,'越来越多的人认为工作只是他们生活方式的一部分，而不是最重要的，随着劳动力在一些国家的萎缩，企业不得不竞争员工，而不是在众多申请者中进行选择。',231350,'More and more people see work as simply one part of their lifestyle, and not the most important one, and as the workforce is shrinking in some countries, businesses are having to compete for staff instead of being able to choose among a lot of applicants.',1,214001),(7575,152,'吸引和留住员工的典型例子是一些传统的做法，比如灵活的工作时间，以及技术进步使之成为可能的东西——远程工作，人们可以在家里、国外或几乎任何他们选择的地方工作。',254000,'Typical examples that will attract and retain staff are traditional ones like flexible (Q37) hours and-something that has been made possible by advances in technology-remote working, with people based at their home, abroad, or almost anywhere they choose.',1,231351),(7576,152,'管理风格几乎肯定会继续变化。',258000,'Management styles will almost certainly continue to change.',1,254001),(7577,152,'高级经理需要的不仅仅是他们一直需要的效率。',263590,'Senior managers will require a lot more than the efficiency that they''ve always needed.',1,258001),(7578,152,'最重要的是，他们需要出色的领导技能，这样他们的组织才能在快速变化的世界中发起并应对变化，在这个