00,'Yes.',1,346001),(7762,155,'好吧。我会让一些大四的学生给我一些建议……也许我能看出来他们写了什么。',352510,'Right.I''ll get some of the final year students to give me some tips (Q29) ...maybe see if I can read what they wrote.',1,346601),(7763,155,'我觉得这是个好主意。',354980,'I think that''s a very good idea.',1,352511),(7764,155,'我不介意给你看看我做了什么。',357260,'I don'' t mind showing you what I did. ',1,354981),(7765,155,'你在国外的时候，别犯我犯过的错误。',360900,'And while you'' re abroad don'' t make the mistake I made.',1,357261),(7766,155,'我太投入了，以至于忘记了为我最后一年回到这里做安排。',367120,'I got so involved I forgot all about making arrangements for when I came back here for the final year (Q30). ',1,360901),(7767,155,'确保你和他们保持联系，这样他们就知道你的选修课了。',372380,'Make sure you stay in touch so they know your choices for the optional modules. ',1,367121),(7768,155,'你不想错过你喜欢的专业。',376000,'You don''t want to miss out doing your preferred specialisms.',1,372381),(7769,155,'好的。',376830,'Right.',1,376001),(7770,156,'今天，我想谈谈自我调节焦点理论，以及领导者的行为如何影响追随者处理不同情况的方式。',100000,'Today,I want to talk about self-regulatory focus theory and how the actions of leaders can affect the way followers approach different situations.',1,88001),(7771,156,'自我调节焦点理论是由托里·希金斯提出的理论。',106000,'Self-regulatory focus theory is a theory developed by Tori Higgins.',1,100001),(7772,156,'他说，一个人在任何时候的注意力都是接近快乐或避免痛苦。',115140,'He says that a person''s focus at any given time is to either approach pleasure or avoid pain.',1,106001),(7773,156,'这是我们每个人都有的两个基本动机，它们使我们有不同的目标。',124650,'These are two basic motivations that each and every one of us has, and they cause us to have different kinds of goals.',1,115141),(7774,156,'不同生活情境中的晋升目标强调成就。',131570,'Promotion goals in different life situations emphasise achievement (Q31).',1,124651),(7775,156,'预防的目标是为了避免惩罚。',138410,'Prevention goals are oriented towards the avoidance of punishment.',1,131571),(7776,156,'在特定情况下，我们的想法可能更多地关注于促进目标或预防目标。',149000,'In a specific situation, our thoughts might focus more on promotion goals or more on prevention goals.',1,138411),(7777,156,'该理论认为，有两个因素会影响我们关注的目标。',156000,'The theory suggests that two factors affect which goals we are focusing on.',1,149001),(7778,156,'首先，有一个长期因素。',160000,'First, there is a chronic factor.',1,156001),(7779,156,'这个因素与一个人的个性有关，每个人都有一个基本的倾向，要么更关注提升目标，要么更关注作为他或她个性的一部分的预防目标。',178640,'This factor is connected to a person''s personality (Q32) and says that each person has a basic tendency to either focus more on promotion goals or focus more on prevention goals as part of his or her personality.',1,160001),(7780,156,'第二，有一个情境因素，这意味着我们所处的环境可以让我们更有可能专注于一组目标或另一组目标。',191450,'Second, there is a situational (Q33) factor which means that the context we are in can make us more likely to focus on one set of goals or the other.',1,178641),(7781,156,'例如，当我们和朋友在一起的时候，我们更有可能想到快乐和提升目标。',201670,'For example, we are more likely to be thinking about pleasure and to have promotion goals when we are spending time with a friend (Q34).',1,191451),(7782,156,'相比之下，如果我们为老板做一个重要的项目，我们更有可能避免犯错，因此我们有更多的预防目标。',218000,'In contrast, if we are working on an important project for our boss, we are more likely to try to avoid making mistakes and therefore have more prevention goals in our mind.',1,201671),(7783,156,'研究表明，我们在特定时间关注的目标会影响我们的思维方式。',226900,'Research has shown that the goals we are focusing on at a given time affect the way we think.',1,218001),(7784,156,'例如，当关注提升目标时，人们会考虑他们的理想自我，他们的抱负和收获。',237440,'For example, when focusing on promotion goals, people consider their ideal self, their aspirations (Q35) and gains.',1,226901),(7785,156,'他们不会考虑他们会失去什么，所以他们以一种更快乐的方式思考。',243550,'They don''t think about what they can lose, so they think in a happier mode.',1,237441),(7786,156,'他们更有动力去改变。',247400,'They feel more inspired to change.',1,243551),(7787,156,'当人们关注预防目标时，他们想到的是“应该”的自己。',254000,'When people are focusing on prevention goals, they think about their \"ought\"self.',1,247401),(7788,156,'它们应该是什么?',256720,'What are they supposed to be?',1,254001),(7789,156,'人们期望从他们身上得到什么?',259530,'What are people expecting from them? ',1,256721),(7790,156,'他们考虑自己对他人的义务。',263280,'They consider their obligations to others.',1,259531),(7791,156,'因此，他们会经历更多的焦虑，并试图避免可能失败的情况。',276000,'As a result, they experience more anxiety and try to avoid situations where they could lose.',1,263281),(7792,156,'既然我已经谈到了这两个焦点以及它们如何影响人们，我想看看领导者的行为方式，或者他们的领导风格，可以影响追随者在特定情况下采取的焦点。',296000,'Now that I have talked about the two focuses and how they affect people,I want to look at the idea that the way leaders behave, or their style (Q36) of leading, can affect the focus that followers adopt in a specific situation.',1,276001),(7793,156,'在谈到领导力时，我们经常会提到变革型领导者和交易型领导者。',305310,'In talking about leadership, we often mention transformational leaders and transactional leaders.',1,296001),(7794,156,'变革型领导者，在与他们的追随者互动时，关注他们的发展。',312730,'Transformational leaders, when interacting with their followers, focus on their development (Q37).',1,305311),(7795,156,'变革型领导人用他们的语言和行动强调变革。',319200,'In their words and actions transformational leaders highlight change.',1,312731),(7796,156,'他们的演讲充满激情，传达了明确的愿景。',325130,'Their speech is passionate and conveys a definitive vision (Q38).',1,319201),(7797,156,'所有这些都可以鼓励追随者去思考什么是可能的。',331510,'All of these things can encourage followers to think about what could be.',1,325131),(7798,156,'换句话说，他们激发了追随者的晋升焦点。',338800,'In other words, they inspire a promotion focus in their followers.',1,331511),(7799,156,'相比之下，交易型领导者专注于发展清晰的结构，告诉他们的追随者对他们的期望是什么。',351160,'In contrast, transactional leaders focus on developing clear structures (Q39) that tell their followers exactly what is expected of them.',1,338801),(7800,156,'虽然他们确实解释了人们听从命令会得到的奖励，但他们更强调了追随者会受到怎样的惩罚，或者如果追随者的行为没有改变，就不会得到奖励。',368350,'While they do explain the rewards people will get for following orders, they emphasise more howa follower will be punished or that a follower won''t get rewarded if his or her behaviour doesn''t change.',1,351161),(7801,156,'简而言之，他们强调了犯错的后果。',374370,'In short, they emphasise the consequences of making a mistake.',1,368351),(7802,156,'这种强调将明显引导追随者专注于避免惩罚和问题。',382470,'This emphasis will clearly lead followers to focus on avoiding punishment and problems.',1,374371),(7803,156,'这显然是一个预防重点。',386610,'This is clearly a prevention focus.',1,382471),(7804,156,'总之，重要的是要理解一个焦点不一定比另一个更好。',396000,'In conclusion, it is important to understand that one focus is not necessarily better than the other one.',1,386611),(7805,156,'对于一个在一个需要大量创新的领域工作的设计师来说，一个提升焦点可能是更好的。',404740,'For a designer who works in a field where a lot of innovation (Q40) is needed,a promotion focus is probably better.',1,396001),(7806,156,'相比之下，预防的重点使人们更谨慎地工作，并产生更高质量的工作可能非常适合像外科医生这样的工作。',419230,'In contrast,a prevention focus which causes people to work more cautiously and produce higher quality work might be very appropriatefor a job like a surgeon, for example.',1,404741),(7807,156,'然而，这项研究的主要观点是，领导者的行为可以极大地影响人们在处理一种情况时是更注重晋升还是更注重预防。',436000,'The main point of the research, though, is that the actions of leaders can greatly influence whether people approach a situation with more of a promotion focus or more of a prevention focus.',1,419231),(7808,157,'这里是桑代克。',90000,'Thorndyke''s.',1,88761),(7809,157,'早上好。',91170,'Good morning. ',1,90001),(7810,157,'那是桑代克先生吗?',93000,'Is that Mr Thorndyke?',1,91171),(7811,157,'请讲。',94000,'Speaking. ',1,93001),(7812,157,'我能帮什么忙吗?',95000,'How can I help?',1,94001),(7813,157,'我公寓里有些东西需要粉刷和修理，不知道你能不能帮忙。',102720,'I''ve got quite a few things which need painting and fixing in the flat and I wonder whether you''d be able to do the work.',1,95001),(7814,157,'我肯定能帮上忙，不过还是让我记下一些细节吧。',106400,'I''m sure I''d be able to help but let me take down a few details.',1,102721),(7815,157,'是的,当然。',108000,'Yes, of course.',1,106401),(7816,157,'首先，你是怎么知道我们的?',111390,'Well, firstly, how did you hear about us?',1,108001),(7817,157,'是我的朋友梅·汉普顿……几年前你为她做了很多出色的工作。',117320,'It was my friend May Hampton... you did some excellent work for her a couple of years ago. ',1,111391),(7818,157,'你还记得吗?',11