d to become one of the busiest ports in the country. ',1,105191),(7879,158,'因为这里已经很繁忙了，勘探者开始寻找其他的矿物，到19世纪末，铅、铜、锰和砷被添加到离开曼纳姆的货物中。',138360,'And because it was already so busy, prospectors began to look for other minerals, and by the end of the nineteenth century, lead, copper, manganese and arsenic were added to the cargos leaving Manham.',1,124401),(7880,158,'在早期，矿石是在开采的同一地区进行熔炼或加工的。',145570,'In the early days, the ores had been smelted-or processed-in the same area they were mined. ',1,138361),(7881,158,'但是，随着需求的增长，熔炼过程需要巨大的工厂熔炉或大火来熔化岩石中的金属，并且当地没有足够的煤炭，所以含有矿物质的岩石必须被运输到很远的地方。',162000,'But, as demand grew, the smelting process required huge factory furnaces or fires to melt the metal from the rock and there was not enough coal in the local area, so the rocks containing minerals had to be shipped long distances (Q13).',1,145571),(7882,158,'可悲的是，在20世纪，曼哈姆港口衰落了，成千上万的工人被迫移民出该地区。',171020,'Sadly, in the twentieth century, the great port of Manham declined, and thousands of workers were forced to emigrate out of the area (Q14). ',1,162001),(7883,158,'港口的建筑年久失修，这个地方也几乎被人遗忘了。',176800,'The building at the port fell into disrepair, and the place became almost forgotten. ',1,171021),(7884,158,'但后来，曼哈姆信托基金会成立，以保护该地区的历史资源。',182750,'But then, the Manham Trust was formed to conserve the historical resources of the area. ',1,176801),(7885,158,'它组织了数十名当地志愿者清除灌木丛，寻找装置的原始轮廓。',190940,'It organised scores of local volunteers to remove undergrowth to find the original outlines of the installations. ',1,182751),(7886,158,'然后，它聘请了专业人员，将设施与原来的港口建筑群的地图匹配起来，并着手重建它。',200810,'It then brought in paid professionals to match installations with maps of the original port complex and to set about reconstructing it (Q15). ',1,190941),(7887,158,'今天，你们可以看到这一雄心勃勃的恢复计划的成果。',206360,'Today you can see the results of this ambitious programme of restoration. ',1,200811),(7888,158,'我们的目的是让曼哈呐港恢复其巅峰时期的状态，成为“全国最大的铜港”，我们相信这将在今年年底前实现。',250910,'The intention, and we believe this will be realised before the end of the 