ble L, by the way, and this type is usually found in large companies, which have lots of different levels in them.(Q35)',1,170464),(8308,168,'这些组织通常有独立的部门，专门从事财务、销售、维护等工作。',192950,'These organisations usually have separate departments that specialise in things like finance,or sales, or maintenance, or whatever.',1,184183),(8309,168,'每个人都由一小组高级管理人员在最高层进行协调，通常每个人的工作都受到一系列规则和程序的控制——例如，有特定的工作描述、纪律规则等等。',209810,'Each one is co-ordinated at the top by a small group of senior managers, and typically everyone''s job is controlled by sets of rules and procedures - for example,  there are specific job descriptions, rules for discipline, and so on.(Q36)',1,192957),(8310,168,'这种文化有什么好处？',213480,'What are the benefits of this kind of culture?',1,209814),(8311,168,'首先，因为它存在于大型组织中，其固定成本或众所周知的管理费用与其产出或生产的产品相比很低。',225600,'Well firstly, because it''s found in large organisations, its fixed costs, or overheads as they''re known, are low in relation to its output, or what it produces.',1,213480),(8312,168,'换句话说，它可以实现规模经济。',230220,'In other words it can achieve economies of scale.',1,225603),(8313,168,'其次，它在技术专长很重要的商业市场中特别成功。',237490,'And secondly, it is particularly successful in business markets where technical expertise is  important.(Q37)',1,230225),(8314,168,'另一方面，这种文化通常很慢地认识到改变的必要性，甚至反应更慢。',246060,'On the other hand, this culture is often very slow to recognise the need for  change, and even slower to react.(Q38)',1,237499),(8315,168,'这种文化适合什么样的人？',249090,'What kind of person does this type of culture suit?',1,246066),(8316,168,'好吧，它适合重视安全并且不想承担责任的员工。',261120,'Well it suits employees who value security, and who don''t particularly want to have responsibility.(Q39)',1,249096),(8317,168,'现在转到任务文化——这种类型存在于以项目为导向的组织中。',268410,'Moving on now to Task Cultures - this type is found in organisations that are projectoriented.',1,261121),(8318,168,'您通常会在公司产品的市场竞争非常激烈或产品本身寿命较短的地方找到它。',277060,'You usually find it where the market for the company''s product is extremely competitive, or where t