e, the spare key to the back door is hanging on a hook on the wall by the sitting room window.(Q16)',1,247735),(8607,174,'请务必在使用后将其放回原处。',258700,'Please make sure to put it back when you''ve used it.',1,255625),(8608,174,'以前的客人把它丢在花园里了，我不得不再做一个！',262730,'The previous guests lost it in the garden and I had to get another one made!',1,258708),(8609,174,'如果您对灯有任何问题，您会在一个大纸板箱中找到一些备用灯泡。',268990,'And if you have any trouble with the lamps, you''ll find some spare bulbs in a large cardboard box.',1,262739),(8610,174,'它在洗衣机的顶部，里面有各种有用的东西。',273550,'It''s on top of the washing machine with all kinds of useful things in it.(Q17)',1,268993),(8611,174,'哦，还有一件事，我们上次谈话时我忘了提...',277100,'Oh, and another thing I forgot to mention when we last spoke ...',1,273558),(8612,174,'是的？',278070,'Yes?',1,277100),(8613,174,'我给你留了一张本地地图。这样您就可以轻松找到自己的方式。',279900,'I''ve left you a local map. so you''ll be able to find your way around easily.',1,278077),(8614,174,'它可以展示出整个区域来，我把它放在你卧室电视机下面的柜子最上面的抽屉里。',289540,'It shows the whole area. I put it in the top drawer of the chest under the TV in your bedroom.(Q18)',1,279909),(8615,174,'那里也有完整的本地信息文件。',292440,'There''s a whole file of local information in there too.',1,289543),(8616,174,'谢谢。参观小镇怎么样？你能给我们什么建议吗？',297350,'Thanks. What about visiting the town? Can you give us any advice?',1,292440),(8617,174,'是的。你需要开车。',300590,'Yes. You''ll need to take the car.',1,297351),(8618,174,'从公寓走真的太远了。',303640,'It''s too far to walk from the flat really.',1,300593),(8619,174,'你只有付钱才能把车停在那儿所有的停车场……我最喜欢车站旁边的那个，你可以在五分钟内从那里步行到市中心。',313590,'You have to pay to leave your car in all the car parks now I''m afraid ... I like the one that''s by the station best and you can walk to the town centre from there in five minutes.',1,303647),(8620,174,'那是所有最好的餐厅都在的地方。',315870,'That''s where all the best restaurants are.',1,313590),(8621,174,'但如果你想要外卖，意大利的意大利面和比萨饼做得非常好。',321150,'But if you want a takeaway, the Italian one does really good pasta and pizzas.',1,315874),(8622,174,'呼叫732281 或者 766119 这是中国菜',330260,'Call 7-3 double 2, 8-1 for that one, or 7 double 6, double 1, 9 for the Chinese.(Q19)',1,321150),(8623,174,'他们都很好，他们都会送到公寓。',334210,'They''re both good and they''ll both deliver to the flat.',1,330263),(8624,174,'至于参观的地方，是的，一定要去看看铁路博物馆。',339980,'As for places to visit, yes, do go and see the railway museum.',1,334214),(8625,174,'展览虽小，但真的很好。星期天会很拥挤，所以我建议你在一个安静的日子去参观它，在一周的晚些时候，但不要在星期四，这是市场日——你找不到停车的地方，这也是一周中唯一的一天他们不开放！还要别的吗？',360030,'The exhibition is small but really good. It gets very crowded on Sundays, so I suggest you visit it on a quieter day, later in the week, but not on Thursdays which is market day - you won''t find anywhere to park and it''s also the only day of the week when they''re not open! Anything else?(Q20)',1,339980),(8626,174,'暂时没有。谢谢！',362033,'Not for the moment. Thanks!',1,360033),(8627,175,'你好，基拉，你好吗？',47700,'Hello, Kira, how are you?',1,45861),(8628,175,'好的，谢谢，保罗，你好吗？',49790,'Fine thanks, Paul, how are you?',1,47700),(8629,175,'非常感谢。很高兴见到你。自从你开始上课已经12个月过去了吧？',55020,'Well, thanks. It''s good to see you. It must be twelve months since you did our course?',1,49795),(8630,175,'那就对了。很高兴回来打招呼。',59090,'That''s right. It''s nice to come back and say hello.',1,55028),(8631,175,'你报了哪门课？',61260,'What course did you enrol in?',1,59094),(8632,175,'事实上，我直接上的是三年级药剂学。',65170,'Actually, I went straight into third year Pharmacy.',1,61268),(8633,175,'他们给了我两年的学分，这可能让我觉得更难了。',70410,'They credited me with two years, which probably made it more difficult for me.',1,65173),(8634,175,'另一方面，你很幸运获得了学分。',73950,'On the other hand, you were lucky to be granted credits.',1,70413),(8635,175,'这就是你选择课程的原因吗？',75640,'Is that why you chose the course?',1,73955),(8636,175,'是的。而且，由于我已经在我的国家完成了这门课程，我认为如果我学习一些我已经知道的东西会更容易。',84260,'Yes. And, as I''d already finished a course in it in my country, I thought it would be easier if I studied something I already knew.(Q21)',1,75646),(8637,175,'没想到你进入了三年级。',86770,'I didn''t realise you went into third year.',1,84261),(8638,175,'我以为你是第一年开始的。难怪这么难！',90860,'I thought you started in first year. No wonder it was so hard!',1,86775),(8639,175,'您认为在这里的大学学习和在您的国家学习的最大区别之一是什么？',97430,'And what do you think is one of the big differences between studying at a university here and studying in your country?',1,90862),(8640,175,'好吧，我发现写作业非常困难，因为我不熟悉这里系统的那个方面。',105250,'Well, I''ve found it very difficult to write assignments, because I wasn''t familiar with that aspect of the system here.',1,97433),(8641,175,'讲师希望学生（你们）更批判性的看待问题。这样的要求让我感觉很难过。',111950,'The main problem is that the lecturers expect you to be critical. That made me feel really terrible.',1,105254),(8642,175,'我想“我怎么可能做到这一点？当别人的研究可能花了五年时间做的时候，我怎么能评论他们呢？” 我想很多来自海外的人都有类似的问题。',126530,'I thought \"How can I possibly do it? How can I comment on someone else''s research when they probably spent five years doing it?\" I think a lot of people who come from overseas countries have similar problems.',1,111956),(8643,175,'但过了一段时间，我变得更容易了。',130260,'But after a while it became easier for me.',1,126532),(8644,175,'人们希望你在阅读和写作过程中遇到问题，但实际上，这更多的是改变你对学术研究的看法的问题。',140760,'People expect you to have problems with the process of reading and writing but, in fact, it is more a question of altering your viewpoint towards academic study.(Q22)',1,130262),(8645,175,'讲座的内容如何？对你来说容易吗？',144680,'How was the content of the lectures? Was it easy for you?',1,140764),(8646,175,'我在理解讲座时真的没有太多问题。',148340,'I didn''t really have many problems understanding lectures.',1,144685),(8647,175,'内容和我之前学过的很相似。',151640,'The content was very similar to what I''d studied before.',1,148343),(8648,175,'那么讲师自己呢？你们国家的讲师基本一样吗?',156870,'And what about the lecturers themselves? Are they essentially the same as lecturers in your country?',1,151649),(8649,175,'实际上，没有。这里。他们更容易接近。',161270,'Well actually, no. Here. they''re much easier to approach.(Q23)',1,156871),(8650,175,'每次讲完你都可以去问他们一些你不明白的事情。',165670,'After every lecture you can go and ask them something you didn''t understand.',1,161271),(8651,175,'或者您可以预约并与他们讨论课程中的任何内容。',169680,'Or you can make an appointment and talk to them about anything in the course.',1,165675),(8652,175,'也许你发现他们不同，因为你现在是一个更成熟的学生，而当你在你的国家学习时，你更年轻，没有那么自信。',177830,'Maybe you found them different because you''re a more mature student now, whereas when you were studying in your country you were younger and not so assertive.(Q24)',1,169684),(8653,175,'不，我不认为那是区别。这里的大多数学生都是这样做的。',183430,'No, I don''t think that''s the difference. Most of the students here do it.',1,177839),(8654,175,'在我的教职员工中，他们似乎都在进行预约——通常是谈论课程中令他们担心的事情，但有时只是谈论他们可能真正感兴趣的事情，他们可能想要专攻的事情。',196760,'In my faculty, they all seem to make appointments - usually to talk about something in the course that''s worrying them, but sometimes just about something that might really interest them, something they might want to specialise in.(Q25)',1,183432),(8655,175,'讲师必须每周为学生留出一定的时间。',201650,'The lecturers must set aside certain times every week when they''re available for students.',1,196762),(8656,175,'听起来还不错。',241440,'That''s good to hear.',1,201651),(8657,175,'你的时间表是怎样的？这是非常忙碌的一年吗？',244900,'And how was your timetable? Was it a very busy year?',1,241448),(8658,175,'非常非常忙。他们让你非常努力地工作。',249260,'Very, very busy. They make you work very hard.',1,244902),(8659,175,'除了讲座之外，我们还进行了很多科目的实践课程。我们在小组中进行了这些。',256060,'Apart from lectures, we had practical sessions in a lot of subjects. We did these in small groups.(Q26)',1,249263),(8660,175,'我每周不得不去社区药房工作四个小时。',261100,'I had to go and work four hours every week in a community pharmacy.',1,256069),(8661,175,'事实上，我非常享受这一切——一直结识新朋友。',266190,'Actually, I enjoyed this very much - meeting new people all the time.',1,261105),(8662,175,'然后在第二学期，我们必须在医院药房获得经验，所以我们每隔一天就去其中一家大医院工作。',276160,'Then in second semester, we had to get experience in hospital dispensaries, so every second day we went to one of the big hospitals and worked there.(Q27)',1,266190),(8663,175,'最重要的是，我们有我们的任务，这花了我很多时间。',281110,'And on top of all that we had our assignments, which took me a lot of time.',1,276166),(8664,175,'哦，我差点忘了，在第一学期和第二学期之间，我们不得不在医院全职工作两周。',288190,'Oh, I nearly forgot, between first and second semesters, we had to work full-time for two weeks in a hospital.(Q28)',1,281111),(8665,175,'这听起来确实是非常沉重的一年。所以你现在很高兴你做到了？有没有一点成就感？',295120,'That does sound a very heavy year. So are you pleased now that you did it? Do you feel some sense of achievement?',1,288191),(8666,175,'是的，我确实感觉更有信心，我认为这是最重要的。',300950,'Yeah, I do feel much more confident, which I suppose is the most important thing.(Q29)',1,295128),(8667,175,'你对海外留学的人有什么建议吗？',305090,'And have you got any recommendations for people who are studying from overseas?',1,300956),(8668,175,'好吧，我想他们需要非常好的英语。',308280,'Well, I suppose they need very good English.',1,305098),(8669,175,'如果他们在进入大学之前花更多的时间学习英语会更好，因为如果你不明白人们在说什么并且你没有时间翻译，你可能会遇到大麻烦。',320770,'It would be much better if they spent more time learning English before they enter the university, because you can be in big trouble if you don''t understand what people are saying and you haven''t got time to translate.',1,308285),(8670,175,'还要别的吗？',321930,'Anything else?',1,320777),(8671,175,'好吧，正如我之前所说，对我来说最大的问题是对这里的教育系统缺乏熟悉。',329740,'Well, as I said before, the biggest problem for me was a lack of familiarity with the education system here.(Q30)',1,321931),(8672,175,'听起来好像这是一个真正的挑战。恭喜，基拉。',333410,'It sounds as if it was a real challenge. Congratulations, Kira.',1,329741),(8673,175,'谢谢，保罗。',334886,'Thanks, Paul.',1,333418),(8674,176,'早上好。',63200,'Good morning.',1,62262),(8675,176,'今天我想展示我们的第二年项目的发现，项目是关于城市花园野生生物的。',69960,'Today I''d like to present the findings of our Year 2 project on wildlife found in gardens throughout our city.',1,63201),(8676,176,'我将首先介绍一下该项目的背景，然后谈谈我们的研究技术，然后说明我们的一些中期发现。',79410,'I''ll start by saying something about the background to the project, then talk a little bit about our research techniques, and then indicate some of our interim findings.',1,69961),(8677,176,'首先，我们是如何选择我们的主题的？ 好吧，我们有四个人在小组中，有一天当我们讨论可能的焦点时，小组中的两个提到他们在他们自己的市中心看到了更多的麻雀鹰——英国最有趣的猛禽之一，想知道为什么他们会大量出现在这些花园中。',100100,'First of all, how did we choose our topic? Well, there are four of us in the group and one day while we were discussing a possible focus, two of the group mentioned that they had seen yet more sparrow-hawks - one of Britain''s most interesting birds of prey - in their own city centre gardens and wondered why they were turning up in these gardens in great numbers.(Q31)',1,79416),(8678,176,'我们都非常好奇为什么野生动物会选择栖息在城市花园中。',106650,'We were all very engaged by the idea of why wild animals would choose to inhabit a city garden.',1,100106),(8679,176,'当乡村本身变得不那么受欢迎时，为什么它如此受野生动物欢迎？',112760,'Why is it so popular with wildlife when the countryside itself is becoming less so?',1,106655),(8680,176,'我们做的第一件事是确定私人花园占用城市土地的比例。',119280,'The first thing we did was to establish what proportion of the urban land is taken up by private gardens.',1,112769),(8681,176,'我们估计大约是五分之一，而这点通过查看城市土地测量局的大范围地图得以证实，确切的说是24%。',129930,'We estimated that it was about one fifth, and this was endorsed by looking at large-scale usage maps in the town land survey office - 24% to be precise.(Q32)',1,119287),(8682,176,'我们自己与邻居和朋友的非正式讨论使我们相信，许多园主在看到野生动物方面都有有趣的经历，因此我们决定对来自城市不同地区的园主进行调查。',144740,'Our own informal discussions with neighbours and friends led us to believe that many garden owners had interesting experiences to relate regarding wild animal sightings so we decided to survey garden owners from different areas of the city.',1,129936),(8683,176,'他们中只有100多人完成了调查，在一年中每两周做一次——勾选他们从备考列表中看到的物种——并添加任何稀有物种的名称。',157160,'Just over 100 of them completed a survey once every two weeks for twelve months - ticking off species they had seen from a pro forma list - and adding the names of any rarer ones.(Q33)',1,144747),(8684,176,'与此同时，我们在整个城市的选定花园中进行自己的观察。',162270,'Meanwhile, we were doing our own observations in selected gardens throughout the city.',1,157167),(8685,176,'我们特意选择了较小的，因为它们是这个城市迄今为止最典型的。',167070,'We deliberately chose smaller ones because they were by far the most typical in the city.(Q34)',1,162274),(8686,176,'该项目的重点是关注规范而不是例外。',171200,'The whole point of the project was to look at the norm not the exception.',1,167071),(8687,176,'除了对城市园林的初步研究外，我们还研究了很多关于农村野生动物衰退的书籍，并思考了可能的原因。',182220,'Alongside this primary research on urban gardens, we were studying a lot of books about the decline of wild animals in the countryside and thinking of possible causes for this.(Q35)',1,171202),(8688,176,'那么我们发现了什么？ 好吧，我只是没有时间在这里告诉你。',187860,'So what did we find? Well, so much that I just won''t have time to tell you about here.',1,182221),(8689,176,'如果你有兴趣阅读我们更全面的调查发现，我们已经在大学网站上制作了详细的图表，当然，小组中的任何一个人都很乐意与你谈论他们。',199250,'If you''re interested in reading our more comprehensive findings, we''ve produced detailed graphic representations on the college web-site and of course any of the group would be happy to talk to you about them.',1,187866),(8690,176,'只需给我们发电子邮件。',200740,'Just email us.',1,199252),(8691,176,'“我们今天决定展示的只是关于三个物种的信息——因为我们认为这些信息很好地表明了整个农村和城市环境中的工作过程。”',217050,'What we''ve decided to present today is information about just three species - because we felt these gave a good indication of the processes at work in rural and urban settings as a whole.(Q36)',1,200741),(8692,176,'第一个产生大量有趣信息的物种是青蛙。',220880,'The first species to generate a lot of interesting information was frogs.(Q37)',1,217055),(8693,176,'这里有一个清晰的模式——它们在有合适水的地方繁殖。',225790,'And there was a clear pattern here - they proliferate where there is suitable water.',1,220885),(8694,176,'花园池塘正在增加，农村池塘正在消失，导致大量迁移到城镇。',232750,'Garden ponds are on the increase, rural ponds are disappearing, leading to massive migration to the towns.',1,225798),(8695,176,'刺猬也发现在城市地区生活更容易——这一次是因为它们的捕食者发现离开农村环境并不那么有吸引力',242600,'Hedgehogs are also finding it easier to live in urban areas - this time because their predators are not finding it quite so attractive to leave their rural environment.(Q38)',1,232759),(8696,176,'所以刺猬在城市里的存活率更高。',245740,'So hedgehogs have a better survival rate in cities.',1,242607),(8697,176,'我们有很多目击事件，所以总而言之，我们可以毫不费力地精确计算它们的数量。',252800,'We had lots of sightings, so all in all we had no difficulties with our efforts to count their numbers precisely.(Q39)',1,245747),(8698,176,'我们的最后一个物种是最优秀的鸟类歌手，画眉鸟。',257870,'Our final species is the finest of bird singers, the song thrush.',1,252807),(8699,176,'随着农村的衰落，他们正在城市花园中复苏，因为这些天园丁正在购买许多不同的植物，这意味着周围有各种各样的种子。',270420,'On the decline in the countryside, they are experiencing a resurgence in urban gardens because these days gardeners are buying lots of different plants which means there''s an extensive range of  seeds around.(Q40)',1,257874),(8700,176,'这就是他们赖以生存的东西。',272310,'Which is what they feed on.',1,270426),(8701,176,'另一个因素是提供筑巢地——在花园里实际上比在农村更好。',278730,'Another factor is the provision of nesting places - which is actually better in gardens than the countryside.',1,272316),(8702,176,'很难相信，但这是真的。',280660,'Hard to believe it, but it''s true.',1,278732),(8703,176,'顺便说一句，我们发现一项关于画眉鸟的大规模新调查即将启动，因此您应该密切关注。',288710,'Incidentally, we discovered that a massive new survey on song thrushes is about to be launched, so you should keep an eye open for that.',1,280667),(8704,176,'现在，我很乐意回答您的任何问题。',291500,'Now, I''d be happy to answer any questions you may have.',1,288718),(8705,177,'嗨，乔治！很高兴你回来了。很多人都给你打电话了。',101760,'Hi, George! Glad you''re back. Loads of people have phoned you.',1,96409),(8706,177,'真的吗？',102450,'Really?',1,101763),(8707,177,'我感觉就像你的秘书！',104600,'I felt just like your secretary!',1,102457),(8708,177,'对不起！今天下午我去图书馆看报纸，发现了一些非常有趣的东西。',111400,'Sorry! I went into the library this afternoon to have a look at a newspaper and I came across something really interesting.',1,104609),(8709,177,'什么？一本书？',112960,'What? A book?',1,111406),(8710,177,'不，是夏季音乐节的小册子——主要是西班牙音乐。看，我在这里有示例。',118010,'No, a brochure from a summer festival - mainly Spanish music. Look, I''ve Example got it here.',1,112962),(8711,177,'西班牙音乐？我真的很喜欢吉他。我们来看一下。那么这个组''Guitarrini''是什么？',127870,'Spanish music? I really love the guitar. Let''s have a look. So what''s this group ''Guitarrini''?',1,118017),(8712,177,'他们真的很好。 他们在图书馆大厅的一个展台上放了一段包含节日所有亮点的视频，所以我听到了。',135670,'They''re really good. They had a video（Q1） with all the highlights of the festival at a stand in the lobby to the library, so I heard them.',1,127874),(8713,177,'他们演奏奇妙的乐器——鼓、长笛和老式吉他。',141140,'They play fantastic instruments - drums and flutes and old kinds of guitars.',1,135672),(8714,177,'我以前从未听说过这样的事。',143460,'I''ve never heard anything like it before.',1,141149),(8715,177,'听起来很棒。',144880,'Sounds great.',1,143467),(8716,177,'好的。那我们去吗？宠坏自己？',148030,'Okay. Shall we go then? Spoil ourselves?',1,144882),(8717,177,'是的，让我们。',149570,'Yes, let''s.',1,148031),(8718,177,'唯一的问题是没有便宜的座位……都是一个价格。',155440,'The only problem is there aren''t any cheap seats ... it''s all one price.',1,149574),(8719,177,'好吧，在那种情况下，我们可以坐在前面——我们会有一个非常好的视野。',160710,'Well, in that case we could sit right at the front - we''d have a really good view.',1,155445),(8720,177,'是的，虽然我认为如果你坐在后面，你实际上可以更好地听到整个事情。',165520,'Yeah, though I think that if you sit at the back you can actually hear the whole thing better.（Q2）',1,160715),(8721,177,'是的。无论如何，我们可以决定什么时候到达那里。',226040,'Yes. Anyway we can decide when we get there.',1,165525),(8722,177,'那你填表格还是我填？',228950,'So will you fill in the form or shall I?',1,226041),(8723,177,'我会做的。姓名：乔治·奥尼尔。地址：西海北大街 48 号。你还记得我们的新邮政编码吗？还是想不起来。',242260,'I''ll do it. Name: George O''Neill. Address: 48 North Avenue（Q3）, Westsea. Do you remember our new postcode? Still can''t remember it.',1,228956),(8724,177,'等一下——我已经把它写在这里了。 WS6 2 YH。',250960,'Just a minute - I''ve got it written down here. WS6 2YH.（Q4）',1,242267),(8725,177,'你也需要电话吗？',252540,'Do you need the phone too?',1,250963),(8726,177,'是的，需要。我真的不擅长数字。',255480,'Please. I''m really bad at numbers.',1,252543),(8727,177,'01674 553242。所以，让我们为 Guitarrini 预订两张票。',266040,'0167 4 553242（Q5）. So, let''s book two tickets for Guitarrini.',1,255481),(8728,177,'好的。如果你确定 7.50 英镑，每个都可以。你觉得这位歌手怎么样？',271900,'Okay. If you''re sure £7.50 each is all right. How do you feel about the singer?',1,266046),(8729,177,'我还没有完全决定。',273850,'I haven''t quite decided.',1,271906),(8730,177,'但我注意到预订表格上的某些内容可能会说服我！',277520,'But I''ve noticed something on the booking form that might just persuade me!',1,273852),(8731,177,'那是什么？',278920,'What''s that then?',1,277524),(8732,177,'免费茶点！',280180,'Free refreshments!',1,278927),(8733,177,'真的吗？',280820,'Really?',1,280182),(8734,177,'是的，看这里。 6月17日星期日。歌手，门票 6.00 英镑包括花园里的饮料。',289030,'Yes, look here. Sunday 17th of June. Singer, ticket £6.00 includes drinks （Q6）in the garden.',1,280824),(8735,177,'对我来说听起来很划算！',290860,'Sounds like a bargain to me!',1,289033),(8736,177,'是的，让我们为此订两张票。还有什么？我现在感觉很热心！',297920,'Yes, let''s book two tickets for that. So, what else? I''m feeling quite keen now!',1,290861),(8737,177,'6 月 22 日的钢琴家怎么样？',300670,'How about the pianist（Q7） on the 22nd of June?',1,297923),(8738,177,'安娜文图拉？我只记得那是我的夜校之夜。',305320,'Anna Ventura? I''ve just remembered that''s my evening class night.',1,300676),(8739,177,'没关系。我只能自己去——但我们可以一起去西班牙舞蹈和吉他音乐会，不是吗？',312100,'That''s okay. I''ll just have to go on my own - but we can go to the Spanish dance and guitar concert together, can''t we?',1,305321),(8740,177,'是的——我相信汤姆和基兰也会喜欢的。',315100,'Yes- I''m sure Tom and Kieran would enjoy that too.',1,312105),(8741,177,'天哪——10.50英镑一张票！我可以看到我们将不得不在本周剩下的时间里没有食物，我们需要预订四个！',323870,'Good heavens-£10.50（Q8） a ticket! I can see we''re going to have to go without food for the rest of the week we''ll need to book four!（Q9）',1,315104),(8742,177,'希望我们是学生 - 看！儿童、学生和老年人可享受 50% 的折扣。',332450,'Wish we were students - look! Children, Students and Senior Citizens get a 50%（Q10） discount on everything.',1,323873),(8743,177,'要是就好了！',333179,'If only!',1,332455),(8744,178,'您好，感谢您邀请我参加您的教师会议，谈论恐龙博物馆，并告诉您一些关于您可以在那里与您的学生一起做的事情。',57980,'Hello, and thank you for asking me to your teachers'' meeting to talk about the Dinosaur Museum and to tell you a bit about what you can do with your students there.',1,48372),(8745,178,'好吧，让我先给你一些基本信息。关于营业时间，我们每周的每一天都从上午 9 点到晚上 8 点开放，周一下午 1.30 点关闭。',72740,'Well, let me give you some of the basic information first. In regard to opening hours, we''re open every day of the week from 9.00 am to 8.00 pm except on Mondays when we close at 1.30 pm.(Q11)',1,57987),(8746,178,'一年中我们只会在12月25日那一天闭店。',78000,'And, in fact the only day in the year when we''re closed is on the 25th of December.(Q12)',1,72749),(8747,178,'您可以在我们开放的任何时候为您的学校团体预订导游。',83550,'You can book a guided tour for your school group any time that we''re open.',1,78000),(8748,178,'如果您将学校团体带到博物馆，当您到达时，我们会要求您与您的团体一起留在停车场。',91260,'If you bring a school group to the museum, when you arrive we ask you to remain with your group in the car park.(Q13)',1,83557),(8749,178,'一位或多位导游将在那里欢迎您，并向您简要介绍旅行的内容。',98000,'One or more of the tour guides will welcome you there and brief you about what the tour will be about.(Q13)',1,91268),(8750,178,'我们在那里这样做是因为我们的入口很小，而且我们在展区确实没有太多空间供简报小组使用。',106490,'We do this there because our entrance is quite small and we really haven''t got much room for briefing groups in the exhibition area.',1,98000),(8751,178,'就您需要的时间而言，如果您带了一个学校团体，您应该计划至少允许 90 分钟的参观时间。',117050,'As far as the amount of time you''ll need goes, if you bring a school group you should plan on allowing a minimum of 90 minutes for the visit.',1,106499),(8752,178,'这允许上下车 15 分钟，导游 45 分钟和游览后活动 30 分钟。',127600,'This allows 15 minutes to get on and off the coach, 45 minutes(Q14) for the guided tour and 30 minutes for after-tour activities.',1,117050),(8753,178,'如果你要在博物馆吃午饭，当然，你必须留出更多的时间。',133430,'If you''re going to have lunch at the museum you will, of course, have to allow more time.',1,127601),(8754,178,'博物馆内有两个咖啡馆，可容纳80人。',138370,'There are two cafes in the museum, with seating for 80 people.',1,133435),(8755,178,'如果你想在那里吃饭，你需要预订一些座位，因为他们在午餐时间会很拥挤。',145420,'If you want to eat there you''ll need to reserve some seating, as they can get quite crowded at lunch time.',1,138378),(8756,178,'然后在博物馆外面的后面有桌子，学生们可以带着自己的午餐，在那里露天吃。',194550,'Then outside the museum at the back there are tables(Q15), and students can bring their own lunch and eat it there in the open air.',1,145428),(8757,178,'当学生们进入博物馆门厅时，我们要求他们在进入博物馆之前在衣帽间检查他们的书包、书籍、午餐盒等。',205610,'When the students come into the museum foyer we ask them to check in their backpacks with their books, lunch boxes, etc, at the cloakroom before they enter the museum proper.',1,194557),(8758,178,'恐怕过去我们在学校访问后会丢失一些东西，所以这是一个严格的规定。',213320,'I''m afraid in the past we have had a few things gone missing after school visits so this is a strict rule.',1,205615),(8759,178,'此外，有些展品很脆弱，我们不希望它们被意外撞到。',219460,'Also, some of the exhibits are fragile and we don''t want them to be accidentally knocked.',1,213326),(8760,178,'但我们确实为学生提供了带有问题和测验的讲义。',224940,'But we do provide school students with handouts with questions and quizzes on them.(Q16-18)',1,219461),(8761,178,'学生们可以在博物馆里学到很多东西，他们有事可做也很有趣。',230980,'There''s so much that students can learn in the museum and it''s fun for them to have something to do.',1,224940),(8762,178,'当然，他们需要带一些东西来写这些。',235040,'Of course they''ll need to bring something to write with for these.(Q16-18)',1,230988),(8763,178,'我们确实允许学生拍照。',238740,'We do  allow students to take photographs.',1,235046),(8764,178,'对于正在做项目的学生来说，对他们所看到的内容进行某种视觉记录是很有用的，他们可以添加到他们的报告中。',246610,'For students who are doing projects it''s useful to make some kind of visual record of what they see that they can add to their reports.',1,238749),(8765,178,'最后，他们不应该带任何吃的东西进博物馆，或者任何种类的饮料。',254000,'And finally, they should not bring anything to eat into the museum, or drinks of any kind.',1,246612),(8766,178,'参观后学生还可以做一些事情。',259060,'There are also a few things the students can do after the tour.',1,254000),(8767,178,'在一楼的剧院连续放映有关恐龙的短片他们可以随时看到。',268540,'In the theatrette on the ground ''floor there are continuous screenings of short documentaries about dinosaurs which they can see at any time.(Q19&20)',1,259062),(8768,178,'我们以前有一个活动室，里面有更多互动的东西，比如制作恐龙模型和绘画，甚至寻找恐龙蛋，但不幸的是，最近因为一场恶劣的风暴，屋顶进水了，损坏了这个活动室，所以目前这个活动室已经关闭了。',287110,'We used to have an activity room with more interactive things like making models of dinosaurs and drawing and painting pictures, even hunting for dinosaur eggs, but unfortunately the room was damaged in a bad storm recently when water came in the roof, so that''s closed at the moment.',1,268548),(8769,178,'但我们确实有一个 IT 中心，学生可以在那里访问包含一系列恐龙游戏的 CD ROM。',294490,'But we do have an IT centre where students have access to CD ROMs with a range of dinosaur games.(Q19&20)',1,287113),(8770,178,'这些游戏很有趣，但他们也教学生恐龙的生活，他们如何找到食物，保护他们的栖息地，在威胁中幸存下来，诸如此类。',306410,'These games are a lot of fun, but they also teach the students about the lives of dinosaurs, how they found food, protected their habitat, survived threats, that kind of thing.',1,294494),(8771,178,'而且......我想这就是我要告诉你的全部内容。',310110,'And ... I think that''s all I have to tell you.',1,306414),(8772,178,'如果您想了解其他任何问题，请随时提出任何问题...',315190,'Please feel free to ask any questions if you would like to know anything else ...',1,310117),(8773,179,'对了,桑德拉。你想见我是想征求我对你们小组提案的一些意见。',60090,'Right, Sandra. You wanted to see me to get some feedback on your group''s proposal.',1,54713),(8774,179,'你提交给地理学会实地考察比赛的那个。',65110,'The one you''re submitting for the Geography Society field trip competition.',1,60090),(8775,179,'我看过你的提议，我认为这是一个非常好的选择。',69650,'I''ve had a look through your proposal and I think it''s a really good choice.',1,65117),(8776,179,'事实上，我对此只有几句话要说，但即使在这样的大纲文档中，您也必须小心避免在提案中甚至在内容页面中出现拼写错误和布局问题。',85220,'In fact, I only have a few things to say about it, but even in an outline document like this you really have to be careful to avoid typos and problems with layout in the proposal, and even in the contents page.',1,69656),(8777,179,'所以在提交之前仔细阅读，好吗？',88890,'So read it through carefully before submitting it, okay?',1,85228),(8778,179,'我会做的。',89800,'Will do.',1,88894),(8779,179,'我已经对提案进行了一些说明，这些内容本可以更好地排序。',95800,'And I''ve made a few notes on the proposal about things which could have been better sequenced.(Q21)',1,89802),(8780,179,'好的。',97270,'Okay.',1,95808),(8781,179,'至于写作本身，我已经对提案进行了注释，以及我认为可以改进的地方。',103340,'As for the writing itself, I''ve annotated the proposal as and where I thought it could be improved.',1,97274),(8782,179,'一般来说，我觉得你经常为此而使用复杂的结构和长句子，结果呢，即使文章中有分段、副标题,要跟上你的想法还是有点困难。所以把它们剪掉一点，可以吗？',122690,'Generally speaking, I feel you''ve often used complex structures and long sentences for the sake of it and as a consequence ... although your paragraphing and inclusion of sub-headings help ... it''s quite hard to follow your train of thought at times. So cut them down a bit, can you?(Q22)',1,103349),(8783,179,'真的吗？',123390,'Really?',1,122692),(8784,179,'是的。并且不要忘记像编号这样的简单格式。',128030,'Yes. And don''t forget simple formatting like numbering.',1,123390),(8785,179,'我没有使用页码吗？',130270,'Didn''t I use page numbers?',1,128039),(8786,179,'我不是那个意思。看，您已经记得包含页眉和页脚，这很好，但清楚地列出想法很重要。',140190,'I didn''t mean that. Look, you''ve remembered to include headers and footers, which is good, but listing ideas clearly is important.(Q23)',1,130274),(8787,179,'给它们编号或使用要点，这更清楚。',144790,'Number them  or use bullet points, which is even clearer.',1,140190),(8788,179,'然后，您将让读者关注您的主要观点。',148220,'Then you''ll focus the reader on your main points.',1,144799),(8789,179,'我认为你建议去纳瓦霍部落公园是个好主意。',154030,'I thought your suggestion to go to the Navajo Tribal Park was a very good idea.',1,148220),(8790,179,'我一直想去那里。我父亲是牛仔电影和《荒野西部》的忠实爱好者，所以我也看了所有史诗级的电影，其中很多还是在那里拍摄的。',165970,'I''ve always wanted to go there. My father was a great fan of cowboy films  and the Wild West so I was subjected to seeing all the epics, many of which were shot there.(Q24)',1,154032),(8791,179,'因此，它对我来说非常熟悉，它在地理上和视觉上都很棒，所以它是我一直想去的地方。我随后做的研究和网上的照片让我更加热衷。',229450,'As a consequence, it feels very familiar to me and it''s awesome both geographically and visually, so it''s somewhere I''ve always wanted to visit. The subsequent research I did and the online photographs made me even keener.',1,165973),(8792,179,'太棒了。对了，我们现在来看看你提案的内容。',234270,'Interesting. Right, let''s look at the content of your proposal now.',1,229458),(8793,179,'你觉得它足够全面吗？',236650,'Did you find it comprehensive enough?',1,234276),(8794,179,'嗯，是的，也不是。您在内容页面上列出了几个不同的主题，但我不确定它们是否都相关。',245770,'Well, yes and no. You''ve listed several different topics on your contents page, but I''m not sure they''re all relevant.',1,236650),(8795,179,'不？好吧，我认为从实地考察的角度来看，我需要关注的一件事是砂岩高原和悬崖本身。',256670,'No? Well, I thought that from the perspective of a field trip, one thing I needed to focus on was the sandstone plateaux and cliffs themselves.（Q25-27）',1,245779),(8796,179,'他们从平坦的景观中拔地而起的方式令人惊叹。',261210,'The way they tower up from the flat landscape is just amazing.',1,256673),(8797,179,'周围较软的岩石被风雨侵蚀，留下这些巨大的露头高出平原。游客涌入该地区也就不足为奇了。',273460,'The fact that the surrounding softer rocks were eroded by wind and rain, leaving these huge outcrops high above the plain. It''s hardly surprising that tourists flock to see the area.',1,261211),(8798,179,'嗯，是的，我同意包括这些观点......',277090,'Well, yes, I''d agree with including those points ...',1,273468),(8799,179,'还有一个事实，那就是它是美国本土纳瓦霍人的故乡，以及随之而来的所有社会历史。',284240,'And then the fact that it''s been home to native American Navajos and all the social history that goes with that.',1,277096),(8800,179,'他们为了从入侵的定居者手中拯救自己的领土而承受的艰辛。',289840,'The hardships they endured trying to save their territory from the invading settlers.',1,284241),(8801,179,'他们的文化如此丰富——所有这些精彩的故事。',294070,'Their culture is so rich - all those wonderful stories.',1,289847),(8802,179,'嗯，我同意这很有趣，但它与你的提案没有直接关系，Sandra，所以在这个阶段，我建议你关注其他考虑因素。',305280,'Well, I agree it''s interesting, but it''s not immediately relevant to your proposal, Sandra, so at this stage, I suggest you focus on other considerations.',1,294071),(8803,179,'我认为关于学生在旅途中实际可以做什么的指示应该更加重要，因此当然需要包括在内并加以扩展。',317200,'l''think an indication of what the students on the trip could actually do when they get there should be far more central, so that certainly needs to be included and to be expanded upon.（Q25-27）',1,305281),(8804,179,'我想看看当地野生动物及植物的一些情况，可并没有我想像的那样多。大概是因为游客的入侵帮了倒忙。',328720,'And I''d like to see something about the local wildlife, and vegetation too, not that I imagine there''s much to see. Presumably the tourist invasion hasn''t helped.',1,317203),(8805,179,'好的，我也会在这两个领域做一些工作。但你是对的，除了一些非常浅根的物种外，没有太多的东西。',339150,'Okay, I''ll do some work on those two areas as well. But you''re right, there''s not much apart from some very shallow-rooted species.',1,328729),(8806,179,'虽然那里冬天寒冷多雪，但大地在夏天的阳光下被烤得那么硬，雨水无法渗透。',347840,'Although it''s cold and snowy there in the winter, the earth is baked so hard in the summer sun that rainwater can''t penetrate.',1,339151),(8807,179,'所以这是洪水或干旱的情况，真的。',350560,'So it''s a case of flood or drought, really.',1,347846),(8808,179,'所以，我明白了。现在，在我们更详细地了解所有内容之前，我有几个事实性问题要问你。',359600,'So, I understand. Now, before we look at everything in more detail, I''ve got a few factual questions for you.',1,350560),(8809,179,'将答案包含在您完成的提案中是个好主意，因为您的草稿中缺少它们。',366660,'It would be a good idea to include the answers in your finished proposal, because they''re missing from your draft.',1,359600),(8810,179,'好的。',367690,'Fine.',1,366666),(8811,179,'所以，你提到了巨石和尖顶，这很好，但是部落公园覆盖了哪些区域？你知道吗？',376460,'So, you mentioned the monoliths and the spires, which was good, but what area does the tribal park cover? Do you know?',1,367692),(8812,179,'12000公顷，平原海拔约5850米。',385580,'12,000 hectares, and the plain is at about 5,850 metres above sea level.（Q28）',1,376463),(8813,179,'比我预期的要大。好的。最近的住宿地点在哪里？',390960,'Larger than I expected. Okay. Where''s the nearest accommodation?',1,385582),(8814,179,'这是您没有包括的实用细节。',394420,'That''s a practical detail that you haven''t included.',1,390965),(8815,179,'你有没有做过这方面的研究？',396000,'Have you done any research on that?',1,394426),(8816,179,'是的。公园本身无处可住，但附近有一个名为古尔丁的旧贸易站。',404900,'Yes. There''s nowhere to stay in the park itself, but there''s an old trading post called Goulding quite near.',1,396000),(8817,179,'各种旅游也从古尔丁开始。',408000,'All kinds of tours start from Goulding, too.',1,404904),(8818,179,'什么样的旅行团？',409730,'What kind of tours?',1,408000),(8819,179,'嗯，最受欢迎的是四轮驱动吉普车——但我不建议雇佣那些。',417000,'Well, the most popular are in four-wheel drive jeeps - but I wouldn''t recommend hiring those.',1,409737),(8820,179,'我认为欣赏该地区的最佳方式是租用马匹并在这些马匹上跋涉。',425550,'I think the best way to appreciate the area would be to hire horses instead and trek around on those.（Q29）',1,417009),(8821,179,'不允许骑自行车，也不能乘坐私家车在该地区开车。',431810,'Biking is not allowed and it''s impossible to drive around the area in private vehicles.',1,425558),(8822,179,'轨道太粗糙了。',434420,'The tracks are too rough.',1,431810),(8823,179,'好的，最后，还有什么值得一游的地方？',438690,'Okay, lastly, what else is worth visiting there?',1,434422),(8824,179,'有几个洞穴，但我没有研究任何细节。我会了解他们的。',445700,'There are several caves, but I haven''t looked into any details. I''ll find out about them.（Q30）',1,438696),(8825,179,'好的。现在我想知道的是...',450110,'Okay, good. Now what I''d like to know is ...',1,445701),(8826,180,'所以，欢迎来到你的地理介绍讲座。',73960,'So, welcome to your introductory geography lecture.',1,70000),(8827,180,'我们将从一些基础知识开始。',75870,'We''ll begin with some basics.',1,73968),(8828,180,'首先，我们通过学习地理学到了什么？',79800,'Firstly, what do we learn by studying geography?',1,75876),(8829,180,'好吧，我们对所有已经影响并继续影响地球表面的过程有了很多了解。',88150,'Well, we learn a great deal about all the processes that have affected and that continue to affect the earth''s surface.（Q31）',1,79804),(8830,180,'但我们学到的远不止这些，因为学习地理还可以让我们了解特定环境与居住在那里的人们之间发展起来的不同类型的关系。',100000,'But we learn far more than that, because studying geography also informs us about the different kinds of relationships that develop between a particular environment and the people that live there.（Q32）',1,88156),(8831,180,'好的。',101180,'Okay.',1,100001),(8832,180,'我们喜欢将地理视为有两个主要分支。',105140,'We like to think of geography as having two main branches.',1,101182),(8833,180,'研究我们星球的性质——它的物理特征，它的实际外观——然后研究我们选择的生活方式以及这些方式对我们星球的影响。',117960,'There''s the study of the nature of our planet - its physical features, what it actually looks like - and then there''s the study of the ways in which we choose to live and of the impact of those on our planet.（Q33）',1,105146),(8834,180,'我们目前使用的碳燃料就是一个很好的例子。',122310,'Our  current use of carbon fuels is a good example of that.',1,117965),(8835,180,'但也有更具体的学习领域需要考虑，我们将在本学期依次研究这些领域。',130000,'But there are more specific study areas to consider too, and we''ll be looking at each of these in turn throughout this semester.',1,122317),(8836,180,'这些包括生物物理地理学，我指的是对自然环境及其所有生物的研究。',137730,'These include bio-physical geography, by which I mean the study of the natural environment and all its living things.',1,130001),(8837,180,'然后是地形——着眼于陆地和海洋的形状。',143090,'Then there''s topography - that looks at the shapes of the land and oceans.',1,137731),(8838,180,'当然，还有政治地理学和社会地理学的研究，这是对人的社区的研究。',150860,'There''s the study of political geography and social geography too, of course, which is the study of communities of people.',1,143095),(8839,180,'我们有经济地理学——我们在其中研究各种资源及其使用——例如农业。',159220,'We have economic geography - in which we examine all kinds of resources and their use -agriculture, for example.',1,150864),(8840,180,'接下来是历史地理学——理解人们和他们的环境以及他们的互动方式在一段时间内发生了怎样的变化——以及城市地理学，这是我特别感兴趣的一个方面，并将其作为它的一部分。重点关注城市的位置，这些城市提供的服务，以及这些城市的人口流动。',184640,'Next comes historical geography - the understanding of how people and their environments and the ways they interact have changed over a period of time - and urban geography, an aspect I''m particularly interested in, which takes as its focus the location of cities, the services that those cities provide, and migration of people to and from such cities.（Q34）',1,159222),(8841,180,'最后，我们有制图。',188000,'And lastly, we have cartography.',1,184645),(8842,180,'这就是地图制作的艺术和科学。',190880,'That''s the art and science of map-making.',1,188001),(8843,180,'你会做很多这样的事情！因此，在继续之前总结一下，我们现在有了关键答案。',199360,'You''ll be doing a lot of that!  So, to summarise before we continue, we now have our key answer...',1,190883),(8844,180,'“学习这门学科很重要，因为如果没有地理知识，我们对周围环境的了解就很少，我们将无法识别与它们相关的所有问题。”',212160,'studying this subject is important because without geographical knowledge, we would know very little\r\nabout our surroundings and we wouldn''t be able to identify all the problems （Q35）that relate to them.',1,199361),(8845,180,'因此，很显然，我们也就无法处在一个见多识广的状态去解决那些问题。',222960,'So, by definition, we wouldn''t be in an informed position to work out how to solve any of them.',1,212162),(8846,180,'好的，现在介绍一些实用性。',226000,'Okay, now for some practicalities.',1,222967),(8847,180,'“地理学家实际上是做什么的？嗯，我们从收集数据开始！在你的第一次实地考察中，你会做很多这样的事情！我们如何做到这一点？有几种方法。”',238630,'What do geographers actually do? Well, we collect data to begin with! You''ll be doing a lot of that on your first field trip! How do we do this? There \nare several means.',1,226001),(8848,180,'例如，我们可能会在一个特定区域内进行人口统计。',245170,'We might, for example, conduct a census-count a population in a given area perhaps.',1,238633),(8849,180,'“我们还需要地球表面的图像，我们可以通过借助计算机生成技术或借助卫星中继。”',254740,'We also need images（Q36） of the earth''s surface which we can produce by means of computer-generation technology or with the help of satellite relays.',1,245174),(8850,180,'“从早期的航海探索世界开始，我们已经取得了长足的进步，当时地理学家只有笔和纸可供使用。”',264820,'We''ve come a very long way from the early exploration of the world by sailing ships when geographers \r\nonly had pens and paper at their disposal.',1,254743),(8851,180,'在我们收集了我们的信息之后，我们必须对其进行分析！ 我们需要寻找模式，最常见的是因果模式。',275000,'After we''ve gathered our information, we must analyse it! We need to look for patterns（Q37）, most commonly those of causes and consequences.',1,264827),(8852,180,'“这种信息有助于我们预测和解决可能影响我们生活的世界的问题。”',281370,'This kind of information helps us to \npredict and resolve problems that could affect the world we live in.',1,275009),(8853,180,'但我们不会对所有这些信息保密。',284710,'But we don''t keep all this information confidential.',1,281379),(8854,180,'然后，我们需要发布我们的发现，以便其他人可以访问它并了解它。',291230,'We then need to publish our findings so that other people can access it and be informed by it.',1,284710),(8855,180,'“发布这些信息的一种方式是地图的形式。”',296810,'And one way in which this information \ncan be published is in the form of maps.',1,291231),(8856,180,'你们都已经在生活的某个阶段使用过一个。',300440,'You''ll all have used one at some stage of your life already.',1,296811),(8857,180,'让我们从地理学家的角度考虑地图的好处。',305170,'Let''s consider the benefits of maps from a geographer''s perspective.',1,300441),(8858,180,'地图可以折叠并放在口袋里，当它们被收集到地图集中时可以提供很好的参考。',312910,'Maps can be folded and put in a pocket and can provide a great store of reference when they''re collected into an atlas.',1,305178),(8859,180,'如有必要，它们可以描绘整个星球的物理特征，或者更详细地描绘其中的一小部分。',321070,'They can depict the physical features of the entire planet if necessary, or, just a small part of it in much greater detail.',1,312917),(8860,180,'但是有一个缺点。',323000,'But there is a drawback.',1,321079),(8861,180,'你不能在一张平面纸上精确地复制三维的东西，比如我们的星球，因为纸只有二维，这意味着地图上总会有一定程度的扭曲。',337060,'You can''t exactly replicate something that is three-dimensional, like our planet, on a flat piece of paper, because paper has only two dimensions, and that means there''ll always be a certain degree of distortion（Q38） on a map.',1,323002),(8862,180,'这是无法避免的。',339180,'It can''t be avoided.',1,337069),(8863,180,'我们也可以使用航拍照片。',342180,'We can also use aerial photographs...',1,339181),(8864,180,'照相机在地球上空拍摄的照片。',346490,'pictures taken by cameras at high altitude above the earth.',1,342182),(8865,180,'这些非常适合显示从地面不易看到的各种地理特征。',353010,'These are great for showing all kinds of geographical features that are not easy to see from the ground.',1,346497),(8866,180,'例如，您可以轻松地说明患病树木的区域或特定时间道路上的交通量或有关深海床的信息。',364000,'You can easily illustrate areas of diseased trees or how much traffic（Q39） is on the roads at a given time or information about deep sea beds, for example.',1,353017),(8867,180,'然后是陆地卫星。',366000,'Then there are Landsats.',1,364001),(8868,180,'这些卫星环绕地球，并将视觉信息传输到接收站的计算机。',373260,'These are satellites that circle the earth and t