371,192,'最近的画作展示了静态姿势的人。',120000,'The more recent paintings show people in static poses.',1,115641),(9372,192,'但是，在 8000 多年前，第一批主导岩画的人类图像充满了动感。',127140,'But the first human images to dominate rock art paintings, over 8,000 years ago, were full of movement.',1,120001),(9373,192,'这些画展示了人们狩猎和烹饪食物，因此他们被命名为“动态”以反映这种能量。',135000,'These paintings showed people hunting and cooking food and so they were given the name ''Dynamic'' to reflect this energy.',1,127146),(9374,192,'考虑到它们被涂成如此简单的棒状形式，这真是太神奇了。',140000,'It''s quite amazing considering they were painted in such a simple stick-like form.',1,135001),(9375,192,'在“甘薯”石画时期，线形画开始向更加自然的形态转变。',145900,'In the Yam period, there was a movement away from stick figures to a more naturalistic shape.',1,140001),(9376,192,'然而，它们并没有达到现代风格，即所谓的“X 射线”，因为它实际上是动物和人类的内部骨骼以及器官的特征。',157090,'However, they didn''t go as far as the Modern style, which is known as ''x-ray'' because it actually makes a feature of the internal skeleton as well as the organs of animals and humans.（Q31)',1,145901),(9377,192,'山药的绘画风格得名于它具有许多曲线形状，实际上类似于称为山药的蔬菜，类似于红薯。',168290,'The Yam style of painting got its name from the fact that it featured much curvier figures that actually resemble the vegetable called a yam, which is similar to a sweet potato.（Q32)',1,157091),(9378,192,'现代绘画很有趣，因为它们包括与欧洲定居者第一次接触时的绘画。',175290,'The Modern paintings are interesting because they include paintings at the time of the first contact with European settlers.（Q33)',1,168291),(9379,192,'土著人通过简单地画出没有手的欧洲人来表达移民服装的概念，这表明他们站着的时候手插在口袋里的习惯!',186690,'Aborigines managed to convey the idea of the settlers'' clothing by simply painting the Europeans without any hands, indicating the habit of standing with their hands in their pockets!',1,175296),(9380,192,'尺寸是另一个特征。',189200,'Size is another characteristic.',1,186699),(9381,192,'最近的图像往往是真人大小甚至更大，但动态人物被画成缩影。',197440,'The more recent images tend to be life size or even larger, but the Dynamic figures are painted in miniature.（Q34)',1,189209),(9382,192,'原住民岩画还记录了数千年来发生的环境变化。',203510,'Aboriginal rock art also records the environmental changes that occurred over thousands of years.',1,197447),(9383,192,'例如，我们从动态画中知道，8000多年前，原住民很少吃鱼，此时海平面要低得多。',214290,'For example, we know from the Dynamic paintings that over 8,000 years ago, Aborigines would have rarely eaten fish and sea levels were much lower at this time.',1,203511),(9384,192,'事实上，鱼直到亚姆时期才开始出现在绘画中，还有贝壳和其他海洋图像。',223000,'In fact, fish didn''t start to appear in paintings until the Yam period along with shells and other marine images.（Q35)',1,214297),(9385,192,'山药传统的绘画也表明，在此期间，原住民远离动物作为他们的主要食物来源，并开始在他们的饮食中加入蔬菜，因为这些特征很突出。',236810,'The paintings of the Yam tradition also suggest that, during this time, the Aborigines moved away from animals as their main food source and began including vegetables in their diet, as these feature prominently.（Q36)',1,223001),(9386,192,'直到 4000 年前的现代时期，淡水生物才出现在画作中。',247790,'Freshwater creatures didn''t appear in the paintings until the Modern period from 4,000 years ago.',1,236811),(9387,192,'所以，这些画已经教会了我们很多。但一直让我们感兴趣的一幅图像被称为“彩虹蛇”。',256580,'So, these paintings have already taught us a lot. But one image that has always intrigued us is known as the ''Rainbow Serpent''.',1,247792),(9388,192,'彩虹蛇是我近期研究项目的焦点，它因其蛇形的身躯而得名，并于4000至6000年前首次出现在“甘薯”时期。',269000,'The Rainbow Serpent, which is the focus of my most recent project, gets its name from its snake or serpent-like body and it first appeared in the Yam period 4 to 6,000 years ago.',1,256583),(9389,192,'许多人认为这是袋鼠、蛇和鳄鱼的奇妙混合物。',274000,'Many believe it is a curious mixture of kangaroo, snake and crocodile.',1,269001),(9390,192,'但我们决定研究彩虹蛇的画作，看看我们能否找到第一批画家所依据的动物。',283170,'But we decided to study the Rainbow Serpent paintings to see if we could locate the animal that the very first painters based their image on.（Q37)',1,274001),(9391,192,'“甘薯”石画时期，恰好是最后一个冰河时代的结束。',287580,'The Yam period coincided with the end of the last ice age.',1,283172),(9392,192,'这带来了环境的巨大变化，海平面上升并稳步向内陆蔓延。',294610,'This brought 