9414),(9462,194,'我们已经升级了所有这些西班牙地点，并大大提高了它们最初的三星级评级。',144840,'We''ve upgraded all these Spanish sites, and improved them considerably from their original three-star rating.',1,137241),(9463,194,'我们相信我们的假期为全家人提供一流的设施。',149850,'We believe our holidays offer superb facilities for the whole family.',1,144846),(9464,194,'希望孩子在一天中的全部或部分时间全神贯注的父母可以利用我们孩子的活动。',159120,'Parents who want their children to be fully occupied for all or part of the day can take advantage of our children''s activities.',1,149855),(9465,194,'这些活动由我们高素质和热情的员工组织。',164060,'These are organised by our well-qualified and enthusiastic staff.',1,159126),(9466,194,'每天都以一场体育比赛开始，也许是足球或排球，然后是为每个人准备一小时的戏剧。',172500,'Each day kicks off with a sports match, perhaps football, or volleyball, followed by an hour of drama（Q13) for everyone.',1,164065),(9467,194,'这可能包括唱歌或跳舞、哑剧或其他活动。',178270,'This may include singing or dancing, mime or other activities.',1,172500),(9468,194,'下午，一周中的每一天都有不同的艺术活动，包括海报比赛或模型制作。',187620,'ln the afternoon,there''s a different art activity for each day of the week including a poster competition or model making.',1,178276),(9469,194,'更重要的是，我们的场地是真正的儿童友好型，考虑到这一点，我们在晚上实行无噪音规则。',197530,'What''s more, our sites are truly child-friendly, and, with this in mind, we operate a no-noise rule in the evenings.',1,187623),(9470,194,'儿童晚间活动通常在9点30分结束，偶尔也会在10点结束，从10点30分开始，度假者应该在有帐篷的地方保持安静。',210670,'Children''s evening activities usually finish at 9.30, or occasionally 10, and from 10.30 holiday-makers are expected to be quiet（Q14) in the areas where there are tents.',1,197532),(9471,194,'我们希望 PS Camping 假期不会出现任何问题，但如果出现问题，我们也希望所有客户都获得保险。',220020,'We want nothing to go wrong on a PS Camping holiday, but if it does, we also want all customers to be insured.',1,210679),(9472,194,'如果您没有自己制定年度保险单，则需要购买我们提供的低成本保险，并且我们要求您在预订假期时进行安排。',231800,'If you haven''t organised an annual insurance policy of your own you''ll need to take out the low-cost cover we offer and we require that you arrange this when you make your holiday reservation.（Q15)',1,220026),(9473,194,'选择 PS Camping 并将其推荐给其他人有很多好处。',237910,'There are many advantages to choosing PS Camping, and to recommending it to others.',1,231805),(9474,194,'作为常客，您将随时了解特别优惠，您的朋友可以享受假期 10% 的折扣，或者以标准帐篷的价格预订豪华帐篷。',250000,'As a regular customer, you''ll be kept informed of special offers, and your friends can benefit from ten per cent off their holiday, or book a luxury tent for the price of a standard one.',1,237917),(9475,194,'作为回报，我们将向您发送一份感谢礼物，您可以从一系列优质商品中进行选择。',293950,'In return, we''ll send you a thank-you present（Q16), which you can choose from a list of high-quality items.',1,250000),(9476,194,'当谈到我们的帐篷时，这些帐篷都配备了最高标准。',298810,'When it comes to our tents, these are equipped to the highest standard.',1,293950),(9477,194,'我们确实考虑到了每一个基本细节，从以瓶装煤气为燃料的烤箱和烹饪圈，到卧室区域的镜子。',308840,'We really do think of every essential detail, from an oven and cooking rings fuelled by bottled gas, to mirrors in the bedroom areas.',1,298814),(9478,194,'如果你不想在室内做饭，你可以在提前要求的情况下借一个烧烤炉，帐篷外甚至还有一条野餐毯可以坐在上面。',320410,'If you don''t want to cook indoors, you can borrow a barbecue if you ask（Q17) in advance for one to be made available, and there''s even a picnic blanket to sit on outside your tent.',1,308845),(9479,194,'在里面，可以找到一盒游戏和玩具，如果需要，可以租用儿童帐篷。',328010,'Inside, a box of games and toys can be found（Q18), and children''s tents can be hired if required.',1,320419),(9480,194,'所有帐篷都有冰箱，例如，如果您想在海滩上度过一天，请索要一个专门设计的 PS Camping 冷藏箱，它可以让您的食物和饮料保持冷藏。',340550,'All tents have a fridge, and if you want to spend the day on the beach, for example, ask for a specially designed PS Camping cool box,（Q19) which will keep your food and drinks chilled.',1,328018),(9481,194,'我们所有的站点都有一流的洗涤设施，中央区域配有洗衣机和晾衣绳，还有拖把和水桶，以防您的帐篷在入住期间需要清洁。',353240,'There are excellent washing facilities at all our sites, with washing machines and clothes lines in the central areas, along with mops and buckets（Q20) in case your tent needs cleaning during your stay.',1,340557),(9482,194,'所有网站都有咖啡馆和或商店，供那些宁愿“在里面吃饭”也不愿在当地餐馆用餐的人使用。',360682,'All sites have a cafe and or a shop for those who''d rather ''eat in'' than dine at a local restaurant.',1,353248),(9483,195,'好吧，你们都在研究公司和工作场所中管理个人的不同风格。',52250,'Well, you''ve both been looking at different styles of managing individuals in companies and the workplace.',1,44343),(9484,195,'菲利普，研究进展如何？',54170,'How''s the research going, Philip?',1,52254),(9485,195,'好吧，我一直在研究为什么个人主义，我的意思是个体差异，是管理研究中如此重要的一个领域。',63310,'Well, I''ve been looking at why individualism, I mean individual differences, are such an important area of management studies.',1,54173),(9486,195,'当你想到任何组织，无论是家族企业还是跨国公司，他们基本上都是一群人在一起工作。',73580,'When you think about any organization, be it a family business or a multinational company, they are all fundamentally a group of people working together.',1,63312),(9487,195,'但正是这些人为他们的工作场所做出的贡献让你意识到他们的重要性。',79100,'But it''s what these individuals contribute to their places of work that makes you realize how important they are.',1,73581),(9488,195,'当然，他们带来了不同的想法，但也带来了他们的态度和学习经验。',85410,'Of course they bring different ideas, but it''s also their attitudes（Q21) and their experiences of learning.',1,79109),(9489,195,'多样性在这些领域也很重要。',88130,'Diversity is important in these areas too.',1,85411),(9490,195,'那么，为什么人们在工作中表现得如此不同呢？',93210,'So why do people behave so differently from one another at work?',1,88135),(9491,195,'有很多原因，但研究表明，很多原因归结为个性。另一个因素是性别。',101690,'There are lots of reasons but research has shown a lot of it comes down to personality. And the other factor is gender.（Q22)',1,93213),(9492,195,'众所周知，男人和女人做很多事情的方式不同，工作场所也不例外。',108800,'It''s a well known fact that men and women do lots of things in different ways, and the workplace is no different.',1,101695),(9493,195,'您是否查看过这种变化对公司的影响？',112300,'Did you look at the effects of this variation on companies?',1,108804),(9494,195,'是的，我做了。从积极的方面来说，接触这种多样性有助于鼓励创造力，而创造力通常是公司的资产。',121660,'Yes, I did. On the positive side, exposure to such diversity helps encourage creativity（Q23) which is generally an asset to a company.',1,112302),(9495,195,'但不幸的是，个体差异也是员工之间冲突的根源，它们可能导致管理困难，有时可能很严重。',195000,'But unfortunately individual differences are also the root of conflict between staff and they can lead to difficulties for management, which can sometimes be serious.',1,121667),(9496,195,'谢谢，菲利普。所以现在我想这里要记住的两件主要事情是识别个人才能，然后利用它。',205000,'Thanks, Philip. So now I guess the two main things to remember here are to identify individual talent and then to utilize it.',1,195001),(9497,195,'所以，珍妮丝，你在寻找员工身上不同的才能吗？',210000,'So Janice, you were looking at identifying different talents in workers.',1,205001),(9498,195,'你认为这对管理者来说容易吗？',213310,'Do you think this is easy for managers to do?',1,210001),(9499,195,'嗯，目前团队合作在工作场所很流行，在我看来，个人的重要性通常被忽视了。',222560,'Well, currently teamwork is in fashion in the workplace and in my opinion the importance of the individual is generally neglected.',1,213311),(9500,195,'管理者的目标应该是那些能够在某种情况下发挥带头作用并且不惧怕承担责任的员工。',232270,'What managers should be targeting is those employees who can take the lead in a situation（Q24) and are not afraid to accept the idea of responsibility.',1,222562),(9501,195,'Janice 确实如此，但不幸的是，许多经理认为在员工中鼓励个性的整个概念太难了。',242280,'That''s true Janice but unfortunately many managers think the entire notion of encouraging individuality amongst their staff is far too hard.',1,232275),(9502,195,'是的，这可能是真的，但我认为管理者最重要的任务之一是一方面考虑个人的需求，另一方面考虑团队合作和一致性。',255560,'Yes, that may be true but I think one of the most important tasks of managers is to consider the needs of the individual on one hand and  group co-operation and conformity on the other.（Q25)',1,242289),(9503,195,'它需要管理层的创造性思维来避免矛盾。',260000,'It requires creative thinking on the part of management to avoid tension.',1,255564),(9504,195,'那么珍妮丝，你认为公司应该寻找什么样的人？',265000,'So Janice, what kind of people do you think companies should be looking for?',1,260001),(9505,195,'嗯，它必须从公司寻找新员工的一开始就开始。',271120,'Well, it has to start from the very beginning when companies are looking for new employees.',1,265001),(9506,195,'当人事部门在申请人之间进行选择时，他们需要寻找打破常规并能独立思考的人。',280630,'When the personnel department is choosing between applicants they need to look for someone who''s broken the mould and can think for themselves.（Q26)',1,271128),(9507,195,'相反，做出这些决定的人通常会使用一系列心理测试来确定一个人是否能够解决问题，或者是否会按照他们的指示行事。',291690,'Instead, people making these decisions often use a range of psychological tests to see if a person is a problem solver, or will do as they''re told.',1,280633),(9508,195,'我不相信这些品质实际上是最重要的。',295710,'I''m not convinced these qualities are actually the most important.',1,291699),(9509,195,'那么你认为成为一名优秀的团队合作者被高估了吗？',300000,'So do you think being a good team player is overrated?',1,295718),(9510,195,'不，它没有被高估。您确实需要学习规则并快速学习它们。',306070,'No, it''s not overrated. You do need to learn the rules and learn them fast.',1,300001),(9511,195,'如果您在组织中工作，任何人都无法解决这个问题。',310000,'No individual can get around this if you''re working in an organization.',1,306072),(9512,195,'那么管理者应该如何应对呢？',313590,'So how should managers deal with this?',1,310001),(9513,195,'奖励。当个人表现出组织期望的行为时，可以给予某种激励。',322460,'Rewards. When an individual demonstrates the behaviour the organisation expects, some kind of incentive can be given.',1,313599),(9514,195,'这里重要的是，这发生在刚开始时，因此新员工立即了解系统规则。',330000,'What''s important here is that this happens right at the beginning（Q27) so new recruits learn the rules of the system immediately.',1,322465),(9515,195,'此外，激励应该是个人真正想要的东西，而这并不总是只是金钱。',337770,'Also the incentive should be something the individual actually wants, and this isn''t always just money.',1,330001),(9516,195,'回到你这里，菲利普。你刚才说，对表现好的人的认可是至关重要的。',344460,'To come back to you, Philip. You were saying that recognition of good performers is essential.',1,337772),(9517,195,'管理者还应该寻找什么？',347460,'What else should managers be looking for?',1,344469),(9518,195,'嗯，管理人员意味着您不仅要了解您的员工，还要了解组织的文化。',356780,'Well, managing people means you not only have an understanding of your employees, but you also recognise the culture of the organization.（Q28)',1,347467),(9519,195,'事实上，对于一些组织来说，创造力和个性可能是他们在工作时间最不想看到的东西！',364210,'In fact, for some organizations creativity and individuality may be the last thing they want to see during working hours!',1,356781),(9520,195,'非常真实。',365350,'Very true.',1,364211),(9521,195,'是的，但管理人员并不像看起来那么容易。',369120,'Yes, but managing people isn''t as easy as it looks.',1,365359),(9522,195,'例如，工作场所的变化可能非常棘手，尤其是在需要增加利润的情况下。',376130,'For example, change in the workplace can be quite tricky, especially if there''s a need to increase profit.',1,369122),(9523,195,'在这种时候，这些经理可能不得不优先考虑利润而不是员工的个人需求。',384490,'And at times like these managers may have to give priority to profit rather than individual staff needs.（Q29)',1,376139),(9524,195,'是的，这给人们带来了困难。',387660,'Yes, and that creates difficult situations for people.',1,384495),(9525,195,'是的，但重要的是管理者能够应对相当高的个人压力。',395000,'Yes but what''s important is that managers are able to deal with quite high levels of personal stress.',1,387667),(9526,195,'在变革时期，他们不仅应该考虑员工的压力，还应该花时间考虑自己。',402720,'During times of change they should be thinking not only about the strain on their staff but take time out to  think of themselves.（Q30)',1,395001),(9527,195,'当然了。那么这对...有什么影响？',407712,'Absolutely. So what are the implications of that for ...',1,402721),(9528,196,'大家下午好！',63000,'Good afternoon, everyone!',1,61643),(9529,196,'这是为我们在纳米比亚的考古实地工作做准备的第一次研讨会；我们非常幸运地从我们研究所获得了这次旅行的部分研究资金，所以我期待你们所有人 200% 的关注和参与。',80000,'This is the first seminar in preparation for our archaeological fieldwork in Namibia; we are fantastically lucky to have received partial research funding for this trip from our Institute, so I shall expect 200% attention and participation from you all.',1,63005),(9530,196,'在本次研讨会中，我将首先简要介绍当代岩画艺术研究，在第二部分中，我将为您介绍我们四月份的实地考察之旅的一些注意事项 - 所以请认真听小心。',95530,'First in this seminar, I''m going to give a brief introduction to contemporary research on rock art, and in the second part I''m going to give you some do''s and don''ts for our fieldwork trip in April（Q31) - so please listen very carefully.',1,80001),(9531,196,'我将首先关注纳米比亚岩画的诠释。',100860,'I''m first going to focus on the interpretation of rock art in Namibia.',1,95535),(9532,196,'我们很幸运能够前往一个可以找到世界上一些最重要遗址的地区。',107540,'We are very fortunate to be going to an area where you can find some of the most important sites in the entire world.',1,100866),(9533,196,'我希望向你展示每个人在看待与我们自己不同的文化时都很容易犯错误——这是我们必须学习的第一课，也是最重要的一课。',117250,'And I hope to show you how easy it is for everyone to make mistakes in looking at cultures which are different from our own - the first and most important lesson we have to learn.',1,107543),(9534,196,'在纳米比亚，既有绘画也有雕刻——那是岩石表面被切掉的地方。',124230,'In Namibia there are both paintings and engravings - that''s where the surface of the rock is cut out.',1,117255),(9535,196,'许多版画展示了动物的脚印，大多数学者过去认为这些的目的很简单，很明显：这种岩石艺术就像一本带有图片的教科书，教孩子们关于足迹的知识：哪条足迹属于哪种动物——长颈鹿、狮子等等。',142080,'Many of the engravings show footprints of animals and most scholars used to think\nthat the purpose of these was simple and obvious: this rock art was like a school book with pictures to teach children about tracks: which track belonged to which animal - giraffe, lion and so on.（Q32)',1,124235),(9536,196,'但也有一些谜团。',144200,'But there were some mysteries.',1,142081),(9537,196,'首先，当你看一幅典型的纳米比亚绘画或版画时，你会看到足迹是重复的，同一种动物有几十个足迹。',153610,'First, when you look at a typical Namibian painting or engraving, you see the tracks are repeated, there are dozens of tracks for the same animal.（Q33)',1,144204),(9538,196,'如果目的是教追踪的话，你希望用一个清晰的图例。',160000,'You''d expect just one clear illustration if the reason - the aim - was to teach tracking.',1,153613),(9539,196,'现在还有两个问题。',163020,'Now there were two more problems.',1,160001),(9540,196,'为什么有些动物的雕刻像你所期望的那样非常准确——所有这些都清晰可辨——而另一些则完全不切实际？另一个谜团——其中一些不切实际的动物——在版画中——似乎是半人型的。',180420,'Why are some of the engravings of animals very accurate as you''d expect - all clearly identifiable - and others quite unrealistic?\nAnd another mystery - some of these unrealistic animals - that''s in the engravings - seem to be half human.（Q34)',1,163021),(9541,196,'例如，有些版画中有人脸的样子。',183860,'Some, for example, have got human faces.',1,180421),(9542,196,'许多研究人员现在认为这些是智者为自己雕刻的照片。',189480,'Many researchers now think that these were pictures the wise men engraved of themselves.',1,183861),(9543,196,'他们相信他们可以使用魔法来控制他们绘制的动物，这样猎人就可以捕捉它们作为食物。',196770,'They believed they could use magic to control the animals they had drawn, so the hunters could then catch them for food.（Q35)',1,189489),(9544,196,'这向你展示了从一种文化到另一种文化的一些危险，因为我们将在没有完全理解的情况下做。',205000,'This shows you some of the dangers of coming from one culture to another, as we''ll be\ndoing, without understanding it fully.',1,196773),(9545,196,'学者们想象孩子们看岩石艺术图片来学习追踪——只是因为他们自己已经从图片中学到了技能； 许多研究人员现在认为，岩石艺术的目的要复杂得多。',217410,'Scholars imagined that children looked at rock art pictures to learn to track -just because they themselves had learnt skills from pictures; many researchers now believe that rock art had a much more complex purpose.',1,205001),(9546,196,'我们将在下周详细讨论它！',225000,'And we''ll talk more about it next week!',1,217411),(9547,196,'现在，在我邀请您参加研讨会第二部分的讨论之前，我想就我们的实地考察提出一些非常重要的观点——事实上，任何考察岩石艺术的实地考察。',235960,'Now before I invite you to Join in a discussion in this second part of the seminar, I''d like to make some very important points about our fieldwork - and in fact any field trip to look at rock art.',1,225001),(9548,196,'我们要去很多地方，我们不会一直在一起。',241120,'We''re going to a number of sites, and we won''t always be together.',1,235965),(9549,196,'管理遗址的人面临的最大问题是——是的，我相信你已经猜到了——访问者造成的损害，尽管这通常是无意的。',251740,'The single largest problem faced by people who manage the sites is - yes, I''m sure you''ve guessed - damage caused by visitors, even though it''s usually unintentional.',1,241124),(9550,196,'每当你去一个地方，不要忘记的是，你可以从远处的观察中学习到很多东西，而不是走遍整个地方。',260000,'Whenever you do go to a site, don''t forget you can learn many things from observing at a distance instead of walking all over it.（Q36)',1,251747),(9551,196,'这确实有助于减轻游客的压力。',263510,'This can really help to reduce visitor pressure.',1,260001),(9552,196,'“好吧，我们两个人，这辈子可能就只来这个地方一次”，但也许有成千上万的人在说同样的话。',272510,'People often say, ''Well, there''s only two of us and just this one time'', but maybe thousands of people are saying the same thing.',1,263511),(9553,196,'“然后是一些指导你的基本规则——我们将在村庄附近建立自己的营地，但是如果你自己去，请记住永远不要在场地上露营。”',282630,'And then some basic rules to guide you - we''ll have our own camp near a village, but\nremember never to camp on a site if you go on your own.',1,272514),(9554,196,'这可能是对那种文化的人的不尊重，当然不要生火，不管它看起来多么浪漫。',290000,'It may be disrespectful to the people of that culture（Q37), and certainly don''t make fires, however romantic it may seem.',1,282631),(9555,196,'在干燥地区真的很危险，这样做很容易烧毁无价的未被发现的材料。',297640,'It''s really dangerous in dry areas, and you can easily burn priceless undiscovered material by doing so.（Q38)',1,290001),(9556,196,'那么，我们将如何在实地考察中欣赏岩画呢？ 通过观察它、绘制它并拍摄它——永远不要触摸它甚至追踪它。',308870,'So, how are we going to enjoy the rock art on our field trip? By looking at it, drawing it and photographing it - NEVER by touching（Q39) it or even tracing it.',1,297644),(9557,196,'岩画是脆弱而珍贵的。',312410,'Rock art is fragile and precious.',1,308874),(9558,196,'请记住，攀登岩石和洞穴可能会在一瞬间摧毁持续了几个世纪的东西。',318680,'Remember that climbing on rocks and in caves can destroy in a moment what has lasted for centuries.',1,312414),(9559,196,'因此在纳米比亚不要逞英雄。 尝试格外小心，并帮助其他人也这样做。',325000,'So no heroics in Namibia, please! Try to be extra careful and help others to be too.',1,318686),(9560,196,'最后，请不要移动岩石或树枝来拍照——你应该保持原样——我相信我可以依靠你来做到这一点。',336390,'And lastly please don''t even move rocks or branches to take photographs - you should leave the site intact - I''m sure I can rely on you to do that.（Q40)',1,325001),(9561,196,'嗯，这就是今天第一次讨论之前我想说的全部内容，但是如果您有任何问题，请现在就问他们 - 不要忘记您会在网上找到有关全球网站的一些有趣信息。',350000,'Well, that''s about all I want to say before today''s first discussion, but if you have any questions please ask them now - and don''t forget you''ll find some fascinating information about world-wi