e other interesting thing is that Antarctica is the driest continent on earth, surprisingly, and so you have to drink large amounts of water when you''re there.',1,230843),(9664,199,'南极洲多少岁了？',243410,'How old is Antarctica?',1,241547),(9665,199,'我们很确定它是一块更大的陆地的一部分，但它在 1.7 亿年前就脱离了大陆的其他部分。',250380,'We''re pretty sure it was part of a larger land mass but it broke away from the rest of the continent 170 million years ago.',1,243419),(9666,199,'你怎么能确定这一点？',252330,'How can you be certain of this?',1,250386),(9667,199,'...因为在南极洲发现的化石和岩石与在非洲和澳大利亚等地发现的化石和岩石相同。',260000,'... because fossils and rocks have been discovered in Antarctica which are the same as those found in places such as Africa and Australia.（Q26）',1,252332),(9668,199,'令人惊讶的是... 想到它曾经与非洲相连 ...',302000,'Amazing ... To think that it was once attached to Africa ...',1,260001),(9669,199,'现在让我们看看南极条约。国际条约的概念可以追溯到多远？',310530,'Now let''s just have a look at the Antarctic Treaty. How far back does the idea of an international treaty go?',1,302001),(9670,199,'好吧，早在 19 世纪，当时有 11 个国家组织了一次国际活动。',317140,'Well, as far back as the 19th century, when eleven nations organised an international event.',1,310536),(9671,199,'那究竟是什么时候？',318930,'When was that exactly?',1,317146),(9672,199,'1870 年。它被称为极地研究会议。',324000,'In 1870. And it was called the Polar Research Meeting.',1,318934),(9673,199,'然后，不久之后，他们组织了一个叫做第一个国际极地年的活动。',329540,'And then, not long after that, they organised something called the First International Polar Year.',1,324001),(9674,199,'那究竟发生在什么时候？',332680,'And that took place when exactly?',1,329548),(9675,199,'从 1882 年到 1883 年的两年多时间。但直到 1950 年代，才提出了国际条约的想法。',343340,'Over two years from 1882 to 1883. （Q27）But it wasn''t until the 1950s that the idea of an international treaty was proposed.',1,332689),(9676,199,'而在 1959 年，该条约实际上已经签署。',347810,'And in 1959 the Treaty was actually signed.（Q28）',1,343347),(9677,199,'您认为该条约的主要成就是什么？',351620,'What do you see as the main achievements of the treaty?',1,347811),(9678,199,'嗯，首先，这意