 to work on their weaker side, but more that they can help them identify the most suitable strategies to use in a given game.（Q32）',1,133789),(9690,200,'虽然大多数培训师都知道用手习惯的重要性，但目前他们不太愿意利用像马修斯这样的科学家可以提供的见解，我认为这是相当短视的，因为关注个人灵活性只是故事的一部分。',168490,'Although most trainers know how important handedness is, at present they are rather reluctant to make use of the insights（Q33） scientists like Matthews can give, which I think is rather short-sighted because focusing on individual flexibility is only part of the story.',1,148608),(9691,200,'无论如何，回到文章。',171430,'Anyway, back to the article.',1,168496),(9692,200,'马修斯发现了一项德国研究，该研究着眼于他所谓的''混合手''，即左右手平等使用的能力。',182340,'Matthews found a German study which looked at what he called ''mixed-handedness'', that is,\r\nthe capacity to use both left and right hands equally.',1,171438),(9693,200,'它考察了 40 位音乐家在各种乐器上的混合习惯。',188330,'It looked at mixed-handedness in 40 musicians on a variety of instruments.',1,182349),(9694,200,'研究人员检查了许多变量，例如演奏乐器的类型、练习的规律性和演奏乐器的时间长度。',200800,'Researchers examined a number of variables, e.g.type of instrument played, regularity of practice undertaken and length of time playing instrument.',1,188334),(9695,200,'......并发现了以下内容：键盘手的混手程度很高，而像大提琴手和小提琴手这样的弦乐演奏者则强烈偏爱一只手。',212830,'...and found the following: keyboard players had high levels of mix-handedness, whereas string players like cellists and violinists strongly favoured one hand.',1,200804),(9696,200,'而且那些更年轻开始练习的人更多地是混合手。',218710,'Also those who started younger were more mixed-handed.（Q34）',1,212836),(9697,200,'Matthews 还报告了对猿的用手习惯的研究。',223570,'Matthews also reports studies of handedness in apes.',1,218716),(9698,200,'猿类获得了很大一部分从蚁丘‘钓鱼’蚂蚁的食物。',230000,'Apes get a large proportion of their food by ''fishing'' ants from ant hills.',1,223579),(9699,200,'研究表明，猿类和人类一样，也显示出用手习惯——尽管对他们来说，左撇子和右撇子大致相同，而大约 85% 的人类是右撇子。',244400,'The studies show that apes, like humans, show handedness - though for them right- and left-handedness is about equal, whereas about 85% of humans are right-handed.',1,230001),(9700,200,'研究表明，持续使用同一只手的猿类比两者之间变化的蚂蚁多钓出 30% 的蚂蚁。',258740,'Studies showed that apes consistently using the same hand fished out 30% more ants than those varying between the two.（Q35）',1,244403),(9701,200,'马修斯开始研究几种不同的运动，并在每种运动中发现了不同类型的用手习惯。',266130,'Matthews started researching several different sports and found different types of handedness in each.',1,258743),(9702,200,'顺便说一下，他用\" 用手习惯\" 形容脚、眼、手的主导边。',273990,'By the way, he uses ''handedness'' to refer to the dominant side for feet and eyes as well as hands.',1,266136),(9703,200,'无论如何，他的团队测量了 2611 名球员的手、脚和眼睛，发现确实存在三种主要类型的侧向性：混合型——你在两边都表现得一样好——手和眼睛都是；单一的——你倾向于偏向一侧 但手和眼睛都偏向同一侧；以及交叉侧向性——球员的手和眼睛只偏向一侧，但它们是相反的两侧。',310000,'Anyway, his team measured the hand, feet and eyes of 2,611 players and found that there were really three main types of laterality: mixed -you work equally well on both\r\nsides - both hand and eye; single - you tend to favour one side but both hand and eye favour the same side; and cross-laterality - a player''s hands and eyes favour only one side but they are opposite sides.',1,273992),(9704,200,'让我们从曲棍球开始。',312130,'Let''s start with hockey.',1,310001),(9705,200,'马修斯发现最好是混合手——这是因为曲棍球棒必须在两个方向上展开——手或眼睛偏向一侧将是一个缺点。',327220,'Matthews found that it was best to be mix-handed - this is because a hockey stick must be deployed in two directions（Q36） - it would be a drawback to have hand or eye favouring one side.',1,312136),(9706,200,'一个有趣的发现是，混合型曲棍球运动员比单手型选手更有信心。',337130,'An interesting finding is that mixed-handed hockey players were significantly more confident（Q37） than their single-handed counterparts.',1,327224),(9707,200,'网球等球拍运动的情况略有不同。',341790,'Things are slightly different in racket sports like tennis.',1,337137),(9708,200,'这里重要的是在一侧有优势的手和眼睛。',349270,'Here the important thing is to have the dominant hand and eye on the one side.',1,341797),(9709,200,'这意味着在大部分动作发生的一侧有更大的视野区域。',355950,'This means that there is a bigger area of vision（Q38） on the side where most of the action occurs.',1,349279),(9710,200,'如果球员横向挥杆，则在大部分挥杆过程中，主眼看不到球拍。',363680,'If a player is cross lateral the racket is invisible from the dominant eye for much of the swing.',1,355951),(9711,200,'这意味着他们只能在很久以后才能做出更正。',367560,'It means that they can only make corrections much later.（Q39）',1,363681),(9712,200,'往往到那时损害已经造成。',370810,'and often the damage has been done by then.',1,367569),(9713,200,'并转向一种相当不同类型的运动，它涉及大而精确的动作——体操。',378720,'And moving to a rather different type of sport which involves large but precise movements - gymnastics.',1,370811),(9714,200,'已经发现交叉手眼偏爱是最好的。',383400,'It''s been found that cross hand-eye favouring is best.',1,378729),(9715,200,'这样做的主要原因是因为它有助于平衡——这当然是这项运动表现的绝对核心。',394316,'The predominant reason for this is because it aids balance (Q40)- which is of course absolutely central to performance in this sport.',1,383405),(9716,201,'早上好。',107660,'Good morning.',1,106548),(9717,201,'哦，早上好。这是……呃……26号房间？',113100,'Oh, good morning. Is this ... er ... room number 26?',1,107662),(9718,201,'是的，这是正确的。',114650,'Yes, that''s right.',1,113107),(9719,201,'这是学生就业中心吗？',117200,'So is this the Student Job Centre?',1,114659),(9720,201,'那必然是，我能帮助你吗？',120240,'It certainly is. How can I help you?',1,117204),(9721,201,'嗯，实际上我正在寻找一份工作——一份兼职工作。你现在有空吗？',127450,'Well, actually I''m looking for a job - a part-time job. Do you have anything available at the moment?',1,120249),(9722,201,'啊，是的……你是注册的学生吗？',131060,'Ah, yes ... Are you a registered student?',1,127455),(9723,201,'恐怕这项服务只提供给全日制学生。',134080,'I''m afraid this service is only available to full-time students.',1,131067),(9724,201,'是的 我是全日制学生。我正在攻读商业研究学位。这是我的学生证。',140260,'Yes ... I am. I''m doing a degree in Business Studies. Here''s my student card.',1,134087),(9725,201,'你在哪一年？',142110,'Which year are you in?',1,140262),(9726,201,'嗯......我已经在大学四年了，但我在第三年，因为我去年休假了。',148610,'Well ... I''ve been at uni for four years but I''m in the Third Year because I took last year off.',1,142118),(9727,201,'对了……好吧，我们就来看看目前有哪些职位空缺。',154690,'R