1,208,'事实上，今天全世界生产了数十万吨味精。',167110,'In fact, hundreds of thousands of tonnes of MSG are produced all over the world today.',1,156008),(10002,208,'那么味精到底是什么？嗯，味精含有百分之七十八点二的谷氨酸，百分之十二点二的钠和百分之九点六的水。',182950,'So what exactly is MSG? Well, Monosodium Glutamate contains seventy-eight point two per\ncent glutamate, twelve point two per cent sodium and nine point six per cent water.(Q34)',1,167113),(10003,208,'谷氨酸是一种天然存在于所有含蛋白质食物中的氨基酸，嗯，所以这包括肉类和奶酪等食物。',194220,'Glutamate is an amino acid that can be found naturally in all protein-containing foods, erm,\nso this includes food such as meat and cheese.(Q35&36)',1,182952),(10004,208,'众所周知，中国和日本的食物都含有味精，但许多人似乎并不知道它也被用于世界其他地区的食品中。',205600,'It is widely known that Chinese and Japanese food contains MSG but many people don''t seem to be aware that it is also used in foods in other parts of the world.',1,194229),(10005,208,'例如，它存在于商业生产的意大利比萨饼、美国快餐中，而在英国，味精用于薯片等食品中。',217310,'For example it is found in commercially made Italian pizzas, in American fast food and in Britain MSG is used in things like potato crisps.',1,205605),(10006,208,'那么，味精究竟是如何工作的呢？ 嗯，在西方世界，我们常说四种“味道”，相信大家都熟悉甜、酸、苦、盐的概念。',233060,'So, how exactly does MSG work? Well, in the Western world, we commonly talk of four ''tastes'', and I''m sure you''re all familiar with the concepts of sweet, sour, bitter and salt.',1,217312),(10007,208,'那么，在 1908 年，池田菊苗发现了第五种“味道”。',238660,'Well,in 1908, Kikunae Ikeda identified a fifth ''taste''.(Q37)',1,233065),(10008,208,'而且人们认为味精会增强某些食物中这种自然产生的‘味道’。',245680,'And it is thought that MSG intensifies this \nnaturally occurring ''taste'' in some food.',1,238660),(10009,208,'因为谷氨酸是在自然食物中很常见的氨基酸，所以我们应该能够发现并尝出它的味道，从进化的角度看，这是说得通的。',258850,'It does make perfect evolutionary sense that we should have the ability to detect or taste glutamate because it is the amino acid which is most common in natural foods.(Q38)',1,245689),(10010,208,'芝加哥大学副教授约翰·普雷斯科特认为，这第五种口味就像其他口味一样有目的。',269360,'John Prescott, an associate professor at the University of Chicago, s