人们自学或在自己的组织中使用。',227020,'It''s a training resource - a collection of materials for people to study on their own, or use in their own organisations.',1,220585),(10135,211,'嗯。你是说书籍和视频吗？',229580,'Uhuh. You mean books and videos?',1,227028),(10136,211,'是的，还有自学手册。加上大量基于计算机的材料，因此人们可以以自己的速度完成它们，并重复他们不确定的任何内容。',239470,'Yes, and manuals for self-study. Plus a lot of computer-based materials, so people can work through them at their own speed, and repeat anything they aren''t sure about.',1,229580),(10137,211,'你可以租用笔记本电脑在自己的家中或工作场所使用，也可以租用可以带走的打印机。',246090,'And you can hire laptops（Q26） to use in your own home or workplace as well as printers（Q27） that you can take away.',1,239472),(10138,211,'它有什么可以用来提高我的学习技能的吗？我对报告写作没有太多想法。我相信我会在课程中需要它。',255910,'Does it have anything that I could use to improve my study skills? I don''t have much idea about report writing（Q28）. and I''m sure I''ll need it on the course.',1,246091),(10139,211,'哦，是的，有很多有用的材料。只需询问其中一名工作人员即可。',260000,'Oh yes, there''s plenty of useful material. Just ask one of the staff.',1,255913),(10140,211,'该中心是否涵盖所有主要业务领域？',262830,'Does the centre cover all the main areas of business?',1,260000),(10141,211,'是的，像金融这样的话题，当然还有营销——这是一个很受欢迎的话题。',267150,'Yes, topics like finance, and of course marketing（Q29） - that''s a popular one.',1,262834),(10142,211,'当地经理似乎在排队借视频！',270120,'Local managers seem to queue up to borrow the videos!',1,267151),(10143,211,'那么，它不只是针对学生吗？',272920,'So it isn''t just for students, then?',1,270121),(10144,211,'不，它仅供会员使用，但任何人都可以加入。',276220,'No, it''s for members only, but anyone can join.',1,272929),(10145,211,'它要多少钱？',277810,'How much does it cost?',1,276228),(10146,211,'对于公司里的人是每年 100 英镑，对个人 50 英镑，我想，学生没有折扣。',284290,'£100 a year for a company, and £50 for an individual（Q30）, with no discount for students, I''m afraid.',1,277815),(10147,211,'这很有帮助。嗯，我想就是这样。',287560,'That''s very helpful. Well, I think that''s all.',1,284291),(10148,211,'我还是回家填报名表吧。感谢你的帮助。',291210,'I''d better go home and fill in the enrolment form. Thanks for all your help.',1,287565),(10149,211,'别客气。再见。',292670,'You''re welcome. Goodbye.',1,291211),(10150,211,'再见。',293687,'Goodbye.',1,292672),(10151,212,'在过去的几周里，我们一直在关注伦敦社会历史的各个方面，今天早上我们将继续关注东区的生活。',69200,'In the last few weeks, we''ve been looking at various aspects of the social history of London, and this morning we''re continuing with a look at life in the area called the East End.',1,60001),(10152,212,'我将从该地区的简要历史开始，然后关注二十世纪上半叶的生活。',76280,'I''ll start with a brief history of the district, and then focus on life in the first half of the twentieth century.',1,69201),(10153,212,'公元1世纪至公元4世纪，当罗马帝国统治英格兰时，伦敦发展成了一个拥有4万5千人的城镇，也就是现今的伦敦东区。伦敦东区位于泰晤士河附近，沿着伦敦东北走向的公路一直通向海岸，在这块海岸上，耕种及畜牧业是当时人民赖以为生的方式。',96900,'Back in the first to the fourth centuries AD, when the Romans controlled England, London grew into a town of 45,000 people, and what''s now the East End - the area by the river Thames, and along the road heading north-east from London to the coast - consisted of farmland with crops and livestock which help to feed（Q31）that population.',1,76289),(10154,212,'罗马人于公元 410 年离开，即 5 世纪初，从那时起，该国遭受了来自当今德国和丹麦、盎格鲁人、撒克逊人和朱特人的部落的一系列入侵，其中许多人定居在东区.',112960,'The Romans left in 410, at the beginning of the fifth century, and from then onwards the country suffered a series of invasions by tribes from present-day Germany and Denmark, the Angles, Saxons and Jutes, many of whom settled in the East End.',1,96908),(10155,212,'他们引进的技术意味着金属和皮革制品首次在那里生产。',119060,'The technology they introduced meant that metal（Q32） and leather（Q32） goods were produced there for the first time.',1,112968),(10156,212,'而且由于东区在河边，船只可以在那里和国外市场之间运输货物。',125920,'And as the East End was by the river, ships could transport goods between there and foreign markets.',1,119061),(10157,212,'在 11 世纪，准确地说是 1066 年，诺曼人征服了英格兰，在接下来的几个世纪里，伦敦成为欧洲最强大、最繁荣的城市之一。',137980,'In the eleventh century, in 1066 to be precise, the Normans conquered England, and during the next few centuries London became one of the most powerful and prosperous cities in Europe.',1,125928),(10158,212,'伦敦东区从中受益，因为那里的限制比城市本身少，在接下来的几百年里，大量外国移民来到这里，带来他们作为工人、商人或放贷人的技能。',153380,'The East End benefited from this, and because there were fewer restrictions（Q33） there than in the city itself, plenty of newcomers settled there from abroad, bringing their skills as workers, merchants or money-lenders during the next few hundred years.',1,137989),(10159,212,'在 16 世纪，第一个码头在建造船只的地方被挖掘出来，最终使东区成为大规模国际贸易的焦点。',163130,'In the sixteenth century the first dock was dug where ships（Q34） were constructed, eventually making the East End the focus of massive international trade.',1,153385),(10160,212,'在 16 世纪后期，当英格兰其他大部分地区的经济陷入困境时，许多农业工人来到东区寻找替代工作。',173430,'And in the late sixteenth century, when much of the rest of England（Q35） was suffering economically, a lot of agricultural workers came to the East End to look for alternative work.',1,163132),(10161,212,'在17世纪，伦敦东部仍然是一块偏僻的、半乡村的移民居住地。',179640,'In the seventeenth century, the East End was still a series of separate, semi-rural settlements.',1,173433),(10162,212,'住宿短缺，因此沼泽地被排干并建造以容纳现在居住在那里的大量人口：到 19 世纪，伦敦是世界上最繁忙的港口，这成为东区的主要就业来源.',196360,'There was a shortage of accommodation, so marshland was drained and built（Q36） on to house the large numbers of people now living there: By the nineteenth century London was the busiest port in the world, and this became the main source of employment in the East End.',1,179642),(10163,212,'那些负担得起居住在更宜人环境中的人搬出，该地区成为绝大多数人生活在极端贫困中的地区，卫生条件令人震惊。',213090,'Those who could afford to live in more pleasant surroundings moved out, and the area became one where the vast majority of people lived in extreme poverty（Q37）,and suffered from appalling sanitary conditions.',1,196367),(10164,212,'这个简短的大纲将我们带到了 20 世纪初，现在我们将转向住房。',220000,'That brief outline takes us to the beginning of the twentieth century, and now we''ll turn to housing.',1,213092),(10165,212,'本世纪初，东伦敦大多数劳动人民的生活条件确实非常基本。',226800,'At the beginning of the century, living conditions for the majority of working people in East London were very basic indeed.',1,220001),(10166,212,'房子建造得十分密集的，因为没有监管，所以通常建造得很糟糕。',233890,'Houses were crowded closely together and usually very badly built, because there was no regulation.（Q38/39/40）',1,226809),(10167,212,'那些贫困的和生活艰难的人被这里的工作机会吸引过来，而且他们也需要有地方住。',239290,'But the poor and needy were attracted by the possibility of work, and they had to be housed.',1,233897),(10168,212,'房客和房东最关心的是住房的可用性，而不是条件。',247410,'It was the availability, rather than the condition, of the housing that was the major concern for tenants and landlords alike.',1,239292),(10169,212,'当时很少有房子通电，所以使用了其他能源，比如用煤生火，可能只加热一个房间。',255490,'Few houses had electricity at this time, so other sources of power were used, like coal for the fires which heated perhaps just one room.（Q38/39/40）',1,247411),(10170,212,'当然，这些产生的烟雾对伦敦曾经闻名的空气污染做出了很大贡献。',262470,'Of course, the smoke from these contributed a great deal to the air pollution for which London used to be famous.',1,255496),(10171,212,'像这样一个又小又潮湿又不卫生的房子很可能会被两个完整的家庭占据，可能包括几个孩子、祖父母、阿姨和叔叔。',274210,'A tiny, damp, unhealthy house like this might well be occupied by two full families, possibly including several children, grandparents, aunts and uncles.（Q38/39/40）',1,262474),(10172,212,'现在，在我继续讨论这种生活方式对健康的影响之前，我先谈谈食物和营养。',281206,'Now, before I go on to health implications of this way of life, I''ll say something about food and nutrition.',1,274214),(10173,213,'早上好，辛茅斯博物馆。我可以帮你吗？',54340,'Good morning, Synmouth Museum. Can I help you?',1,50698),(10174,213,'哦是的。早上好。我对儿童工作坊很感兴趣，我想了解更多信息。',61230,'Oh yes. Good morning. I''m interested in the children''s workshops and I''d like a little more information, please.',1,54346),(10175,213,'你是说艺术和手工艺工作坊吗？',63910,'Do you mean the Art and Craft workshops?',1,61234),(10176,213,'是的。一个朋友的朋友提过它们——孩子们可以画画、做模型等等。',70070,'Yes. A friend of a friend mentioned them - the children do painting and make models and so forth.',1,63917),(10177,213,'当然是。嗯，我从哪里开始说呢？首先，你可能知道的是，他们每周六都跑步。',79030,'Yes, of course. Um, where