se?',1,295752),(10388,217,'我正在考虑注册开通您的某个阶段互联网服务。',302830,'I was thinking of registering for your internet（Q10） service at some stage.',1,299087),(10389,217,'哦是的。 你想让我把这方面的信息发给你吗？',306510,'Oh, yes. Would you like me to send you information about that?',1,302834),(10390,217,'请，是的。',307540,'Please, yes.',1,306516),(10391,217,'您是否想收到有关银行其他服务的信息——保险、贷款等？',314210,'And would you like to receive information about the bank''s other services - insurance, loans, anything like that?',1,307548),(10392,217,'嗯，我不不是很想，谢谢。',316360,'Hmm, I don''t think so, thanks.',1,314215),(10393,217,'那没关系。 最后一件事，如果你同意...',321321,'That''s OK then. And one last thing, if you agree ...',1,316364),(10394,218,'“欢迎大家，来到著名作家塞巴斯蒂安·乔治 (Sebastian George) 曾经的故乡 Rosewood 迷人的房子和花园。”',55870,'Welcome, everybody, to the lovely house and gardens of Rosewood, once the home of the \nfamous writer, Sebastian George.',1,47145),(10395,218,'他在 1902 年买下了这座房子，尽管他在两年前第一次看到它。',61690,'He bought the house in 1902 although he had first seen it two years earlier.',1,55872),(10396,218,'当时业主把它租给了租客，因为乔治下定决心买它的速度太慢了。',68510,'At that time the owners let it out to a tenant because George was too slow making up his mind to buy it（Q11）.',1,61690),(10397,218,'“当它重新回到市场上时，他毫不犹豫地立即以 9,300 英镑的价格买下了它，尽管房子没有卫生间，楼上没有自来水，也没有电。”',83350,'When it came back on the_market, there was no hesitation and he bought it immediately, for £9,300, even though the house had no \nbathroom, no running water upstairs, and no electricity.',1,68511),(10398,218,'从他来到这里时算起，他已经结婚十年了。',87160,'When he came here, he''d been married for ten years.',1,83357),(10399,218,'“在那段时间里，他成为了英语世界最著名的作家之一。”',92690,'During that time, he''d become one of the most famous writers in the English-speaking world.',1,87169),(10400,218,'他的职业成功是巨大的，但他的个人生活却没有那么成功。',98710,'His professional success was enormous, but his personal life wasn''t as successful.',1,92692),(10401,218,'“他不再与他的兄弟和睦相处，并且在他的长女约瑟芬七岁时就去世了，这让他感到非常沮丧。”',109040,'He was no longer on speaking terms with his brother and had been devastated by the death at the age of seven of his elder \ndaughter, Josephine.（Q12）',1,98711),(10402,218,'搬到 Rosewood 让这个家庭开始了新的生活。',113450,'Moving to Rosewood allowed the family to start a new life.',1,109043),(10403,218,'乔治将罗斯伍德视为英格兰这一地区传统乡间别墅的典范，并在此创作了一些他最成功的作品。',123580,'George regarded Rosewood as a pure example of a traditional country house of this part of England and did some of his most successful writing here.（Q13）',1,113457),(10404,218,'这栋房子和它的庭院成了家庭的避风港，让他们得以远离尘嚣。',130200,'The house and its grounds became the family haven and their escape to privacy and quiet.',1,123588),(10405,218,'墙壁和直棂窗是用当地的砂岩建造的，屋顶的瓦片和烟囱的砖都是用当地的粘土烤制的，里面的木结构来自周围生长的橡树。',193430,'The walls, and the mullioned windows were built of the local sandstone, the tiles on the roofs and the bricks of the chimney stack were baked from local clay, and the wooden structures inside came from oak trees which grow around here.',1,130209),(10406,218,'现在，请看一下我给你的房子和花园的地图。',198780,'Now, please look at the map I''ve given you of the house and gardens.',1,193439),(10407,218,'我们在信息中心。',202120,'We''re here at the Information Centre.',1,198786),(10408,218,'沿着标有箭头的路径，您来到的第一个区域是您左侧的果园。',209720,'Follow the path marked with the arrow and the first area you come to is the orchard on your left.',1,202122),(10409,218,'沿着小路往前走，右边是菜园，当你绕过第一个拐角时，你会发现，在你的左边，种植了不同类型的梨树和一些可爱的花朵， 这就是众所周知的梨巷——由乔治本人设计。',232000,'As you go further down the path, there''s the kitchen garden on the right and as you go round the first sharp corner you will find, to your left, an area where different types of pear tree have been planted as well as some lovely flowers,and this is known as Pear Alley （Q14）- designed by George himself.',1,209726),(10410,218,'旁边是温室，种植了一些外来植物和水果。',237730,'Next to this is the greenhouse where some exotic plants and fruits are grown.',1,232007),(10411,218,'沿着第二个拐角处的小路往前走，在您的右手边，您会看到桑园的入口，那里种满了 500 年的古树。',248140,'Follow the path round the second corner and on your right you will see the entrance to the Mulberry Garden（Q15） with its 500-year-old tree.',1,237734),(10412,218,'经过桑园，沿着小路一直走到房子的前面。',253870,'Past the Mulberry Garden, follow the path until you reach the front of the house.',1,248141),(10413,218,'我建议你花一个小时在这座可爱的建筑周围闲逛。',258280,'I suggest you spend a good hour wandering around this lovely building.',1,253878),(10414,218,'导游每两小时带领参观团体参观一次。',262550,'A guide takes visitor groups round every two hours.',1,258280),(10415,218,'“如果您想购买乔治的任何书籍或其他纪念品，请从侧门离开房子，在那里您会找到我们的商店。”',271480,'If you would like to purchase any of George''s books or other souvenirs, then leave the \nhouse by the side entrance , where you will find our shop.',1,262550),(10416,218,'它位于房子和车库之间，车库里有一辆曾经属于乔治的华丽老劳斯莱斯汽车。',281460,'which is situated between the house and the garage（Q16） which contains the magnificent old Rolls-Royce car which used to belong to George.',1,271488),(10417,218,'我想这时候你可能也需要休息一下，吃点点心。',287060,'I expect by this time you may also be in need of a rest and some refreshment.',1,281464),(10418,218,'大多数游客都是，那你为什么不去车库另一边的茶室呢？',294670,'Most visitors are, so why don''t you visit the tea room on the far side of the garage（Q17）?.',1,287068),(10419,218,'如果你有时间，可以沿着达德威尔河步行一段可爱的路。',300000,'If you have time, there is a lovely walk down towards the River Dudwell.',1,294672),(10420,218,'对我来说，这是庄园最好的地方。',303230,'For me, this is the best part of the estate.',1,300000),(10421,218,'这不在地图上，但都清楚地标明了路标。',307630,'This isn''t on the map but it is all clearly signposted.',1,303236),(10422,218,'你穿过田野沿着河岸延伸的小溪。',312040,'You cross the field（Q18） which spreads along the banks of the river.',1,307639),(10423,218,'在春天，这个地区非常值得一游。',315640,'In spring, this area is well worth a visit.',1,312042),(10424,218,'“当你穿过人行天桥时，花一两分钟看水从下面流过，然后继续沿着 River Walk 穿过林地。”',324710,'Spend a minute or two watching the water pass by underneath as you cross the footbridge（Q19）, \nand then continue along the River Walk through the woodland.',1,315644),(10425,218,'在炎热的夏日，这条小路上的树木提供了令人愉悦的遮荫。',330000,'On a hot summer''s day the trees along this path provide welcome shade.',1,324716),(10426,218,'“最终你来到了曾经为房子供电的水磨坊——在乔治的时间里，每天晚上只有大约只供四个小时”',339520,'Eventually you come to the water mill which \nused to provide the electricity for the house - only about four hours every evening - in \nGeorge''s time.',1,330000),(10427,218,'最后，对于那些想看到周围乡村美景的人来说，当你从磨坊回来时，在第一个转弯处向左转，然后爬上观景台。',353800,'And, finally, for those of you who would like to see stunning views of the surrounding countryside and who are a little bit more energetic, when you return from the mill take the first turning on your left and climb up to the viewpoint（Q20）.',1,339525),(10428,218,'你不会后悔的来这里的。',355660,'You won''t regret it.',1,353801),(10429,218,'好好享受你的游览！',360000,'Enjoy your visit!',1,355669),(10430,219,'露西，我们真的需要着手完成这项营销任务。',42700,'Lucy, we really need to get working on this marketing assignment.',1,38775),(10431,219,'离学期结束只有五周的时间来设计、实施，然后写出结果。',48660,'We''ve only got five weeks left to the end of term to design it, carry it out, and then write up the results.',1,42708),(10432,219,'当然。 好吧，让我们现在就开始吧。 让我们看一下说明。',53380,'Sure. Well, let''s get started right now. Let''s go over the instructions.',1,48663),(10433,219,'我们到底要做什么？',55210,'What exactly do we have to do?',1,53383),(10434,219,'好吧，它在这里说我们必须看看娱乐业的一个领域。这里有一个不同类型的列表。',61360,'Well, it says here we have to look at one area of the entertainment industry（Q21）. There''s a list of the different types.',1,55216),(10435,219,'这些是什么？',62590,'What are they?',1,61361),(10436,219,'音乐、电影、戏剧、运动和外出就餐。',66440,'Music, cinema, theatre, sport, and eating out.',1,62598),(10437,219,'这就是全部？',67650,'Is that all?',1,66447),(10438,219,'看起来像。',68770,'Looks like it.',1,67654),(10439,219,'所以我们选择行业的一个分支，然后我们看看两组不同的人是如何使用它的？ 是对的吗？',74500,'So we choose one branch of the industry and then we look at how two different groups of people use it? Is that right?',1,68778),(10440,219,'是的。',75740,'Yes.',1,74509),(10441,219,'我们是否必须使用任何特定的方法来获取我们的数据？',79370,'And do we have to use any particular method to get our data?',1,75745),(10442,219,'我们可以寄出一份调查问卷，或者进行面对面的采访，甚至是观察吗？',85170,'Can we mail out a questionnaire, or do face-to-face interviews, or maybe even observations?',1,79372),(10443,219,'实际上，看起来我们别无选择。 我们必须进行电话采访。',90000,'Well actually, it looks like we don''t have a choice. We have to do telephone interviews.（Q22）',1,85178),(10444,219,'好的，所以至少我们不必浪费时间在不同的方法之间做出决定。',94840,'OK, so at least we don''t have to waste time deciding between the different methods.',1,90000),(10445,219,'是的，没错。哦，另一个要求是受访者的数量。',99710,'Yeah, that''s right. Oh, and the other requirement is the number of interviewees.',1,94844),(10446,219,'不要太多，我希望。十？二十？',102980,'Not too many, I hope. Ten? Twenty?',1,99714),(10447,219,'好吧，我们必须做两组，记住，看起来我们必须为每组面试十五个人。',110190,'Well, we have to do two groups, remember, and it looks like we have to interview fifteen for each group.',1,102987),(10448,219,'那一共是三十个。这需要很长时间。',114350,'That''s thirty（Q23） altogether then. It''s going to take ages.',1,110199),(10449,219,'是的，但请记住的是，我们正在一起努力完成这件事，所以我们每个人只需要做十五个。',119220,'Yes, but remember we''re working on this together, so we''ll only have to do fifteen each.',1,114354),(10450,219,'好的，这些都是要求吗？',122570,'OK, so those are all the requirements?',1,119226),(10451,219,'是的，看起来像。',124280,'Yes, looks like it.',1,122570),(10452,219,'那么，首先，我们要选择哪个区域？我更喜欢看电影，因为那是我花最多钱的地方。',133260,'So, first, which area are we going to choose? My preference would be cinema, since that''s where I spend most of my money.',1,124289),(10453,219,'嗯，我不认为这是一个好主意。我不认为那里的市场存在巨大差异。',138440,'Hmm, I don''t think that''s such a good idea. I don''t think there are huge differences in the market there.',1,133269),(10454,219,'我的意思是，无论男女老少，无论贫富，都去看同一部电影。',142600,'I mean you get young and old, male and female, rich and poor all going to the same movies.',1,138449),(10455,219,'是的，也许你是对的。那就让它成为音乐吧。',148000,'Yeah, maybe you''re right. Let''s make it music then.',1,142604),(10456,219,'对。那么，我们将比较和对比哪两组呢？',152870,'Right. So, what two groups will we compare and contrast?',1,148000),(10457,219,'男性和女性？',154780,'Male and female?（Q24）',1,152873),(10458,219,'不，我的大多数女性朋友都喜欢和我一样的音乐。',159080,'No. Most of my female friends like the same music as me.',1,154784),(10459,219,'我认为，不同年龄段的人更有可能表现出差异。',205490,'Different age groups would be much more likely to show up differences, I think.',1,159083),(10460,219,'是的，我想你又对了。我会做一些笔记，可以吗？',209170,'Yeah, I suppose you''re right again. I''ll take some notes, shall I?',1,205492),(10461,219,'所以......年龄组。好。你怎么认为？一组是二十五岁或以下，另一组是四十五岁或以上？这样应该可以显示出差异。',221820,'So ... Age Groups. Well. What do you think? Maybe twenty-five or under for one group, and forty-five or over for the other group? That should show up differences.',1,209170),(10462,219,'对。',222920,'Right.',1,221828),(10463,219,'行。下一个。他们喜欢什么样的音乐怎么样？让我们给他们一些选择，然后我们就可以打勾。',230000,'OK. Next. How about the kind of music they like - let''s give them some choices and then we can just tick boxes.',1,222926),(10464,219,'行。 让我们来听流行音乐、爵士乐、民谣、轻音乐……还有什么？',236910,'OK. Let''s have pop, jazz（Q25）, folk, easy listening ... What else?',1,230000),(10465,219,'好吧，我们应该包括古典。 有些人喜欢它，你知道的。',242000,'Well, we should include classical（Q26）. Some people like it, you know.',1,236915),(10466,219,'好的好的。 然后我们应该了解他们听音乐的方式。',246000,'OK .. OK. And then we should have how they listen to music.',1,242000),(10467,219,'媒介。 对。 让我们包括收音机、CD——然后我猜还有电视。',252160,'The medium. Right. Let''s include radio, CD - and then I guess there''s TV.',1,246000),(10468,219,'音乐会呢？ 你知道，在酒吧和大厅里。',254970,'What about concerts（Q27）? You know, in pubs and halls.',1,252161),(10469,219,'哦，是的，我们当然应该包括现场音乐。',256790,'Oh yeah, we should include live music of course.',1,254979),(10470,219,'好的，我们现在开始了！ 下一个问题是可能是关于他们实际获得音乐的地方。',262380,'OK, we''re on a roll now! Next point could be about where they actually get their music.',1,256794),(10471,219,'你是说，他们是在音乐商店还是百货商店买的？',266290,'You mean like, do they buy it in music shops, or department stores（Q28）?',1,262383),(10472,219,'可以，或者从网上下载。',268350,'Yes, or download it from the Internet.',1,266299),(10473,219,'对。 那可能是录制的音乐。 然后我们需要另一个现场音乐部分。 他们去哪里弄现场音乐？',275130,'Right. That could be for recorded music. Then we need another section for live music. Where do they go for that?',1,268353),(10474,219,'行。 比方说迪斯科、酒吧、俱乐部、音乐厅。 。。',280290,'OK. Let''s say disco, pub, club（Q29）, concert hall . . .',1,275135),(10475,219,'或者歌剧院！ 我想我们应该包括卡拉 OK 酒吧。',282820,'Or opera house（Q30）! And I guess we should include karaoke bars.',1,280291),(10476,219,'在这个城市里没有多少人！',284440,'Not many of them in this city!',1,282823),(10477,219,'好啊那我们就不谈了。那么，还有什么要做呢？',289170,'OK. We''ll leave that out then. So, what''s left to do?',1,284447),(10478,219,'那就是了。 好吧，现在我们可以为它制定一个时间表。',294000,'That''s it. Well, now we can make a time-scale for doing it.',1,289175),(10479,220,'大家早晨好。',61970,'Good morning everyone.',1,60000),(10480,220,'上周，我们正在研究爱尔兰的狩猎采集者，他们从英格兰穿过爱尔兰海。',67820,'Last week we were looking at the hunter-gatherers in Ireland, across the Irish Sea from England.',1,61977),(10481,220,'今天，我们将进入四到六千年前的时期，即新石器时代，也就是爱尔兰引入全面农业经济的时期。',80550,'Today, we''re going to move on to the period between four and six thousand years ago, known as the Neolithic period, which is when a total farming economy was introduced in Ireland.',1,67827),(10482,220,'现在，关于爱尔兰第一批新石器时代定居者的起源有几种假设，但其中大部分都存在问题。',89290,'Now, there are several hypotheses about the origins of the first Neolithic settlers in Ireland,but most of these contain problems.（Q31）',1,80550),(10483,220,'例如，关于它们来自英国的理论存在相当大的考古困难。',95770,'For instance, there are considerable archaeological difficulties about the theory that they came from England.',1,89297),(10484,220,'证据并没有真正累加起来。',98490,'The evidence doesn''t really add up.',1,95772),(10485,220,'“但关于它们直接来自欧洲大陆的理论存在更大的实际问题。”',105650,'But there are even greater practical problems about the theory that they came directly \nfrom continental Europe.',1,98499),(10486,220,'一方面，尚不清楚有多少男性和女性可以被运送到爱尔兰从而来建立一个可行的人口。',116100,'For one thing, it''s not clear just how sufficient numbers of men and women could have been transported to Ireland to establish a viable population.',1,105655),(10487,220,'如你所知，以前存在的狩猎采集经济是以分散的小群体为基础的。',123790,'As you know, the hunter-gatherer economy which existed beforehand was based on small scattered groups.',1,116107),(10488,220,'农业经济几乎肯定需要更大的社区来完成种植和照料足够的农作物以维持全年所需的所有工作。',135000,'The farming economy would almost certainly have required much larger communities to do all the work needed to plant and tend sufficient crops to sustain them through the year.',1,123793),(10489,220,'早期的农民饲养了各种动物，包括牛和羊。',140000,'The early farmers kept various animals, including cattle and sheep.',1,135000),(10490,220,'也有猪的证据，但这些可能是本地野生物种的后裔。',147300,'There''s also evidence of pigs, but it is possible that these could have been descended from the native wild species.',1,140000),(10491,220,'“现在，我们从现代农业中了解到，如果种畜数量低于大约 300 只雌性，当地物种的未来就处于危险之中。”',158320,'Now, we know from modern farming that if the level of breeding stock falls below about \nthree hundred females, the future of the species locally is at risk.',1,147308),(10492,220,'所以我们必须假设，从新石器时代的农业开始，种羊的数量就会大大超过三百只，全国牛群的规模也应该差不多。',171270,'So we must assume that from the beginnings of Neolithic farming the number of breeding sheep would have considerably exceeded three hundred, and the national cattle herd must have been of a similar size.（Q32）',1,158327),(10493,220,'问题是这些是如何被带到该地区的以及它们来自哪里。',176730,'The question is how these were brought to the area and where they came from.',1,171278),(10494,220,'“人们通常认为新石器时代的定居者使用皮船运输牲畜。”',183090,'It''s usually suggested that the Neolithic settlers used skin-covered boats to transport \nlivestock.（Q33）',1,176731),(10495,220,'但是这种方法会严重限制殖民舰队的范围。',188090,'But this method would have severely restricted the range of the colonising fleets.（Q33）',1,183092),(10496,220,'“必要的动物运输量意味着这些牲畜不太可能来自英格兰以外的任何地方。”',197460,'The sheer volume of animal transport necessary means it''s unlikely that this livestock \ncould have been brought from anywhere further than England.',1,188091),(10497,220,'“作物呢？嗯，这段时间有两种主要的谷类作物被引入爱尔兰：小麦和大麦，都有几个品种。”',208820,'What about crops? Well, 