59),(10589,223,'在福特汉姆，我们拥有与初等教育以及特殊需求相关的材料，但您当然需要熟悉这两个网站以充分利用我们的资源。',125000,'At Fordham we hold material relating to primary education, as well as special needs, but of course you''ll need to familiarise yourself with both sites to make the most of our resources.',1,112976),(10590,223,'你没有提到期刊。他们在两个图书馆都有吗？',130410,'You haven''t mentioned periodicals. Are they held at both sites?',1,125000),(10591,223,'目前的问题是，对，但是如果您想查看之前的问题，您需要使用在福特汉姆举行的 CD-ROM 数据库。',138760,'Current issues, yes but if you want to look at back（Q25） issues you''ll need to use the CD-ROM databases which are held here at Fordham.',1,130410),(10592,223,'我知道了。现在，关于借书。我住在城外，所以我希望我能借很多东西，并减少我必须做的旅行次数.',151270,'I see. Now, about borrowing books. I''m living out of town, so I''m hoping I can borrow quite a few items, and cut down on the number of trips I have to make .',1,138764),(10593,223,'对，好吧，会员可以从每个图书馆一次借两本书。',155630,'Right, well, members can borrow two books at a time from each site.',1,151271),(10594,223,'只有两本书？',157390,'Only two books?',1,155630),(10595,223,'每个图书馆可以借两个，但总共可以借四个。',160660,'Only two from each site, but that''s four altogether.',1,157394),(10596,223,'哦，我明白了，我能借多久？',165000,'Oh I see, and how long can I hang on to them for?',1,160663),(10597,223,'借阅期限为一个月，当然书可以续借。',169580,'The borrowing period is one month, but of course books can be renewed.',1,165000),(10598,223,'您可以将任何项目最多重新续期 3 次。',173010,'You can renew any item a maximum of three times.',1,169581),(10599,223,'我必须来图书馆吗？',175800,'Do I have to come to the library to do that?',1,173012),(10600,223,'不，您可以通过电话或电子邮件进行，但您不能以这种方式续订过期书籍，只能在书籍上标明的到期日期之前或之时续订。',185710,'No, you can do it by telephone or email, but you can''t renew overdue（Q26） books this way, only before or on the due date stamped in the book.',1,175808),(10601,223,'我们需要您的全名、您的借阅者编号和您借阅项目的站点库的名称。',192980,'We''ll need your full name, your borrower number and the name of the site library you borrowed the items from.',1,185718),(10602,223,'所以理论上我最多可以借书三个月——你说的是这个吗？',198700,'So theoretically I can borrow books for up to three months - is that what you''re saying?',1,192983),(10603,223,'是的，只要他们没有被召回。',201110,'Yes, provided they''re not recalled.',1,198700),(10604,223,'那么，接下来会发生什么？',203620,'So, what happens then?',1,201118),(10605,223,'好吧，有时另一位借书人要求某件物品，在这种情况下，我们会向您发送一封信，您必须在七个工作日内归还该书。',212490,'Well, sometimes an item is requested by another borrower, in which case we''d send you a letter, and you''d have to return the book within seven working days（Q27）.',1,203629),(10606,223,'别忘了，我们周日休息。',215000,'Don''t forget we''re closed on Sundays.',1,212492),(10607,223,'好的。',252910,'OK.',1,215000),(10608,223,'我猜我需要很长时间才能找到我需要的东西，因为这里书籍有很多。',258100,'I expect it''ll take me a while to find what I need. There''s such a lot here.',1,252914),(10609,223,'是的，但是如果您需要入门帮助，本学期我们将举办三场学习技能研讨会。',265730,'Yes there is, but if you need help getting started, this term we''re running three study skills workshops.',1,258103),(10610,223,'哦？他们在做什么的？',267660,'Oh? What are they on?',1,265730),(10611,223,'呃，让我看看。第一个是关于资源的——是的，就是这样。',274350,'Er, let me see. The first one''s on resources - yes, here it is.',1,267666),(10612,223,'如何使用图书馆的资源。这包括全部，而不仅仅是印刷和技术资源。',280630,'How to use the library''s resources. That includes everything, not just the print and technical resources.（Q28/29/30）',1,274359),(10613,223,'这听起来很有用。有什么关于使用互联网的吗？',285000,'That sounds useful. Is there anything on using the Internet?',1,280637),(10614,223,'呃，让我们看看。 互联网上的初学者是上学期的。这学期是在网上找研究资料。',295000,'Er, let''s see. The one on the Internet for beginners was last term.This-term it''s finding research materials online.（Q28/29/30）',1,285000),(10615,223,'这听起来也很有趣，最后一个是什么？',295000,'That sounds interesting too, hum, what''s the last one?',1,295000),(10616,223,'这是一个关于论文的研讨会。',303140,'It''s a workshop on dissertations.（Q28/29/30）',1,295000),(10617,223,'你是什么意思 - 如何写一个？',305890,'What do you mean - how to write one?（Q28/29/30）',1,303140),(10618,223,'呃......不，它更多地与学术写作惯例有关，你知道 - 编写参考书目以及如何在你的文本中引用资源。',314600,'Er...no it''s more to do with academic writing conventions, you know - writing a bibliography and how to refer to sources in your text.',1,305890),(10619,223,'之类的东西。 不管怎样，这里有一份传单，里面有关于这三个方面的信息。',319220,'That sort of thing. Anyway, here''s a leaflet with information about all three.',1,314607),(10620,223,'非常感谢。 那将非常有用。',322340,'Thanks a lot. That''ll be very useful.',1,319225),(10621,223,'别客气。',323428,'You''re welcome.',1,322348),(10622,224,'好吧，大多数人认为狮子只来自非洲。',65860,'Well, most people think that lions only come from Africa.',1,61523),(10623,224,'“可以原谅你，你如果这样想的话，因为事实上大多数狮子确实来是自非洲。”',71190,'And you would be forgiven for thinking this, because in fact most lions do come from Africa.',1,65863),(10624,224,'但情况并非总是如此。',74090,'But this hasn''t always been the case.',1,71198),(10625,224,'“如果我们回到一万年前，我们会发现有狮子在地球的广阔的地区漫步。”',80690,'If we go back ten thousand years we would find that there were lions roaming \nvast sections of the globe.',1,74092),(10626,224,'但不幸的是，现在狮子以前的栖息地只剩下很小的一部分。',87650,'But now, unfortunately, only very small sections of the lions'' former habitat remain.',1,80693),(10627,224,'我特别感兴趣的是亚洲狮，它是非洲狮的一个亚种。',93980,'My particular interest is Asiatic lions, which are a sub-species of African lions.',1,87655),(10628,224,'亚洲狮作为一个亚种分裂和发展至今已有近十万年的历史。',100000,'It''s almost a hundred thousand years since the Asiatic lions split off and developed as a sub-species.（Q31）',1,93985),(10629,224,'曾经，亚洲狮生活在遥远的西方，一直到希腊，它们在那里被发现，后分布在一个向东穿过中东各国，一直延伸到印度的地带。',111790,'At one time the Asiatic lion was living as far west as Greece and they were found from there, in a band that spread east through various countries of the Middle East, all the way to India.',1,100000),(10630,224,'“在博物馆里，你现在可以看到印有亚洲狮清晰图像的希腊硬币。”',118470,'In museums, you can now see Greek coins that have clear images of the Asiatic lion on them.（Q32）',1,111799),(10631,224,'它们中的大多数可追溯到公元前 500 年左右。',122540,'Most of them are dated at around 500 B.C.',1,118473),(10632,224,'然而，欧洲在两千年前看到了它的最后一只亚洲狮子自由漫游。',128320,'However, Europe saw its last Asiatic lion roaming free two thousand years ago.（Q33）',1,122542),(10633,224,'“在接下来的 1900 年里，其他地区的亚洲狮的数量稳步下降，但直到 19 世纪，它们才从除印度以外的任何地方消失。”',140530,'Over the next nineteen hundred years \nthe numbers of Asiatic lions in the other areas declined steadily, but it was only in \nthe nineteenth century that they disappeared from everywhere but India.',1,128329),(10634,224,'那么，您如何区分亚洲狮和您可能更熟悉的非洲狮呢？ 嗯，总的来说，亚洲狮没有非洲狮那么大。',153370,'So, how can you tell an Asiatic lion from an African lion, with which you''re probably more familiar? Well, in general, Asiatic lions are not as big as African lions.',1,140537),(10635,224,'颜色或多或少相同，但鬃毛的外观不同 - 那是狮子脸部和颈部周围的毛发。',161240,'The colour is more or less the same, but the appearance of the mane is different - that''s the hair around the lion''s face and neck.',1,153377),(10636,224,'亚洲狮的鬃毛明显短于非洲狮。',166700,'The Asiatic lion''s mane is noticeably shorter than the African lion''s.',1,161244),(10637,224,'亚洲狮子的下侧也有很长的皮肤褶皱，而非洲狮子没有很多。',178360,'Asiatic lions also have a long fold of skin on their undersides, whereas not many  African lions have this.（Q34）',1,166704),(10638,224,'好吧，我现在想和你谈谈印度的吉尔保护区。',183160,'Well, I''d like to talk to you now about the Gir Sanctuary in India.',1,178369),(10639,224,'那是我刚回来的地方。',185960,'That''s where I''ve just come back from.',1,183161),(10640,224,'该保护区是专门为保护亚洲狮而设立的。',190120,'The sanctuary was established specifically to protect the Asiatic lion.',1,185965),(10641,224,'面积1450平方公里，大部分为森林。',196180,'It''s 1,450（Q35） square kilometres in area and most of it is forest.',1,190124),(10642,224,'印度现在大约有三百头亚洲狮子，几乎所有的亚洲狮子都在这个保护区。',203810,'There are now around three hundred Asiatic lions in India and almost all of them are in this sanctuary.',1,196182),(10643,224,'但是，尽管生活在避难所中，这使它们免受猎人的伤害，但它们仍然面临着许多威胁其生存的问题。',211860,'But despite living in a sanctuary, which makes them safe from hunters, they still face a number of problems that threaten their survival.',1,203816),(10644,224,'生存问题其中之一就是永远存在的危险疾病\n。',215750,'One of these is the ever-present danger of disease.（Q36）',1,211864),(10645,224,'“这就是 1994 年杀死超过三分之一非洲塞伦盖蒂狮子的原因，人们担心吉尔保护区可能会发生类似的事情，并杀死那里的许多亚洲狮子。”',230000,'This is what killed more than a third of Africa''s Serengeti lions in 1994, and  \npeople are fearful that something similar could happen in the Gir Sanctuary and kill off many of the Asiatic lions there.',1,215752),(10646,224,'印度的狮子特别脆弱，因为它们的基因库有限。',235730,'India''s lions are particularly vulnerable because they have a limited gene pool.',1,230000),(10647,224,'这样做的原因很有趣——因为它们都是几十只狮子的后裔，这些狮子被一位对它们特别感兴趣的王子所救。',245680,'The reason for this is interesting - it''s because all of them are descended from a few dozen lions that were saved by a prince（Q37） who took a particular interest in them.',1,235736),(10648,224,'他非常富有，而且他设法保护了他们——否则他们可能已经完全灭绝了。',252730,'He was very wealthy, and he managed to protect them - otherwise they''d probably have died out completely.',1,245682),(10649,224,'当你在印度看到亚洲狮时，你感受到的是巨大的生命力。',258690,'When you see the Asiatic lion in India, what you sense is enormous vitality.',1,252735),(10650,224,'它们是非常令人印象深刻的野兽，当你看着它们时，你永远不会猜到它们有这个弱点。',265650,'They''re very impressive beasts and you would never guess that they had this vulnerability when you look at them.',1,258695),(10651,224,'我应该补充一点，亚洲狮并没有自己的吉尔庇护所。',270000,'The Asiatic lions don''t have the Gir Sanctuary to themselves, I should add.',1,265657),(10652,224,'实际上，他们大约与两千名农民分享。',274240,'They actually share it with about two thousand farmers.',1,270000),(10653,224,'事实上，狮子的饮食中有很大一部分是这些农民的牲畜——山羊、鸡等——他们的比例高达三分之一。',283650,'A significant proportion of the lions'' diet（Q38） is made up of the livestock of these farmers - goats, chickens and so on - as much as a third, in fact.',1,274248),(10654,224,'它们甚至会攻击人类，尤其是在干旱时期。',289710,'And they''ve even been known to attack（Q39） humans, especially in times of drought.',1,283652),(10655,224,'最后一条有趣的信息——在古印度，对一个人的领导能力的最大考验之一就是与狮子搏斗。',298300,'One final piece of interesting information - in ancient India one of the greatest tests of leadership（Q40） for a ma