romised to discontinue \nthis practice.',1,201938),(10729,226,'由于这张婴儿床在各个方面都是安全的，因此我们将 Mother''s Choice 婴儿床作为我们的最佳选择。',211190,'As this cot will then be safe in every way, we have made the Mother''s Choice cot our best buy.(Q19)',1,204954),(10730,226,'恭喜 Mother''s Choice！那么，您应该在婴儿床上寻找哪些功能呢？ 很明显，安全是一个非常重要的因素，以及舒适和便利。',223580,'Congratulations Mother''s Choice! So, what features should you look for in a baby''s cot? Well obviously safety is a very important factor as well as comfort and convenience.',1,211196),(10731,226,'我们建议，如果您要购买婴儿床，请确保存在的任何金属都没有生锈或以任何方式弯曲。',230900,'We recommend that, if you are buying a cot, do make sure that any metal present is not rusted or bent in any way.',1,223587),(10732,226,'您应该确保您的婴儿床只有圆形或光滑的边缘，没有任何锋利的边缘，这对于木制婴儿床尤其重要。',240300,'You should ensure your cot has only rounded or smooth edging without any sharp(20) edges, this is especially important for wooden cots.',1,230903),(10733,226,'现在是幼儿床。',243480,'And now on to beds for toddlers.',1,240309),(10734,227,'打扰一下，有人告诉我来这里咨询一下，呃，管理文凭课程？',51760,'Excuse me, I was told to come here for advice about, erm, Management Diploma courses?',1,44328),(10735,227,'你肯定来对地方了。嗨，我的名字是莫妮卡。',56050,'You''ve certainly come to the right place. Hi, my name is Monica.',1,51762),(10736,227,'很高兴见到你。我的名字是安德鲁，安德鲁哈里斯。',60060,'Nice to meet you. My name is Andrew, Andrew Harris.',1,56054),(10737,227,'那么，安德鲁，你看过我们的文凭课程简介了吗？',65120,'So, Andrew, have you seen our diploma course prospectus yet?',1,60063),(10738,227,'是的，我已经看过了。事实上，我认为关于课程内容的信息真的很有用，但恐怕我对你可以完成课程的所有不同方式感到有点困惑：全日制高强度、非全日制等等。',80930,'Yes, I''ve already looked at it. In fact, I thought the information on course content was really useful, but I''m afraid I''m a bit confused by all the different ways you can do the course: full-time intensive, part-time and so on.',1,65123),(10739,227,'好吧，让我们看看我能不能帮忙。我认为每种课程类型都有其优点和缺点，所以这真的取决于你——你自己的学习习惯，当然还有你的经济状况。你现在在工作吗？',96850,'Well, let''s see if I can help. I think each course type has its advantages and disadvantages, so it really depends on you - your own study habits, and your financial circumstances, of course. Are you working at the moment?',1,80933),(10740,227,'是的。在过去的三年里，我一直在当地医院的行政部门工作。在此之前，我在一家计算机工程公司的办公室工作了两年。所以，我有大约五年的相关工作经验。我希望注重的是人事管理。',115470,'Yes. I''ve been working in the administration section of the local hospital for the last three years(Q21). And before that I worked in the office of a computer engineering company for two years. So, I''ve got about five years of relevant work experience. And what I''m hoping to focus on is Personnel Management.',1,96853),(10741,227,'我知道了。你是打算辞去目前的工作去学习，还是考虑休一年假？',123620,'I see. And are you planning to leave your current job to study, or are you thinking about just taking a year off?',1,115476),(10742,227,'我想知道我的选项是什么，真的。我不想辞掉我的工作或任何事情，我的雇主希望我获得更多的资格，但显然，如果我能在不花太多时间离开工作的情况下参加课程会更好。',140180,'I want to know what my options are, really. I don''t want to quit my job or anything and my employers are keen for me to get some more qualifications but obviously, it would be better if I could do a course without taking too much time away from work.',1,123625),(10743,227,'对，那么你真的不想修全日制课程吗？',144830,'Right, so you don''t really want to do the full-time course, then?',1,140188),(10744,227,'不，不想。这也是一个财务问题。你看，我的办公室已经同意支付课程本身的费用，但如果我想全日制学习，我将不得不休无薪假，而且，我认为我无法在没有薪水的情况下养活自己整整一年。',162840,'No, not really. It''s also a question of finances. You see, my office have agreed to pay the cost of the course itself(Q22), but I would have to take unpaid leave if I want to study full-time and, well, I don''t think I could afford to support myself with no salary for a whole year.',1,144831),(10745,227,'好的。好吧，你还有另外两种可能性：你可以参加非全日制课程——那将是两年多的时间，而且你不必请假——或者你可以参加我们所说的“模块化”课程。',177710,'OK. Well, you have two other possibilities: you could either do the part-time course - that would be over two years(Q23) and you wouldn''t have to take any time off work - or you could do what we call a ''modular'' course.',1,162842),(10746,227,'如果你愿意，你可以在 18 个月内做到这一点——或者更长时间，它非常灵活，这取决于你。',184000,'You could do that in eighteen months if you wanted - or longer, it''s quite flexible and it would be up to you.',1,177710),(10747,227,'嗯。那么兼职课程包括哪些内容呢？',187730,'Mmm. So what does the part-time course involve?',1,184001),(10748,227,'为此，您将参加夜校并每周进行两次讲座。',192620,'For that you would join an evening class and have a lecture twice a week.',1,187731),(10749,227,'然后，您必须每月一个周末参加研讨会或讨论会。',198170,'Then, you''d have to attend a seminar or discussion workshop one weekend a month.',1,192627),(10750,227,'我必须做什么样的课程作业？',200830,'What kind of coursework would I have to do?',1,198172),(10751,227,'嗯，由各种各样的组成。你应该每个月写一篇文章，这将计入你的最终评估。在课程结束前你有一个案例研究要做，这可能涉及进行调查或类似的事情，而且你需要每四个星期提交一份简短的报告。',218340,'Well, it''s a mixture. You''d be expected to write an essay(Q24) each month, which counts towards your final assessment. You have a case study to do by the end of the course, which might involve doing a survey or something like that, and also you need to hand in a short report(Q25) every four weeks.',1,200834),(10752,227,'所以，除了每天工作之外，还有很多工作。这听起来像是很多学习——而且真的很累。',226430,'So, that''s quite a lot of work, then, on top of working every day. It sounds like a lot of studying - and really tiring.',1,218346),(10753,227,'是的，你肯定不会有太多空闲时间！',267740,'Yes, you certainly wouldn''t have much free time!',1,226432),(10754,227,'“模块化”课程怎么样？我必须为此做些什么？',271640,'What about the ''modular'' course? What would I have to do for that?',1,267744),(10755,227,'这就是你有机会在短期内全日制学习的地方。',276640,'That''s where you get the opportunity to study full-time(Q26) for short periods.',1,271647),(10756,227,'这样，您就可以在白天完成大量课程作业并参加讲座和研讨会。',281730,'That way you can cover a lot of coursework and attend lectures and seminars during the day.',1,276647),(10757,227,'每个模块持续一个学期，比如说，一次大约十二周。这有明显的优势 - 主要是您可以以更密集的方式学习，这更适合某些人。',295660,'And each module lasts for one term(Q27), say, about twelve weeks at a time. There are obvious advantages in this - the main one being that you can study in a much more intensive(Q28) way, which suits some people much better.',1,281734),(10758,227,'我需要做多少这些“模块”才能获得文凭？',300420,'And how many of these ''modules'' would I have to do to get the diploma?',1,295663),(10759,227,'目前的计划是两个模块 - 然后你必须选择一个主题来更深入地工作 - 但你可以根据你的工作，所以你不需要离开办公室，需要多长时间由你决定。',313530,'The current programme is two modules(Q29) - and then you have to choose a topic(Q30) to work in more depth - but you can base that on your job, and so you don''t need to be away from the office, and how long it takes is up to you.',1,300427),(10760,227,'重要的是你不必学习和工作。你可以一次专注于一件事。',320050,'The important thing is that you don''t have to study and work. You can focus on one thing at a time.',1,313536),(10761,227,'是的，我可以看到。听起来确实很有吸引力！不过，它会更贵。',325480,'Yes, I can see that. It certainly sounds attractive! It would be more expensive, though.',1,320058),(10762,227,'我的意思是，我必须在每个模块进行时无薪养活自己。',329150,'I mean, I''d have to support myself without pay for each module.',1,325488),(10763,227,'这是真的，所以这对你来说可能是个问题。听着，你为什么不和你的雇主商量一下，然后......',335810,'That''s true, so that might be a problem for you. Look, why don''t you talk this over with your employers and .. .',1,329150),(10764,228,'好的，所以我们一直在研究各种社会和文化群体对个人财务管理的态度——他们认为存钱有多重要，以及他们存钱的目的是什么。',76270,'OK, so we''ve been looking at the attitudes of various social and cultural groups towards the management of their personal finances - how important they feel it is to save money, and what they save their money for.',1,62360),(10765,228,'我们尚未考虑的一个方面是性别。',79930,'One aspect that we haven''t yet considered is gender.',1,76273),(10766,228,'因此，如果我们考虑性别问题，我们基本上是在问男性和女性对存钱的态度是否不同，以及他们是否为不同的事情存钱。',89960,'So if we consider gender issues we''re basically asking whether men and women have different attitudes towards saving money, and whether they save money for different things.',1,79935),(10767,228,'早在 1928 年，英国作家乔治·伯纳德·肖 (George Bernard Shaw) 在他的《智能女性社会主义和资本主义指南》中写道，“男人应该了解政治、经济和金融，因此不愿意接受必要的指导。”',106180,'Back in 1928 the British writer George Bernard Shaw wrote in his Intelligent Women''s Guide to Socialism and Capitalism that ''A man is supposed to understand politics(Q31), economics and finance and is therefore unwilling to accept essential instruction.''',1,89962),(10768,228,'他还说，“不那么自负的女人，更愿意学习”。',112300,'He also said, ''A woman, having fewer pretensions, is far more willing to learn''.(Q32)',1,106183),(10769,228,'现在，尽管现在人们可能会对这些陈述中包含的许多假设提出质疑，但最近的研究确实表明，男性和女性对经济问题的态度存在一些非常根本的差异。',126880,'Now, though these days people might question a lot of the assumptions contained in those statements, recent research does suggest that there are some quite fundamental differences between men and women in their attitudes to economic matters.',1,112303),(10770,228,'让我们看看男人和女人实际上是为了什么而存钱的。',131640,'Let''s look at what men and women actually save for.',1,126883),(10771,228,'对北美女性的研究发现，女性更有可能为孩子的教育存钱，她们也更有可能存钱买房。',144800,'Research studies of women in North America have found that women are far more likely to save for their children''s education(Q33) and they are also more likely to save up in order to buy a house one day.',1,131640),(10772,228,'另一方面，同样的研究还发现，男性倾向于为买车而存钱，顺便说一下，在北美，买车占家庭预算的比例高得惊人。',150860,'The same studies have found that men, on the other hand, tend to save for a car(Q34), which by the way takes a surprisingly large amount of the household budget in North America.',1,144806),(10773,228,'顺便说一句，这在北美占据了惊人的大量家庭预算。',156510,'which by the way takes a surprisingly large amount of the household budget in North America.',1,150867),(10774,228,'但男性存钱的另一个主要优先事项是退休。',161570,'But the other main priority for men when saving money is their retirement.',1,156515),(10775,228,'当他们赚钱时，他们比女性更有可能为晚年存钱。',168110,'When they''re earning, they''re far more likely to put money aside for their old age than women are.',1,161571),(10776,228,'现在这相当令人不安，因为事实上女性为老年储蓄的需求远大于男性。',178200,'Now this is rather disturbing, because in fact the need for women to save for their old age is far greater than for men.',1,168113),(10777,228,'让我们考虑一下。',180560,'Let''s consider this for a moment.',1,178204),(10778,228,'首先，在全世界范围内，女性的寿命可能比男性长很多年，因此她们需要钱来支持她们在此期间的生活，这是一个事实。',191170,'To start with, it is a fact that throughout the world, women are likely to live many years longer than men, so they need \nmoney to support them during this time.',1,180569),(10779,228,'由于女性很可能在老年时没有伴侣，因此她们可能不得不支付护理费用，因为她们没有配偶来照顾她们。',202120,'Since women are likely to be the ones left without a partner in old age, they may therefore have to pay for nursing care(Q35), because they don''t have a spouse to look after them.',1,191171),(10780,228,'此外，北美的高离婚率正在为女性创造一个贫困循环。',209060,'Furthermore the high divorce rates in North America are creating a poverty cycle for women.',1,202124),(10781,228,'离婚妇女往往需要照顾孩子，因此她们需要更多的钱来照顾自己和他人。',224080,'It is the divorced women who will most often have to look after the children and thus they need more money to look after not just themselves but others.',1,209065),(10782,228,'那么对于这种情况可以做些什么呢？北美的人口中可能有越来越多的老年妇女。',233150,'So what can be done about this situation? The population in North America is likely to contain an increasing number of elderly women.',1,224086),(10783,228,'研究表明，目前对女性来说，需要一场危机才能让她们考虑未来的财务状况。',241110,'The research indicates that at present for women it takes a crisis(Q36) to make them think about their future financial situation.',1,233157),(10784,228,'但当然，对于任何人来说，这是做出重要决定的最糟糕的时刻。',246340,'But of course this is the very worst time for anyone to make important decisions.',1,241119),(10785,228,'今天的女性需要向前看，提前思考——而不是等到她们面临压力。',253000,'Women today need to look ahead, think ahead - not wait until they''re under pressure.',1,246341),(10786,228,'例如，即使是二十出头的女性也需要考虑养老金，随着越来越多的女性担任专业职务，有迹象表明这种情况正在开始发生。',264970,'Even women in their early twenties(Q37) need to think about pensions, for example, and with increasing numbers of women in professional positions there are signs that this is beginning to happen.',1,253003),(10787,228,'然后研究还表明，由于缺乏信心，女性避免有效地处理自己的经济状况。',273900,'Then research also suggests that women avoid dealing effectively with their economic situation because of a lack of confidence.(Q38)',1,264974),(10788,228,'他们克服这个问题的最佳方法是让自己获得适当的信息，这样他们就可以减少对他人建议的依赖。',283160,'The best way for them to overcome this is by getting themselves properly informed so they are less dependent on other people''s advice.',1,273904),(10789,228,'已经制定了许多举措来帮助他们做到这一点。',287570,'A number of initiatives have been set up to help them do this.',1,283163),(10790,228,'例如，这所学院是提供资金管理夜间课程的教育机构之一，越来越多的女性正在参加此类课程。',299320,'This College, for example, is one of the educational institutions which offers night classes in Money Management(Q39), and increasing numbers of women are enrolling on such courses.',1,287570),(10791,228,'在这里，他们可以就不同的储蓄方式获得建议。',303520,'Here, they can be given advice on different ways of saving.',1,299327),(10792,228,'例如，许多女性不愿意投资股票和股票，但这些可能是非常有利可图的。',311530,'Many women are unwilling to invest in stocks and shares, for instance, but these can be extremely profitable.',1,303529),(10793,228,'通常建议一个人至少 70% 的储蓄应该用于低风险投资，但对于其余部分，财务顾问通常建议承担一些消息灵通的风险。',324730,'It is usually advised that at least 70% of a person''s savings should be in low-risk investments(Q40) but for the rest, financial advisors often advise taking some well-informed risks.',1,311538),(10794,228,'诸如此类的举措可以为女性提供舒适、独立的退休生活所需的经济技能和知识。',332640,'Initiatives such as this can give women the economic skills and knowledge they need for a comfortable, independent retirement.',1,324738),(10795,228,'人口中老年妇女比例的增加可能会产生其他经济后果。',339590,'The increasing proportion of elderly women in the population is likely to have other economic consequences.',1,332647),(10796,229,'早上好，北学院图书馆。我怎么帮你？',88890,'Good morning, North College Library. How can I help you?',1,85247),(10797,229,'我想知道是否可以加入图书馆。',91870,'I was wondering if it was possible to join the library.',1,88897),(10798,229,'你是北大的学生吗？',93960,'Are you a student at North College?',1,91878),(10799,229,'不，我不是，但有人告诉我可以加入，即使我不是。',98210,'No, I''m not, but someone told me it was possible to join, even if I wasn''t.',1,93965),(10800,229,'没错，就是这样。你18岁以上吗？这是我们的最低加入年龄。',103320,'That''s right, 