 of money.',1,189697),(10871,230,'我们准备好运送自行车的集装箱，但没有钱支付账单。',198330,'We had containers of bikes ready to send, but no money to pay the bills.(Q15)',1,193527),(10872,230,'这是一个可怕的情况。',200700,'It was a terrible situation.',1,198339),(10873,230,'我们设法确保自行车准时出动，但其他问题持续了几个月。',243120,'We managed to ensure the bikes went out on time, but the other problems carried on for several months.',1,200701),(10874,230,'幸运的是，我们在 2001 年 10 月获得了企业奖，这对我们帮助很大。',249430,'Fortunately in October 2001 we won an Enterprise Award which helped us enormously.',1,243121),(10875,230,'我们投资了七万五千英镑奖金中的一万五，以帮助确保我们的未来。',256030,'We invested fifteen of the seventy-five-thousand-pound(Q16) prize money to help secure our future.',1,249439),(10876,230,'赢得该奖项有助于提升我们的形象，而这笔钱使我们能够支付我们所有的运费，这是我们最大的开支。',265460,'Winning the award helped raise our profile, and the money enabled us to pay all our shipping costs, which represent our greatest expense.',1,256030),(10877,230,'Pedal Power 改变生活——当有人从我们这里得到一辆自行车时，他们的收入增加了 14%。',273010,'Pedal Power changes lives - when someone gets a bicycle from us, they see a 14% increase in their income.',1,265460),(10878,230,'我们目前正在寻求投资计算机，以便我们的办公室工作人员可以做得更好。',279280,'We''re currently looking to invest in computers(Q17) so that our office staff can do an even better job.',1,273019),(10879,230,'由于我们的工作，许多国家的人们现在有了更好的生活水平——到目前为止，我们已经为 46,000 人提供了自行车。',289320,'Because of our work, people in a number of countries now have a better standard of living - so far we''ve provided 46,000 people with bikes.',1,279283),(10880,230,'但我们希望在年底前送出更多，至少 50,000 个。',294050,'But we''d like to send more, at least 50,000 by the end of the year.',1,289326),(10881,230,'现在，您可以通过多种方式支持 Pedal Power 的工作，而不仅仅是拿自行车去您所在地区的收集点。',301650,'Now there are many ways in which you can support the work of Pedal Power, not just by taking a bike to a collection in your area.',1,294053),(10882,230,'我还想说，如果你确实有一辆自行车要捐赠，不管它的状况如何——如果我们不能修理它，我们会把它拆下来作为备件。',311930,'I should also like to say if you do have a bike to donate, it doesn''t matter what condition it''s in - if we can''t repair it, we''ll strip it down for spare parts.',1,301650),(10883,230,'我们总需要购买工具，而这些工具价格高昂，所以我们欢迎您提供任何东西。',319680,'Of course, to do that we always need tools(Q18), which are expensive to buy, so we welcome any that you can give.',1,311937),(10884,230,'另外，你可以联系我们办公室的志愿者，他们会建议你可以组织一些活动来为我们筹集资金。',328500,'Also, you could help by contacting the voluntary staff at our offices, they''ll be able to suggest activities you could organise to bring in funds for us.(Q19)',1,319684),(10885,230,'人们做各种各样的事情——当然包括赞助的自行车骑行。',333120,'People do all kinds of things - including, of course, sponsored bike rides.',1,328507),(10886,230,'此外，我们总是很想知道其他可以从接收自行车中受益的地方，并欢迎在旅行中去过发展中地区的人们提出建议。',344600,'Also, we''re always interested to hear of other places that would benefit from receiving a consignment of bikes,(Q20) and welcome suggestions from people who''ve been to developing regions on their travels.',1,333129),(10887,230,'我们希望通过这样的广播节目，我们将能够提高公众意识，这将导致政府组织也定期为我们提供财政支持，这是我们真正需要的。',357680,'We hope that by talking on radio programmes like this, we will be able to raise public awareness, which will lead to government organisations also giving us regular financial support, something that we really need.',1,344601),(10888,230,'如果您想了解有关在哪里捐赠旧自行车或以其他方式提供帮助的更多信息，请联系我们。',364480,'If you''d like some more information about where to donate an old bicycle or offer help in other ways please contact us on...',1,357688),(10889,231,'首先我想说，克里斯蒂娜和易卜拉欣，上周我真的很喜欢看你们关于学生生活的视频，我可以看到小组的其他人也很喜欢。 你做得很好，我希望你能从中收获很多。',58220,'First of all I''d just like to say, Cristina and Ibrahim, that I really enjoyed watching your video about student life last week, and I could see that the rest of the group did too. You did really well, and I hope that you got a lot out of it.',1,43590),(10890,231,'我想将本教程用作反馈会议，您可以在其中反思做项目的经验。 所以克里斯蒂娜，我想知道，你最喜欢制作视频的什么？',72740,'I''d like to use this tutorial as a feedback session, where you reflect on the experience of doing the project. So Cristina, I was wondering, what did you enjoy most about making the video?',1,58228),(10891,231,'我喜欢使用相机。',75200,'I liked using the camera.',1,72746),(10892,231,'你是第一次操作这样的相机吗？',78130,'Is it the first time you''ve operated one like that?',1,75205),(10893,231,'是的。',78780,'Yes, it is.',1,78130),(10894,231,'那么结果非常好！ 还有别的吗？',81960,'Well the results were very good! Anything else?',1,78787),(10895,231,'我也很喜欢拜访我们拍摄的一位英国学生。 我以前从未进过英国人的家。',89810,'I also enjoyed visiting one of the British students we filmed. I''d never been inside a British home(Q21) before.',1,81966),(10896,231,'好的，克里斯蒂娜，谢谢。 你呢，易卜拉欣？ 你喜欢什么？',94110,'OK Cristina, thanks. What about you, Ibrahim? What did you enjoy?',1,89816),(10897,231,'对我来说，这是一个很好的机会去了解其他课程的学生，因为我们小组中的每个人都在学习英语，而我们通常与学院的其他人没有太多关系。',104480,'Well for me it was a very good chance to get to know students who are on other courses, because everyone in our group is studying English, and we don''t usually have much to do with the rest of the college.',1,94116),(10898,231,'对很好。你觉得你现在会保持联系吗？',108650,'Yes, good. Do you think you''ll maintain the contact now?',1,104489),(10899,231,'但愿如此。我邀请了他们三个下周和我共进晚餐。',111900,'I hope so. I''ve invited three of them to have dinner(Q22) with me next week.',1,108650),(10900,231,'很好！如果你还没有决定要做什么，我可以告诉你他们会喜欢尝试阿拉伯菜肴。当然，这对你的英语也有好处。',121540,'Great! If you haven''t decided what to make yet I can tell you they''ll love trying Arab dishes. And of course, it''s good for your English too.',1,111903),(10901,231,'克里斯蒂娜，你发现了什么？从英语实践的角度来看，该项目最有用的方面是什么？',128550,'Cristina, what did you find? What was the most useful aspect of the project from the point of view of the English practice?',1,121544),(10902,231,'我认为，当我们被展示如何剪辑电影时，我们必须按照说明进行操作。',135900,'I think, when we were being shown how to edit the film, we had to follow the instructions.',1,128551),(10903,231,'这对我来说是非常好的做法。而且我还学到了一些我以前没听过的技术词汇。',142270,'And that was very good practice for me. And I also learned some technical(Q23) words that I hadn''t heard before.',1,135900),(10904,231,'易卜拉欣呢，你呢？什么对你的英语最有用？',146750,'What about you Ibrahim? What was the most useful for your English?',1,142279),(10905,231,'是听英国学生讲话，因为他们说话的速度不像我们课程的大多数导师那么慢。',152880,'It was listening to the British students, because they don''t speak as slowly as most of the tutors on our course.',1,146753),(10906,231,'我认为他们说话的速度很自然，所以这迫使我习惯它。他们使用很多俚语。',159430,'I think they speak at natural speed, so it forces me to get used to it. And they use a lot of slang.(Q24)',1,152888),(10907,231,'所以你学会了一些有用的新单词？',162300,'So you learned some new words which will be useful?',1,159433),(10908,231,'是的。',162760,'Yes.',1,162300),(10909,231,'好的。我很高兴它有帮助。好吧，我们已经谈到了一些关于享受和语言练习的内容。还有其他好处吗？',173330,'Good. I''m glad it helped. Well, we''ve talked a little bit about enjoyment, and about language practice. Were there any other benefits?',1,162767),(10910,231,'你觉得你还从这个项目中学到了什么？它在其他方面有用吗？',178280,'What else did you feel you''d learnt from the project? Was it useful in other ways?',1,173330),(10911,231,'是的，首先，我学会了如何使用摄像机。',183080,'Yes, well firstly, I learned how to use a video camera.',1,178282),(10912,231,'而且，我认为我真的学到了很多关于与其他人一起工作的知识。',188360,'And also, I think I really learned a lot about working together with other people.',1,183088),(10913,231,'我以前从来没有和一个团队做过任何事情，我们必须找到合作的方式。呃，妥协，有时说服别人，当他们不同意你的时候。',201770,'I''ve never done anything with a group before, and we had to find ways of cooperating(Q25), erm, and compromising, and sometimes persuading(Q26) people, when they don''t agree with you.',1,188367),(10914,231,'是的，这是一次非常有用的经历，我知道。',204630,'Yes, that is a very useful experience, I know.',1,201775),(10915,231,'你呢，易卜拉欣？',243970,'What about you, Ibrahim?',1,204631),(10916,231,'好吧，我想我学到了很多关于编辑的重要性。',247370,'Well, I think I learnt a lot about how important editing(Q27) is.',1,243975),(10917,231,'当你在拍摄时，你认为一切都会很有趣，但实际上我们最后剪掉了大约一半，然后就更好了。',255270,'When you''re filming you think that everything''s going to be interesting, but in fact we cut around half of it in the end, and then it was much better.',1,247376),(10918,231,'好的。好吧，我想问的最后一件事。作为一个群体，你认为你犯了什么错误？',264670,'Good. Well, one last thing I''d like to ask. What mistakes do you think you, as a group that is, made?',1,255278),(10919,231,'我的意思是，换一种说法，如果你必须从头再来，你有什么不同的做法吗？',270770,'I mean, to put it another way, if you had to do it all over again, is there anything you''d do differently?',1,264675),(10920,231,'我们没有很好地计划。例如，我们没有决定完成项目每个单独步骤的日期，我们应该在一开始就同意这一点，因为我们总是迟到！',285070,'We didn''t plan very well. For example, we didn''t decide on dates when we''d complete(Q28) each separate step of the project, and we should have agreed about that in the beginning, because we were always late with everything!',1,270776),(10921,231,'正确的。还要别的吗？',287010,'Right. Anything else?',1,285078),(10922,231,'我认为我们应该尝试更多地使用相机进行实验。',291440,'I think we should have tried to experiment(Q29) more with the camera.',1,287010),(10923,231,'我的意思是角度，焦点和那种东西。',295680,'I mean with angles, and the focus and that kind of thing.',1,291444),(10924,231,'所以你应该更雄心勃勃？你同意吗，易卜拉欣？',299010,'So you should have been more ambitious? Do you agree, Ibrahim?',1,295689),(10925,231,'并不。事实上，我认为我们的野心太大了。我们缺乏经验，也没有太多时间，我们试图做太多事情，想要拍一部长片。',310080,'Not really. In fact, I think we were too ambitious. We were inexperienced, and we didn''t have a lot of time, and we tried to do too much, to make a long(Q30) film.',1,299015),(10926,231,'下次我会做一个更短的，并试图让质量更好。',314180,'Next time I would make a shorter one and try to get the quality better.',1,310088),(10927,231,'嗯，这很有趣。 下学期我们将做另一个视频项目——当然，内容不同——但你将有机会将这次学到的知识付诸实践。',326660,'Well, that''s very interesting. Next semester we will be doing another video project - with a different content, of course - but you''ll have an opportunity to put into practice what you''ve learnt this time.',1,314180),(10928,231,'你有什么想法...',329260,'Do you have any ideas about ...',1,326669),(10929,232,'今晚我要和你谈谈南极洲那块非凡的大陆——偏远、充满敌意，目前永久无人居住。',70770,'Tonight I''m going to talk to you about that remarkable continent Antarctica - remote, hostile and at present uninhabited on a permanent basis.',1,60016),(10930,232,'对于早期的探险家来说，这是一场终极的生存竞赛；对于像我这样的研究人员来说，它仍然是一个充满智力挑战的地方；而对于现代游客来说，它简直就是一片美丽的荒野。',86350,'For early explorers, it was the ultimate survival contest; for researchers like me, it remains a place of great intellectual challenge; while for the modern tourist, it''s simply a wilderness of great beauty.',1,70770),(10931,232,'首先，一些事实和数据。',88610,'First, some facts and figures.',1,86359),(10932,232,'南极洲是一个极端的地方——最高、最冷、最寒冷的大陆，面积是英国的五十八倍以上。',98970,'Antarctica is a place of extremes - the highest, coldest and windiest continent and over fifty-eight(Q31) times the size of the UK.',1,88610),(10933,232,'冰盖包含了世界上几乎 70% 的淡水和 90% 的冰，但由于降雪量非常低，从技术上讲，该大陆的大部分地区令人难以置信地属于“沙漠”类别！',114400,'The ice-cap contains almost 70% of the world''s fresh water and 90% of its ice, but with very low snowfall, most of the continent technically falls unbelievably into the category of ''desert'' (Q32)!',1,98970),(10934,232,'巨大的冰山每年都会从大陆上脱落，而在冬天，周围一半的海洋会结冰，这意味着它的大小几乎翻了一番。',125200,'Huge icebergs break off the continent each year, while in winter half the surrounding ocean freezes over, which means its size almost doubles.',1,114409),(10935,232,'研究和探索已经在南极洲进行了两百多年，并涉及来自许多不同国家的科学家，他们在研究站上共同工作。',138880,'Research and exploration has been going on in Antarctica for more than two hundred years, and has involved scientists from many different countries, who work together on research stations.',1,125200),(10936,232,'在这里，科学和技术支持以极具成本效益的方式整合在一起——我们的南极研究计划有几个仅限夏季的站点和两个全年开放的站点；我在其中一个全年的。',156450,'Here science(Q33) and technical support have been integrated in a very cost-effective way - our Antarctic research programme has several summers -only stations and two all-year-round ones; I was based on one of the all-year-round ones.',1,138883),(10937,232,'研究站实际上是大约 20 人的自给自足社区。',163220,'The research stations are really self-contained communities of about twenty people.',1,156458),(10938,232,'有生活和工作空间、带大型食品店的厨房、小医院和设备齐全的健身房，以确保每个人在业余时间都能保持健康。',175300,'There''s living and working space, a kitchen with a huge food store, a small hospital(Q34) and a well-equipped gym to ensure everyone keeps fit in their spare time.',1,163223),(10939,232,'该站自己发电，并使用卫星链路与外界通信。',182840,'The station generates its own electricity and communicates with the outside world using a satellite link.',1,175309),(10940,232,'我们的站——零一——有一些特殊功能。',188000,'Our station - Zero One - had some special features.',1,182845),(10941,232,'它不是建在陆地上，而是建在数百米厚的冰架上。',194220,'It wasn''t built on land but on an ice-shelf, hundreds of metres thick.',1,188003),(10942,232,'补给品是用大型雪橇从一艘 15 公里外位于冰边的船上运到我们这里的。',201210,'Supplies were brought to us on large sledges from a ship(Q35) fifteen kilometres away at the ice edge.',1,194229),(10943,232,'生活在南极并不总是那么舒服。',206220,'Living in the Antarctic hasn''t always been so comfortable.',1,201214),(10944,232,'积雪给同一地点之前的四个站点造成了巨大的问题，这些站点被掩埋并最终被重量压碎。',216610,'Snow build-ups caused enormous problems for four previous stations on the same site, which were buried and finally crushed by the weight.',1,206226),(10945,232,'幸运的是没有人受到伤害，但这些建筑对建筑师来说是一个巨大的挑战，他们最终想出了一个非凡的解决方案——这些建筑被放置在平台上，这些平台可以通过可伸展的腿抬高到不断变化的积雪水平之上。',234870,'Fortunately no-one was hurt, but these buildings became a huge challenge to architects who finally came up with a remarkable solution - the buildings are placed on platforms(Q36) which can be raised above the changing snow level on legs which are extendable.',1,216611),(10946,232,'食物是在极地气候中生存的最重要方面之一。',245220,'Food is one of the most important aspects of survival in a polar climate.',1,234877),(10947,232,'生活在那里的人们需要从他们的食物中获得更多的能量，既要保暖又要承担繁重的体力劳动。',254250,'People living there need to obtain a lot more energy from their food, both to keep warm and to undertake heavy physical work.',1,245226),(10948,232,'也许你知道英国一个成年人平均每天可能需要大约 1,700 大卡；南极洲的某个人将需要大约 3,500 - 刚好比两倍多！这种能量由碳水化合物和脂肪含量高的食物提供。',276400,'Maybe you know that an adult in the UK will probably need about I, 700 kilocalories a day on average; someone in Antarctica will need about 3,500(Q37) - just over double! This energy is provided by foods which are high in carbohydrate and fat.',1,254258),(10949,232,'实地工作的口粮提出了一个额外的问题。',281950,'Rations for fieldwork present an additional problem.',1,276405),(10950,232,'它们需要提供最大的能量，但它们还必须紧凑且轻便，以便于运输。',290180,'They need to provide maximum energy, but they must also be compact and light for easy transport.',1,281951),(10951,232,'准备了特殊的盒子，每个盒子里有足够一个人吃二十天的食物。',296730,'Special boxes are prepared, each containing enough food for one person for twenty days.',1,290183),(10952,232,'您可能熟悉通过冷冻干燥加工的咖啡，它可以在保持食品质量的同时大大减轻重量 - 嗯，这种展示方式非常适合我们的情况。',312380,'You may be familiar with coffee processed by freeze-drying, which preserves the quality of the food product while making a large saving in weight - well, this type of presentation is ideal in our situation.',1,296738),(10953,232,'早期的极地探险者并没有这种，他们的饮食通常不足以保证他们的健康。',320020,'It wasn''t available to earlier polar explorers, whose diet was commonly insufficient for their health.',1,312386),(10954,232,'我认为站在科学的前沿对在南极工作的每个人都具有特殊的吸引力，无论以何种身份。',329410,'I think that being at the cutting edge of science has a special appeal for everyone working in Antarctica, in whatever capacity.',1,320024),(10955,232,'作为一名海洋生物学家，我自己的研究很有趣。但也许气候变化研究才是最关键的研究领域。',339790,'As a marine biologist, my own research was fascinating; but it''s perhaps climate change research that is the most crucial field of study.',1,329417),(10956,232,'在这个一般领域内，测量冰盖体积和稳定性的变化至关重要，因为这些可能对世界海平面和洋流产生深远影响。',354120,'Within this general field, surveying changes in the volume and stability of the ice-cap is vital, since these may have profound effects on world sea levels and on ocean currents（Q38）.',1,339795),(10957,232,'第二个重要领域是监测南极洲上空臭氧层空洞的大小，因为这是全球紫外线辐射水平的指标。',366520,'A second important area is monitoring the size of the hole in the ozone layer above Antarctica, since this is an indicator of global ultra-violet radiation levels.',1,354129),(10958,232,'第三，冰盖中的气泡本身就提供了一个污染指数，因为在其中冻结的是过去 50 万年以前大气的样本，这些为我们提供了农业和工业等人类活动影响的证据。',386660,'Thirdly, bubbles in the ice-sheet itself provide an index of pollution（Q39） because frozen inside them are samples of previous atmospheres over the past 500,000 years, and these provide us with evidence for the effects of such human activities as agriculture and industry.',1,366528),(10959,232,'年轻人在南极洲工作一段时间的机会越来越多——不仅是像我这样的项目中担任研究助理，而且还担任各种初级行政和技术职位，包括地图制作者的职位空缺。',407140,'There are an increasing number of opportunities for young（Q40） people to work for a period in Antarctica - not only as research assistants in projects like mine, but also in a wide range of junior administrative and technical positions including vacancies for map-makers.',1,386663),(10960,232,'我希望我提供的见解将鼓励您在这片迷人的大陆上抓住这些机会。',416660,'I hope that the insights I''ve provided will encourage you to take up these opportunities in this fascinating continent.',1,407143),(10961,233,'早上好，请坐。我怎么帮你？',128790,'Good morning, please take a seat. How can I help you?',1,124278),(10962,233,'嗯，我正在考虑买一辆新车，我想要一些建议。',133240,'Well, I''m thinking of buying a new car and I''d like some advice.',1,128792),(10963,233,'当然，是的。你有什么特别的想法吗？',137650,'Sure, yes. Had you got any particular make in mind?',1,133248),(10964,233,'我对 Lida 很感兴趣——我以前有过一辆，而且很喜欢。但我还没有真正下定决心。',144730,'I''m interested in a Lida - I''ve had one before and liked it. But I haven''t really made up my mind.',1,137654),(10965,233,'当然。我们有各种型号。嗯，对。发动机尺寸呢？有任何想法吗？',152420,'Sure. We''ve got various models. Umm, right. What about the engine size? Any ideas?',1,144734),(10966,233,'我目前拥有的是 1.2 升发动机，但我发现它在长途旅行中有点慢。',159660,'The one I''ve got at the moment''s a 1.2 litre engine but I find it a bit slow on long journeys.',1,152426),(10967,233,'这次我想要更多的力量...... 1.4 应该就好，我认为我不需要 1.6 或任何东西。',166070,'I''d like a bit more power this time ... a 1.4 （Q1）should do, I don''t think I need a 1.6 or anything.',1,159665),(10968,233,'好的。好吧，我认为您正在查看的模型是 Max。这是一张图片。',172070,'Right. Well I think the model you''re looking at is the Max. Here''s a picture.',1,166074),(10969,233,'哦，是的……你有一个吗？',175550,'Oh, yes ... have you got one in?',1,172078),(