 be to alter how they''re running things（Q26） - the management layers and the processes.',1,230596),(11227,239,'所以在你的分析中试着考虑所有的选项。Jason？',247710,'So in your analysis try to think of all the options. Jason? ',1,242132),(11228,239,'是的，这很有趣，因为我发现它是一家非常有用的公司来学习。',252590,'Yes, it''s interesting because I''ve found it a really useful company to study.',1,247711),(11229,239,'它的问题跨越了所有类型的行业，幸运的是它是如此之大——一家小型甚至中型的公司现在已经倒闭了。',262490,'Its problems cross all types of industries and it''s lucky it''s so big - a smaller or even medium-sized company would have gone under by now.',1,252598),(11230,239,'嗯嗯其实我想让你们两个做的就是今天讨论完就走，写个报告。',270480,'Ah well in fact, what I want you two to do is to go away when we''ve finished our discussion today and write a report.',1,262494),(11231,239,'在过去的几届会议上，我们对英国的电信市场进行了总体研究，我希望您以 Box Telecom 为例，并提出一些解决问题的方法。',285160,'We''ve looked in general at the telecommunications market in the UK over the last few sessions and I want you to take Box Telecom as an example and suggest some ways in which they might overcome their problems.（Q27）',1,270489),(11232,239,'并概述你为什么这么想的原因——但尽量让它与公司保持内在联系，而不是拖入其他例子。',295150,'And outline the reasons why you think as you do - but try and keep it intrinsic to the company rather than dragging in other examples.',1,285165),(11233,239,'可以吗，卡琳？',296920,' Is that OK, Karin?',1,295150),(11234,239,'是的，我想我可以做到。',299960,'Yes, I think I can do that.',1,296929),(11235,239,'就个人而言，我对此抱有很大希望。',302880,'Personally I''ve got great hopes for it.',1,299961),(11236,239,'我认为它会恢复。',304240,'I think it will recover.（Q28）',1,302889),(11237,239,'他们所做的那场广告活动非常强大，他们的产品非常创新——他们开创了新的趋势。',311880,'That advertising campaign they did was very strong and they''re very innovative with their products - they set new trends.',1,304249),(11238,239,'公司必须恢复，你不觉得吗，杰森？',315620,'The company''s got to recover, don''t you think, Jason?',1,311884),(11239,239,'嗯 - 我不确定。',317570,'Hmmm - I''m not sure.',1,315627),(11240,239,'我认为可以，但除非他们设法吸引到适当水平的投资，否则这不是定局。',323960,'I think it can but it''s not a foregone conclusion unless they manage to attract the right level of investment.',1,317572),(11241,239,'如果他们的复苏要持久，公司肯定需要提振并吸引更多高技能工人。',330830,'The company definitely needs a boost（Q29） and to attract more highly skilled workers if their recovery is to be long-lasting.',1,323963),(11242,239,'当我与营销经理交谈时，他对我说，他认为公司拥有一支优秀的管理团队——但他会这么说，不是吗——但他们不得不使用过时的生产机器，这可能花费很多才能正确。',345590,'When I was talking to the marketing manager he said to me that he thinks the company had got a great management team - but he would say that, wouldn''t he - but they are suffering from having to work with outdated production machinery and that could cost a lot to put right.',1,330833),(11243,239,'好吧，我个人认为股市是罪魁祸首。',349300,'Well, personally I think the stock market is to blame.',1,345596),(11244,239,'我认为他们对公司抱有过高的期望，然后当它没有表现时不可避免地看起来很糟糕。',355480,'I think they were expecting too much of the company and then inevitably it looked bad when it didn''t perform.',1,349309),(11245,239,'市场应该有更现实的预期。',358810,'The market should have had more realistic expectations.',1,355482),(11246,239,'卡琳，我不同意你关于广告活动的看法。',362800,'And I disagree with you about the advertising campaign Karin.（Q30）',1,358818),(11247,239,'这就是他们可以做一些创新的地方——开始销售。',367740,'That''s where they could do with some innovation（Q30） - to get sales kick-started.',1,362804),(11248,239,'无论如何，让我们看看你想出了什么。',369703,'Anyway, let''s see what you come up with.',1,367748),(11249,240,'好的，你们都安顿好了吗？好吧，首先，欢迎来到卡迪夫大学。',66070,'OK, are you all settled? Well, first of all, welcome to Cardiff University.',1,59050),(11250,240,'我在这里解释我们可以为您提供什么。',69060,'I''m here to explain what we can offer you.',1,66071),(11251,240,'现在，作为大学的新生，你可能需要某种指导来帮助你有效地利用图书馆进行学习和研究。',78170,'Now, as a new student at the university, you will probably need some sort of guidance to help you to use the library effectively to study and research.',1,69065);
INSERT INTO `cambridge_listening_item` VALUES (11252,240,'你们中的一些人询问了导游，但我们发现这让人们感到困惑。',83990,'Some of you have asked about a guided tour but we find this rather muddles people.',1,78172),(11253,240,'因此，在第一周，我们进行了一系列讨论，重点关注图书馆及其资源的不同方面。',91550,'So, in this first week, we run a series of talks which focus on different aspects of the library and its resources.（Q31）',1,83993),(11254,240,'您还会发现，要充分利用图书馆，您确实需要具备计算机知识，因此本学期我们都会开设小班课程，让您快速了解如何访问计算机上的信息。',105220,'You''ll also find that to get the most out of the library you really do need to be computer literate and so all this term we run small classes which will bring you up to speed on how to access the computer-loaded information.',1,91557),(11255,240,'好的，现在让我给你概述一下你可以使用的东西。',109930,'OK, now let me give you an outline of what''s available to you.',1,105226),(11256,240,'你会发现计算机越来越多地被用作研究工具。',114300,'You’ll find that the computers are increasingly used as a research tool.',1,109937),(11257,240,'许多学生在互联网上进行大部分研究，图书馆的计算机永久在线。',120390,'Many students do most of their research on the internet and the library computers are permanently online.',1,114304),(11258,240,'找到您需要的内容后，您会发现您可以轻松地将文本保存在您的个人计算机空间中，以便在需要时打印出来。',127260,'Having found what you need, you''ll find you can readily save texts on your personal computer space to print off when you need.',1,120392),(11259,240,'您可能认为这是获取信息的最快方式，但链接可能很慢。',132790,'You might think that it is the fastest way to get information but the links can be slow.',1,127269),(11260,240,'很明显，你可以在那里找到很多信息，但其中大部分是无用的信息，因为它来自备受争议的来源——所以要学会分辨。',141810,'Clearly you can find lots on there but much of it is useless information as it is from highly debatable sources（Q32） - so be critical.',1,132795),(11261,240,'您还会发现该库已从 MLA 等专业参考来源将几张 CD-ROM 加载到计算机上。',150210,'You''ll also find that the library has loaded several CD-ROMS onto the computers from specialist reference sources such as the MLA.',1,141815),(11262,240,'这意味着我们可以以很少的额外成本扩展我们为您提供的内容，并节省了我们投资越来越多书籍的必要性。',158070,'It means we can expand what we offer you at very little extra cost（Q33） and saves us having to invest in more and more books.',1,150210),(11263,240,' CD-ROMS 包含与参考书完全相同的信息，因为两者是一起更新的。',164120,'The CD-ROMS contain exactly the same information as the reference books as the two are updated together.',1,158076),(11264,240,'现在，你们中的大多数人都需要在工作中参考期刊文章，并且您会发现您也可以在线访问这些文章，我们鼓励您这样做。',173860,'Now most of you will need to refer to journal articles in your work and you''ll find you can also access these online and we encourage you to do so.',1,164128),(11265,240,'很明显，你们中的一些人会发现印刷版在货架上更容易获得，但恐怕最终都会逐步淘汰这些印刷版。',183020,'Clearly some of you will find the printed version more accessible as it sits on the shelves but I''m afraid the intention is to phase these out eventually.（Q34）',1,173860),(11266,240,'但是，您仍然可以打印文本版本，而不是影印期刊页面。',189260,'However, you will still be able to print off a version of the text rather than photocopying the journal pages.',1,183024),(11267,240,'所以你必须习惯在线工作。',192090,'So you must get used to working online.',1,189267),(11268,240,'当然，除了 CD-ROMS 之外，我们还有全系列的经典参考书供您使用，每本都有数份。',201930,'Naturally we do still have the full range of classic reference books, additional to the CD-ROMS, for you to use and there are several copies of each one.',1,192093),(11269,240,'这是因为你们中的一些人可能更喜欢借书而不是坐在图书馆里。',207010,'This is because some of you may prefer to borrow a book rather than sit in the library.（Q35）',1,201939),(11270,240,'这些有限制的借用时间，因此它们不会在货架上丢失太久。',212560,'There is a restricted loan time on these so that they are not missing from the shelves for too long.',1,207010),(11271,240,'虽然图书馆的每个部分都有一个部门经理，但他们很忙，因此，如果您在找东西时遇到困难，您应该咨询相关的编目助理。',223630,'Although there is a Section Manager for each part of the library, they are very busy and so, if you do get stuck looking for things, you should ask the relevant Cataloguing Assistant.',1,212567),(11272,240,'作为您的培训主管，我只是监督您的入职培训，并且在最初的一周之后不会出现。',235890,'As your Training Supervisor, I just oversee your induction（Q36） and will not be around after this initial week.',1,223633),(11273,240,'你们中的一些人可能有兴趣知道图书馆正在提供有关撰写论文的专门培训课程。',242330,'Some of you may be interested to know that the library is offering specialised training sessions on writing a dissertation.',1,235893),(11274,240,'显然，这与你们这些本科生无关；它只适用于研究生。',247980,'Obviously this is not relevant to those of you who are undergraduates; it is just for postgraduates.',1,242332),(11275,240,'您的部门将讨论论文的计划阶段 - 即您将要做什么 - 与您一起，我们将专注于它的结构。',257490,'Your department will discuss the planning stage of the dissertation - i.e. what you''re going to do - with you and we will focus on the structure of it.',1,247985),(11276,240,'但是，培训还将包括一些时间在计算机上。',261710,'However, the training will also include some time on the computers.（Q37）',1,257497),(11277,240,'我知道你们中的大多数人都知道如何组织文件，但我们可以向您展示运行数据程序的不同方法。',268550,'I realise most of you know how to organise files but we can show you the different ways to run data programmes.（Q37）',1,261717),(11278,240,'您的导师会在一开始就告诉您如何列出他们需要的章节，但您需要询问他们希望您如何组织参考书目，因为它因您的学科领域而异。',280920,'Your tutors will tell you at the outset how to set out the chapters they require but you will need to ask them how they would like you to organize the bibliography（Q38） because it varies depending on your subject area.',1,268554),(11279,240,'当你写好了一些的时候，这里的培训师会为你查看草稿版本，看看它是否可以。',286860,'When you''ve got something together the trainer here will look through the draft version for you to see if it''s OK.（Q39）',1,280921),(11280,240,'最后一点，对于那些在国外注册的人，如果您觉得需要，我们可以提供关于论文的单独会议。',296530,'And, one final point, for those of you who have registered from abroad, we can offer individual sessions on dissertations if you feel you need them.',1,286869),(11281,240,'如果您需要语言课程，可以从法务部旁边的国际中心获得。',302630,'If you require language lessons then they are available from the International Centre next to the Law Department.（Q40）',1,296531),(11282,241,'早上好。',101290,'Good morning.',1,100019),(11283,241,'早上好。我怎么帮你？',103390,'Good morning. How can I help you?',1,101291),(11284,241,'我知道学校会组织......嗯，去不同的地方旅行......',108340,'I understand that the school organises ... umm, trips to different ...',1,103393),(11285,241,'是的，我们每个月运行五个：周末三个，周三下午两个。',114530,'Yes, we run five every month: three during weekends and two Wednesday afternoon trips.',1,108347),(11286,241,'什么样的地方？',116280,'What sort of places?',1,114531),(11287,241,'好吧，显然它各不相同，但总是具有历史意义的地方，也提供各种购物场所。因为我们的学生总是问这个问题……然后我们去找那些我们知道有导游的地方，因为这为参观提供了一个很好的重点。',132860,'Well, obviously it varies, but always places of historical interest and also which offer a variety of shopping(Q1). because our students always ask about that ... and then we go for ones where we know there are guided tours(Q2), because this gives a good focus for the visit.',1,116285),(11288,241,'你们旅行远吗？',134560,'Do you travel far?',1,132869),(11289,241,'好吧。显然，我们在这里很幸运。因为我们可以说我们所有的访问都不到三个小时车程。',141470,'Well. we''re lucky here, obviously. because we''re able to say that all our visits are less than three hours drive.',1,134567),(11290,241,'它们要花多少钱？',143120,'How much do they cost?',1,141479),(11291,241,'它再次变化——一个人在 5 到 15 磅之间，取决于距离。',148840,'Again it varies - between five and fifteen pounds a head, depending on distance.',1,143129),(11292,241,'啊哈 ..',149920,'Ah ha . ..',1,148847),(11293,241,'哦，如果人数超过 12 人，我们会提供安排特别旅行的机会。',155610,'Oh, and we do offer to arrange special trips if, you know, there are more than twelve(Q3) people.',1,149921),(11294,241,'哦，对了，我会记住的。以及通常的时间是什么时候？',160330,'Oh right, I''ll keep that in mind. And what are the times normally?',1,155617),(11295,241,'我们尽量保持它相当固定，以便学生了解这种模式。我们早上八点三十分出发，下午六点回来。我们认为最好将这一天保持在相当短的时间内。',172590,'We try to keep it pretty fixed so that, that students get to know the pattern. We leave at eight-thirty a.m. and return at six p.m. We figure it''s best to keep the day fairly short.',1,160339),(11296,241,'哦是的。我们如何预订位置？',176710,'Oh yes. And how do we reserve a place?',1,172599),(11297,241,'你在布告栏上签上你的名字。你知道在哪里吗？',179830,'You sign your name on the notice board(Q4). Do you know where it is?',1,176715),(11298,241,'啊哈。我今天早上看到了。',181890,'Ah ha. I saw it this morning.',1,179838),(11299,241,'我们确实要求您提前三天注册，以便我们知道我们有足够多的人有兴趣运行它，如果需要，我们可以取消，当然全额退款。',192280,'And we do ask that you sign up three days in advance so we know we''ve got enough people interested to run it, and we can cancel if necessary, with full refund of course.',1,181891),(11300,241,'没关系，谢谢。',229220,'That''s fine, thanks. ',1,192284),(11301,241,'本学期计划进行哪些访问？',232150,'And what visits are planned for this term?',1,229223),(11302,241,'好吧，恐怕日程还没有打印出来，但是我们已经确认了日期并计划了可选的额外访问，如果您愿意，您也可以提前预订。',245410,'Right, well I''m afraid the schedule hasn''t been printed out yet, but we have confirmed the dates and planned the optional extra visits which you can also book in advance if you want to.',1,232151),(11303,241,'哦，没关系。如果你能给出一些周末的想法，那么我可以，你知道，确定什么时候见朋友，等等。',253630,'Oh that''s all right. If you can just give some idea of the weekend ones so I can, you know, work out when to see friends, et cetera.',1,245416),(11304,241,'行，可以。嗯，第一个是圣艾夫斯。',259650,'Oh sure. Well, the first one is St Ives. ',1,253631),(11305,241,'那是在 2 月 13 日，我们将只有 16 个可用位置，因为我们乘坐的是小巴。这是镇上的一天，可选择参观赫普沃斯博物馆。',272690,'That''s on the thirteenth of February(Q5) and we''ll have only sixteen places available ''cos we''re going by minibus. And that''s a day in town with the optional extra of visiting the Hepworth Museum.',1,259657),(11306,241,'啊对...是的...听起来很好。',275360,'Oh right . .. yeah . . . that sounds good.',1,272691),(11307,241,'然后是 2 月 16 日的伦敦之旅，我们将乘坐一辆中型长途汽车，所以上面会有 45 个位置，让我们看看，可选的额外设施是伦敦塔。',290320,'Then there''s a London trip on the sixteenth of February and we''ll be taking a medium-sized coach so there''ll be forty-five places on that, and, let''s see, the optional extra is the Tower of London(Q6).',1,275366),(11308,241,'哦，我已经去过了。',293150,'Oh, I''ve already been there.',1,290329),(11309,241,'之后是 3 月 3 日的布里斯托尔。',296400,'After that there''s Bristol(Q7) on the third of March.',1,293154),(11310,241,'在哪里？',297420,'Where?',1,296404),(11311,241,'布里斯托... B-R-I-S-T-O-L。',300600,'Bristol .. . B-R-I-S-T-O-L.',1,297428),(11312,241,'好的  ..',301820,'OK . ..',1,300605),(11313,241,'那是一辆不同的小巴，有 18 个座位，哦，可选的额外内容是参观 S.S. Great British。',312000,'That''s in a different minibus with eighteen places available, oh, and the optional extra is a visit to the S.S. Great Britain.',1,301828),(11314,241,'好的 .. ',314090,'OK .. .',1,312008),(11315,241,'我们将在 3 月 18 日去索尔兹伯里，那总是很受欢迎，因为可选的额外设施是巨石阵，所以我们乘坐有 50 个座位的大客车 . .',325510,'We''re going to Salisbury on the eighteenth of March and that''s always a popular one because the optional extra is Stonehenge, so we''re taking the large coach with fifty seats ...',1,314091),(11316,241,'哦好。',326990,'Oh good.',1,325518),(11317,241,'然后最后一个是三月二十三日去巴斯。',331370,'And then the last one is to Bath on the twenty-third of March.',1,326994),(11318,241,'哦是的。巴斯是罗马城吗？',334370,'Oh yes. Is Bath the Roman city?',1,331376),(11319,241,'是的，没错，那就是十六座小巴。',338200,' Yes, that''s right, and that''s in the sixteen-seater minibus.',1,334375),(11320,241,'可选访问在哪里？',340410,'And where''s the optional visit?',1,338205),(11321,241,'这是美国博物馆 - 非常值得一游。',343520,'It''s to the American Museum(Q8) - well worth a visit.',1,340413),(11322,241,'好的，那太好了，谢谢你所做的一切 . .',347370,'OK, well that''s great, thanks for all that . . .',1,343521),(11323,241,'我的荣幸。顺便说一句，如果您想了解有关任何旅行的更多信息，请查看学生报纸。',354140,'My pleasure. By the way, if you want more information about any of the trips, have a look in the student newspaper(Q9).',1,347374),(11324,241,'好的。',355060,'OK.',1,354149),(11325,241,'或者，和我的助理谈谈；她的名字是简·延托布——那是 Y-E-N-T-O-B。',363020,'Or, have a word with my assistant; her name is Jane Yentob(Q10) - that''s Y-E-N-T-O-B.',1,355063),(11326,241,'对，我明白了。非常感谢您的帮助。',366560,'Right, I''ve got that. Thank you very much for all your help.',1,363022),(11327,241,'不客气。我希望你喜欢这些旅行。',369422,'You''re very welcome. I hope you enjoy the trips.',1,366569),(11328,242,'大家下午好，欢迎来到滨江工业村。',45770,'Good afternoon everybody and welcome to Riverside Industrial Village.',1,38769),(11329,242,'在您开始参观之前，我将简要介绍一下博物馆的历史，然后再让您自行游览。',53920,'To start your visit, I''m just going to