36120,'OK ... Now what about bar five?',1,333318),(11417,243,'第五栏是关于那些因为需要公共汽车或火车才能进入城市或上班而搬家的人。',344490,'Bar five is about those people who move because they need a bus or train to get them into the city or to go to work.',1,336124),(11418,243,'好的，还有第六栏？',347360,'OK ... And bar six?',1,344490),(11419,243,'第六栏很有趣。',350140,'Bar number six is interesting.',1,347361),(11420,243,'这个原因很多——人们搬家是因为他们想住在一个更有吸引力的社区。',356790,'That reason was given quite a lot – people moving because they wanted to be in a more attractive neighbourhood(Q30).',1,350142),(11421,243,'哦，是的，非常感谢。',359870,'Oh, yes, thank you very much.',1,356790),(11422,244,'女士们，先生们，美好的一天。',59260,'Good day, ladies and gentlemen.',1,57058),(11423,244,'我今天被要求和你谈谈城市景观。',63320,'I have been asked today to talk to you about the urban landscape.',1,59260),(11424,244,'我将在演讲中重点关注两个主要领域：植被如何对城市气候产生重大影响，以及我们如何更好地利用树木来规划我们的城市，为我们提供更舒适的生活环境。',79490,'There are two major areas that I will focus on in my talk: how vegetation can have a significant effect on urban climate, and how we can better plan our cities using trees to provide a more comfortable environment(Q31) for us to live in.',1,63324),(11425,244,'树木可以对我们的城市产生重大影响。',83640,'Trees can have a significant impact on our cities.',1,79494),(11426,244,'他们可以使整个城市的风少一点或多一点，如果这是你想要的。',90810,'They can make a city, as a whole, a bit less windy or a bit more windy(Q32), if that''s what you want.',1,83645),(11427,244,'如果是澳大利亚城市炎热的夏日，它们可以让它变得更凉爽，或者如果它是一个干燥的内陆城市，它们可以让它变得更潮湿一些。',100690,'They can make it a bit cooler if it''s a hot summer day in an Australian city, or they can make it a bit more humid(Q33) if it''s a dry inland city.',1,90816),(11428,244,'在局部范围内 - 即在城市内的特定区域 - 树木可以使局部区域更阴凉、更凉爽、更潮湿且风更小。',113990,'On the local scale - that is, in particular areas within the city - trees can make the local area more shady(Q34), cooler, more humid and much less windy.',1,100698),(11429,244,'事实上，树木和各种植物可用于使城市街道在特定区域实际上不那么危险。',123990,'In fact trees and planting of various kinds can be used to make city streets actually less dangerous(Q35) in particular areas.',1,113999),(11430,244,'你问，树木是如何做到这一切的？嗯，一棵树和一栋建筑之间的主要区别在于一棵树有一个内部机制来保持温度调节。',138400,'How do trees do all that, you ask? Well, the main difference between a tree and a building is a tree has got an internal mechanism to keep the temperature regulated.',1,123995),(11431,244,'它通过叶子蒸发水分，这意味着叶子的温度永远不会和我们自己的体温差很远。',148580,'It evaporates water through its leaves and that means that the temperature of the leaves(Q36) is never very far from our own body temperature.',1,138402),(11432,244,'在炎热的晴天，建筑物表面的温度很容易比我们的温度高 20 度。',156920,'The temperature of a building surface on a hot sunny day can easily be twenty degrees more than our temperature.',1,148581),(11433,244,'另一方面，树木比建筑物更凉爽，因为它们会出汗。',163300,'Trees, on the other hand, remain cooler than buildings because they sweat.',1,156923),(11434,244,'这意味着它们可以加湿空气并使其冷却——这一特性可用于改善当地气候。',177000,'This means that they can humidify the air and cool it - a property which can be exploited to improve the local climate.',1,163300),(11435,244,'树木还可以帮助抵御风力。',180410,'Trees can also help break the force of winds.',1,177002),(11436,244,'高层建筑使地面风更大的原因是，随着风越来越高，它会越来越快。',191050,'The reason that high buildings make it windier at ground(Q37) level is that, as the wind goes higher and higher, it goes faster and faster.',1,180415),(11437,244,'当风吹到建筑物上时，它必须去某个地方。',195150,'When the wind hits the building, it has to go somewhere.',1,191052),(11438,244,'其中一些越过顶部，一些绕过建筑物的侧面，迫使那些高空风下降到地面。',203900,'Some of it goes over the top and some goes around the sides of the building, forcing those high level winds down to ground level.',1,195158),(11439,244,'当你有树时，这不会发生。',206820,'That doesn''t happen when you have trees.',1,203909),(11440,244,'树木过滤风并大大减少风，防止你经常在高层建筑周围发现的那些非常大的强阵风。',217610,'Trees filter the wind and considerably reduce it(Q38), preventing those very large strong gusts that you so often find around tall buildings.',1,206825),(11441,244,'建成区的另一个问题是高层建筑加剧了交通噪音。',225060,'Another problem in built-up areas is that traffic noise is intensified by tall buildings.',1,217617),(11442,244,'通过在路边种植树木带，您可以让事情变得更安静，但大部分车辆噪音仍然会穿过树木。',235540,'By planting a belt of trees at the side of the road, you can make things a little quieter, but much of the vehicle noise still goes through the trees.',1,225065),(11443,244,'树木还可以帮助减少周围环境的噪音，尽管效果并不像人们想象的那么大。',244480,'Trees can also help reduce the amount of noise in the surroundings, although the effect is not as large as people like to think.',1,235549),(11444,244,'尤其是低频噪声，它只是穿过树木，就好像它们不存在一样。',250420,'Low-frequency(Q39) noise, in particular, just goes through the trees as though they aren''t there.',1,244480),(11445,244,'虽然树木可以显着改善当地气候，但它们确实占用了大量空间。',258290,'Although trees can significantly improve the local climate, they do however take up a lot of space.',1,250421),(11446,244,'有要考虑的根系统和阻塞窗口的分支等等。',263970,'There are root systems to consider and branches blocking windows and so on.',1,258297),(11447,244,'因此，将树木融入当地景观可能很困难。',268770,'It may therefore be difficult to fit trees into the local landscape.',1,263978),(11448,244,'如果你有我们所说的街道峡谷——一整套高楼环绕在一条狭窄的街道上，你就无能为力了。',278500,'There is not a great deal you can do if you have what we call a street canyon - a whole set of high-rises enclosed in a narrow street.',1,268779),(11449,244,'树木需要水才能生长。',281610,'Trees need water to grow.',1,278509),(11450,244,'它们还需要一些阳光才能生长，你需要空间来放置它们。',286990,'They also need some sunlight to grow and you need room(Q40) to put them.',1,281616),(11451,244,'如果您有机会将建筑物推倒并更换它们，那么您突然可以开始寻找不同的方式来设计街道并引入……',297810,'If you have the chance of knocking buildings down and replacing them, then suddenly you can start looking at different ways to design the streets and to introduce ...',1,286997),(11452,245,'哦，彼得，你来了。',92970,'Oh, Peter, there you are.',1,90965),(11453,245,'你好久才来。是什么让你这么久？',95520,'You''ve been ages.What kept you so long?',1,92975),(11454,245,'对不起，我来晚了，莎莉。你是不是等了很久？',98560,'I''m sorry I''m so late, Sally. Have you been waiting long?',1,95529),(11455,245,'哦，半个小时。',99