'crime which is committed for the corporate organisation'' - the company - ''not against it'', unquote.',1,119030),(11577,248,'因此，根据此定义，员工盗窃等犯罪 - 诸如对实际雇主的贪污或欺诈之类的事情被排除在外。',139990,'So crimes like theft by employees(Q32) - things like embezzlement or fraud against one''s actual employer are excluded according to this definition.',1,129613),(11578,248,'员工可能参与其中，但他们首先为公司行事——他们甚至可能没有意识到自己正在犯罪，或者他们可能意识到但他们认为这是可以原谅的，因为这是政策，否则他们可能会失去工作。',158170,'The employees may be involved but they''re acting in the first place for the company - they may not even realise they''re committing a crime or they may realise but they feel it''s excusable because it''s policy, or because otherwise they may lose their jobs.',1,139993),(11579,248,'所以在这里，真的，我们谈论的是权力和犯罪之间的联系。',164070,'So here, really, we''re talking about the links between power and crime.',1,158175),(11580,248,'现在，与传统或传统犯罪相比，这是一个少为人知的领域。',172080,'Now, this is one area that much less is generally known about than conventional or traditional crime.',1,164070),(11581,248,'大众媒体相对忽视了它——例如，与新闻广播、犯罪连续剧和电影等中的传统犯罪相比，它往往被低估——它们很少处理公司犯罪。',188130,'It has been relatively ignored by the mass media(Q33) - for example, it tends to be under-reported in comparison with conventional crime in news broadcasts, and in crime serials and films and so on - they very rarely deal with corporate crime.',1,172085),(11582,248,'它在学术界也往往被忽视——对传统犯罪的研究要多得多，可用的数据也多得多。',196810,'And it also tends to be ignored in academic circles(Q34) - there''s been far more research on conventional crime and far more data is available.',1,188136),(11583,248,'与其他类型的犯罪相比，对公司犯罪缺乏兴趣有几个原因。',204050,'There are several reasons for this lack of interest in corporate crime, compared with other types of crime.',1,196816),(11584,248,'它通常非常复杂，而对于传统犯罪，通常可以在没有专业知识的情况下了解正在发生的事情。',212870,'It''s often very complex, whereas with conventional crime it''s usually possible to follow what''s going on without specialist knowledge(Q35).',1,204058),(11585,248,'除此之外，虽然传统犯罪通常具有很多人类利益，但公司犯罪通常少得多。',221300,'As well as this, whereas conventional crime usually has a lot of human interest, corporate crime often has much less.',1,212878),(11586,248,'第三个原因，也可能是最重要的一个原因，是受害者通常不知道——他们认为自己的不幸是一场意外，或者不是任何人的错。',234240,'The third reason, and possibly the most significant one, is that very often the victims are unaware(Q36) - they think their misfortune is an accident or that it''s the fault of no-one in particular.',1,221308),(11587,248,'他们不知道自己是犯罪的受害者。',238290,'They''re unaware that they''ve been victims of a crime.',1,234240),(11588,248,'因此，当我们查看公司犯罪的影响时，我们可能会发现很难评估成本。',245880,'So, when we look at the effects of corporate crime we may find it''s very difficult to assess the costs.',1,238292),(11589,248,'但这些成本在经济和社会方面都非常可观。',256260,'But these costs can be very considerable in both their economic and social aspects.',1,245887),(11590,248,'我们先来看看经济成本。',258990,'Let''s look at the economic costs first.',1,256266),(11591,248,'例如，如果一家公司正在生产果汁并将其产品稀释至略低于应有的浓度，那么数以百万计的人可能会为他们的一盒橙汁支付少量额外费用。',275380,'For example, if a company is producing fruit juice and it dilutes its product so that it''s just a little below the concentration it should be, many millions of people may be paying a small amount extra for their carton of orange juice.',1,258997),(11592,248,'现在，像这样的小额金额对于个人客户来说似乎微不足道——太小了，不用担心——但对于公司来说，这种欺骗可能会导致巨额非法利润。',287820,'Now small amounts like this may seem insignificant for individual customers(Q37) - too small to worry about - but for the company this deception might result in massive illegal profit(Q38).',1,275385),(11593,248,'然而，所有关于公司犯罪的研究都一致认为，与抢劫和盗窃等传统犯罪相比，此类犯罪实际上剥夺了个人更多的金钱。',299690,'However, all studies of corporate crime agree that the individuals are in fact deprived of far more money by such crime than they are by conventional crime like robbery and theft.',1,287823),(11594,248,'除此之外，我们还必须考虑企业犯罪的社会成本，这些成本也很难评估，但相当可观。',309210,'In addition to this, we have to consider the social costs of corporate crime and these are again very difficult to assess, but they are considerable.',1,299699),(11595,248,'它们很重要，因为它们会破坏公众对商业世界的信心，而且更重要的是，因为它们影响的主要人群实际上不是社会中较富裕的阶层，而是较贫穷的人——所以这里的公司掠夺穷人以利富人。',329750,'They''re important because they can undermine the faith of the public in the business world and also, more importantly, because the main group of people they affect are, in fact, not the richer sections of society but the poorer - so here companies are robbing the poor to benefit the rich.',1,309211),(11596,248,'还有两点与公司犯罪有关，我想参考几年前发生的特定事件来说明。',339050,'There are two more points to do with corporate crime that I''d like to illustrate with reference to a specific event which occurred several years ago.',1,329756),(11597,248,'这是一艘大型油轮的爆炸，造成五十多名船员丧生。',345410,'This was an explosion of a large oil tanker which caused the loss of more than fifty lives of the crew.',1,339053),(11598,248,'这是一次本不应该发生的爆炸，随后的调查没有将责任归咎于当时实际在油轮上的任何人，而是油轮的所有者。',358160,'It was an explosion which never should have happened and a subsequent inquiry laid the blame not on anyone who had actually been on the tanker at the time, but on the owners of the tanker.',1,345411),(11599,248,'他们故意决定不对即将出售的油轮进行必要的维修工作，而正是这种缺乏维修工作直接导致了爆炸。',370320,'They had deliberately decided not to carry out necessary repair work on the tanker as it was due to be sold, and it was this lack of repair work which was directly responsible for the explosion.',1,358164),(11600,248,'现在，这说明了与公司犯罪有关的两点。',374940,'Now this illustrates two points to do with corporate crime.',1,370323),(11601,248,'首先，它不一定是故意的。',378470,'First of all, that it does not have to be intentional.',1,374944),(11602,248,'油轮的所有者当然不打算让它爆炸。',382940,'The owners of the tanker certainly did not intend it to explode.',1,378473),(11603,248,'但是，如果个人或组织没有足够认真地考虑其行为的可能结果，则可能会导致非常严重的后果。',392940,'But very serious consequences can result from people or organisations not considering the possible results of their actions seriously enough.',1,382948),(11604,248,'这里的主要罪行是对人类结果的漠不关心，而不是真正意图伤害任何人，但这并没有减少结果的悲惨。',403000,'The main crime here was indifference to the human results rather than actual intention to harm anyone, but that didn''t make the result any less tragic(Q39&40).',1,392943),(11605,248,'这引出了我的第二点——公司犯罪可能有非常严重的后果。',411410,'And this leads me to my second point - that corporate crime can have very severe consequences.',1,403002),(11606,248,'这不仅是公司获得的利润超过其应有的利润，而是可能影响无辜者生活的事件，但公司通常会因为他们说他们无意伤害任何人，而可以避免承担责任他们行动的结果。',428750,'It''s not just a matter of companies making bigger profits than they should do, but of events which may affect the lives of innocent people, and yet very often companies, because they say they didn''t intend to harm anyone, can avoid taking responsibility for the results of their actions.',1,411417),(11607,248,'这是法律中一个非常危险的漏洞。',432530,'And that has been a very dangerous loophole in the law.',1,428750),(11608,248,'公司犯罪的另一个例子是……',436610,'A further example of corporate crime was...',1,432532),(11609,249,'Sara，听说你想搬进寄宿家庭，对吗？',103930,'SARA, I''ve heard that you want to move into a homestay family. Is that correct?',1,98563),(11610,249,'是的，这是对的。',105430,'Yes, that''s right.',1,103931),(11611,249,'我一直和阿姨住在一起，现在我表弟从新加坡来了，我阿姨需要给他房间。',112400,'I''ve been staying with my aunt and now my cousin is arriving from Singapore and my aunt needs the room for him.',1,105432),(11612,249,'哦，那真是倒霉。',114520,'Oh, that''s bad luck.',1,112408),(11613,249,'好吧，我需要先了解一些细节。',117470,'Well, I''ll need to get some particulars first.',1,114525),(11614,249,'萨拉，你的全名是什么？',119840,'Sara, what''s your full name?',1,117477),(11615,249,'Sara Lim，那是最后没有“h”的 Sara。',124250,'Sara Lim, and that''s Sara without the ''h'' at the end.',1,119841),(11616,249,'嗯..你多大了，莎拉？',127450,'Mmm... How old are you, Sara?',1,124251),(11617,249,'二十三，才刚刚。八月二十一日是我的生日。',132720,'Twenty-three, only just. It was my birthday on the twenty-first of August.',1,127456),(11618,249,'昨天生日快乐。',135760,'Happy birthday for yesterday.',1,132726),(11619,249,'你在澳大利亚多久了？',137750,'How long have you been in Australia?.',1,135764),(11620,249,'在阿德莱德待一年，在悉尼待六个月。',142070,'A year in Adelaide and six months i