 mean, I don''t want to start off something and then have to abandon it if they just can''t cope with it.',1,393444),(11951,255,'我可以看到我们最终为他们做了几乎所有的工作。',404330,'I could see us ending up doing just about all of the work for them.',1,401178),(11952,255,'我想你是对的。',405970,'I guess you''re right.',1,404335),(11953,255,'哦，好吧，也许我们可以把这个想法储存起来以备后用。',410340,'Oh well, maybe we could store that idea away for later.',1,405977),(11954,255,'是的，让我们希望这第二本书有更好的东西！',413800,'Yep, let''s hope this second book has something better!',1,410349),(11955,256,'今天我们来看看我最喜欢的鱼之一——鲨鱼。',63410,'Today we''re going to look at one of my favourite fish - the shark.',1,57965),(11956,256,'如您所知，鲨鱼以能够伤害或杀死人类的非常危险的生物而闻名，我想谈谈澳大利亚的鲨鱼。',75970,'As you know, sharks have a reputation for being very dangerous creatures capable of injuring or killing humans, and I''d like to talk about sharks in Australia.',1,63417),(11957,256,'鲨鱼是相当大的鱼，通常长到十多米，在澳大利亚捕获的最长的鲨鱼已经达到十六米。',87310,'Sharks are rather large fish, often growing to over ten metres and the longest sharks caught in Australia have reached sixteen metres.',1,75975),(11958,256,'当然，鲨鱼的重量因大小和品种而异，但在澳大利亚捕获的最重的鲨鱼是白尖鲨——重达七百九十五公斤——相当大！鲨鱼的结构与大多数鱼类不同：它们不是由骨头制成的骨架，而是具有坚韧有弹性的软骨骨架。',110880,'Sharks vary in weight with size and breed, of course, but the heaviest shark caught in Australia was a White Pointer - that weighed seven hundred and ninety-five(Q31) kilograms - quite a size! Sharks have a different structure to most fish: instead of a skeleton made of bone, they have a tough elastic skeleton of cartilage.',1,87316),(11959,256,'与骨头不同的是，这种坚硬、柔韧的材料很像你的鼻子，可以让鲨鱼在游泳时轻松弯曲。',119070,'Unlike bone, this firm, pliable material is rather like your nose, and allows the shark to bend easily as it swims.',1,110882),(11960,256,'鲨鱼的皮肤不像其他鱼那样被鳞片覆盖：而是皮肤被倒刺覆盖，使其具有像砂纸一样的粗糙纹理。',130120,'The shark''s skin isn''t covered with scales, like other fish: instead the skin''s covered with barbs, giving it a rough texture like sandpaper.',1,119073),(11961,256,'如你所知，鲨鱼的游泳速度非常快。',133570,'As you know, sharks are very quick swimmers.',1,130120),(11962,256,'这是通过它们的鳍实现的，一组在侧面，另一组在身体下方，尾巴也有助于鲨鱼快速向前移动。',144360,'This is made possible by their fins, one set at the side and another set underneath the body, and the tail(Q32) also helps the shark move forward quickly.',1,133571),(11963,256,'与其他鱼类不同，鲨鱼如果想停留在特定深度就必须不停地游动，而且它们很少在水面游动。大多数情况下，它们在海底游泳，清除并捡起躺在海底的食物。',158600,'Unlike other fish, sharks have to keep swimming if they want to stay at a particular depth, and they rarely swim at the surface. Mostly, they swim at the bottom of the ocean, scavenging and picking up food that''s lying on the ocean floor(Q33).',1,144360),(11964,256,'虽然包括鱼类在内的大多数其他动物都是通过视力来捕食猎物，但鲨鱼主要通过嗅觉来捕猎。',167260,'While most other animals, including fish, hunt their prey by means of their eyesight, sharks hunt essentially by smell.',1,158609),(11965,256,'他们有非常敏锐的嗅觉——并且在他们看到食物之前很久就能感觉到食物的存在。',179280,'They have a very acute sense of smell(Q34) - and can sense the presence of food long before they can see it.',1,167260),(11966,256,'在澳大利亚，人们大部分时间都在海滩度过，政府已经意识到必须防止鲨鱼在其海滩附近游泳。',187760,'In Australia, where people spend a lot of time at the beach, the government has realised that it must prevent sharks from swimming near its beaches.',1,179288),(11967,256,'结果，他们推出了沙滩网计划。',192050,'As a result, they''ve introduced a beach-netting program.',1,187764),(11968,256,'沙滩网或网状网涉及将大网与海岸平行设置：这意味着新南威尔士州海滩上的网是在某一天设置的。',202360,'Beach-netting, or meshing, involves setting large nets parallel to the shore(Q35): this means that the nets on New South Wales beaches are set on one day.',1,192057),(11969,256,'然后在第二天举起并出海。',205560,'And then lifted and taken out to sea on the next day.',1,202363),(11970,256,'当鲨鱼网于 1939 年首次开始使用时，只有悉尼市区的海滩被网格化——选择这些海滩是因为城市附近的海滩通常是最多游泳者的地方。',219500,'When shark-netting first began in 1939, only the Sydney metropolitan beaches were meshed - these beaches were chosen because beaches near the city are usually the most crowded with swimmers.',1,205564),(11971,256,'十年后的 1949 年，系统网格划分扩展到包括悉尼南部的海滩。',227710,'Ten years later, in 1949, systematic meshing was extended to include the beaches to the south of Sydney.',1,219501),(11972,256,'由于该项目在悉尼取得了普遍的成功，鲨鱼网在 1970 年左右被引入昆士兰州。',236270,'As a result of the general success of the program in Sydney, shark-meshing was introduced to the state of Queensland around 1970.',1,227713),(11973,256,'新西兰当局也对其进行了研究，但认为网格化不经济——太平洋的大溪地也是如此。',243730,'The New Zealand authorities also looked at it, but considered meshing uneconomical - as did Tahiti in the Pacific.',1,236271),(11974,256,'大约在同一时间，南非将网格引入其一些最受欢迎的游泳海滩。',250450,'At around the same time, South Africa(Q36) introduced meshing to some of its most popular swimming beaches.',1,243730),(11975,256,'开始啮合时，第一年就捕获了大约 1500 条鲨鱼。',257140,'When meshing began, approximately fifteen hundred sharks were caught in the first year.',1,250452),(11976,256,'然而，这在随后的几年里有所下降，从那时起，平均每年的捕捞量只有 150 只左右。',265150,'However, this declined in the years that followed, and since that time, the average annual catch has been only about a hundred and fifty(Q37) a year.',1,257140),(11977,256,'大多数鲨鱼是在最温暖的月份捕获的，从 11 月到 2 月，此时鲨鱼最活跃，空气和海洋都处于最高温度。',276450,'The majority of sharks are caught during the warmest months, from November to February(Q38), when sharks are most active and when both the air and the ocean are at their maximum temperature.',1,265155),(11978,256,'尽管捕捞量很大，但有些人认为鲨鱼啮合并不是捕捉鲨鱼的最佳方式。',282900,'Despite quite large catches, some people believe that shark meshing is not the best way to catch sharks.',1,276457),(11979,256,'并不是他们认为鲨鱼害怕网，也不是因为它们在网里吃洞，因为这些都不是真的。',289580,'It''s not that they think sharks are afraid of nets, or because they eat holes in them, because neither of these is true.',1,282908),(11980,256,'但是，网格似乎确实不如其他一些方法有效，尤其是当有大浪和强大的海流以及任何让沙子移动的东西时 - 将网压下来的沙子。',303490,'But meshing does appear to be less effective than some other methods, especially when there are big seas with high roiling waves and strong currents(Q39) and anything that lets the sand move(Q40) - the sand that''s holding the nets down.',1,289582),(11981,256,