器、玻璃器皿，甚至混凝土。',115910,'And examples of ceramics are everyday things like earthenware pots, crockery, glassware and even concrete.',1,105612),(12106,260,'这一切是怎么开始的呢？这一切大约在两万九千年前开始。那时候人们发现，如果你从地里挖出一些软质黏土，倒入模具使之成型，并加以高温，等它冷却以后，黏土就转化成了一种又硬又脆的材料。',142880,'So how did it all begin? Well it all started around 29,000 years ago when humans discovered that if you dig up some soft clay from the ground, mould it into a shape and then heat it up to a very high temperature, when it cools, the clay has been transformed into something hard and rigid.(Q31)',1,115912),(12107,260,'那么，最早的这些人是怎样利用这项发现的呢？他们创造出了小塑像，也就是小型雕像，描绘的都是动物、神明或任何黏土能塑成的形状。',159190,'And so 一 what did those first humans do with their discovery? Well 一 they created figurines which were small statues and which depicted animals or gods or any shape that the clay could be moulded into.',1,142889),(12108,260,'所有这些活动都集中在南欧，那里也有证据表明陶瓷是在很久以后才创造出来的。',169370,'And all this activity was centred around southern Europe where there is also evidence of ceramics that were created much later.(Q32)',1,159192),(12109,260,'早期人类还发现了他们的发现的实际用途，例如储存谷物之类的东西——尽管有缺点。”',180370,'The early humans also found a practical use for their discovery, such as storing things like grain - although there were drawbacks.',1,169373),(12110,260,'翻译改为：这些罐子都是多孔渗水的，所以，尽管它们能用来装水，要想长期存水是不可能的。',190860,'The pots were porous so that, although they could carry water in them, it wasn''t possible to store it over a long period.(Q33)',1,180375),(12111,260,'而且，它们很脆，如果掉下来很容易破碎。',196260,'And also, they were quite brittle and shattered very easily if they were dropped.',1,190869),(12112,260,'但尽管存在这些问题，但还是要经过数千年的时间才能有所改善。',203770,'But despite these problems, it was many thousands of years before there were any improvements.',1,196265),(12113,260,'在公元前 200 年左右的中国，他们发现通过在粘土中添加矿物质可以改善陶瓷的外观和强度。',215770,'In China at around 200 BC, they discovered that by adding minerals to the clay they could improve both the appearance and the strength of the ceramics.(Q34)',1,203771),(12114,260,'但人们也花了几乎一千年的时间，才完善了生产过程，制造出高质量的陶制品，也就是人们所知的瓷器。',225950,'But it took nearly a thousand years before they perfected the process to produce high-quality ceramics known as porcelain.',1,215779),(12115,260,'一旦他们完善了这个过程，他们就将它保密了——又是一千年！ 与最早的陶瓷相比，瓷器更轻、更细、更硬、更白，数百年来成为中国对外贸易的重要商品。',249450,'And once they had perfected the process, they kept it a secret - for another thousand years! Compared to the first ceramics, porcelain was lighter, finer, harder and whiter and became an important commodity in China''s trading with the rest of the world for hundreds of years.',1,225953),(12116,260,'事实上，瓷器变得如此珍贵，人们称其为“白色的金子”，外国派出间谍潜入中国，查探到底他们对黏土作了怎样的处理，才生产出如此高质量的商品。',264640,'In fact, it became so valuable that it was known as white gold and spies were sent to China to discover what they did to the clay to produce such high-quality merchandise.(Q35)',1,249453),(12117,260,'直到十八世纪，这个秘密才开始揭开。',271530,'It wasn''t until the eighteenth century that the secret began to unravel.',1,264644),(12118,260,'国王要求一位名叫约翰·弗里德里希·博特格的德国炼金术士用铅炼金。',281470,'A German alchemist called Johann Friedrich Bottger was asked by the king to make gold out of lead.',1,271535),(12119,260,'不幸的是，Bottger 没能做到这一点，很快就放弃了，但为了取悦国王，他尝试制作高品质的瓷器。',293060,'Unfortunately, Bottger failed to achieve this and soon gave up, but in order to please the king he attempted to make high-quality porcelain.',1,281476),(12120,260,'经过多年的实验，他发现通过在非常优质的粘土中添加石英和一种称为瓷石的材料，他成功地获得了与中国人在过去 1000 年中所取得的相同结果。',317000,'And after many years of experimentation, he discovered that by adding quartz and a material called china stone to very high-quality clay he managed to get the same results that the Chinese had been achieving for the last 1,000 years.(Q36)',1,293061),(12121,260,'现在看看另一种陶瓷，它是用沙子和矿物质混合并加热到超过 600 摄氏度制成的。',327300,'Well now look at another ceramic which is made from mixing sand with minerals and heating to over 600 degrees Celsius.',1,317009),(12122,260,'当这种混合物冷却时，结果当然是玻璃。',333450,'When this mixture cools the result is of course glass.',1,327308),(12123,2