产生的二氧化碳。',158940,'To my mind, the reports talk too much about the carbon dioxide produced by the trucks that deliver the fresh goods to the shops andtake the waste away.',1,148387),(12607,271,'他们忘记了二氧化碳的关键原因之一。',163950,'They forget about one of the key causes of carbon dioxide.',1,158947),(12608,271,'当然，如果这些报告真的对人们有用，那么它们需要更加全面。',172430,'Absolutely,If the reports are actually going to be useful to people, they need to be more comprehensive.',1,163950),(12609,271,'你说的“人”是指谁？',175210,'Who do you mean by ''people''?',1,172435),(12610,271,'好吧，政府，行业……制作电视节目的人。',181030,'Well, the government, industries ... people making television programmes.',1,175213),(12611,271,'你有看过关于食品浪费的纪录片吗？',185070,'Have you seen any documentaries about food waste?',1,181035),(12612,271,'印象中没有。',187160,'Not that I remember.',1,185075),(12613,271,'我的观点正是。这些天来，他们似乎都在关注你的肉、水果和蔬菜的来源。',196680,'My point exactly. These days they all seem to be focusing on where your meat,fruit and vegetables are sourced from.(Q23)',1,187164),(12614,271,'我们被鼓励在本地购买，而不是从海外购买。',201060,'We''re being encouraged to buy locally, not from overseas.',1,196687),(12615,271,'这可能是一件好事，但我仍然希望看到一些关于浪费的东西。',207190,'That''s probably a good thing but I''d still like to see something about waste.',1,201067),(12616,271,'对，杂志文章也是这样的，全都在说脂肪含量、含糖量、食品中的添加剂和色素，但从来不谈食品是怎样送上饭桌的，也没谈过食品倒到垃圾桶后会发生什么。',225100,'Yes., it''s the same with magazine articles - it''s all about fat and sugar content and the kind of additives and colouring in food - but nothing about how it reaches your table and what happens after it ends up in the bin.',1,207197),(12617,271,'好吧，我们只有 15 分钟的演讲时间，所以我认为我们必须限制我们对食物浪费后果的看法。',235900,'Well, we''ve only got 15 minutes for this presentation, so I think we''ll have to limit what we say about the consequences of food waste.',1,225108),(12618,271,'我们要专注于什么？',238990,'What do we want to concentrate on?',1,235906),(12619,271,'我知道有别的成果展示会谈到食品、耕作方法和对环境的影响，所以，我觉得我们可以省去这些内容。',251750,'Well, I know some of the other presentations are\r\nlooking at food and farming methods and what they do to the environment, so I think we''ll avoid that.',1,238996),(12620,271,'而在一些国家，人们买不起自己农场种植的食物——这在上学期已经讨论过了。',260610,'And the fact that in some countries, people can''t afford the food grown on their own farms - that was covered last term.',1,251759),(12621,271,'好的。我们不想重复。',264220,'OK. We don''t want to repeat stuff.',1,260615),(12622,271,'最让我担心的是，在经济衰退中，政府应该鼓励企业寻找削减成本的方法。',274210,'What concerns me above all else is that in a recession governments should be encouraging business to find ways to cut costs.(Q24)',1,264220),(12623,271,'显然，美国的超市有 11% 的水果被浪费掉了。',281390,'Apparently supermarkets in the USA lose about 11 % of their fruit to waste.',1,274211),(12624,271,'那就是把钱扔了。',283810,'That''s throwing money away.',1,281396),(12625,271,'好吧——我们将专注于那个问题。无论如何，它应该引起其他人的注意。',290310,'All right - we''ll focus on that problem. It should get the others'' attention, anyway.',1,283811),(12626,271,'现在，您想如何开始演示？',295120,'Now, how do you want to begin the presentation?',1,290317),(12627,271,'不过，我们不要从统计开始，因为这是每个人都会做的事情。',300540,'Let''s not start with statistics,though, because that''s what everybody does.',1,295123),(12628,271,'” 我同意。我们给其他学生一系列问题来回答如何——关于他们怀疑他们每天浪费的东西？',310990,'I agree. How about we give the other students a set of questions to answer - about what they suspect they waste every day?',1,300544),(12629,271,'“我很好。可能是一个更好的选择\r\n而不是展示垃圾填埋场的图片。',317910,'I''m fine with that. Probably a better option(Q25)\r\nthan showing pictures of landfill sites.',1,310995),(12630,271,'这样会更加个性化。',321320,'It''ll be more personalised, that way.',1,317916),(12631,271,'“好了，现在开始吧……',358800,'All right, now let''s start ...',1,321326),(12632,271,'好的，现在让我们看看不同的研究人员和组织正在从事的项目吗？',367150,'OK, shall we now have a look at the projects that different researchers and organisations are working on?',1,358801),(12633,271,'对我来说，我真正喜欢的项目是塔夫茨大学的项目——你知道，他们发明了微小的可食用贴片，贴在新鲜食物上，显示细菌的含量，以及你是否还能吃。',384680,'For me, the project I really liked was the one at Tufts University - you know, where they''ve invented tiny edible patches to stick on fresh foods that show you what level of bacteria is present, and so whether you can still eat it.',1,367153),(12634,271,'这是一个好主意，因为它会告诉您是否需要在食物熄灭之前快点吃掉。',391320,'It''s a great idea as it tells you if you need to hurry up and eat the food before it goes off.',1,384681),(12635,271,'贴片的另一个好处是它们的制造成本显然很便宜。',398250,'The other good thing about the patches is that apparently they''ll be cheap to manufacture.(Q26)',1,391329),(12636,271,'“很好。然后我认为另一件很棒的事情是麻省理工学院的项目。',405230,'Good. Then the other thing I thought was great was the Massachusetts Institute of  Technology project.',1,398252),(12637,271,'我没有看到那个。',407840,'I hadn''t seen that.',1,405234),(12638,271,'嗯，他们开发了这些可以检测微量乙烯的传感器。',414240,'Well,they''ve developed these sensors that can detect tiny amounts of ethylene.',1,407840),(12639,271,'显然，乙烯是水果中的天然植物激素，使它们变得成熟。',420980,'Ethylene is the natural plant hormone in fruit that makes them turn ripe, apparently.',1,414240),(12640,271,'研究人员认为他们可以将传感器连接到纸板箱上——然后超市可以用便携式设备扫描传感器，看看里面的水果有多成熟。',433870,'The researchers think that they can attach the sensors to cardboard boxes - and then supermarkets can scan the sensors with a portable device to see how ripe the fruit inside is.',1,420981),(12641,271,'与从货架上取下每个盒子并打开它相比，这一定是一种更快的方法来检查成熟度。',441640,'That''s got to be a quicker way to check for ripeness than taking each box off the shelf and opening it.(Q27)',1,433878),(12642,271,'那当然，而且我还认为Lean Path也值得一提。',446590,'Definitely.And I thought that Lean Path was worth mentioning, too.',1,441644),(12643,271,'他们的浪费跟踪技术意味着餐饮服务商可以看到浪费了多少食物以及为什么浪费了。这最终会增加他们的利润。',458480,'Their waste tracking technology means that caterers can see how much food is being wasted and why.That''ll increase profits for them eventually.(Q28)',1,446595),(12644,271,'是的。你读过零百分比吗？',462800,'Yes.And did you read about Zero PerCent?',1,458486),(12645,271,'他们制作了这款智能手机应用程序，允许餐厅向食品慈善机构发送捐赠警报。',469980,'They''ve produced this smartphone application that allows restaurants to send donation alerts to food charities.',1,462808),(12646,271,'然后，慈善机构可以捡起不需要的食物并将其分发给有需要的人。',476050,'The charities can then pick up the unwanted food and distribute it to people in need.',1,469988),(12647,271,'从长远来看，这肯定会使附近较贫困的家庭受益。',482490,'In the long run, that''ll definitely benefit poorer families in the neighbourhood.(Q29)',1,476054),(12648,271,'没有孩子应该饿着肚子上学。',485350,'No kid should go to school hungry.',1,482497),(12649,271,'我同意。我还看到，有好些美国州政府正在考虑引入强制性堆肥，那人们就不能把食品废物扔到垃圾桶里了，只能放在堆肥箱。',502260,'I agree.And I read that quite a few local governments in the USA are thinking about introducing compulsory composting in their states - so you can''t put any food waste into your rubbish bins,just the compost bin.',1,485356),(12650,271,'“嗯，我想这对人们来说意味着更多的工作。',506920,'Well, I guess that means a bit more work for people.',1,502267),(12651,271,'我的意思是，他们必须自己将有机废物和有机废物分开，然后再将其取出到堆肥箱中，你知道有些人是多么的懒惰！',518710,'l mean, they have to separate the organic and in organic waste themselves before they take it out to the compost bin, and you know how lazy some people are!',1,506924),(12652,271,'但我想如果我们都开始堆肥。 我们会为自己的食物浪费问题做一些积极的事情，而不是依靠政府来解决它。',531280,'But I guess if we all start composting. we''d be doing something positive about the problem of food waste ourselves, rather than relying on the government to sort it out.(Q30)',1,518716),(12653,271,'话虽如此，并不是每个人都有花园，所以...',536550,'Having said that, not everyone has a garden so ...',1,531289),(12654,272,'嗯，大家早上好。',77130,'Well, good morning everyone.',1,75495),(12655,272,'如您所知，我们一直在研究新西兰毛利人实践的不同种类的艺术和手工艺——至少在 18 世纪欧洲人开始到达之前。',87890,'As you know, we''ve been looking at different kinds of art and craft that were practised by the Maori people of New Zealand - at least before the Europeans began to arrive in the 18th century.',1,77139),(12656,272,'所以，本次讲座的重点是风筝制作；风筝是如何制作的，它们的外观和它们的用途。',96810,'So, the focus of this lecture is kite making; how the kites were made,their appearance and the purposes they served.',1,87898),(12657,272,'好吧，让我们从它们的制作方式开始。',101100,'Well,let''s start with the way they were made.',1,96814),(12658,272,'与其他毛利艺术传统一样，风筝制作涉及某些仪式。',107530,'As with other Maori artistic traditions, kite-making involved certain rituals.',1,101105),(12659,272,'首先，只有牧师才能放飞和掌控最大最神圣的风筝。',114380,'So, firstly, only priests were allowed to fly and handle the largest, most sacred kites.',1,107530),(12660,272,'而且制作风筝也有规定相应的尺寸和规模，牧师要严格执行，而且在制作小型和大型的风筝时，严禁出现食物。',125720,'There were rules, too, for the size and scale of the kites that the priests had to follow, and during the preparation of both small and large kites, food was strictly forbidden.(Q31)',1,114382),(12661,272,'就外观而言，风筝经常被设计成本土鸟类或毛利人的神灵，有时，也许不太常见的是知名英雄的形象。',138250,'In terms of appearance,kites were frequently designed in the image of a native bird, or a Maori god, and sometimes, perhaps less often, a well-known hero.(Q32)',1,125727),(12662,272,'你们能想象一下，毛利人最初来到一个新国度--新西兰的时候，他们可能也花了好些时间来寻找合适制作风筝的材料。但在反复试验，不断犯错后，他们找到了一些植物和树木，他们可用其树皮（甚至是树根）来制作风筝的框架和筝翼。',158940,'You can imagine that when Maori first arrived in the new country, in New Zealand, it may have taken some time to find suitable materials for their kites- but through trial and error no doubt, they found plants and trees that provided bark and even roots that they could use to make the frames and wings of their kites.',1,138250),(12663,272,'在框架建成后，风筝必须进行装饰。',164530,'And after the frame had been constructed, the kite then had to be decorated.',1,158945),(12664,272,'为此，牧师们采用了长长的茅草，在风筝飞舞时会在后面随之飘荡。',171990,'For this the priests used long grasses, and these - when the kite was in the air - would stream along behind it.',1,164535),(12665,272,'他们还使用各种羽毛为他们的作品添加，嗯，颜色。',178510,'They also used a variety of feathers to add, um, colour to their creations.(Q33)',1,171998),(12666,272,'嗯，这一切意味着在天空中很容易看到风筝，但你也可以听到毛利人的风筝。',186040,'Well,all this meant it was easy to see a kite in the sky but you could also hear Maori kites.',1,178516),(12667,272,'它们确实可能很吵，这是因为有些牧师喜欢在风筝上挂一排长长的贝壳。',193490,'They could be quite noisy indeed, and this was because some priests liked to hang a long row of shells from the kite.(Q34)',1,186043),(12668,272,'你可以想象它们会如何在风中嘎嘎作响——它们如何完全吸引你的注意力。',200570,'You can imagine how they''d rattle and clatter in the wind - how they might completely capture your attention.',1,193494),(12669,272,'正如我之前所说，最常见的形象可能是一只鸟，其他风筝制作文化也是如此，但风筝被设计成特定的形状——所以有三角形、矩形和钻石形状的风筝。',218360,'As I said before, the most common image was probably a bird,and that''s the same for other kite-making cultures, but the kites were designed in particular shapes - so there were kites that were triangular, rectangular and also shaped like a diamond.(Q35)',1,200576),(12670,272,'而且有的很大，实际上需要几个人来操作。',224130,'And some of them were so large, it would actually require several men to operate them.',1,218361),(12671,272,'有些风筝上布满图案，为了制作这些图案，毛利人用不同的红黑颜料。这些颜料的基本成分是炭或红褐色黏土，与从某种鲨鱼身上提取的鱼油混合而成。',245940,'Um, some of the kites were also covered in patterns, and to make these patterns, the Maori used different pigments of red and black, and these were either made from a charcoal base or from red-brown clay which had been combined with oil obtained from a local species of shark.(Q36)',1,224136),(12672,272,'现在，在我忘记之前，如果你有机会，一定要参观奥克兰博物馆，因为他们展出了最后幸存的“鸟人”风筝。',256280,'Now, before I forget, if you have a chance, do visit the Auckland Museum because they have the last surviving ‘birdman''  kite on display.',1,245945),(12673,272,'这是一种风筝，在框架的顶部有一个木制面具——它是一个人头面具——你可以清楚地看到它有一个纹身和一副牙齿。',267370,'This is the kind of kite that has a wooden mask at the top of the frame - it''s a mask of a human head - and you can clearly see it has a tattoo and also a set of teeth.(Q37)',1,256287),(12674,272,'相当令人印象深刻 - 也是毛利人工艺和象征意义的一个很好的例子。',272920,'Quite impressive - and a good example of Maori craftsmanship and symbolism.',1,267375),(12675,272,'对了，说到风筝的用途和作用，它们当然有多种用途。',280440,'Right, turning to the purpose and function of the kites, they certainly had multiple uses.',1,272921),(12676,272,'最开始，放飞风筝是和神灵交流的一种方式。当风筝升空，毛利人会用它们来传达信息，可能是求丰收，战争中的好运气，一次成功的狩猎远征。',296790,'Primarily, the flying of kites was a way of communicating with the gods and when the kites rose into the air, the Maori used them to deliver messages - perhaps requesting a good harvest,good fortune in war, a successful hunting expedition.(Q38)',1,280446),(12677,272,'所以，这些风筝对一个社区来说是非常有价值的——一代人将传给下一代的珍贵物品。',304710,'So, these kites were incredibly valuable to a community - treasured objects that one generation would pass to the next.',1,296793),(12678,272,'人们还会出于其他原因放风筝，例如吸引邻村的注意。',311930,'People would also fly kites for other reasons, for example, to attract the attention of a neighbouring village.',1,304714),(12679,272,'这是在毛利长老之间需要会面时进行的——确实是一种方便的方法。',318060,'This was done when a meeting was required between Maori elders- a convenient method, indeed.(Q39)',1,311938),(12680,272,'最后，在战争时，有传统故事描述，一个毛利战士发现自己被敌人包围时，一个风筝能为他提供逃生的可能。这些风筝承重力非常强，能将一个人升到空中。因此，这名战士还能用风筝将自己降落到敌方防御工事中，就能从内部开始发动攻击。',343980,'And finally, when it comes to war, there are traditional stories that describe how when a Maori warrior found himself surrounded by his enemies，a kite could actually provide the possibility of escape - the kites were powerful enough to take a man up into the air;  and for this reason, they could also be used to lower him into enemy fortifications so that an attack could begin from the inside.(Q40)',1,318065),(12681,272,'我很高兴，看上去风筝制作开始复兴了，人们又对此感兴趣了… ',351460,'Well, I''m happy to say there seems to be a revival and growing interest in kite-making, and ...',1,343985),(12682,273,'你好，这里是城市交通失物招领处，有什么可以帮你吗？',39210,'Hello.City Transport Lost Property. How can I help you?',1,32709),(12683,273,'噢，你好。我打来是想问问我昨天丢的行李箱。我也不指望会找回来，但我想，我总要试试看。',49320,'Oh, hello. Yes, I''m, er, calling about a suitcase I lost yesterday. I don''t suppose I''ll get it back but I thought I''d try.',1,39214),(12684,273,'有些人确实会把拾到的失物交过来，所以也许你运气很好也说不定。让我把信息登记在电脑上吧。',57990,'Well, some people do hand lost items in so you might be lucky. Let''s put the details into the computer.',1,49322),(12685,273,'好的。',58730,'OK.',1