acket pocket.',1,150164),(12702,273,'钱、衣服、任何私人物品？',159130,'Money, clothing, any personal items?',1,155561),(12703,273,'哦，让我想想。我有一把雨伞。它是黑色的，不是蓝色的，但显然这并不像其他东西那么重要。',169410,'Oh, let me think. I had an umbrella. It was black, no blue, but obviously that isn''t as important as the other things.(Q4)',1,159133),(12704,273,'不，但这一切都有助于我们识别您的财产并将其归还给您。',175820,'No, but it all helps us identify your property and get it back to you.',1,169413),(12705,273,'无论如何，我只需要向您询问有关您旅程的一些基本细节。那是昨天，是吗？',185900,'Anyway, I just need to ask you for some basic details about your journey. So it was yesterday,was it?',1,175820),(12706,273,'这是正确的。下午 - 大约下午 2 点，也许是 2.30。',235330,'That''s right. In the afternoon - around 2 pm, maybe 2.30.',1,229906),(12707,273,'好的，那就是 5 月 13 日。',240130,'OK.So that''d be May the 13th.(Q5)',1,235335),(12708,273,'是的。我正要去海布里。那是我住的地方。',244500,'Yes. I was heading to Highbury. That''s where I live.',1,240135),(12709,273,'好吧，我想你提到了护照。',249170,'All right, and you mentioned a passport,I think.',1,244505),(12710,273,'所以我猜你是从机场来的。',252910,'So you were coming from the airport I presume.(Q6)',1,249175),(12711,273,'没错，我想回家想得不得了，那时候又很累，我想这就是为什么我恰好就忘记了我的行李箱。',262620,'Yes- and I was looking forward to getting home so much - and what with being tired and everything-I think that''s why I just forgot about the case.',1,252913),(12712,273,'“当你迷路的时候你是怎么旅行的\n你的财产？',267260,'And how were you travelling when you lost\nyour property?',1,262620),(12713,273,'我的意思是，你用的是什么交通工具？',271300,'I mean, what kind of transport were you using?',1,267261),(12714,273,'我本来打算坐火车，但这意味着还要坐一段公交车，我不想费这么多工夫，所以最后决定坐出租车了。',281260,'I thought about getting the train, but that would have meant a bus journey as well, and I couldn''t be bothered so I decided to take a taxi eventually.(Q7)',1,271301),(12715,273,'那是我必须离开的地方。',283780,'That''s where I must have left it.',1,281261),(12716,273,'某种程度而言，这是个好消息。很有可能司机发现了这个箱子，然后送过来。但愿吧。',292100,'Well, that''s good news in a way. It''s more likely that a driver would have found it and handed it in.',1,283781),(12717,273,'但愿如此。',293930,'I hope so.',1,292100),(12718,273,'好吧，我现在需要你的个人信息。',297300,'Well, I need your personal details now.',1,293938),(12719,273,'请告诉我你的全名好吗？',300310,'Can I have your full name, please?',1,297308),(12720,273,'是的，是丽莎·多切蒂。 我会为你拼写。 它是 D-O-C-H-E-R-T-Y。',310040,'Yes.It''s Lisa Docherty. I''ll spell that for you. It''s D-O-C-H-E-R-T-Y.(Q8)',1,300313),(12721,273,'“ 谢谢。接下来，如果我能得到你的地址——如果我们设法找到它，最好的地址是把它寄给你吗？',320090,'Thank you. And next, if I could have your address - the best address to send you the property if we manage to locate it?',1,310045),(12722,273,'“当然。它是 15A 河道 - 那就是海布里，正如我所说。',326790,'Sure. It''s number 15A River Road - and that''s Highbury, as I said.(Q9)',1,320098),(12723,273,'谢谢。请稍等。',330070,'Thank you.Just a moment.',1,326790),(12724,273,'只有最后一件事——那就是你的电话号码。',334870,'There''s just one final thing - that''s your phone number.',1,330075),(12725,273,'我想我的手机最好。 呃，等一下，我永远记不住自己的号码。',341130,'I guess my mobile would be best. Er, hang on, I can never remember my own number.',1,334875),(12726,273,'好的，我明白了。 它是 07979605437。',353680,'OK, I''ve got it. It''s 07979605437.(Q10)',1,341139),(12727,273,'很好。 我认为这就是我们在这方面所需要的一切。',359790,'Very well. I think that''s everything we need at this end.',1,353689),(12728,273,'我去看看数据...',362400,'I''ll have a look at the data on ...',1,359795),(12729,274,'欢迎大家来到这里。',44430,'Welcome to everyone here.',1,42972),(12730,274,'希望您在我们村度过愉快的时光，欣赏当地的风景。',50530,'I hope you enjoy your stay in our village and enjoy the local scenery.',1,44434),(12731,274,'我会在一分钟内告诉你一些关于森林和山路的事情，但首先，我会让你知道村里所有东西的位置。',60680,'I''ll tell you a bit about the forest and mountain tracks in a minute, but first, I''ll just give you an idea of where everything is in the village.',1,50537),(12732,274,'所以，我们在旅游信息中心，当你从中心出来时，你就在柳巷，就在池塘对面。',71830,'So, we''re here in the tourist information centre, and when you come out of the centre, you''re on Willow Lane, just opposite the pond.',1,60681),(12733,274,'如果你想去超市买食物和水，往右走，这是最快的方法，然后在柳巷的末端右转，就是你来到的第二栋楼，在旧火车站对面。',88520,'If you want to get to the supermarket for your supplies of food and water, go right, that''s the quickest way,and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it''s the second building you come to, opposite the old railway station.(Q11)',1,71837),(12734,274,'如果你们打算做些真正意义上的爬山运动，需要些设备，我们这儿就有个很好的登山用品店，走五分钟就到了。',100820,'If you''re planning on doing some serious climbing and you need some equipment, we do have an excellent climbing supplies store just five minutes'' walk away.(Q12)',1,88522),(12735,274,'出了旅游信息中心后向左转，沿着柳树巷一直走到松树街——你要沿着这里向左走——然后一直走，沿着右边的山路往前走，直到你走到下一个向左拐的地方——往下走，你就会来到登山用品商店(Q12)。',124620,'Turn left once you''re outside the tourist information centre, take Willow Lane all the way up to Pine Street - you want to go left along here - then keep walking and go up Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you''ll come to the climbing supplies store(Q12).',1,100820),(12736,274,'如果你到了出售滑雪通行证的小楼，你就会知道你走得太远了。',130750,'If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you''ll know you''ve gone too far.',1,124620),(12737,274,'您还需要前往松树街参观博物馆 - 如果您对村庄的历史和古老的金矿开采业感兴趣，它虽小但非常值得一游。',143910,'You also need to head to Pine Street for the museum - it''s small but well worth a visit if you''re interested in the history of the village and the old gold mining industry.',1,130756),(12738,274,'所以，当你从这里到达松树街时，你会看到那条旧铁路线在路的另一边——向左转进入松树街，一直走到山路，过了这里，博物馆就在你的左边，就在铁路线的后面。(Q13)',164030,'So, when you reach Pine Street from here, you''ll see the old railway line on the other side of the road- turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road,and just past here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line.(Q13)',1,143910),(12739,274,'不用担心越过轨道。',167170,'Don''t worry about crossing over the tracks.',1,164033),(12740,274,'火车在 1985 年停止通过这里。',171300,'The trains stopped running through here in 1985.',1,167171),(12741,274,'如果您打算沿着更轻松的森林步道走，您可能想租一辆自行车。',178480,'If you''re planning on following one of the easier forest walks, you might like to hire a bicycle.',1,171308),(12742,274,'要到达出租店，您需要再次前往松树街。',184400,'To get to the hire shop,again you need to head to Pine Street.',1,178483),(12743,274,'在松树街的左边，你会看到市政厅，沿着你来到它前面的小路走，你会在大厅后面找到自行车出租店。',197660,'On the left-hand side of Pine Street,you''ll see the Town Hall,go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you''ll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall.(Q14)',1,184407),(12744,274,'他们有各种各样的自行车，所以我相信您会找到适合您需求的东西。',204420,'They have a good range of bikes so I''m sure you''ll find something that suits your needs.',1,197664),(12745,274,'最后但同样重要的是，如果您在漫长的一天跋涉后饿了，我可以推荐我们当地的咖啡馆。',212850,'Last but not least, if you''re hungry after a long day''s trek I can recommend our local café.',1,204424),(12746,274,'同样，当您离开旅游信息中心时，右转并沿柳巷行驶，直到它与松树街汇合 - 而就在对面 - 在铁路轨道的另一边 - 就是咖啡馆。',261540,'Again, when you leave the tourist information centre,turn right and follow willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the cafe.(Q15)',1,212850),(12747,274,'好的，让我告诉你一些关于我们这里的不同轨道的信息。',266790,'OK, let me tell you a little bit about the different tracks we have here.',1,261548),(12748,274,'所有这些都从山路的尽头开始 - 您会在那里找到一个停车场，您可以在那里停放您的车辆。',274720,'All of them start at the end of Mountain Road -and you''ll find a parking lot there where you can leave your vehicles.',1,266798),(12749,274,'让我们从北角赛道开始。',277810,'Let''s start with North Point track.',1,274723),(12750,274,'这是一条穿过低地森林的平缓路线 - 适合骑自行车，如果您有小孩，可能是适合您的路线。',285620,'It''s a gentle route through lowland forest - good for biking and probably the one for you if you have small children.',1,277818),(12751,274,'有一个木屋，您可以在赛道尽头停留，但请注意，它实际上只是一个过夜的避难所，您需要带上自己的睡袋和烹饪设备。',297830,'There''s a wooden hut where you can stay at the end of the track but be aware that it''s really just an overnight shelter, and you''ll need to take your own sleeping bags and cooking equipment.(Q16)',1,285628),(12752,274,'另一种选择是银河赛道。',301870,'Another option is the Silver River track.',1,297833),(12753,274,'顾名思义，您将沿着河流走大部分路，您会看到一些我们美丽的本土鸟类，但这条赛道也穿过茂密的森林地区。',314980,'As the name suggests, you''d be following the river for most of the way, and you get to see some of our beautiful native birds, but the track also goes through a densely forested area.',1,301873),(12754,274,'不幸的是，有些地方的路标不是很好，您确实需要良好的地图阅读技能以避免迷失方向，我担心这种情况经常发生在游客身上。',330110,'Unfortunately, the signposting isn''t very good in places and you do need good map-reading skills to avoid becoming disoriented, which happens to visitors a little too frequently, I''m afraid.(Q17)',1,314984),(12755,274,'克罗辛峡谷将带你穿越一些令人惊叹的风景，但沿途有几个地方您需要获得克服一些相当大的岩石所需的健身水平。',343230,'Valley Crossing will take you through some stunning scenery but there are several points along the way where you''ll need the level of fitness required to get over some pretty big rocks.(Q18)',1,330119),(12756,274,'石桥线是较短的路线，但非常陡峭，因为这条路线会带你们去往瀑布，需要你们有良好的身体条件才能完成。',355010,'Stonebridge is one of the shorter tracks, but very steep as it takes you up to the waterfall, and you do need to be in good condition to manage it.(Q19)',1,343236),(12757,274,'最后，亨德森山脊步道将带您一路到达山顶。',362600,'Lastly, the Henderson Ridge track will take you all the way to the summit of the mountain.',1,355010),(12758,274,'但要记住，今年这个时候，天气非常多变。假如云层突然降低，游人很容易就会偏离路线。',375070,'Do bear in mind, though, that at this time of year the weather is very changeable and if the cloud suddenly descends, it''s all too easy to wander off the track.(Q20)',1,362602),(12759,274,'最好在您想去的早晨向我们查询天气预报。',381790,'It''s best to check with us for a weather report on the morning you think you want to go.',1,375074),(12760,274,'在登顶的路上，有一家酒店，提供舒适的客房和优质的餐点，值得大家攀登。',390760,'On the way to the summit, there''s a hotel which provides comfortable rooms and quality meals, so it''s worth climbing all .',1,381795),(12761,275,'好吧，詹姆斯，我看过你的案例研究，初稿看起来很有希望。',48150,'Well ,James, I''ve had a look over your case study and for a first draft, it looks promising.',1,39124),(12762,275,'老实说，当你告诉我们必须写一家家具公司时，这听起来不像是我感兴趣的那种东西，但从那以后，我改变了主意。',59090,'I have to be honest, when you told us we had to write about a furniture company, it didn''t sound like the kind of thing that would interest me, but since then, I''ve changed my mind.',1,48154),(12763,275,'为什么？',60500,'Why''s that?',1,59098),(12764,275,'好吧，如你所知，Furniture Rossi 是一家澳大利亚公司，与一些高街商店相比仍然相对较小，但它有计划扩展到国外市场。',73410,'Well, as you know, Furniture Rossi is an Australian company, still comparatively small compared to some of the high street stores, but it''s got plans to expand into foreign markets.',1,60509),(12765,275,'所以我出于这个原因选择了它。它正在经历转型——它是一家旨在打造全球品牌的家族企业。',82830,'So I chose it for that reason. It''s going through a transition - it''s a family-run business aiming to build a global brand.(Q21)',1,73413),(12766,275,'好吧，你已经在你的写作中清楚地表明了这一点。',86520,'All right, and you''ve made that clear in your writing.',1,82830),(12767,275,'不过，我认为您忽略了一件事情，那就是卢卡·罗西（Luca Rossi）最初在澳大利亚创办家具公司的原因。',96040,'One thing, though, that I think you''ve overlooked is why Luca Rossi started a furniture company here in Australia in the first place.',1,86520),(12768,275,'好吧，他刚刚获得了艺术学位，不是吗？',99370,'Well, he''d just got an arts degree, hadn''t he?',1,96045),(12769,275,'人们试图说服他从事学术工作，但他想要一份实用的工作——他认为从长远来看会更令人满意。',108660,'And people were trying to talk him into an academic profession but he wanted a practical job -something he thought would be more satisfying in the long run.',1,99370),(12770,275,'他的祖父曾是一名工匠。',111420,'His grandfather had been a craftsman.',1,108662),(12771,275,'他在意大利制造家具，并将这项技能传给了卢卡的父亲，而且，卢卡认为他想继续这一传统。',121060,'He''d made furniture in Italy and he''d passed this skill on to Luca''s father,and well,Luca thought he''d like to continue the tradition.(Q22)',1,111428),(12772,275,'是的，这就是他做出决定的动机。',125220,'Yes, that was the motivation behind his decision.',1,121063),(12773,275,'您认为是什么让家具罗西比其他家具公司更具竞争优势？',133040,'And what was it, do you think, that gave Furniture Rossi a competitive edge over other furniture companies?',1,125222),(12774,275,'我认为肯定不是价格。',135390,'I wouldn''t think it was price.',1,133048),(12775,275,'它一直处于市场的高端，但根据我的研究，这与员工的态度有关——他们真正专注于提供良好的客户服务。',146670,'It''s always been at the higher end of the market, but according to my research, it was to do with the attitude of the employees - they were really focused on giving good customer service.(Q23)',1,135393),(12776,275,'是的，卢卡·罗西坚持这一点。',150130,'Yes, Luca Rossi insisted on that.',1,146679),(12777,275,'他们的宣传活动还强调了木材仅来自澳大利亚森林这一事实，但他们的竞争对手也是如此，因此不会让他们脱颖而出。',163530,'Their promotional campaigns also emphasised the fact that the wood only came from Australian forests, but that was the case with their rivals,too, so it wouldn''t have made them stand out.',1,150134),(12778,275,'我们马上就仔细研究一下你案例研究的内容，但我想在你写第二稿以前先给出个总体评价。',175520,'OK, we''ll have a careful look at the content of your case study in a minute, but I just want to make a general comment first, before you start writing your second draft.',1,163536),(12779,275,'好的。',176690,'OK.',1,175529),(12780,275,'是的，我更想看到你的意见，更批判性的思考，而不是赤裸裸的事实。',185500,'Yes, what I''d like to see more of is your opinion, a bit more critical thinking, rather than the bare facts.(Q24)',1,176696),(12781,275,'但是很高兴看到您这次在引用时一直很小心。',190570,'But it''s good to see you''ve been careful with your referencing this time.',1,185501),(12782,275,'谢谢。我反复阅读我的作品，所以我很确定语言没有任何错误。',197160,'Thanks.And I read and re-read my work so I''m pretty sure there aren''t any errors with the language.',1,190572),(12783,275,'是的，没关系。哦，但此时我可能会提到另一件事。',203650,'Yes, it''s fine.Oh, but there''s one other thing I could probably mention at this point.',1,197166),(12784,275,'是的？',204650,'Yes?',1,203651),(12785,275,'好吧，在学期结束时，您还将进行演示 - 也是关于家具罗西的。',211760,'Well, at the end of term, you''ll also be giving a presentation - also on Furniture Rossi.',1,204651),(12786,275,'是的，我还没有考虑太多。',215610,'Yes, I haven''t given it much thought yet.',1,211765),(12787,275,'可以理解。但是，在您撰写案例研究时，我建议您考虑一下我的哪些信息适合在您的演示文稿中使用。',225420,'Understandably. But, while you''re writing the case study, I''d recommend you think about what I kind of information would be suitable to use in your presentation.',1,215613),(12788,275,'记住——上一次你就公司做演讲时，你花了相当多的时间向观众提供财务数据，但他们可能需要更多地了解公司战略。',239780,'Remember - the last time you gave a presentation on a company, you spent a considerable part of the time providing the audience with financial data, but they probably needed to hear more about company strategy.',1,225424),(12789,275,'是的，我确实过于关注数字了。',244750,'Yes, I did concentrate rather too much on the figures.(Q25)',1,239781),(12790,275,'这次我会确保有一个平衡。',247360,'I''ll make sure there''s a balance this time.',1,244756),(12791,275,'好的。',278050,'Good.',1,247361),(12792,275,'好的，让我们想想你的案例研究的内容——Furniture Rossi 的历史。',285690,'OK, so let''s just think about the content of your case study - the history of Furniture Rossi.',1,278053),(12793,275,'我在第四段看到你在谈论卢卡罗西如何为他的新企业筹集资金 - 然后你在谈论客户群越来越广泛 - 但是什么推动了这种增长？',302970,'I see here in paragraph four you''re talking about how Luca Rossi raised the capital for his new business venture - and then you''re talking about the customer base growing much wider - but what was it that prompted this growth?',1,285693),(12794,275,'嗯，这与公司销售的家具产品的质量有关。',308490,'Well, that was to do with the quality of the furniture products that the company was selling.(Q26)',1,302972),(12795,275,'人们喜欢这一切都是手工制作的，并且会持续下去。',312450,'People loved that it was all hand-made and would last.',1,308497),(12796,275,'因为客户的需求不断增长？',315930,'And because demand from customers kept growing?',1,312459),(12797,275,'那么，Rossi 需要聘请更多的工匠，这样他们才能确保订单按时准备好，然后，他还必须建立两个新仓库，以加快配送速度。',329330,'Well, then Rossi needed to take on more craftsmen so they could make sure the orders were ready on time, and then, he also had to set up two new warehouses to make distribution quicker.(Q27)',1,315930),(12798,275,'是的。从那里开始，公司真正成长起来。',333790,'Yes. And from there, the company really grew.',1,329332),(12799,275,'但是想想接下来发生了什么。',336320,'But think what happened next.',1,333792),(12800,275,'他们开始寻找增加利润的方