ted to religion.(Q31)',1,92737),(13173,284,'到了 17 世纪，欧洲的统治者开始使用烟花作为标记皇室场合的一种方式。',117550,'By the 17th century, the rulers of Europe had started using fireworks as a way of marking royal occasions.',1,109929),(13174,284,'技术人员被雇用来上演壮观的表演，展示自然的各个方面，以太阳、雪和雨的形式呈现。',128780,'Technicians were employed to stage spectacular shows which displayed aspects of nature, with representations of the sun, snow and rain.(Q32)',1,117555),(13175,284,'这些节目是为了贵族的享受和给普通人留下深刻印象而设计的。',135630,'These shows were designed for the enjoyment of the nobility and to impress ordinary people.',1,128782),(13176,284,'但烟花也引起了科学家们的兴趣，他们开始思考它们的新用途。',143670,'But fireworks also aroused the interest of scientists, who started to think of new uses for them.',1,135633),(13177,284,'在看到一个烟花表演时，一个龙模型被火箭沿着绳索推进，科学家们认为，以类似的方式，人类可能能够实现飞行——这是当时许多科学家的梦想。',161120,'After seeing one firework display where a model of a dragon was propelled along a rope by rockets,scientists thought that in a similar way, humans might be able to achieve flight - a dream of many scientists at the time.(Q33)',1,143679),(13178,284,'其他科学家，如化学家罗伯特·博伊尔，注意到一个烟花实际上是如何点燃另一个烟花的，他想到烟花可能提供一种有效的方式来展示恒星是如何形成的。',178920,'Other scientists, such as the chemist Robert Boyle, noticed how in displays one firework might actually light another, and it occurred to him that fireworks might provide an effective way of demonstrating how stars were formed.(Q34)',1,161121),(13179,284,'当时的科学家经常依靠皇家法院获得赞助，但不同国家的法院与科学家之间的关系存在相当大的差异。',193000,'Scientists at the time often depended on the royal courts for patronage, but there was considerable variation in the relationships between the courts and scientists in different countries.',1,178923),(13180,284,'这反映在对烟花的态度和使用烟花的目的上。',198840,'This was reflected in attitudes towards fireworks and the purposes for which they were used.',1,193003),(13181,284,'在 17 世纪中叶的伦敦，科学家普遍不信任烟花。',206520,'In London in the middle of the 17th century there was general distrust of fireworks among scientists.',1,198849),(13182,284,'然而，在本世纪后期，科学家和技术人员开始研究可能使用烟花的实际目的，例如使用火箭帮助水手在海上建立自己的位置。',221670,'However, later in the century scientists and technicians started to look at the practical purposes for which fireworks might be employed, such as using rockets to help sailors establish their position at sea.(Q35)',1,206521),(13183,284,'在俄罗斯，情况就不同了，圣彼得堡科学院在为法院制作烟花表演方面发挥了关键作用。',232860,'It was a different story in Russia, where the St Petersburg Academy of Science played a key role in creating fireworks displays for the court.',1,221672),(13184,284,'在这里，当权者将烟花视为群众教育的重要内容，而烟花表演往往包含科学信息。',245510,'Here, those in power regarded fireworks as being an important element in the education of the masses,and the displays often included a scientific message.(Q36)',1,232863),(13185,284,'学院的成员希望这可能会鼓励皇室在政府中的许多人考虑关闭学院的时候保持学院的开放。',257130,'Members of the Academy hoped that this might encourage the Royal Family to keep the Academy open at a time when many in the government were considering closing it.',1,245513),(13186,284,'在巴黎，情况再次不同。',261690,'In Paris, the situation was different again.',1,257138),(13187,284,'巴黎科学院在举办烟花表演方面没有任何作用。',268010,'The Paris Academy of Sciences played no role in staging fireworks displays.',1,261690),(13188,284,'相反，这项任务落到了皇家绘画和雕塑学院的成员身上。',274320,'Instead the task fell to members of the Royal Academy of Painting and Sculpture.',1,268014),(13189,284,'与俄罗斯一样，制造烟花的技术人员的工作很少受到关注。',281820,'As in Russia, the work of the technicians who created the fireworks was given little attention.',1,274327),(13190,284,'相反，他们创造的烟花和奇观都是为了鼓励公众相信国王的至高无上的权威。',292910,'Instead, the fireworks and the spectacle they created were all designed to encourage the public to believe in the supreme authority of the king.(Q37)',1,281822),(13191,284,'然而，科学在法国贵族中也非常受欢迎，时尚社会蜂拥而至，例如尼古拉斯·勒梅里（Nicolas Lemery）展示的火山喷发。',307880,'However, science was also enormously popular among the French nobility, and fashionable society flocked to demonstrations such as Nicolas Lemery''s display representing an erupting volcano.',1,292915),(13192,284,'科学家的目的基本上是为时尚社会提供娱乐，而院士们则通过展示自然的普遍规律来取悦令人惊叹的观众。',325820,'The purpose of scientists was basically to offer entertainment to fashionable society,and academicians delighted in amazing audiences with demonstrations of the universal laws of nature.(Q38)',1,307882),(13193,284,'在 18 世纪的过程中，技能的流通和技术交流导致了进一步的发展。',334540,'In the course of the 18th century, the circulation of skills and technical exchange led to further developments.',1,325822),(13194,284,'来自意大利的烟花专家开始环游欧洲，为许多欧洲法院举办表演。',343900,'Fireworks specialists from Italy began to travel around Europe staging displays for many of the European courts.',1,334548),(13195,284,'建筑师和舞台设计师 Giovanni Servandoni 在巴黎举办了盛大的展览，以色彩缤纷的寺庙和凯旋门为特色。',356510,'The architect and stage designer Giovanni Servandoni composed grand displays in Paris, featuring colourfully painted temples and triumphal arches.',1,343908),(13196,284,'由 Servandoni 上演的烟花表演会以与歌剧相同的方式组织，甚至分为不同的表演。',366300,'A fireworks display staged by Servandoni would be structured in the same way as an opera, and was even divided into separate acts.(Q39)',1,356514),(13197,284,'意大利烟花专家也应邀在伦敦、圣彼得堡和莫斯科演出。',374700,'Italian fireworks specialists were also invited to perform in London, St Petersburg and Moscow.',1,366303),(13198,284,'随着这些专家在欧洲各地传播，他们试图利用烟花对更广泛的观众的吸引力，包括不断壮大的中产阶级。',387000,'As these specialists circulated around Europe, they sought to exploit the appeal of fireworks for a wider audience, including the growing middle classes.',1,374707),(13199,284,'与上个世纪一样，烟花为展示科学规律和理论以及新发现提供了资源，现在的展示向公众展示了令人着迷的电现象。',404580,'As in the previous century,fireworks provided resources for demonstrating scientific laws and theories, as well as new discoveries,and displays now showed a fascinated public the curious phenomenon of electricity.(Q40)',1,387008),(13200,284,'到 18 世纪中叶，烟花被出售供私人消费。',410640,'By the mid-18th century, fireworks were being sold for private consumption.',1,404583),(13201,284,'因此，烟花的历史向我们展示了科学家、技术人员和社会其他人之间存在的各种关系......',421800,'So the history of fireworks shows us the diverse relationships which existed between scientists, technicians and the rest of society...',1,410648),(13202,285,'你好，希拉里洛奇养老院，Cathy在说话。',79960,'Hello, Hilary Lodge retirement home, Cathy speaking.',1,74785),(13203,285,'你好，我叫John Shepherd。',83240,'Hello, my name''s John Shepherd.',1,79965),(13204,285,'请问你是家里的经理吗？',87070,'Could I ask if you''re the manager of the home?',1,83246),(13205,285,'这是正确的。',88060,'That''s right.',1,87076),(13206,285,'哦，很好。你好，凯茜。我的一个朋友是 Hilary Lodge 的一名志愿者，如果你需要更多的人，我也愿意帮忙。',100720,'Oh, good.Hello,Cathy. A friend of mine is a volunteer at Hilary Lodge, and I''d like to help out,too, if you need more people.',1,88061),(13207,285,'我是兼职工作，所以我有很多空闲时间。',105920,'I work part-time, so I have quite a lot of free time.',1,100720),(13208,285,'我们总是很高兴能得到更多帮助，约翰。',109540,'We''re always glad of more help,John .',1,105920),(13209,285,'我可以告诉你一些志愿者参与的活动吗？',115760,'Shall I tell you about some of the activities that volunteers get involved in?',1,109540),(13210,285,'请。',116640,'Please.',1,115765),(13211,285,'好吧，星期一晚上我们组织计算机培训。',121910,'Well, on Monday evenings we organise computer training.',1,116643),(13212,285,'我们有六台笔记本电脑，五六个居民定期参加会议。',129410,'We''ve got six laptops, and five or six residents come to the sessions regularly.',1,121914),(13213,285,'他们现在都可以很好地编写和发送电子邮件，但是我们的培训师刚刚搬走，我们需要两三个志愿者来帮助居民创建文件。',146150,'They''re all now fine at writing and sending emails, but our trainer has just moved away, and we need two or three volunteers who can help the residents create documents.(Q1)',1,129416),(13214,285,'只是简单的事情，真的。',148940,'Just simple things, really.',1,146157),(13215,285,'我当然有兴趣这样做。',152330,'I''d certainly be interested in doing that.',1,148942),(13216,285,'伟大的。然后在周二下午，我们有一个非正式的歌唱班，大多数居民都会参加。',163930,'Great. Then on Tuesday afternoons we have an informal singing class, which most of the residents attend.',1,152332),(13217,285,'我们有一个键盘和一个演奏者，但如果你想加入唱歌。你会很受欢迎的。',174200,'We''ve got a keyboard, and someone who plays, but if you''d like to join in the singing，you''d be very welcome.(Q2)',1,163934),(1